description:
How I feel about McGriddles may rattle some cages so if you’re the sort that gets defensive about foods that you like, kindly refrain from reading what I’ve written below—even though I know that you still will because hUmAn NaTuRe.

And just to reiterate: yes I know it’s fast food and therefore I should manage my expectations accordingly. But so is KFC’s cheesy bbq meltz and those suckers are amazing so I’m sorry but stfu Karen.
.
.
.
.
.
No I’m not leaving this up to public opinion, I’m straight up calling it: The McGriddles is overhyped and most certainly not worth my buck. It’s essentially a sick incestual affair between hot cakes and big breakfast gone horribly wrong. Sure there’s the cheese and egg element that tries to provide some semblance of allure (and palatability) but otherwise it’s just a sad, twisted mongoloid of a burger that neither sparks breakfast cheer nor lunchtime satisfaction.

The hot cakes were mushy the way a sponge cake would be if you dropped it in the drain and picked it up again and the artificial maple aroma simply doesn’t bode well with the oregano and black pepper-heavy sausage patties. I’m sorry, it just doesn’t. Turkey bacon is, as you would expect from fake bacon, dry, lacklustre and excruciatingly difficult to stomach—similar to an old belt your mother probably beat you with when you were younger.

But with all that said, I know many folks swear by this hotshot McDonald’s seasonal and by all means I’m not here to sway your opinion. I can somewhat understand why the McGriddles is a hit but I’m afraid it just isn’t for me. Food is subjective after all…

… but so is the mortal definition of hell.

I don’t know about you but I prefer my lunches with a little more oomph. Oomph in the form of a perfectly executed tonkatsu, moist centre and crunchy all around, paired with a savoury-sweet mess of runny egg and roughly diced white onions over a bed of short grain Niigata rice.

If there’s one place that’s able to inspire fond memories of having fluffy, piping-hot chips by the pier in Perth or the crispiest, most gratifyingly moorish pieces of battered fish in the cold dead of night in London, it’s @goodintentions.sg . They don’t even specialise in fish & chips, they just do it well.

Paired with a crisp lager or a hazy IPA, it’s a ménage à trois in your mouth you never knew you needed. Really solid stuff—and I mean that with the very best of intentions. 😉

If there’s one thing @goneroguebrewing does remarkably well, it’s their Kawa Ebi thin crust pizza. I’m not crazy about pizza but what they did here—combining Japanese elements such as umami-loaded bonito and crispy river shrimp alongside mozzarella cheese and their house-made spicy mayo—really left an impression on me.

You get a nice salty crunch from the lil crustaceans, a smoky savouriness from bonito shavings and the melty cheese and creamy mayo that gives it such a profound richness and heat. Absolutely killer. 🦐

An all day brunch affair solidified with a tasty nosh, a formidable craft beer tap selection and a bona fide cocktail program designed by one of the industry’s most prolific (shoutout to @vinywc ), it goes without saying that @goodintentions.sg is one to take note of.

The newest kid to take up residence along the bustling Tanjong Katong stretch, what instantly allured me was their cosy space that spans two floors—the ground floor where their beer taps reside along with a quiet reading-room-type space which I’m told is perfect for intimate conversations and well… reading, as well as the upper deck, spacious and bright, fit for merry-making and all-out debauchery should you desire it.

I could spend all day and all night there. Drink till I’m sloshed the night before and wake up to a hearty, polished brunch that would no doubt expel the previous night’s easy-earned hangover. Remember the name @goodintentions.sg and pay a visit pronto.

[📝 Review] Rumour’s Beach Club Food Galore 🍕

✨ A place to chill & unwind by the beach ✨

Apart from the inevitable scorching sun, I would gladly spend my weekends at the beach sipping on wine while indulging in these delectable spread. 

🌶 Balinese Mixed Rice
Classic, a must get for me. The pieces of shredded chicken were well marinated. Beef chunks were tender and melty!

🍕 Rumours Pizza
Bigger in real life, it was riddled with beef salami, mushroom, basil, cherry tomato and black olive. It’s creamy and dripping in sauce. 

🍤 Calamari 🥠 Nachos
These are the perfect finger food to chill by the beach!

🍚 Indonesian Fried Rice
The concoction of shrimp paste sambal was extremely addictive. Dipped the crispy fried chicken and garlic crackers with it and there was no turning back. 

🍷 White wine
🍸 Margarita 

P.S. Food was great and I would love to go back again!

Overall Rating: 8.5/10

[📝 Review] Knockhouse Cafe’s FRENCH TOAST ($12)

✨ Fluffy soft pillows ✨

Beautifully presented, the toast was drizzled in salted caramel and sugar dusting with ice cream and seasonal fruits on the side. Each bite was greeted with a soft pillowy mouthfeel as the light buttery fragrance permeated through. 

P.S. It was so soft and light! Didn’t feel surfeiting at all!
Wished that there were more slices!

Rating: 8/10

[ 🎉 GIVEAWAY 🎉] BROTHERBIRD CROISSANTS 🥐

‼️ 4 Lucky Winners, March Box worth $32.50 ‼️

✨ A new channel @DroolingFork brings us our cult favourite croissants ✨

To join the giveaway:
1️⃣Follow @carbsforlyfe & @DroolingFork
2️⃣Like & save this post
3️⃣Tag ONE friend per comment (Multiple entries to increase your chances!
4️⃣Share this post on IGS and tag @carbsforlyfe & @DroolingFork

*Giveaway is open to people residing in SG and ends on 15th March. Announcement the next day via IGS & DM and prize collection is by appointment.
*This giveaway is not affiliated with Instagram. Redemption dates will be 18-20, 25-27 Mar. They are also hosting a giveaway on their YouTube channel too.

What’s in the box 🎁 Review:

🍩 ROCHER CROISSANT
Packed with oozing thick hazelnut filling, enwrapped by a dark chocolate glaze, the sweetness from the chocolate paired very well with the crispy croissant. 

🥕CARROT CAKE TWICE-BAKED
Topped off with dehydrated carrot in a bed of cream cheese frosting, the croissant was an interesting spin to the carrot cake! The shell revealed a pool of carrot cake frangipane. 

🥨 CINNAMON BROWN SUGAR KNOT
Tightly knot, it was densely packed with a mix of cinnamon and brown sugar. Drizzled in a cream cheese glaze, I swoon as I’m biased over cinnamon. 

🐥 CHICKEN LASAGNE TWICE-BAKED
For individuals who love savoury food, this chicken bolognese filling with sauce mornay, dehydrated tomato and dusting of parmesan cheese is the one for you!

🥐 BB's ORIGINAL CROISSANT
A classic, the original croissant emitted the flavour of the french butter. It was mellower in the richness of butter and geared towards a saltier profile. Coated in a sugar glaze with sea salt, what’s wrong with being basic?

🍤 MENTAIKO PRAWN TWICE-BAKED
Creamy luscious mix of mentaiko prawn filling was glistening as I uncovered the crispy croissant. Scattered with a dusting of mozarella cheese, the creaminess was a resounding yes. 

Thank you @DroolingFork for sending this box over and hosting this giveaway! ✨

📍Every Wed-Fri, 10am - 6pm Bali Lane cafe is available for you to "Work-From-Coffeehouse" with $6 offset in any drinks/croissant for every mains purchased.

[📝 Review] KOAL’s Bread Roll 🍞 ($8)

✨ Relatively new restaurant by @lesamisgroupsg✨

Served in a piping hot pan, the glistening shin caught my eye. Embedded with a handful of bacon and spring onions, the savoury bread was pillowy soft! 

The fragrance from the grilled spring onions and chopped bacon permeated through. The smear of chive butter added a touch of creaminess to the dinner rolls. 

P.S. As a bread lover, I was excited that they serve this for dinner! Bread anytime of the day yea?

Rating: 7.8/10

[📝 Media Drop] SöngHè's New Crop Rice 🍚

✨ Unstoppable with a bowl of fried rice ✨

The only time I’ll plough through bowls of rice is when I’m treated to freshly fried rice. Be it pineapple fried rice, stir fried rice, as long as it’s seasoned to taste, I can’t control myself. 

With the new crop rice, it’s convenient to clean with just a one time rinse! The rice grains were plump and moist! The recommended cooking guidelines are 1 cup of rice to 0.9-1 cup of water. Subjected to preference, adjust the volume of water to achieve the desired texture!

Whipped up servings of fried rice and enjoyed the texture and taste to it!

📍Available at Fairprice, Giant, Cold Storage, Sheng Siong, and their online platform Prime, Minimarts, Esso, Redmart/ Lazada, Shopee, Foodpanda, Amazon, Q0010

Thanks @getkobe for sending this packet of @songhe.rice over! ✨
taggedFullName2: Sōng Hè Fragrant Rice 松鹤香米 🍚

Hidden in the quiet corner on Braddell Road, between Bishan and Toa Payoh, is BRDL Restaurant & Bar. One of the three dining concepts under The Refectory, BRDL offers sophisticated European dishes with Asian flavours as well as interesting cocktails, invigorating alcohol and drinks. The space is airy with very high ceilings, interior design is chic with industrial feel, ambience is chill and relaxing. 

We visited them to try their exclusive dinner menu ($58 per pax) curated for the Nespresso SG Restaurant Week Spring 2022. The dishes are:

Welcome Snack
▪️Dried shrimps financier accompanied with uni and furikake butter (Daily rotation of surprises from the kitchen) 

1st Course
▪️Foie Gras & Duck Leg Terrine
▪️Mussel Chowder 

2nd Course
▪️Green Curry Barramundi
▪️Roasted Cod 

3rd Course
▪️Herb Crusted Lamb Rack
▪️Wagyu Cheek Rendang 

Dessert
▪️Mango Sticky Rice
▪️Durian Cheesecake 

I was utterly impressed with the menu. Every dish was absoutely delicious and the presented exqusitely. Each element was well-excuted, complementing and bursting with flavours. Chef Russell had displayed great techniques and creativity through his dishes. Thank you, Chef. 

To experience the special Nespresso Restaurant Week menu or visit BRDL for it's regular menu, check out website https://therefectory.asia/ or reserve a table at linktr.ee/TheRefectory (link in @brdlsg bio).  

You  may also check out the DiningCity app or website www.restaurantweek.sg for booking!

📍BRDL Restaurant & Bar
351 Braddell Rd,
01-01, S579713

Supply & Demand Esplanade is a modern Italian trattoria with a rooftop terrace and bar, known for serving up hearty pasta and delicious hand-opened thin-crust pizzas.

They are participating in the Nespresso Singapore Restaurant Week Spring 2022, which is happening from 4 to 27 March. Don't miss the fabulous deals (starting from $28) featuring more than 100 top restaurants in Singapore on DiningCity!

Featuring here is the 5-Course Set Dinner ($68 per person)

STARTER
Truffle Mushroom Arancini
Scallop Crudo
Stracciatella

MAIN COURSE
Crab & Scallop Tagliatelle
Seared Beef Pizza

DESSERT
Chocolate Berries Cake
Trio Of Cheese (+$6 supplement)

The set dinner was absolutely scrumptious, I enjoyed every dish. Not only tasty, but the dishes were also beautifully presented. I love that they focus on seasonal produce and homemade goods, the pasta was handmade fresh and sourdough freshly baked. All desserts were all proudly made in-house, they even have an Organic Herb Garden on the rooftop terrace! Come during sunset and you can enjoy a wonderful evening at the rooftop terrace with a beautiful view.

Check out the DiningCity app or website www.restaurantweek.sg for more info and booking!

description:
Call me old-fashioned or old school... whatever, but I still prefer to pen down my thoughts, plans and schedules on physical dairies and planners, even in this digital era. 

I love these premium quality paper products from Collins Debden, a reowned diary and stationery brand from UK. They are reputated for quality, style and innovation for over 200 years. 
Their paper-based products come from environment sustainable sources that are FSC® or PEFC™-certified. 

Featured here are the Engima Diary, Legacy Notebook and Planner Set. 

The Enigma diary is very functional with its 3 Year Calendars, Monthly Planners, and Note Pages. It's great for goal setting, plan meetings and keeping my busy schedules organised. 

The Legacy Notebook is perfect for note-taking and especially useful for jotting down my cooking recipes. 

I use the Weekly and Daily Planners to note down all my to-complete-tasks from my daily workout plans to housechores to collaborations. Really, my perfect companion! 

Check out their products here

I enjoyed a unique private dining experience at Nest At One Farrer and tried their degustation menu for the Nespresso SG Restaurant Week Spring.

Located at the top floor of One Farrer Hotel, @nestatonefarrer invites diners to immerse themselves in the safety and exclusivity of their very own private dining room while dining on exquisite cuisine.

The special 5-Courses degustation menu ($168/pax) features a few Nespresso coffee infused dishes that are curated to wow your palate.

The exclusive dishes for the Nespresso Restaurant Week Spring 2022 are:

1st Course
Kaiso Seaweed Salmon
(Nespresso infused dish)

2nd Course
Creamy Pine Mushroom with Chawanmushi

3rd Course
Black Cod with Salsa Verde

4th Course
Wagyu Beef

5th Course / Dessert
Caramel Nespresso Chocolate Sphere
(Nespresso infused dish)

I love both the dining experience and the food at Nest. All the dishes were excellent and exquisitely presented. Each and every element was well-executed and complemented each other. The private dining in the repurposed hotel rooms was exclusive and comfortable. A great experience i would love to recommend 👍

The Nespresso SG Restaurant Week Spring is on now till 27 March 2022. Don't miss the fabulous deals featuring more than 100 top restaurants in Singapore!

Check out the DiningCity app or website www.restaurantweek.sg for more info and booking!

New Bento Shop in Stanley Street, Central! 

From the same owners of Kenko Shokuhin Ramen, @kenko_ramen_ikkyu126 has recently opened right next door, selling a variety of delicious bento boxes for very reasonable price!

They have 20+ options with staple favourites like teriyaki chicken, pork cutlet, grilled salmon and so much more. Whether you are a meat-eater, pescatarian or vegetarian - there’s something for everyone!

I really enjoyed the variety that you get in these bento boxes 🤩 for this Fried Chicken bento, you get a side of tsukemono and potato salad. A nice balance of flavours and tender chicken meat. The portions are beyond decent! Also picked up a miso soup for $15. An overall hearty and tasty meal😍

Well worth the price and if you’re craving Japanese food, definitely make a pit stop here!

description:
@boxfansg serves variety of affordable and quality customisable bowls, along with sides and even bubble tea! 

We ordered 2 mains from Build Your Own Bowl menu (base + protein + 2 toppings):
🔹Mala Creamy Prawn ($9) with golden enoki + onsen egg + koka noodles
🔹Mentaiko Salmon ($10) with onsen egg + sautéed mushrooms + pearl rice 

The mains were hearty and well balanced. We loved that the mala creamy prawn had mala fragrance without the spiciness, and the mentaiko salmon was less salty than many others. For the mains, we'd highly recommend the koka noodles with signature scallion oil. 

We also went for their sides — Vegetable Tempura ($5), Oden ($5), Asian Spiced Edamame ($4). All were so yummy and of a good sharing portion! 

Their Breezer Tea ($5.80), which contains watermelon and lychee, was so refreshing! If you're a fan of taro, you'd like their Taro Milk Tea ($4.80)!

Box饭 also offers other options like Har Cheong Gai Fried Rice, Mac&Cheese and Aglio Olio. 

If you stay in the North, you're in luck for once! Box饭 is located along a street of F&B merchants, definitely worth a visit! Do note that Box饭 is closed on Mondays.

Flavourful, savoury & delightful would be how we will describe the myriad of Peranakan fusion cuisine served here at @slake.sg 🦢

Swipe right to join us as we immersed ourselves thoroughly at their latest outlet concept, as well as salivate at their mouthwatering food options.

Special highlights from our visit includes their Chye Poh Fries ($12), Battered Pig Ears ($14), Slake Crabcakes ($19), as well as their Seafood Laksa Linguine ($22).

Overall an experience that swept us off our feet, and we hear that they also have value-for-money weekday set menus for everyone as well. Definitely a restaurant worth our calories. ✨

Valentine's day is coming up tomorrow, and a beautiful way to celebrate this season would be sharing delicious desserts with your loved ones.

Featured in frame is @lawfully_bakes Mirror Glazed Chocolate Raspberry Mousse Cake ($14) - a sinfully decadent, yet balanced mousse cake with a good ratio of sweetness, bitterness alongside a touch of raspberry filling (see 3rd picture for cross section close up) to cut any potential cloying sensation.

Just for the Valentine week, they are offering free delivery for their mousse cake, even for singular orders. ✨

#chocolatemoussecake #valentinecake #sgig #igsg #homebakersg #WBFSG #worldbestfoodies

Along with The Batman movie, @littlecaesars_sg has launched a new Batman Calzony!

The Batman Calzony Combo ($20.88) consists of:
1x Batman Calzony Pizza
1x Wings (6pcs)
1x Crazy Calzony Sauce
2 x drinks

Little Caesars is well-known for its affordable and quality pizza. We loved how the homemade crust is slightly fluffy, buttery and crispy. We're surprised that the pizza wasn't cloying despite that it isn't thin crust! It's definitely not the usual pepperoni piazza — the mixture of parmesan, mozzarella, garlic crazy spread and julienned pepperoni. Their Crazy Sauce is specially made using vine-ripened California crushed tomatoes. 

On the side, we also ordered Stuffed Crazy Bread and Caesar Dip Packs. We'd highly recommend the Stuffed Crazy Bread — the cheese filling is so generous! 

The Batman Calzony is also available as ala carte ($10.90) or with a drink ($12.90).

Little Caesars is also running a series of promotions in collaboration with The Batman movie. Do check out their page for details!
location: Little Caesar's Pizza at Singpost Centre

I tried the Curement Herbal hair treatment from Japan at the salon, and the results are so amazing. This is a 3 step treatment combined with ultrasonic infrared iron to allow the product penetrate deeper into the hair. My hair feels super moisturized and soft after this treatment. I perm my hair every year and this has definitely repaired some of the damages. 

They are located very close to Vancouver City Center and they having stalls right in front of the store along with free street parking nearby! 

A special thanks to @William_muse for making my hair look healthy again!

Michelin 3 Stars in Paris 💫

I have to say contrary to most people, I didn’t have the best experience in Paris, BUT this place is one of my absolute loves 💯

We went there for lunch a couple years ago & had to catch a flight after, and the restaurant tailored our set menu to our schedules making sure we have plenty of time to get to the airport while also ensuring we have the best experience there. Towards the end of our meal the chef noticed we still got some time left, so he added a razor clam course for us 🥰

Even though we had a tighter schedule, the lunch experience was amazing. The food, the service & the chef was just incredible. This is one of my best Michelin experiences & I miss Paris solely because of this 👌🏻

Thank you @guysavoy for our wonderful lunch & I can’t wait til going back in the future 🤍

✨ A K A S A K A  J A P A N E S E  R E S T A U R A N T • Japanese and Korean Food✨

Featuring:
🍣 BC Roll 
🍱 Chicken Teriyaki Bento Box
🐮 Galbi Korean Beef Short Ribs

Akasaka is a Japanese restaurant that I always visit when I’m in Surrey because of their consistency and friendly service. Due to a building renovation in November 2021, they had to close down and move out of their Guildford location. However, they found a new location in Fleetwood and recently opened back up again! Their current menu is not as extensive as before, but they will be adding more to the menu. They serve both Japanese and Korean dishes, so you get to eat both cuisines in one place! I always get their BC roll because they use actual grilled salmon skin! 😋 #supportlocal
 
 
📍 #101-15988 Fraser Hwy, Surrey BC

✨ W A S U T A  P A S T A • Bookmark this if you’re looking for some Japanese Italian pasta! ✨

Tucked away on the second floor of a building along river road in Richmond, you will find this small Japanese Italian 🇯🇵🇮🇹 fusion restaurant @wasutapasta. Their pasta are all handmade fresh in house and was cooked al dente. I had the Fettuccine Scallop Uni Cream Sauce Pasta. It comes with a complimentary house salad and olives (lunch only). The sauce was creamy and rich with a slight uni taste. However, as I kept eating, I did find it to be on the saltier side. 

Featuring:
🍝 Fettuccine Scallop Uni Cream Sauce • $20.00
Rating: ⭐️⭐️⭐️.5
 
 
📍202-7080 River Road, Richmond BC
🗓 Reservations are recommended!

✨ T O M A H A W K • OLDEST RESTAURANT IN VANCOUVER (1926) 🇨🇦✨

HAPPY FRIDAY!!! Thinking about where to brunch this weekend? If so, you need to go check out @tomahawkrestaurant , a hidden gem located in North Vancouver. They serve your classic Canadian comfort food. 

Featuring:
🍳 Classic Egg Benny • $16.25
🍞 Fluffy French Toast • $13.40

The classic egg Benny is made with two poached free run eggs and Yukon style bacon along with their signature hollandaise sauce and a side of hash brown potatoes! So delicious and satisfying! 

The fluffy French toast are thick sliced French bread dipped in their secret batter, griddled to a golden brown and sprinkled with icing sugar. I also love their pure Canadian maple syrup as it wasn’t overly sweet! 
 
 
📍 1550 Philip Ave, North Vancouver BC
🕛 TUES-THURS 9AM-4PM; FRI-SUN 9AM-8PM

Thank you @tomahawkrestaurant for the wonderful brunch experience! #media

Looking for a quick bite? Head over to GRAB N GO ! @grabngo_official has three different locations. The one I visited was tucked away on the second floor of Robson Public Market! They offer a wide variety of fillings for their inaris (sushi rice stuffed inside a fried tofu pouch) and I love how they are made to order. I ordered three kinds: Mentaiko Crabmeat, Baby Octopus, and Grilled Unagi. All three were really tasty! I can’t wait to go back to try all their other fillings!

Ratings: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
 
 
 📍 #213-1610 Robson Street, Vancouver BC (Located on the 2F of Robson Public Market)

[Kulto]
Another once-a-month Spanish food gathering, and this time to try @kulto.sg!

Octopus 'Galician Style' ($32)
The texture here was good! Q soft and tender, and the sauce is not bad, just that I personally prefer those that comes with a smokey or burnt flavour.

🌟 Iberico Chorizo, Confit potato & Soft Eggs ($24) 📸 3
The chorizo was slightly smokey, and had a good bite, which also went well with the potato and runny eggs 🤤. The addition of onions was also 💯! Oh how much I'd love to have this for breakfast regularly 😍.

Jamon Iberico Croquettes & Crab Croquettes ($14/ 4 pcs) 📸 4, 5
They usually sell in 4 pcs, but you can choose to get 2 of each flavour instead. Jamon Iberico tasted like carbonara in a croquette, but can't put my finger on which shop's carbonara it's similar to. For the Crab Croquette, it was really similar to the sauce used in dry laksa pasta.

🌟 Homemade Cheese Terrine with Truffle & Honey Olive Oil ($22) 📸 6
Really creamy and light cheese that's similar to cream cheese texture. Very mild mushroom fragrance and flavour, I loved this combination! Super crispy bread to pair with too, defo enjoyable!

Charcoal Lamb Rack with Carrots & Caramelised Baby Onions ($38) 📸 7
The baby onions nicely helps to mask the gaminess of the lamb. The pairing sauce was slightly sour, reminding of vinegar. 

Seafood Paella (2-3 pax $39) 📸 2
This was literally the most hyped dish here but ended up being the most disappointing one here? The rice texture really no-go, it was pretty hard (not crispy), similar to undercooked rice. The juice from the prawn head also made it really fishy, which we didn't really enjoy. 

🌟 Kulto Cheesecake ($14) 📸 8, 9
The cheesecake was really molten and quite creamy! The sorbet was really tangy - personally not a fan of the sorbet here, so would just go for the cheesecake. 

Whiskey Cake with Almonds ($14) 📸 10
Actually didn't expect them to pour whiskey over the cake, because we expected the whiskey to be infused instead. Whiskey is definitely strong and slightly spicy. Cream is really light, but reminiscent of the traditional bakery vanilla cream cake. Great for those who love whiskey!

Overall Rating: 8/10

description:
[Milano Pizza & Wine] 
@milanopizzasg is a sister of @pastabar_sg, and I was really excited to finally book a seat to try it!

Sicilian Grandma Pizzas (6" square, 2" deep pie):
Let's first talk about the dough - their Grandma Pizzas use sourdough, so it's slightly tangy in flavour. I'd say it's really unique, with it being slightly thick, crispy on the outside and slightly airy on the inside! 

Mortadella & Burrata ($27++)
This was probably my favourite that night! We had 1-2 pizzas before this, so I really loved how the burrata helped to cut through some of the greasiness with its light and creamy flavour. The mortadella isn't strong unlike meats like Parma ham, so you don't get to taste much of the meat as a whole.

Truffle Mushroom ($38++)
This came with truffle cream and fresh shaved truffle, but you only get a slight hint of truffle. Expected it to be really strong, but the mixed mushrooms are instead more overpowering. Personally would prefer even stronger truffle flavour, but those who love mushroom flavours more would prefer this.

Neo-Neopolitan 12" Pizzas:
Beef Cheek Bolognese ($34++) 📸 4
Slow-simmered beef cheek. Felt that their neopolitan pizza doughs are slightly tougher, especially once it cools a little. 

Sausage & Hot Chilies ($28++) 📸 5
Homemade pork sausage is used here, and comes with pickled hot chillies. Didn't remember this to be spicy tho!

Korea town ($32++) 📸 6
You do taste Korean flavours, which comes from the Gochujang & kimchi. Overall decent pizza, except some slices of the Marinated Short Rib were really chewy and almost impossible to bite through (we were guessing tendon?).

Desserts:
Amalfi Lemon Meringue Pie ($16++)
This was good! The lemon was surprisingly not really tangy, and the pie was of the flaky kind with layers similar to millefeuille. Overall paired with the basil cream, this was q a delight to have.

Tiramisu Pie ($16++)
I tried this before the lemon meringue, and I really liked the tiramisu flavour! But this really took the backseat once I had the lemon meringue pie.
The pie here was quite dry and didn't have much flavour - wouldn't mind to remove the pie entirely, and just serve tiramisu 😂.

Overall Rating: 7/10

description:
[90 Minutes] - Tasting
For those who love Korean Hotpot, here's one affordable option near Dhoby Ghaut MRT!

For 90 minutes, you get to enjoy buffet with free flow soft drinks! You also get to pick the sauce for your hotpot - we got Classic (Homemade + Gungjung) & Rose (Carbonara + Volcano).

Buffet Prices: 
Mon - Fri Lunch/ Dinner 
• Adult: $15.90++/ $23.90++
• Child: $9.90++/ $12.90++
• Student: $13.90++/ $19.90++
• Senior: $13.90++/ $19.90++

Sat, Sun, Eve PH, PH
• Adult: $24.90++
• Child: $12.90++
• Student: $19.90++ 
• Senior: $19.90++ 

Add-ons: 
Cheese Ring ($9.90)
This came pretty stretchy, but you have to eat it very quickly because they'll harden very fast, making it really difficult to eat afterwards!

Corn Dog ($4.50/ pc)
This came piping hot but we only ate it when it had cooled down, so it was no longer crispy, but the flavour from the sauce was not too bad. 

Overall really enjoyed the Cheese and Sweet Potato Tteokbokki, because of the filling within, and they were pretty chewy! There's also some cooked food available including Gyoza, Fishcake, etc.

Don't forget to save some stomach as the leftover soup from your hotpot can be used to cook Fried Rice, and the staff would be there to help you cook it!

PROMO:
There's 30% off with Burpple Beyond Deals (if you already have Burpple Membership), or you can quote "WEIP6886" for 30% off when you sign up for Burpple Premium Plan! 🤭

Thank you @burpple for the invite and @90minutes.sg for hosting!

description:
[Don Lechon]
Have you tried Filipino food before? I've had decent ones previously, and this place was pretty famous for their pork, so I was really excited to head down to try it.

You can choose to get rice meals/ order dishes ala carte here, but the former will come with rice and smaller portion of meat that's more suitable for 1 pax.

Lechon Sisig Ala Carte ($14)
This was the better of the 2 dishes. It's meant to be piping hot when served, but it only sizzled for a good 15s before it stopped, which was pretty disappointing. The meat here was quite flavourful and went well with rice, but it's apparently meant to be crispier. (Swipe to 3rd 📸 for sizzle)

Chopped Lechon (0.5kg - $22, 1kg - $40)
I came here for these, but these were served cold, which already meant what we were having weren't of the best quality. Some pieces of skin were crispy, but there were some that were very hard and almost impossible to bite through. There's nothing special about the pork here as well other than its thick cut.

Overall pretty disappointing, and after being hyped for such a long time, I guess the standards have really dropped drastically.

Overall Rating: 5/10

description:
[Spacebox] - Invited Tasting
@spaceboxsg has really interesting Space-themed bistro bar vibes, and are great for those who love to drink and enjoy loklok/ zichar dishes there!

Assorted Skewers
Their broccoli is a must-try! Really well-grilled with that charred/ smoky flavour. There's q a good variety of meat skewers (pork, beef, lamb, chicken), as well as meatball, crabmeat, lotus root and Taiwan Sausage!

Grilled Scallops (Garlic/ Cheese)
I liked the generous amount of cheese used for their scallops, and the 冬粉 (glass noodles) used for the garlic one was pretty flavourful too!

Moonlight Hor Fun
This was a little similar to having CKT, but not that I mind it, because it's again flavourful, and the noodles are q well-cooked, so definitely enjoyable!

Yang Zhou Fried Rice
This fried rice isn't the kind with strong wokhei, but it's more of comforting, hearty ones which some may enjoy too.

辣子鸡 Szechuan Spicy Chicken 
Although this wasn't spicy at all, I personally really liked the strong spice flavours, which was enough to keep me going at it.

Roast Pork with Garlic
I really liked this dish?! Really soft and tender pork, which was pretty flavourful too. For those who love garlic, you can pair their pork with an entire garlic clove, which definetely will pack a huge GARLIC punch, and best part is the garlic skin was really crispy! 

Enoki Mushroom
It's not extremely strong on the butter or garlic in the sauce here, but it's still pretty enjoyable with a good bite in the sauce that it's cooked in!

If you're up for some veg, there's also Sambal Lady's Fingers which aren't really spicy, and 油麦菜 (Chinese Lettuce) that was surprisingly q enjoyable too!

Thank you @fatpigdiary for inviting and @spaceboxsg for hosting!

description:
Sales tax or GST will be hiked in Singapore wef 1st January 2023 but vendors have already started raising their prices this month when the impending hike was announced. #inflation
.
This luscious yoghurt cream cake with mixed fruit topping (pictured in frame) used to cost SGD52 but is now priced at SGD58, an increase of more than 10%.
.
Made in Singapore swiss rolls which used to cost SGD10 per roll already had their prices hiked in January 2022 by 20% to SGD12 per roll. (Swipe for next photo.) Usually the swiss rolls at the Rich & Good Cake Shop at Jewel Mall Changi Airport are sold out by early afternoon. There used to be snaking queues even on weekdays but there's no queue at all when we visited so we bought their kaya^ swiss roll and durian cream swiss roll for tea. Hello Weekend.🙂
.

description:
(Not Sponsored) Deliveroo is having SGD1.30 fee promo till Sunday, 13th March 2022 so we didn't have to order our lunch from just one F&B store to minimize delivery fees. To beat the Monday blues, we ordered hearty bowls from Ah Lock's Kitchen and from Yu Pan (御品).
.
The first three photos feature #noodlebowls from Ah Lock's Kitchen, whose Hakka tofu  rice bowls popular with the downtown office crowd need no intro.(Swipe for more pics.) Today, I had the #YTF 'beehoon' or rice vermicelli soup which has housemade pork meatballs, fried 'tau kee' or beancurd sheets, stuffed 'taukwa' or beancurd and leafy greens (帝王菜 which Ah Lock's Kitchen refers to as 'mani chye'). Their new crispy chicken cutlet bowl is not bad. However, instead of a slab of chicken cutlet (as shown in the Deliveroo app photos), the noodle bowl comes with a few slices of pre-cut fried chicken. My lunch mate, enticed by Deliveroo's photo, was expecting more meat for the SGD7.80 price tag. #chickennoodles
.
The 4th, 5th, 6th photos feature food from Yu Pan (御品), with stalls in various coffee shops and food courts selling tasty fishball soup and sliced fish soup with choice of noodles and rice. The sliced fish vermicelli soup is a  guilt free meal, thick slices of market fresh white fish in a sweet, clean tasting broth. What is surprising ~ Yu Pan's signature soup 招牌汤 which is MSG-free but remarkably slurpalicious broth 😋 with generous portions of minced pork, sliced lean pork and sliced bittergourd .... does not contain any sliced fish.😅 To enjoy the best of both worlds, order the sliced #fishsoup and their signature soup and mix both together.🥣 御品招牌汤 on its own is a balanced, one dish keto meal. 🤗 
^Deliveroo's prices: fishball noodle soup SGD5.50 || fish soup only w/o noodles or rice SGD6.50; fish soup with noodles/rice SGD7.50
.

Sunday morning bake: 𝗕𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗕𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗕𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗦𝗲𝘀𝗮𝗺𝗲 𝗕𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗮 𝗕𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱🍌🍞 As a sucker for black sesame, I had to try this recipe from @justine_snacks 🥺 Could use more black sesame and butter cos I ran out, otherwise this bread is soft, moist and tasty 👅 Adapted recipe:

- 113g unsalted butter
- 400g banana 
- 50g raw sugar
- 2 eggs
- 1 tsp vanilla extract
- 180g flour
- 1 1/2 tsp baking soda
- 1/2 tsp salt
- 95g black sesame paste

Brown butter on the stove, till light brown flecks that appear turn golden brown and there’s a toasty aroma. Take it off the stove and whisk with sugar to combine (I didn’t have enough butter, so I replaced the rest with grapeseed oil). Let the mixture cool for 5-10 mins. Once it’s cool, whisk in eggs and vanilla extract, then mashed bananas. Add in flour, salt and baking soda. Divide batter into two and add black sesame paste into one half. (I didn’t have enough black sesame paste so I divided the mixture into 1/3 with black sesame and 2/3 without instead). Pour batter into a pan, alternating between the black sesame and original batter. Bake in preheated oven at 180c for 50-60 mins. 
#oatlyhomecafe

Tried something new at @breadyard , featuring the 𝗚𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁 𝗩𝗲𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗕𝗼𝘄𝗹 ($𝟭𝟰++)🌱 Lots of healthy ingredients - eggplant, broccoli, chickpeas, hummus, onions, pomegranate, amba (mango pickle) - on a bed of brown rice, with a drizzle of tahini on the side. Definitely get this if you love Mediterranean flavours and is looking for a healthier brunch/lunch. Sourdough was also served on the side but not sure how it’s supposed to go together with the rice bowl, except for adding carbs on carbs. Was also not tangy enough imo😢

Had the 𝗟𝗼𝗻𝗴 𝗕𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗸 ($𝟯.𝟱𝟬++) for drinks and it was decent - full bodied and not acidic👏🏻

‼️PSA: Use Burpple for 20% off! But note that it only applies to mains, not drinks. ALSO, stick around till 5pm for 50% off bread and 30% off cruffins!!! Super worth😋😋

𝘙𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘨: 7/10. Probably would stick to my fav 𝘗𝘶𝘭𝘭𝘦𝘥 𝘗𝘰𝘳𝘬 𝘌𝘨𝘨𝘴 𝘉𝘦𝘯𝘦𝘥𝘪𝘤𝘵 next time~ 
#oatlyyums #oatlyburps

Nourishing, protein-packed meal😋 Kim Dae Mun serves affordable Korean fare in Orchard, at the basement of Concorde Hotel. Had to try one of my fav dishes from any Korean place - 𝗚𝗶𝗻𝘀𝗲𝗻𝗴 𝗖𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗻 𝗦𝗼𝘂𝗽 ($𝟭𝟱) + $𝟬.𝟱𝟬 to upgrade to 𝗥𝗲𝗱 𝗕𝗲𝗮𝗻 𝗥𝗶𝗰𝗲. Absolutely value for money as I was served half a chicken, with both breast and thigh meat. The breast meat can be quite dry and tough but dipping it in the seasoned salt at the side helped to bring some flavour back to it. The soup was generously filled with glutinous rice too, along with red dates, garlic and ginseng. Although I must say that the flavour of the soup is not the best that I’ve tasted, I’m willing to overlook it for the generosity of ingredients at this price point.

𝘙𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘨: 8/10. Worth a visit when you’re in town🙂
#oatlyyums

🤯12 FREE FLOW BANCHANS? Amidst the tens of Korean restaurants in Beauty World, Kim’s got us coming back for this unlimited spread of side dishes🤤

Got the 𝗦𝗽𝗶𝗰𝘆 𝗣𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗦𝗼𝘂𝗽 ($𝟮𝟮++) this time but was slightly disappointed. $22 for three medium to small pieces of fish… and tofu and vegetables... Soup wasn’t particularly flavourful either. 😢

𝘙𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘨: 7/10 overall, 5/10 for my order. Tried other dishes and they were much less disappointing, though I must say the highlight would still be the banchan 
#oatlyyums

Happy weekend! Kicked off the weekend with a burger night @25degreesinsingapore ! 🍔

Purchased a Chope voucher which scored us two burgers at the price of one @ $𝟭𝟱++🥳 My friend and I shared the 𝗡𝘂𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝗢𝗻𝗲 and 𝗡𝘂𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝗧𝘄𝗼, and we both preferred the latter. Not to say the first one wasn’t good, we were just not used to the slightly funky, almost blue-cheese-like smell of the cheese. Both burgers featured super soft buns and smoky, juicy and thick beef patties. 

We also shared the 𝗖𝘂𝗿𝗹𝘆 𝗙𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀 ($𝟱++) and these were standard. As good as fries can be. 🍟

𝘙𝘢𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘨: 8.5/10. Amazing stuff that’d have me coming back👅
#oatlyyums

🍴DINE OUT🍴
📍Bread Yard, Fusionopolis📍
💸 Pulled Pork Eggs Benedict: $14
💸 Beef Kofta Shakshuka: $16
💸 Cruffin (Matcha, Passionfruit): $5 each
💸 Dirty Chai Latte: $6
*Prices not inclusive of GST and before Burpple discount (20% off mains)
....
Discovered a cafe in One-North with good food, generous portions and affordable prices the other day👍! Definitely recommend the Pulled Pork Eggs Benedict, with slightly sweet-tasting pulled pork and poached eggs over a nicely toasted brioche🍞. Love that the egg yolk was nice and runny, which serves like a sauce🍳. When we had all the elements in one bite, it was really an explosion of flavours in our mouths, super satisying🎆!! 

Also, don't leave without trying their cruffins, which is a hybrid of a croissant and muffin🥐🧁. We tried two of their flavours and preferred the matcha over the passionfruit. The matcha flavour was strong and not too sweet. Wish there was more matcha filling though😅!! On the other hand, the passionfruit filling was a little too sweet for us. 

Overall, a great cafe to chill at but it can get a little busy during weekends lunch so be sure to head down a little earlier☺️!

🍴TAKE OUT🍴
📍Nasty Cookie📍
...
Got some nasty cookie treats for ourselves for the weekend🌚!! If you're eating it at home, be sure to heat it up first so that it is slightly warm and oozy on the inside🔥. Texture wise, the cookies are on the thicker, denser and chewier end🍪. They are quite fragrant and buttery, but taste waaay too sweet for our liking. After a while, it got a bit jelak and it was hard to finish one whole cookie alone. Truly a sinful and indulgent snack😶!!

🍴DINE OUT🍴
📍Poke Theory, 111 Somerset📍
...
Love these vibrant looking poke bowls from poke theory, they not only look great but taste great as well🥗! They offer a wide variety of poke and sides, making it super customisable. Our favourite poke is their mentaiko mayo salmon and orginal shoyu salmon, both super good👍. It tastes really fresh as well, perfect for a light and healthy meal~😀

👩‍🍳MUNCH AT HOME👩‍🍳
After all that intense CNY cooking🤯, our family has been making simple meals and one of them is the simple one-pan Oyakodon (Chicken and Egg bowl)🐓🥚! Really love the combination of the slightly sweet and salty dashi sauce with chicken, creamy eggs, and soft onions over rice🍚. You can pan-fry the chicken first if you want them to be slightly charred and fragrant, but that's completely optional😊. Overall, a super comforting rice bowl that's good to have for a quick meal~😋

🍴DINE OUT🍴
📍Cafe Found, Ngee Ann City📍
💸 Matcha Layered Cake
...
Tried Cafe Found which was located within The Editor's Market at Ngee Ann City. The Matcha Layered Cake🍵 was pretty good, with alternating layers of matcha ganache, cream cheese🧀 and macademia crust which added a nice crunch to it. There were two sizes available and we ordered the bigger one, which was quite a hefty portion😲. Recommend to share it among three or more people👭👭 as the cream cheese could get a bit overwhelming after some time. Overall, a nice spot to chill at after shopping🛍️, but seats were quite limited and we wouldn't say the food left a lasting impression on us😕!

Their coffee was worth the long wait, round body with chocolate note ☕

"What tea is on the menu?" This is probably the idea we brought along when we visit a TWG chain in Singapore, preparing ourselves to indulge in their quality and popular tea varieties with some tea time desserts to go along. And so we are proven wrong with the all-day mains featuring pastas to many kinds of western cuisines. 

While the V-day special menu featured on most of our plates (photos for reference and we did not do a full review anyway since they are off the menu at this juncture), the regularly featured wagyu tenderloin is one dish that captivates us from all angles. 

From the flavourful bearnaise sauce to the tenderness of the wagyu slices, accompanied by a matcha truffle drizzled fries, this dish is worth every feature in the atmospheric tea garden at MBS.

As we are mentally prepared to join the snaking queues of KBBQ chains along the popular go-to Tanjong Pagar Street on a New Year Eve, our attention instantly switched towards a similar concept store with the name 'On Dol'. 

The plethora of vegetable choices to use as wraps was a pleasant surprise to us and we firmly believed that this is a one of a kind here in SG. Yes we admit we cant even call out half of the vegetable names but we are totally spoilt for choices with the wide range of banchan (side dishes including those to be grilled along the meat) and main dishes (besides meat; steamed egg, seafood stew) to come along. 

Not forgetting the highlight of the show with different cuts of pork meat which are grilled on hot stone by the friendly hyungnim. For $80++, you end your 2pax set meal with a choice of a hot stone pot rice or fried rice. We had the fried rice and the friendly staff reappeared to fry the fragrant rice with the remaining pork from the BBQ. There you have a tasty portion of fried Bibimbap. Look what the staff prepared for us!

Having missed out for a few time due to overwhelming crowd, we finally had the chance to visit this popular dessert spot. 

Hidden at a corner of the quiet Fortune Centre with a homely and cosy setting, @yatkayan rolls us back to our sweet nostalgic memories by serving up bowls of classic 糖水. The plain chendol stands out in particular with its flavourful blend and perfectly done pandan jelly. 

With a balanced taste and combination, this bowl of chendol is arguably one of the best chendols out there in the island. Probably even better than the one you had in a town somewhere across the shore?

[Review] While my husband is a huge fan of coffee desserts, I have never been as interested until I tried my very first Tiramisu. And this love for Tiramisu has gotten even stronger after tasting the version from @epilopz

We love that this Tiramisu has distinctive layers made up of cream and cake, which contributes to a rather dimensional texture overall. Fresh ingredients including made-in-italy mascarpone cheese, freshly brewed espresso and their special blend of coffee liqueurs are used to create this beauty. While the taste of alcohol is more obvious in some parts than others, the level of alcohol is sufficient and blends well with the aromatic coffee flavour to create a harmonious whole. It is also not too soggy and very creamy 🤤. We really enjoyed this Tiramisu and don't mind getting this in the future again.

The Basque Burnt Cheese cupcakes are of the perfect size for individual consumption and will make a great tea-time snack! The cheesy flavour is prominent and tastes of high quality. The burnt part of the cake is on point too, right level of char in our opinion.

Overall the desserts are well-made and we can feel the love the baker has for each piece. Most importantly, their bakes are made-to-order to ensure freshness. So if you like a good dessert sent to your home, check out @epilopz for their delectable treats!

[Recipe] This is a very delicious drink which we truly enjoyed! A green milk tea with a light fruity flavour from the use of blueberries and the right level of sweetness. Give it a try and let us know what you think!

Ingredients

50g fresh blueberries
20g sugar

100ml milk
1 tsp green tea powder
60ml hot water
1 tsp honey

1) Mash and combine blueberries with sugar. Set aside.

2) Dissolved green tea powder in hot water (around 80°c). Add honey and stir into green tea.

3) Add blueberry syrup from point 1 into a glass. Add a moderate amount of ice. Pour milk and top with honey green tea from point 2.

Done!

[Review] 4.8/5 Rating Online
Lake View Golden Seafood Soup

This eatery at IMM Jurong East serves Pao Fan "泡饭" and soup dishes, and we recently tried 2 of their popular soups for brunch as they open at 10am daily.

1) Signature Golden Seafood Soup ($10.90)
As the name suggests, this is their Golden Boy! It's comes with a wide range of seafood like big prawn, scallop, clams and batang fish. It is complemented with their homemade meatballs, fried egg floss, rice puffs, tomatoes and vegetables. The thick broth is full of umami flavour from the seafood and vegetables, and we love slurping it to the last drop with the crispy rice puffs. Definitely a must try if you visit!

2) Golden Shabu Shabu Soup ($8.90)
This soup is also seafood and tomato based, but not as thick as their signature. The pork was finely sliced and tender to the bite. We love their flavourful meatballs which has a light chewy bite. The quality of the handmade meatballs is definitely much higher than the mass produced versions.

Overall the food is of a high standard and we will return to @lakeviewgoldenseafood to try their steamed fish which seems promising!

Address: 
2 Jurong East Street 21, 01-K09 IMM, Singapore 609601

[Review] 4.7/5 Rating Online
@Whyzee.sg

This 6 inch Red Velvet Cake comes with a twist - it contains a layer of creamy and "Gao" (thick) peanut butter filling. Definitely 100% appealing to fans of peanut butter! The delicious cream cheese in the cake complements perfectly with the peanut butter for a rich and sweet flavour, which to our delight, is not cloying at all. The red velvet cake layers by themselves are not too sweet, but the chocolate flavour is not strong either. If you prefer intense chocolaty flavour, then opt for another cake.

This online bakery offers 1 hour express delivery so if you are pressed for time, it may save your day. We ordered the cake just a day before my Hubby's Birthday Celebration and went with the 3pm to 6pm slot. The cake arrived at the designated time, though we did not receive any notification that it had reached us (the cake was left at our doorstep). It would have been nice if the bakery provided plates and forks too, which is what many bakeries do nowadays.

Overall, we enjoyed the cake and will consider purchasing again in the future. There is a 10% discount for new customers with the discount code WHYZEENEW10, which does sweeten the deal! In total, we spent about $53 including delivery for this cake.

Have a great week ahead!

[Recipe] Stewed Pork Bee Hoon

A super easy and quick recipe on a busy day! Comforting dish that I used to enjoy as a kid. Here is how I made it -

Ingredients

1 can of Narcissus Brand Stewed Pork / 红烧猪肉 (397g) and 1 can of Gulong Brand Stewed Pork Chops / 红烧排骨 (256g)

Half a packet of dried beehoon (around 185g to 200g). Soak in room temperature water till fully rehydrated.

2 tbsp of cooking wine

4 medium sized shitake dried mushrooms, soak in water to rehydrate till fully soften. Reserve the mushroom water.

Moderate amount of green vegetables (l precooked in advance)

Around 1 cup of water (approx 240 ml, including mushroom water)

Steps

1) Pour all the canned stewed pork and stewed pork chops, together with their soaking liquid, into a big pot. Also add in sliced rehydrated mushrooms. Lastly, add around 1 cup of water (including mushroom water) into the pot. Turn on the heat and bring the liquid to a boil.

2) Add in the rehydrated Bee Hoon and stir into the liquid. Boil everything together. Cover with a lid and let the Bee Hoon simmer. Add in pre-cooked vegetables after the Bee Hoon has simmered for five to ten minutes. Mix everything well. Add more liquid if it is drying up too quickly.

3) When most of the liquid has been soaked up by the Bee Hoon or when the Bee Hoon reaches the texture you like, give it a taste test and add seasoning if needed. I did not add any as I find the Bee Hoon already flavourful enough.

*Note - If you find the taste too salty, you can top up with some hot water. However, do not boil it down again or you will be back to the same state.

4) To add some fragrance to the dish, pour in cooking wine at the sides of the pot and mix everything well (optional).

And that's it! Hope you like this recipe and have a great day 😊

#TRAVELWITHGANDA X #MARRIOTTMELBOURNEDOCKLANDS
.
Having called Docklands home for almost the past decade, I have witnessed how this important part of Melbourne has grown
.
I see Docklands as a blank canvas, a canvas for any artists to paint a stroke on. That probably is also the reason why we see more and more unique buildings emerging in this waterfront suburb
.
One of the latest additions of which I am very excited to check out myself upon my return  is the arrival of the luxurious @marriottmelbournedocklands, which in case you are not aware yet, will be launching in 2 days.
.
While I am still unable to witness & experience it myself, I encourage you all to check it out and tell me what you think. Marriott Melbourne Docklands will be ready to welcome you from November 24 onwards.
.
Book your stay now at marriottmelbournedocklands.com
#MarriottMelbourneDocklands #MelbourneMarriottDocklands #marriottdocklands

#TRAVELWITHGANDA X #FOUNTAINHEAD
.
After almost a decade (a good 9 years) of not being back to the capital city, I finally returned
.
With so many new places in town, it was honestly overwhelming and boy, I surely had forgotten how big Jakarta is and how far things are from point to point (especially when the main purpose of the trip wasn’t merely just for leisure)
.
But one of the places that I managed to check out is @fountainhead.co located in West of Jakarta which is such an adorable spot with a classic modern exterior and interior, and for those of you who knows my love for #arches and that petal shaped canopy! #love
.
#fountainheadcafe #jakartabarat #meruya #cafehopping #architecture #interiordesign #cafedesign #hospitalitydesign #cafeinterior #classicmodern #contemporarydesign #monochromatic #facadedesign #cafeporn #jakartacafe

#blessed #twentysix
.
The last time I celebrated my birthday back home in Indonesia was when I turned 16 and who would have thought that a decade later, in the middle of the world pandemic, I get to celebrate my birthday at home again (with the company of my whole family)
.
Of course, having another lockdown birthday isn’t great. But there is always a silver lining to everything. If there wasn’t a pandemic currently happening, I would have gone back to Australia and probably wouldn’t have the chance to celebrate with my complete family members (and best friends) again
.
My heart is full from the amount of loves that each one of you had showered me with and I couldn’t be more grateful
.
Turning 26 surely makes me feel that I have to take adulting even more seriously now and as always, I am always very excited to unfold what life has got in store for me. While usually I would wish for every things that my heart desire, this year on top of my wish is surely for all of us to be healthy always and that may life goes back to normal again
.
Thanks for reading all my random thoughts that had been filling my head the past few days. Stay safe and healthy and please pray that this waistline is not going to be severely affected by the amount of cakes I have been savouring
.
Special thanks to @graciaganda @gladysganda @sherrilynchang @khekhee @lyccocymirror @sherly.herliana @sherlycarolinelie @summercatz_ @yoojin_1211 @nadcitra @wita___99 @debbie.i @deviline2911 @vel0711 @byanch_c @limkage @tiffchantellejo @vvlautan @peanotshell

~Chapati Veggie Set~
From @delhiexpresssg 
With spicy cauliflower & butter paneer.

One of my go-to stalls when visiting @laupasat.sg 😋

It comes with 2 sheets of chapati, any 2 veggie options to complete the set & a cup of dessert-of-the-day. 
These 2 are my fav options, the paneer is buttery & savory while the cauliflower is crispy & spicy!

May look like the portion is small, but it’s really just nice for my tummy. Although there were starving days where I’d then order the 3 veggie set that comes with rice as well🤣.

My indian colleagues recommended this stall to me so pretty it’s pretty guaranteed coming from the right source, eh?

Enjoy 10% when purchasing with kopitiam card (applicable for all stalls there too) 😉

~Hotteok~ 호떡
Aka korean sweet pancakes

I made my own hotteok for snacks! 😋

I love having these! Though it’s pretty much just flour, peanuts & sugar😂.

It’s really more on the texture that’s crispy & chewy, with that sweet nutty cinnamony fillings that makes this an interesting & addictive snacks😋.

Was worried that the hotteok will burst if I put too much fillings, but turns out I was just being too careful. Will stuff more fillings next time!😍

Happy Monday! It rains today, so these hotteok feels just right for the weather❤️

description:
~🌸Sakura 🌸~ @gardensbythebay 

When it’s Spring, it’s time for Cherry Blossoms 😍. And since Gardens By the Bay’s here to present you Sakura, you don’t have to fly all the way to Japan or Korea 😉

The festival’s happening at Flower Dome & will end on 3rd April 2022. Not all has bloomed yet, so you’ll still get the chance to see them bloom probably in the next few weeks. Nevertheless, to those who cant wait (like me 😝) there are already a few beautiful trees ready for you to take as many photos as you wish📸

Ticket goes for $12 (or $20 if you wish to visit Cloud Forest as well) and cheaper for the kids & seniors.

Happy Saturday!🌸💞

Topped with fresh ingredients and generous portion, you can’t go wrong with these pizzas!

We had the Goldenroy Weekday Special Set which consists of four flavors (2boxes, two flavors/box) and Parmesan Garlic Knots, eaten with tangy pepper sauce. 

Pizza flavors include:
- Roy’s favorite (Mushroom Pesto)
- Kryptonite (Clam & Garlic)
- Here comes the sun (Roast Beef & Garlic)
- That 10k Bitcoin (Beef pepperoni & Rare Cheese)

The trend for sourdough pizza is showing no sign of slowing down- and rightly so! It’s delicious and good for the gut, also the characteristic dough serves as a healthy backdrop for all the robust gourmet toppings.

Visited @aliceboulangeriesg last weekend, where we tried out a couple of dishes from their all-new brunch menu, as well as their made-in-house pastry and desserts:
•
~Tiger Prawn Capellini: This is seriously yummy and we highly recommend trying this! The pasta was al dente and the tiger prawns were fresh, but it was the prawn stock that brought everything together and elevated this dish to a must-try!
•
~Alice’s Big Breakfast: This is a solid brunch plate; each ingredient was good individually - nothing to complain about really!
•
~Yuzu Tart: Yuzu lovers will definitely enjoy this! There is a huge burst of yuzu flavour as you bite into the tart, with hints of alcohol from the gin. It did get a tad jelak towards the end though.
•
~Champagne Ispahan: This is our favourite among the trio! Taste was unique and refreshing! We loved how the champagne jelly brought the flavours of lychee, raspberry and rose together! Highly recommended!
•
~Pistachio Chocolate Croissant: This is a good croissant overall, but it would have been perfect if the pistachio taste was stronger.
•
✨ Overall Rating: 4/5
🏷 Alice Boulangerie
📍 #01-05/11, Icon Village, 12 Gopeng St, Singapore 078877
⏰ Sun-Thurs: 8am to 6pm, Fri-Sat: 8am to 9pm
.

We visited @beastandbutterflies recently to try some new dishes on their menu (*available on dinner menu only, the rest are available on brunch, lunch & dinner menus):
•
~*Prime Rib of Beef (1kg) w/ baked cheesy garlic cauliflower gratin & blue cream cheese sauce: Would recommend ordering this whopping 1kg portion of beef to share if you’re a group of meat lovers dining together! Although the beef wasn’t as tender as what I would’ve liked, it was still really well-seasoned and had a good bite to it! Not the biggest fan of the blue cream cheese sauce though; did not think it went well with the beef. I recommend going for the black pepper or red wine sauce instead.
•
~Cod Papilotte in superior soy sauce w/ classic rosemary butter roasted potatoes: The cod fish had a nice firm texture, and it was paired very nicely with the soy sauce too!
•
~Octopus Salad: This is a good salad! Each ingredient shone individually, but the star of the show is of course the octopus which was done really well!
•
~Mushroom Veloute: Thick & creamy, just the way I like it!
•
~Orh Nee Brûlée: I like how they incorporated orh nee into this classic dessert, where instead of custard, you get an orh nee base. The richness of the orh nee is a nice contrast to the sweetness of the caramelised sugar. Love it!
•
~Pandan Panna Cotta: Smooth and pretty fragrant, with the gula melaka syrup adding an extra sweetness!
•
✨ Overall Rating: 3.8/5
🏷 Beast & Butterflies
📍 90 Robertson Quay, Level 1, Singapore 238259
⏰ Sun-Thurs: 6.30am to 10pm, Fri-Sat: 6.30am to 10.30pm

Here’s the 4-course Dinner Set Menu ($88/pax) from @una.singapore that has been specially created for @nespresso.sg Restaurant Week, happening now to 27 Mar 2022. You can chose from 2 dishes for each course; I’ve put a * beside the dishes that have Nespresso infused in them:
•
Appetiser (Tomato Heirloom Con Esparragos / Vieira Con Habas Y Jamon*) 3rd & 4th pic: Both were good in their own ways. The Tomato Heirloom Con Esparragos was really refreshing, while the Vieira (scallop) was nicely seared and the jamon (bacon) added a nice crunch (we couldn’t really taste the Nespresso in the milk foam though)! Verdict: Either one works.
•
Soup (Consome al Jerez / Consome de Tomate) 5th pic: Both consommés were done really well, but in terms of flavour, we preferred the tangy and flavourful Consome de Tomate over the more earthy Consome al Jerez. Verdict: Go for the Consome de Tomate.
•
Main (Bacalao Asado / Pluma Iberica) 1st & 2nd pic: Similar to the appetisers, both mains were equally enjoyable in their own ways! The Black Cod was broiled to perfection, and the butterbean stew beneath was so moreish too! The Pluma Iberica was well-grilled, tender, juicy, and went really well with the potato foam. Verdict: Either one works.
•
Dessert (Churros Con Canela Azucar* / Tarta de Queso "La Vina"): The churros were light and crispy, and went well with both the Nespresso coffee cream (Nespresso taste was prominent) and dark chocolate sauce. We weren’t impressed with the Burnt Cheesecake though, as we found it too dense to our liking. Verdict: Go for Churros Con Canela Azucar.
•
The food was really good overall, matched by a lovely dining ambiance as well! You can make your reservations via the DiningCity app or www.restaurantweek.sg.
•
✨ Overall Rating: 4/5
🏷 UNA at The Alkaff Mansion
📍 10 Telok Blangah Green, Level 2, Singapore 109178
⏰ Tues to Sun: 6pm - 10.30pm, Fri: 11.30am - 2.30pm & 6pm - 10.30pm

Finally tried GoKoKu omg 
 1. CORNET ($1.90) 
The cream is sho good .I really love the custard cream .It's not too sweet and it kinda melts in my mouth .Warning cornet is not crispy at all but I think it matches the texture of the cream.the cornet is chewy and like buttery. And the cream is throughout the cornet so overall it's super satisfying 
2. Earl Grey Scone ($2) 
Y'all I was shook .The earl grey flavour is very prominent .It's super fragrant and I finished it without spreading other stuff on top it was( this comes from someone who cannot take bread /pastry without filling btw so it means the earl grey flavour really quite strong) And the middle part really quite moist so the scone is not dry .
3. Matcha Cream Pan ($2.2) 
Please get it if you go gokoku omg .THE CREAM RATIO IS SO GOOD.The matcha cream has strong matcha flavour and not sweet .The bread itself is also quite good like matcha and grains kind of flavour .Really not bad . 
4. Cheesecake croissant ($2.4) 
Dear gokoku it's either you make the cheesecake filling really more cheesy or you at least have more cheesecake filling .The filling is quite little but what I was disappointed is that the cheesecake flavour isn't that outstanding .

OVERALL REALLY NEEDA GO BACK TO GET MORE HEHEHE

📍 @coucouhotpotsg at @sunteccity 
Taiwanese style hotpot and bubble tea from China. 

There are total of 6 soup bases available. I ordered the signature Taiwan Style Spicy Soup base 台式麻辣锅 and Coconut Chicken Soup base 清凉椰子鸡锅 ($28.9-single/ $39.9 twin) 
⭐️ 5/5 
💌 for the Taiwan Mala soup is not so much like HDL spicy and 麻, is more light and able to drink as a spicy soup. Of course the plus point is the refillable braised tofu when u order this soup base! The braised tofu is really tasty and compliment so well with the rice like mapo tofu !! 
Next is the refreshing coconut chicken soup base that comes with coconut waters and chicken with a hint taste of lemongrass and water chestnut. My fav soup so far ! 😍

1. Appetizer Spread $5.8/pax 
💌Get this only if u need sauces. In my opinion, the soup based are flavorful enough. Honestly, doesn’t really worth the price. There were only 2 appetizers  available where both also some seaweed dishes. 

2. Beef Chunk Roll, Australian Lamb Leg, Mashed Prawn paste, Live Tiger Prawn
💌 the quality of the meat were pretty good and the tiger prawns really fresh. 

3. Da Hong Pao Bubble tea $6.8
⭐️3/5 
💌 the only good bout this is really worth it as it is really one huge glass of milk tea. But taste wise, I think is ok, not the best bubble tea.  Can’t complain much as you can have both best things at once 😅
…
Overall ⭐️5/5
Total spending $120/pax

This journey has taught me the value of learning, practicing, growing, and being patient. Turned it into an ice white mocha in the end.

Pretty warm out today, so decided to take a light jog with Kenji and Princess. Jogging with the weight of a stroller & going uphill had me sweating! We stopped by the playground and took a break to “picnic,” so that I can eat all the calories back 😅🐷I am exhausted.

So much for resetting 😅 My belly is happy and full again thanks to @zanetax3 ‘s delicious homemade pizza. We each customized toppings. I did a truffle oil, white & red sauce mix, basil, mushrooms, prosciutto, goat cheese, mozzarella & Parmesan. It was “chef’s kiss!” Thanks for also grabbing all these goodies for us! The honey lavender coffee and almond croissant were so good! ❤️
Resetting: what I ate today.
Food diary . I spend a lot of time in the kitchen. 😮‍💨

📍Lindt Home of Chocolate, Zurich

Let the Lindt Chocolate Factory take you on a journey through time to chocolate history. 
Starting from the origins of chocolate, to the expansion to Europe and finally landing in Switzerland home of big names like Lindt, Cailler and Nestle. 

We watched the step by step process of sourcing and preparing the cocoa beans from Africa to the machine production line of the finest Lindt chocolates. Culminating in a delicious gourmet of liquid chocolate, an assortment of free-flow bits of chocolate and a buffet of chocolate truffle balls. We were completely drunk on chocolate till we could eat no more. 

A must see when you’re down in Zurich!

💰: 10CHF/pax

📍Gruyère 

Cheese Fondueeeee!🧀🧀

A Swiss melted cheese dish typically served with steamed potatoes and bread (some places offered pickles too), which you then dipped the carbs goodies into pot of melted cheeeeese mmmm yummz especially in such cold weather! 

We tried one in Interlaken and one in Gruyère and they tasted slightly different. The latter was slightly milder in taste and even our anti-cheese friend quite enjoyed it too! 

Definitely a must-try if you’re in Switzerland!👍🏻

Sir: 3.5/5🌟
Mdm: 3.7/5🌟

📍McDonald’s Swiss

We made a personal checklist to tick off the McDonald’s in every country we go to, so here we are!! Decided to bring the crew to enjoy a little posh Iranian fine dining last night after all the yummy Swiss meals we’ve been devouring😉

𝐁𝐢𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐲 𝐁𝐚𝐜𝐨𝐧 🥓 
Personal all time fav of Marcus since his Denmark’s days. The defining feature of the burger is none other than its special ranch sauce! When you bite into the huge juicy beef patty, with onions that complement the ranch sauce… oooof! Excellent combination!! It leaves you wanting more! 

Sir: 4.9/5🌟

𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐏𝐚𝐩𝐫𝐢𝐤𝐚🫑
They named this the Big Bang B Chicken Paprika but in reality, this was nothing more than just your typical McChicken burger with some “paprika” sauce with non-existent heat in it. The only saving grace is probably the steamed bun since Pris doesn’t like sesame bun haha.

Mdm: 2.5/5🌟

𝐌𝐜𝐅𝐥𝐮𝐫𝐫𝐲 𝐂𝐚𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐫 & 𝐊𝐚𝐦𝐛𝐥𝐲🍦
Cailler is a famous Swiss Choc brand and our guess is Kambly is some sort of Swiss biscuit. There was quite a generous bits of choc chunks and biscuit pieces, with some choc sauce in it. Quite yummy but could prob do with some Oreo mixed in as well? 😛

Sir & Mdm: 3/5🌟

Of course, dining out in Switzerland is never cheap. As you can see, even a McDonald meal can cause us almost SGD$40 but it’s the cheapest you can get here so🤷🏻‍♂️🤷🏻‍♀️

Our virgin Paragliding experience with Skywings Paragliding. It was sucha amazing experience to be gliding through the sky of a very picturesque view. 

We got the Sensational Package (at 160CHF) which includes 10-30mins air time, taking off at Beatenburg (at 1370m) and landing at Interlaken. 

We also added another 40CHF to get all the photos and videos taken by our pilots to transfer into our smart phone on the spot! Definitely a 💯 experience!!🤗

What a day…. Due to the Russian airspace ban, our Finnair flight path got affected. And 24hours + 3 flights later, we finally set foot at our destination. But… we realised that’s not the end of our “mis-venture”. Surprise surprise….Our luggages did not followed us through to Switzerland!🤦🏻‍♀️ So yes, we are now living off our only set of clothings that we are wearing so we had to beg, borrow, steal our friends’ extra sets of winter wear🥺 stay tuned to find out what happens to our missing luggages….🥲 till then, pray hard for us to reunite with our luggages sooooon

Durian snowflake with Black glutinous rice, and Almond paste with Black glutinous rice. 
The glutinous rice tasted like it was almost unsweetened and a bit bitter in fact😅

mochi ice cream is not authentic mochi 🗣 mochi can be made with different types of starches but glutinous rice flour (using short-grain rice)  is most commonly used. starches are made up of amylose and amylopectin. short grain rice primarily consists of amylopectin which is responsible for the chewiness and stretch that are key characteristics in mochi. if a medium or long grain rice were to be used to make mochi, the product would be much more brittle and would not have the iconic texture mochi is meant to have.

Last week’s meal kit from TFK featured a Shrimp Risotto 🍤🍚 that was light and delicious! I added some asparagus that my uncle gifted since the two seemed perfect together. The colors of this dish look so fresh and summery, which tbh, has been what the weather has been like despite it only being March 😥 This particular kit also came with a head of broccoli 🥦, but I wanted to save it for a different meal during the week 😅 Broccoli is one of my fave veggies, and it deserves the full spotlight imo 😂

Happy weekend everyone! 💚 Hope you have a fun and restful weekend 😊

Sunday brunch idea 💡Sweet Potato Hash 🍠 with Soft Boiled Eggs 🥚and Ciabatta 🥖 since a hash feels like weekend food for some reason 😆 Although if you’re like me and prefer to sleep in until almost noon on most Sundays, it’s more like a lunch/dinner meal 😂

I flavored my hash with cumin, paprika, and other warm spices since I felt it would match the sweet, earthy flavor of the sweet potatoes. I paired this with soft boiled eggs and the last of my frozen ciabatta for a hearty meal 💚 

Happy Sunday everyone! Hope you had a great weekend 🥰

My friends and I went on a staycation last weekend and this Korean BBQ 🇰🇷🥓and Hotpot 🥘 was the first full meal we had at the house. There’s really something amazing about cooking and eating outdoors, especially when surrounded by great people 💚

Ngl, this kbbq grill was a nightmare to clean, even more so when in a rented house, but the food and experience of eating under the stars really was worth it 😊 Plus, the grill definitely saved us when the induction burner refused to cooperate 😂

A bit of a late post but I hope everyone had a good weekend (or as good of a weekend as you can get given the threat of Russia 🥲)! Praying for the people of Ukraine and that this attack would end soon 😔

Weekday meals for our family mainly include dishes that need to be cooked once but will last for two meals 😆 One dish that’s part of our regular rotation is Ground Chicken 🍗 flavored with Chinese bean paste eaten with lots of rice. 

The dish used to be made with ground pork, but we’ve been trying to make healthier decisions during the past year hence the switch. I do think ground chicken works in this case because it’s a good, relatively bland vehicle for the strong and distinct bean paste flavor. For my bowl here, I added shredded lettuce, corn, and cilantro for some added texture, flavor, and nutrition.

Wie die Blumenwiese in die Käsetheke kam
 
Antoine de Fribourg der Käsekünstler aus dem 17Jh, verfeinert sein Rezept.
 
Bei dem ersten Käse hatte Antoine den Käsebruch sehr hoch erhitzt und fein geschnitten. Am nächsten Tag als er sie aus dem Järb nahm waren sie sehr kompakt und hart.
 
Antoine wollte einen Käse produzieren, der auf der Zunge zergeht wie Butter und er sagte sich vielleicht sollte ich nicht nur die Temperatur tiefer halten, sondern auch den Käsebruch weniger fein scheiden. Antoine legte den Käse vom Vortag ins Salzbad und fing mit dem Käsen an.
 
Nachdem am Vortag die Milch viel zu schnell dick wurde, erhitzte er diesmal die Milch nur leicht bevor er das Lab zugab und dieses Mal brauchte die Milch 30 Minuten zum dick werden.
 
Antoine nahm wieder die Harfe, er schnitt den Bruch etwas weniger fein, dann erhitzte er diesen und bevor er sich fast die Hände verbrannte, nahm er das Kessi vom Feuer.
 
Er rührte dann den Käsebruch noch eine Zeitlang weiter und füllte die Käse in die Järbe.
 
Am Abend schrieb er wieder sorgfältig auf was er gemacht hatte und nummerierte am nächsten Tag die Käse.

Antoine de Fribourg der Käsekünstler aus dem 17Jh, alleine auf seiner Alp

Nachdem Antoine bei seinem Vetter Gustave das Käsen gelernt hat, war es jetzt Zeit die Alp seines Vaters zu übernehmen.

Bevor er auf die Alp zog, bereitete er das Lab vor. Er schnitt die in Salz getrockneten Kälbermägen in kleine Stücke und legte sie für 5 Tage in ein Gemisch aus Salz, Borsäure und Wasser.

Auf der Alp angekommen, begann als erstes die grosse Putzorgie. Jedes Melkgeschirr und jedes Instrument wurde sauber geputzt und ausgekocht, so wie es Ihm sein Vater gezeigt hatte. Dann wurden die Kühe gemolken. Das Abendgemelk kam in das grosse Kessi, morgens wurden die Kühe erneut gemolken und auch diese Milch wanderte ins Kessi.

Antoine musste die Milch erhitzen auf exakt 32°. Er versuchte sich zu erinnern wie sich 32° am Ellbogen anfühlten. Er erhitzte die Milch und spürte die Temperatur mit dem Ellbogen, dann schüttete er das mit Wasser verdünnte Lab ins Kessi. Normalerweise sollte es ca. 30 Minuten dauern, bis die Milch gerinnt. Die Ideale Zeit Pause zu machen. Da es die erste Produktion war blieb Antoine beim Kessi und schon nach kurzer Zeit war die Milch dick.

Antoine erschrak holte schnell die Käseharfe und begann den Käsebruch zu schneiden. Als Antoine sich fast die Hände verbrannte holte er das Tuch und hob die Käsemasse aus dem Kessi.

Er füllte den Käse in 2 Järbe ein und beschwerte die Masse.

Am Abend schrieb Antoine exakt auf, wie er heute die Käse produziert hatte. Er überlegte sich, wieso die Milch wohl so schnell dick wurde und er beschloss am nächsten Tag die Milch weniger zu erwärmen.

Möchten Sie einen Käse von Antoine probieren? Er ist bei Edeka Scheck-in erhältlich @scheckincenter

📍Wild Child Pizzette

Have reviewed their pizzas before (which were great - they even have a fried margherita) but this dessert deserves a post on its own. $13 for a pecan tart may sound a bit ridics but damn I love the gel-like consistency of the caramelised layer, with plenty of crunchy pecans in each bite. Crust was super buttery with a sturdy texture (nothing too crumbly) though it was a little greasy. Best paired with a solid whisky sorbet… honestly this takes the cake (or should I say, tart). 
•
Value: 3/5
Taste: 4/5
Ambience: 4/5

📍Habibi-san

Enjoy a lively fusion of flavours at @habibisansg — a middle eastern izakaya at Haji Lane with a mix of Greek and Middle Eastern influences in their food. Go for their tasting menu ($65/pax) and you get a nice selection of meats and other exotic dishes, with a strong smoky flavour infused in almost every item. Some favourites - the pork jowl, chicken hearts (!!), roasted brussel sprouts, Fremantle octopus and chickpea hummus 🤤 Desserts were pretty good too – especially the truffle brie. They also serve bespoke cocktails here by @barstoriessg … definitely worth a visit if you want the best of both worlds 🍽🍸🤗
•
Value: 4/5
Taste: 5/5
Ambience: 4/5

📍Pickle Bakery

Featuring two cinnamon pastries from @picklebakery — a small takeaway-only bakery at Everton Park famous for their sourdough breads and other viennoiseries. Reach in the early morning and you will be spoilt for choice 😛(they usually sell out by noon).

The cinnamon roll ($6) is definitely not your typical fluffy version; this comes with an ultra crisp caramelised bottom layer that gives it a solid crunch. Wasn’t too sweet yet the earthy fragrance of the cinnamon was pretty strong. 

Another crowd favourite is the cinnamon chip scone ($5) – incredibly moist and fluffy with a slightly crumbly texture and plenty of cinnamon chips hidden beneath the crust. Good option if you prefer your scones to be cakey / slightly dense as compared to the usual floury ones. A tad pricey but portion size is quite generous (probably 2x the ones outside), and plus points for the prominent flavours in both pastries!
•
Value: 4/5
Taste: 5/5

📍Drunken Farmer

@drunkenfarmer_sg takes over the same spot operated by @commonmanstan at night where it’s transformed into a wine bar, famous for its sourdough pizzas, fermented snacks and their fruity wines. Tried the classic Margherita ($18) and I was quite impressed by the chewy texture - their pizza dough uses a sourdough starter giving it a tangy touch. Looks ordinary with its homemade temple stracciatella cheese and garnished with basil leaves on top, but sometimes simple is best.👍🏻 The dough could be airier with more crisp, but that’s probably the nature of a sourdough pizza.🍕😝 

The sourdough karaage ($20) is a spin-off from the usual classic chicken karaage with sourdough added to the batter giving it a refreshing tang (with the slight beer taste). Super crispy with tender thigh meat beneath the batter, and I love their housemade kimchi mayo – a creamy concoction with a slight tinge of fermented essence. Must try!
•
Value: 3/5
Taste: 4/5
Ambience: 4/5

📍Raw Kitchen Bar

Get a slice of Bali at @rawkitchenbar — a mod-asian restaurant along the Kallang river with alfresco dining and fusion Balinese cuisine. Good option to consider if you want an escape from the hustle and bustle!

The Black Mamba 🦑 ($27) seems to be a crowd favourite with a mashup of different flavours and textures; tiger prawns with a raw yolk atop the squid ink rice, complemented with a side of their fermented chilli sambal and lime. Not too bad but I wouldn’t say it was impressive - somehow lacked the fragrance that I was expecting from the rice itself but it was pretty mild. 

Go for the pad krapao croquettes for starters ($8) – portion is incredibly small but the burst of umami flavours is so worth it. Love the mish-mash of stir-fried chicken paired with Thai basil vinaigrette.

Can’t go without the classic warung pork ribs ($25) for a true Balinese cuisine – thankfully this was as good as their seafood offerings. Love the barbecued glaze with the ribs full of flavour. Meat was surprisingly tender too.

Take note that you shouldn’t come here on a rainy day cos the indoor seating is really limited 😆 the alfresco vibes are really nice at night tho! ✨ 
•
Value: 3/5
Taste: 4/5
Ambience: 4/5

Last weekend my friend invited us for scrumptious dinner at @miso.salmon .
Their vibrant food presentation really inspired me to sketch!

Miso Salmon is an authentic Inaniwa udon specialty restaurant, importing their noodles directly from Japan. 
Inaniwa udon is slightly different from the ones we usually have - the noodles are much thinner than regular udons, almost like kuay teow but denser and more chewy. Here's what we had:

1. Tiger Prawn with Mentaiko Bowl ($19)
This delectable dish is not only colourful, but delicious as well. The soft udon is accompanied by crunchy mentaiko and ebiko bits, exciting my sensory experience with every bite 😋

2. Customised spicy miso bowl 
We tried customising a bowl, filled with all our favourite ingredients, hahaa. They also have shirataki konjac noodles as an option!

3. Yakitori chicken with truffled mushroom don ($15)
The Japanese rice is yummy, while the chicken goes well with truffle and mushrooms. Be sure to mix the egg yolk throughly! 

Sides:
1. Chicken kaarage - your standard can't go wrong sidedish
2. Aburi mentai tamagoyaki - goooood stuffs!
3. Truffle edamame - I can't stop munching on this, will go so well with a beer!

Oh yes, did I mention that their prawns are PEELED!? I was getting ready to be messy but nope! It was pure bliss to have prawn without the hassle. 

Miso Salmon is a Japanese casual dining restaurant located at Tanjong Pagar (Peck Seah Street) that offers exclusive flavours (special udon and miso!) at a affordable price. Here's another option for you if you're in the area!
