The famous @tanstutu. Lauded as the OG of all the tutu kueh stalls in sg. So thankful I got to try these gems without have to brave the (minimally 1h) queue. 

Albeit having it 2h after purchase, the steam rice cakes were soft, fluffy and comes with a slight chew. 

🥥My fav filling was coconut - freshly grated and fried with gula melaka. Every bite was loaded with strong aroma of caramelised coconut and the shavings made it so mouthful 

🥜Crushed peanuts was yum too. It had a hint of saltiness, making it well balanced from the sweetness of all the other flavours. 

🍫As much as I embrace a modern twist on these traditional gems, didn’t fancy the chocolate flavour as much as the former two.

#1 prawn noodles on my list has to be from River South (Hoe Nam) Prawn Noodles. Never a fan but this converted me when I first had it more than a decade ago. Used to be our family brekkie every Sunday without fail. 

🥢Big Prawns with Small Intestine ($9)
If you don’t already know, I’m a big fan of small intestines and this is my ONLY combo for prawn noodles. The intestines seemed to have shrunk over the years and became more soggy (without the usual chew). Hence, (literally) loosing the charm of this ingredient, which is the powdery substance within. 

Likewise, the soup wasn’t as gao as before but it was still flavourful. You could taste the sweetness from every sip and imagine how much prawn heads and shells goes into making the broth. 

Do also remember to complete your meal with  their signature fish cake ($1.50). Bouncy, chewy and no fishy aftertaste.

A fancy dinner (RARE for me) where STEAKS ARE HIGH, BUT WELL WORTH IT.🐄 @fatbellysg 

🍴Blue Label Full Blood Wagyu ($178+)
Haven't had one in sg that blew me away since Don Julio in Buenos Aires. This was almost comparable, beef was done medium rare and it was so juicy and tender, loaded with just the right amount of fats. The gfs keep going 'mmm so good' everytime they take a bite haha

We opted for the Bordelaise and Scampi Butter. The former paired really well with the beef while the latter had a strong umami aftertaste, which goes better with toast imo. 

🍴Burrata ($26+)
A creamy bomb of oozy cheesy goodness accompanied by plums, tomatoes & herb oil. 

🍴Cream Curly Kale ($16+)
Nice rendition of the otherwise hard and sometimes bitter kale. Egg is always a good idea. 

🍴Crusted Mac & Cheese ($18+)
For all the pasta + cheese + truffle lovers!

🍴Grilled Mushrooms ($14+)
Your usual pan fried mushrooms but nothing special to shoutout. 

🥄Fat Belly's Tiramisu ($16+)
Never a fan of tiramisu BUT I LIKED THIS. Fingers were well soaked and ratio of that and mascapone layer was well balanced.

🥄Valrhona Chocolate Bruciato ($16+)
Presentation was lovely, pear sorbet was very refreshing and goes pretty well with the chocolate.

You make my heart melt and I’ll always love you un-CONE-ditionally 🌹@cornettosg @cornetto

💁🏻‍♀️ stealing cuddles from the fur kid as we wait for the lift. It's like he knows he can't get out of hugs these days. 😅

We're slowly getting back into the pace of life and catching up with backlogs. It's amazing how much difference 2 weeks can make.

🤦🏻‍♀️ Meet this con artist. He wormed his way into my heart (and home), acts cute, eats like a king, and gets away with everything.

On days he doesn't have to go to school, he refuses to leave the house for a toilet break till after lunch. Sometimes till after dinner! And I thought I wasn't a morning person! 🙄

His allergy medicine costs 50 times that of my own, he can't eat 95% of kibble brands out there and he rejects the other 5%. He prefers home cooked food… that is freshly cooked! Not pre-cooked then put in the fridge then wamed up at meal times. 🙄 Even for durian he prefers fresh over chilled. 🙄🙄🙄

He snows furrrrr all over my home, has 3 beds and leaves his toys all over the floor! 🙄 Plus he lives with me rent-free.

He gets grouchy when you scratch him the wrong way, wants rubs on demand and gets annoyed if I play my music too loud. 🙄🤷🏻‍♀️

He huffs in frustration at me, throws tantrums in his crate when he doesn't get what he wants, argues back like a husky when being scolded and keeps all guests in check by making sure they don't move around the home. 😅🙄

But sigh. Love is fckin' blind. 🤷🏻‍♀️

The music, the lyrics, the energy.

Thank you for making us sore and hoarse with happiness @thescriptofficial! Definitely one for the books (and gram)!

The last weeks of 2021 were all about family and friends, and catching up on moments that we’ve missed because we’ve been apart for far too long.

There was a fair share of laughs and a few reserved moments of tears… it was nonetheless a wonderful week which reminded me how lucky I am to have a strong support system back home.

Throughout my flight back to Riyadh, I’m reminded of a quote from a Winnie the Pooh book (that I can relate to right now) about saying goodbye. In that book, Pooh said “How lucky I am to have something that makes saying goodbye so hard”.

I love the fact that Pooh took something as painful and hard as saying goodbye and saw it from a different perspective. The quote shifted my paradigm, and I realised that the pain of saying goodbye is because I’ve had the opportunity to be in a place and with people that made the goodbyes so hard. For that, I should be (and am) grateful. Such a profound thought from a small stuffed teddy bear.

So as my plane took off into the setting sun, I know that Singapore is home, truly. It will always be a place and community that is hard to say goodbye to; and for that I am lucky.

Until next time 🇸🇬
Feels reel good to be home 🇸🇬 #firstreel

After lunch, we made our way down to Atlas coffeehouse to grab some coffee. We ordered their butterscotch banana pancake with coffee and a cold brew. The pancake came with caramelised banana slices, butterscotch, ice cream, and crunchy cornflakes. The pancake was crispy on the outside but soft and fluffy in the inside! The butterscotch sauce though. It is a bit too sweet for our liking and we glad we did not pour them all.  Overall it is still a good dessert... I do return to Atlas from time to time because I enjoy their laid back atmosphere. It’s a place where you can wind down and have a good time with your friends or loved ones (I think this place is dog friendly too!)

Once again, 2021 taught me to accept how things can change abruptly and we don’t have control over those changes. So… since I have to give my mum’s Tangyuan a miss, I decided to give myself a happy meal. When come to comfort food, mala is in the top of my list! But this time, I ordered a plant based burger from @threebunssg that I have been wanting to try. The burger came with Impossible beef meat patty, truffled aioli, brie, ketchup, tomato, lettuce, pickles and brioche bun.  The Brioche bun was soft and light. The plant based patty mimicked the look and feel of a ground beef soooo well. The patty was juicy and smoky! Overall, It was a great burger…

Happy winter solstice! 

Thank you @tamjiak_veggiez for recommendation!

Happy Chinese New Year to everybody!

Feeling lucky that we scored an outdoor table at @nextdoorspanishcafe.

We tried a few items on their menu including:
1) Mixed Cold Cuts ($32)
2) Huevos Rotos con Jamón Ibérico y Trufa ($16) - Truffles crushed potatoes with Jamón Ibérico and runny egg
3) Classic Seafood Paella ($32)
4) Secreto Ibérico con Mojo Picón ($36) 
5) Tortilla de Patatas ($9) - Traditional Spanish Omelette

Their food is great for sharing and I love how it felt like we were not in Singapore for a bit. Their food does not come cheap, but I would definitely head back again when craving for some Spanish food!

Stay home Valentine’s Day dinner date idea with steak from @bishoku.sg.

This is my first time cooking a steak dinner and I am glad that it was so easy to put together! The beef was so tender and juicy and we paired it with baked portobello mushrooms and hasselback potatoes. They are currently running a promo at $12 for their 100% grass-fed Australian steak (200-220g) which I think is very value for money!

What do you normally like to eat your steak with? 

P.s. Thank you @bishoku.sg for sending this over.

All ready for Chinese New Year thanks to @fragrance_bak_kwa!

I tried my hand at making Chinese New Year snacks for the first time with a recipe I found on @apeakfood and I am glad it worked out well!

Just in case you have not stocked up yet, do check out the wide range of snacks available on @fragrance_bak_kwa online shop. Their pork floss is selling for $4.20 for 100g and they do have other flavours as well. This snack was so addictive, we ended up finishing everything we made 😂.

Wishing everyone a Happy Lunar New Year 🧧

P.s. Items were gifted but all opinions are my own.

Let’s have hotpot and grill together at @nuerhong_restaurant together!

Their buffet selection includes more than 80 varieties of seafood, meat, vegetable and side dishes from just $29.90 per person onwards which is very value for money. The options available are really perfect for those that want a bit of everything but my favourite items would their cuttlefish, pork belly and ginseng chicken soup! Personally I would skip on the Mala soup and perhaps choose another soup base like Laksa instead.

If you are keen to try, here are some of the ongoing promotions that they have:
1. All Day Seafood Hotpot & BBQ Promotional prices from $29.90 for adults, $25.90 for students/senior citizens, $19.90 for children
2. $10 instant e-voucher in membership account after liking and following on FB & IG
3. Promotional Dine-in Vouchers on their website

Thank you @nuerhong_restaurant for this tasting invitation and for the enjoyable meal thanks to the friendly staff!

📍 Hong Qin Fish and Duck Porridge 

One of the more well-known establishment in Geylang, Hong Qin Fish and Duck Porridge serves up amazing old school braised dishes at a highly affordable price( ～$20 for 2 pax). 

We ordered a feast, duck porridge, fish soup, and an assortment of braised dishes : taupok, egg, duck and salted vegetable and we are happy to say that all of the dishes tasted great. 

The duck porridge was simple but delicious. Gravy generously dripped over white porridge, topped with some duck meat that went excellently with the chili provided. 

The fish soup was light and refreshing, and was a good contrast to the strong flavors of the braised dishes. The fish slices was also thick and fresh, and we finished it up in an instant. 

The braised dishes though were the star of the show. The taupok accompanied with the braised marinade was oozing with flavor, and the salted vegetables was salty and soft, just the way it should be. It might be too flavorful if eaten alone, but with porridge or rice, the dishes were absolutely perfect. The braised duck was surprisingly slightly tough, but all in all, we still had a great experience at the store, and would recommend all old-school braised dish lovers to try this out. 

P.s. Please take note, this is Hong Qin Fish and Duck Porridge not Chong Qing Grilled Fish, don’t mix up yeah 🌚

Our rating : 4.5/5

📍Hai Xian Zhu Zhou

You might be thinking “why should I pay for Ke Kou Mian or a pack of Maggie when I can whip it up myself in the comfort of my own home?” Well, that’s because you probably can’t do it as well as Hai Xian Zhu Zhou can. 

We ordered the Tom Yum Koka Noodles ($4.50) that came with sliced pork, minced meat balls, vegetables, pork liver and to top it off, we added a poached egg ($0.50) to complete the meal. 

The first thing we tried was the broth and it was packed with flavor and nothing like what you get from those instant packets. The sliced pork was extremely soft and tender, and honestly tasted like the Iberico pork you could enjoy at Haidilao. The noodles were also springy and had a nice bite to it, but the meatball was what truly stole the show. Extremely well marinated and tender, the meatballs were delicious and really made the dish an A-star dish.

We think it’d be excellent for supper but sadly the store closes at 3pm so be sure to head down early! (No worries, it’s great for lunch as well) 

P.s Definitely kou ke (thirsty) for this comfort bowl of ke kou mian 🌚

Our rating: 4.85/5
location: Hai Xian Zhu Zhou 海鲜煮粥

description:
📍Binomio

Binomio’s bin on our mind so were we ever happy when we finally had the time to give the establishment a try. 

Located at Craigs Road, the small restaurant seeks to pair casual tapas with fine dining. 

We ordered the set lunch and had the beef tartare with caviar and toast for our appetizer and the seafood paella for our main course.

The beef tartare was beautifully served in a bone marrow, and the caviar was arranged neatly beside it. The tartare had a unique zest and acidity to it, and the flavors of the meat paired with the richness of the caviar went excellently with the toasted bread. 

The paella was delicious as well; the rice soaked up the flavors of the seafood and was extremely tasty. The restaurant was also very generous with their seafood and the dish boasted of many fresh prawns and clams, making the main course highly delightful. 

We finished up with desserts but alas we were so excited to eat it we didn’t take any pictures. But it was pretty good, take our word for it. 

All in all, Binomio offered quality Spanish food at a decent price point and we would definitely be back sometime soon. 

P.s no worries, the food is delicious and definitely doesn’t belong in the bin🌚

Our rating : 4.5/5

📍China Whampoa Ban Mian

If you agree that Ban Mian is a staple, well, you’ll be more than happy to try this gem nestled away at Geylang Lor 14. 

Other than the well known L32 ban mian, China Whampoa Ban Mian (CWBM) also serves delicious noodles and is a great alternative for those who are impatient and unwilling to queue for their food.

We ordered the dry ban mian with meatballs and we slurped up the bowl in an instant. The handcrafted egg noodles was of a great texture, and we couldn’t stop slurping on it. The meatballs for us though were the star of the show. Extremely flavorful and tender, the meatballs paired with the speciality chili that the restaurant provided was so addictive that we almost ordered another bowl just for the meatballs. 

The best part of it though, you can get a hearty bowl of this noodles for $4.50, a definite steal. 

All in all, this is a good place to try for Banmian lovers. We’re not saying it’s the best, but hey it’s a great option for sure. 

P.s. Wham Poa (one bowl) of this noodle might not be enough 🌚

Our rating : 4.3/5

📍Salted Caramel

Those staying in the hood of Thomson would be familiar with this artisan ice cream cafe, Salted Caramel. 

Salted Caramel offers a wide array of interesting handcrafted ice cream for you to choose from, ranging from blue milk, lemon cheesecake, hazelnut praline, horlicks Tim tam, to espresso and the list goes on and on. We ordered the waffles with a double scoop of chocolate sorbet and earl grey ice cream ($12.60) and we were glad we chose those flavors. The chocolate sorbet was extremely rich and yet not too sweet at the same time. It carried the right amount of cocoa-y bitterness and went really well with the waffles. The earl grey ice cream was also light and refreshing and the light tea fragrance really helps in whetting our appetites.

The waffles were incredibly crispy on the outside and moist and fluffy on the inside. The light and airy waffles, accompanied with the high quality ice cream truly made the visit to this establishment worthwhile and if we are ever in the vicinity, we will be sure to save some space for dessert and pop by for a sugary treat.

P.s. Fret not, unlike what their name suggests, they do serve other amazing flavors besides salted caramel 🌚

Our rating: 4.4/5

Save this place for your next bagel date!

Visited @monumentlifestyle a few weeks back and their extensive selection of New York-style bagels surely satisfied my bagel cravings.😮‍💨

The bagels (without fillings) came in five flavours - 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗻, 𝘀𝗲𝘀𝗮𝗺𝗲, 𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗱𝗱𝗮𝗿, 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗼𝗻. Along with the bagels came 3 different handmade schmears - 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘄𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗿𝘆, 𝗴𝗮𝗿𝗹𝗶𝗰 𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗯 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗷𝗮𝗹𝗮𝗽𝗲𝗻̃𝗼 𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗱𝗱𝗮𝗿!🥯

I usually prefer savoury flavour profiles, but I fell in love with their crowd-favourite strawberry schmear. It had a sweet and pleasant tanginess that reminded me of haagen-dazs strawberry icecream.🍓We spent quite some time taking pictures so the bagels naturally became a little tough to chew (please don’t be like us…)

We also tried out a tasting platter for their signature sandwich bagels - 𝗹𝗼𝘅, 𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘆 𝗵𝗮𝗺, 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗶 𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗻𝗲𝘄 𝘆𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗲𝗿. My favourite out of the lot is the 𝗹𝗼𝘅, which came with generous chunks of smoked salmon and tangy cream cheese that was light on the palate. The fillings were also packed really neatly so there’s no need to worry about the mess that usually comes with stuffed bagels.🥺

From now till end Feb, quote “thefluffypao” to enjoy 10% off food items till the end of Feb! You’ll have to follow both my account and @monumentlifestyle to enjoy this offer.‼️

Thank you @monumentlifestyle for the warm hospitality and @hungryshuen for extending the invite!!

Here’s an underrated burpple gem tucked away in lavender! 😮‍💨 

Visited @oberstrassesg last Friday and ordered their 𝗼𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 that came with a cushion of creamy and buttery scrambled eggs. I really enjoyed the silky texture of the eggs, but it wasn’t as fantastic flavour-wise. It felt a lil bland after a while and could definitely be elevated with some seasoning. 🍳

On the other hand, the chorizo was juicy and the mild spice made it even more flavourful (tasted like otah tbh). Bacons were also crispy with a good fat to meat ratio. Rosti hash was slightly disappointing though as it disintegrated easily and was also pretty thin. The veges had a nice crisp and were paired nicely with sesame sauce (yes, I wiped the whole plate clean despite being a non-vege lover😳). 

Overall, this was a pretty hearty lunch and portions were just nice!! The vibes were also laid-back with limited seatings available in the cafe. Total damage was slightly under $15/pax after burpple’s 30% discount. Definitely not the best deal out there but it’s pretty decent for the quality! This cafe is also less than a minute walk away from thai baàng so you can get your bread fix too while cafe hopping. 😆👌

‼️AFFORDABLE cinnamon rolls and fluffy brioche donuts from a not-so-hidden gem in the east! It’s my second time trying bakes from @puffandpeaks and I found my second experience to be a lot better than my first!! 

Ok firstly, the brioche donuts were HUGE and had an ideal 7:3 filling to dough ratio. I’m honestly pretty impressed that they held their shape really well and weren’t oily even after a day in the fridge. That made my life WAY easier when it came to taking pictures.😮‍💨 

I got the donuts in the following 4 flavours - 𝗱𝗮𝗿𝗸 𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗲, 𝗹𝗲𝗺𝗼𝗻 𝗰𝘂𝗿𝗱, 𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗮, & 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮, but I only tried the latter two. Fillings wise, the 𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗮 stood out more to me! It tasted like an upgraded version of goreng pisang but without the greasiness. I was expecting a bittersweet umami filling from the 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮 donut but it was evidently absent. 😰

I know they’re most known for their donuts but their 𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗼𝗻 𝗿𝗼𝗹𝗹𝘀 take centre stage for me. They’re really fluffy and moist on the inside. And it was packed FULL of cinnamon flavours without being cloying. A pity that no one really raves about this. 🥺

Overall, I found them to be really affordable for their quality (~$3.50 each). Puff and peaks is located REALLY far from me but I’m thankful that group buys exist! I wanna try their black ssm friand too but it’s always not available in group buys.. 🥲

I have been eyeing on Gyunami ever since their old days at Amoy but they have relocated to Orchard!! I ordered their signature 𝘄𝗮𝗴𝘆𝘂 𝗯𝗲𝗲𝗳 𝗱𝗼𝗻𝗯𝘂𝗿𝗶 and it came with a glorious volcanic sous vide egg! 🍳

First off, the presentation was already a solid 10/10 for me. Taste wise, I liked that the beef slices were well seasoned and roasted medium rare. The egg yolk was flowy and it gave a creamy dimension to the overall dish. The yogurt sauce provided a slight tanginess but somehow the rice still tasted a lil bland. Maybe a truffle-infused rice might do the job. 🤪 

Overall, this donburi was good and reasonably priced, though nothing too mind blowing in terms of taste. The service was efficient but I didn’t particularly enjoy the ambience. There were pretty limited seats and it honestly felt even more cramped with all the soft toys surrounding us. 🥲

They are on burpple so the bill amounted to $12.50 for a donburi along with miso soup! It’s definitely a fuss-free meal option in town but don’t expect too much!!

You know CNY is coming when cafes start to introduce items with ORH NEE! 🤤 Tried @simple.cafesg’s yam swiss roll and yam nian gao donut and both CNY specials were pretty impressive!! 

𝗬𝗮𝗺 𝗦𝘄𝗶𝘀𝘀 𝗥𝗼𝗹𝗹
Tried A LOT of orh nee swiss rolls and this is surely one of the more memorable ones that I’ve had! There were rectangle chunks of orh nee embedded in the fresh cream and the cake itself was light and fluffy. The cream was also generous and it didn’t taste too overwhelming! 👌👌

𝗬𝗮𝗺 𝗡𝗶𝗮𝗻 𝗚𝗮𝗼 𝗗𝗼𝗻𝘂𝘁
I think this is the first time that I have seen nian gao in donuts and this combination surprisingly went pretty well!! The sticky, chewy texture of nian gao definitely gave more dimensions to the smooth and fragrant orh nee fillings, though it still got a lil jelak towards the end. Additionally, I liked that the donut wasn’t oily, but I wished that it was fluffier!! 

Also, I really liked the minimalistic interiors in this Taiwanese cafe with chill Mandopop music playing in the background. They do carry a humble selection of other Taiwanese-style bakes, and I’ll be back to try their signature sweet potato swiss roll! 🍠👊

Had such a wonderful and affordable breakfast @chaoyuexuandimsum:
1.  厨皇天鹅酥配南瓜球 - SGD5.80. I think this is like an art piece for dim sum. A truly beautiful signature dish.
2.鲜肉生煎包 - SGD4.80. The pau is fluffy and nicely crispy outer pan-fried layer. And, is not too oily.
3. 酥炸雪梨球 -SGD4.80. Another beautiful art piece. I like the chewy texture of the skin and the fillings are tasty.
4. 蜜汁叉烧肠粉 -SGD4.80. The skin is soft and the sauce is good. The best part is quite a lot of flavourful cha siew in the roll.
5.红油抽手拉面 - SGD5.80. The noodles is very QQ and the sauce is good. And, comes with generous portion of dumplings.

Would recommend to try this place as the dishes are high quality yet quite reasonably priced and well plated with attention to detail. The service is friendlyand excellent. Quite spacious and comfortable seating, though is a small shop. Just so happen, I went at the right time (some time after opening but before lunch), so did not queue for long.
location: Chao Yue Xuan Dim Sum 潮粤轩点心

description:
Stay connected and keep each other updated!

Had lunch with my "work spouse" (currently my hubby) in town and saw some tables of colleagues/friends having lunch together and I was reminded of those lunch hours I used to have with my colleagues where we would talk about all kinds of things (from bosses to co-workers to current news). Those were such fun lunch hours.

Hope you manage to keep finding nice lunch places and continue to stay connected with your colleagues or friends!

The place we had lunch @theexchangesingapore , nice layout and spacious restaurant serving good quality food and affordable lunch sets. We had:
1. Soup of the day (carrot soup), Pan Seared Chicken Breast and 2 Scoops of NZ ice-cream. The soup is solid and hearty where you taste the smoky flavors of nicely roasted carrots. The Seared Chicken Breast is tasty yet healthy lunch that allows for indulgence in yummy chocolate ice-cream which is not too sweet and includes chopped chocolate that give extra dimension.
2. Grilled Tiger Prawns Summer Salad, Herb Crusted Snapper and Pana cotta. The grilled prawns is so flavourful and pairs well with the refreshing salad. The snapper is fresh and generously seasoned. And, finally finished off with very solid and well- done pana cotta.

I like the attention to detail in putting the dishes together and the quality of the ingredients used is topnotch. 

Check out the lunch set menu in my post.

Thank you for the invited tasting, it had been a nice lunch.

Monga Fried Chicken has launched their very own Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice set menu! Fans of Braised Pork Rice (Lu Rou Fan | 滷肉饭) will agree that this is possibly one of the most beloved and recognisable Taiwanese food.

The Braised Pork Rice menu also allows customers to choose between a few set options below. All set choices come with an egg-drop soup and a soft drink (one can top up $1.90 to change soft drink to new Monga’s Fruit Tea additions!)

✅Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice Set with 3 pieces Chicken Nuggets
✅Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice Set with 2 pieces Crispy Chicken
✅Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice Set with 3 pieces Chicken Wings
✅Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice Set with 1 Juicy Thigh Cutlet
✅Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice Set with Sweet Potato Fries
✅Taiwanese Braised Pork Rice Set with Mashed Potato

Available in all Monga Singapore outlets at Jem, ION Orchard, and SingPost Centre.

I tried the Salt-baked Sri Lankan Crab as well as Lobster in Black Truffle Sauce. Both were fabulous. You can really taste the sweetness of the Sri Lankan Crab as it is not masked with any sauce. And as for the lobster, the earthy and savoury truffle sauce was so moreish. I couldn't get enough of it. The Mee Goreng was also a surprising hit. First time trying out The Original Boat Noodles at @ChangiCityPoint_sg, despite passing by this place countless times. The concept is interesting, basically you can choose from many noodle permutations as each bowl costs only $1.50. The idea is so that you can try many flavours instead of a single bowl. Good concept but all I can think of is, SO MANY DISHES TO WASH!!

Anyway, my favourite flavour was the Tom Yum one using instant noodles. What's not to love right? My friend recommended that we just get 2 of those from the start, because she has been here several times. She also recommended the $4.90 crispy chicken skin, which was super crispy and super sinful! 

Due to a special guest appearance (scroll right), I wasn't able to fully concentrate on the food. I'll have to return again to slowly savour the food and eat with 2 hands! A luxury these days sometimes!

Now here’s a question, how many bowls of noodles can you down?

#sghalal #halalfoodsg

Visited the lovely Capitol Arcade area again. The area really exudes a posh and serene vibe, yet you will find that most of the restaurants are pretty wallet friendly. For example, most of them offer set lunches at around $19 - $22 for a 2 course meal. That's not what you would expect here at first glance

Visited @LaScalaRestaurant again for their pastas. We ordered the Spaghetti Costiera and Tortellacci Ricotta E Spinaci Ravioli, both $29. The ravioli was really nice, even though it's vegetarian. Nice bite, nice sauce, just perhaps a tad salty especially the top pieces. The seafood pasta was nice too, especially the succulent prawns, but I suppose not particularly memorable.

But like I said, I really like the peaceful vibe at Capitol Arcade, and I'll probably be back again to try the set lunches of all the restaurants one by one.

Happy birthday to myself! My parents took me and @Edward365 for a birthday lunch at @MisatoSingapore. The last time I was here was back in 2018! Good to know this place is still around despite many upheavals in the F&B industry, and especially at Centrepoint. Food is still good and value for money, although there was some issues with the seating arrangement. The server insisted we sit next to the noisy kitchen, instead of an empty table at the far end! Why on earth would I do that when I know the next customer is going to be directed to that nice quiet table?

Anyway, trying this Ebi Donburi $19.90 for the first time. The tiger prawns are huge, and the eggy top is really delicious too. Such a big portion, I couldn't finish half the rice! Edward surprisingly polished off 90% of his black pig katsu $19.90. My father got the wasabi prawns which was enjoyable, but he said my prawns looked bigger. My mother got some seafood hot pot thing (not pictured). It's good in that it's mild and pleasantly sweet from the veggies rather than from heavy use of seasoning. And of course, the ultra wobbly jelly that is a must order even if it is $9.90!! 

They don't take reservations so customers in the know will arrive by 11.45 am to chope a place when they open at 12noon!

With potted plants and blocks of muted colors against a white backdrop, Guerilla Coffee gives off a zen, Japanese-garden aesthetic.
 The cafe at Suntec City is spacious with a mix of coffee tables and steps for their customers to sit on (like the ones at Funan).

While it was tempting to soak in all that tranquility in the cafe, we opted for a cup of Hot Latte and Mint Mocha to go.

The latte was full-bodied, with a bitter aftertaste. A hint of chocolate was present, but it wasn’t something that warrants a second visit any time soon. It was just your regular cup of coffee.

The face of butchers have always been burly men in bloodied aprons, with a cleaver tightly-gripped in their hands. While brute strength is a desirable trait to hack the carcasses easily, Chef Heba Kim prides on the delicate touch of a woman that makes it easier for nimble cuts around the bones.

When we asked her why she chose to join a male-dominated industry, Kim said that she had taken on an interest in meat parts.

After graduating from a livestock hygiene training institute in South Korea, Kim opened The Butcher's Dining, Singapore's newest Korean butchery and dining concept along Havelock Road, with the aspiration to educate the masses on the different parts of meat.

东边阳西边雨。唯美画面。
在忙碌的时间表里， 别忘了给自己一杯咖啡/茶的时间。珍惜生活中, 身边的美好。

细雨：让人好想去看场浪漫的初雪。

闪亮的钻石雨： 在灿烂的午后阳光下，犹如钻石般璀璨的雨珠。颗颗闪闪发亮的，让人不禁停下欣赏。
。
钻石之所以那么有吸引力，不只是因为它的价格。除了那需要精准又漫长的切割打磨抛光过程，决定了它的标价。 它独特的亮点才是最吸引人的 - 只有它自己才能打磨自己。因为钻石是最尖硬的物质。
。
好比我们每一位，其实都是富有无限潜能的钻石原石。
只有我们自己才能决定自己的身价和价值。在面对生活挑战时，是否要爬起来，继续勇敢前行。在历经磨炼，成为自己眼中自信满满，闪闪发光发亮的钻石。
。
懂得辨别和了解自己的价值，就会明白珍爱自己的可贵和责任。不断的学习、蜕变和成长。 不为别人，只为自己能不失优雅的尽情绽放生命活力，活出自己想要的人生。我们每一刻都是完整的，无缺。
别把第二个人的想法强加在自己身上 （包括父母在内），然后在不如意时，把责任推给别人。反之亦然。
。
这是我的钻石话语。它是给自己一份真诚的励志、提醒和欣赏。
愿你们都能成为自己心目中那颗闪闪发亮的钻石 - 真实不虚的模样，坚韧不拔的灵魂。共勉之。
。

Batard 
Japanese fruit tomato tart with fennel pollen and burrata- 
The pastry is so fluffy and flaky that it crumbles and disintegrates in your mouth. It tastes really buttery without being fatty, all thanks to the tinge of sweetness and tangy flavours from the tomato. The burrata’s stringy creamy texture adds flavours to the dish and everything tastes balanced :)

Broccoli agnolotti with Black Périgord Truffle. Never knew truffle, cream sauce and broccoli can taste so amazing tgt. I love the doughy chewy texture of the agnolotti. Enjoyed this dish tremendously. 

Beef tartare cannelloni —
Crispy on the outside yet the tartare filling is underwhelming. Lovely appetiser nonetheless.

Madeleines are alright, with crispy surface and a lemoney tinge. 

One thing I dislike: wayyyy too much carbs for lunch (😖hyperglycaemic drowsy state)

#tastebud_syp #batard #batardhk #預約困難 #sypeats #connaughtroad #finewineexperience

Batard
Yas Mama I did it I got a table at BATARD lol. Just gonna focus on their signature roast chicken in this post. The flesh is so tender, juicy and silky that jus was oozing out on slicing 😍. The seasoning is so on-point - it highlights the original flavours of poultry while masking the slightly yeasty unpleasant taste. It’s just the right amount of savoury. The skin is light and crispy and they’ve mastered the Maillard effect 👌🏻. The pilaf rice that comes with is scrumptious too. It’s moist and so flavourful without being overly greasy. 
The signature dish is impeccable and delicious and there’s nothing to complain about. Nevertheless, it doesn’t have the wow-factor I was looking for and I prolly won’t fight for a table.

Frantzén’s Kitchen
(Bf takeover! I let 👦🏻 take the food pics with his Leica this time and hmm I’d have to agree the camera does a much better job than iPhone. Any recommendations if I am to invest in a new camera? Leave your comments below! 👇🏻 )

We visited Frantzen’s Kitchen on their last day of business before it closes down for a renovation to become EMBLA! The restaurant has been on my bucket list for at least 2 years and I’m feeling so lucky to be able to secure a table on the last day and have their BEST OF FRANTZENS KITCHEN 2016-2021 menu.

The venison is cooked to a perfect medium rare and really tender. Aptly paired with celeriac puree and quince compote, the flavor of venison is much enhanced. It’s quite complex and a little too fruity for me. 

The French toast never disappoints! So much winter truffle has been grated on top 😍. I really like the fluffy texture and mellow oaky taste. The cheese and onion filling spices things up and it’s such a decadent treat. 

North Atlantic cod is such comfort food to me. The silky fish is paired with smoked beurre blanc sauce, which is the BEST beurre blanc I’ve ever had. It’s so buttery and rich yet light in consistency. It goes quintessentially with the spinach that comes with. I actually appreciate the sauce-drenched spinach more than the cod itself. The peas and walnut adds to the texture and gives a nutty twist to this classic dish. 

The Scallop from the Sea of Japan. It’s a fusion dish with uni emulsion, barigoule dashi and artichoke. Finally some decent artichoke in HK 😌 gosh am I excited. The scallop is fresh and delicious and I enjoyed the sweet emulsion as well. Wish it was a larger portion. 

Pumpkin, broccolini and truffle. The pumpkin puree has great flavours and umami. The broccolini is rather bland though. 

Last but not least comes our dessert - liquorice crème brûlée. Forgive me for not being a huge fan of liquorice and raspberry. I found the crystallised violets a bit too sweet for me. I didn’t enjoy the dish.
.
.
.

description:
Gaddi’s
Last post about Gaddi’s!
The Challans Duck Breast is paired with orange sauce, baby turnips and lavender honey (how special!). The duck breast is really tender and delicious. The sauce and condiment added fruity flavours to the dish. It’s very refreshing and appetising. 

👦🏻 ordered the black onyx beef tenderloin with freshly shaved truffle. He enjoyed it but I didn’t really like it cuz I found to a bit too soft. 

Dessert, unfortunately, is the most disappointing of all. I could barely stomach the whole thing. The Mont Blanc has an EXTREMELY thin layer of chestnut mousse. The cassis sorbet and berry sauce are way too sour and overwhelming. It tastes nothing like a monc Blanc. I’m just gonna go for the French cheese platter next time.

The petit fours are presented nicely and actually more delicious than the dessert. The latte is just alright. 

Overall: very lovely bread basket. Nice ambience for Christmas celebration. Appetisers and mains are great but steer clear of the dessert 😅

Gaddi’s
Cannelloni de Marcassin - my fav appetiser of the meal. Love the savoury red wine sauce and wild boar. 

Consommé de bouillabaisse. The sweetest and briniest seafood consommé I’ve ever tasted 😍 I’m a huge fan of the broth. The scallop is huge but rather bland. I don’t really like the fennel confit either.

The CNY snacking (& feasting😌) has begun!! Who else loves CNY snacks!!!🙋🏻‍♀️🙋🏻

Got to try these unique CNY snacks from @5loves2fishers 
💗 Osmanthus Pineapple Tart Balls
💗 Mala Pineapple Tarts Balls

These pineapple tarts balls had a nice crunch to it. The floral osmanthus was so fragrant, complementing the sweet pineapple. The mala flavoured is a real treat for those whom are mala lovers! Personally didn’t find it rly spicy, so it’s great for spice beginners🔥

These pineapple tarts balls are going at $18/bottle, and $30 for a pair of the same flavour! Perfect time to stock up your snacks for CNY🤩🤩🤩

Special mention to the awesome packaging!! Makes it so great for gifting this festive season🎊💯

Thank you @5loves2fishers for these treats🍍😋 #relle_dessertbreadsnack

🍽😋 𝙄𝙣𝙙𝙪𝙡𝙜𝙚 𝙮𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙥𝙖𝙡𝙖𝙩𝙚𝙨 𝙖𝙩 𝘾𝙖𝙡𝙞 𝙬𝙞𝙩𝙝 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙙𝙚𝙡𝙞𝙜𝙝𝙩𝙨 𝙤𝙛 𝙈𝙤𝙙𝙚𝙧𝙣 𝙎𝙤𝙪𝙩𝙝𝙬𝙚𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙣 𝙘𝙪𝙞𝙨𝙞𝙣𝙚
<𝐏𝐑𝐎𝐌𝐎 𝐂𝐎𝐃𝐄: 𝐐𝐮𝐨𝐭𝐞 “𝐑𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐞𝟐𝟎” 𝐭𝐨 𝐞𝐧𝐣𝐨𝐲 𝟐𝟎% 𝐨𝐟𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐢𝐫 𝐀𝐥𝐚-𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐞 𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐮!! Applicable for both online & dine-in>🔥❤️

Here’s what I tried!💗
✅Angus Striploin ($38)
Tender and juicy 150 days grain-fed Angus steak grilled to your choice of perfection, served with red wine sauce, roasted garlic, sautéed baby vegetables and roasted baby potatoes. This paired so nicely with some red wine, and special shoutout to the extremely juicy tomatoes.

✅Salmon Pesto ($30)
Grilled salmon fillet on top of penne tossed with pesto and cream served with baked garlic bread and lime wedges. I really liked the creamy pesto sauce with the al dente pasta, paired with salmon that wasn’t over cooked. 

✅Cream of wild mushroom soup ($12)
Rich and creamy soup with chunks of Shimeiji, pure white mushrooms and shiitake, drizzled with truffle oil, served with toasted garlic bread.

✅Cali Platter ($32)
Mexican wings, stuffed jalapeño, Santa Fe crab cake, chimichanga, nachos, garlic bread, truffle fries served with guacamole, sour cream, mango avocado salsa & bbq sauce. My favourite here is the stuffed jalapeños with cream cheese that was spicy and paired nicely with the sweetness of the mango dip. This platter is great for sharing, there’s something for everyone!

Paired these dishes with some lovely drinks, a Cosmopolitan ($14)
and a glass of Red Wine ($8) 🍹🍷

Ending off the meal with some sweets, a Molten Lava Torte ($12) that combines the elements of a chocolate cake baked to perfection, served with summer berries compote & vanilla icecream.

This place is great for date night!💗 Thanks @cali.singapore for the invite and delicious food😋 #relle_caferestaurant

🇯🇵🍽𝘾𝙧𝙖𝙫𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙦𝙪𝙖𝙡𝙞𝙩𝙮 𝙟𝙖𝙥 𝙛𝙤𝙤𝙙 𝙖𝙩 𝙧𝙚𝙖𝙨𝙤𝙣𝙖𝙗𝙡𝙚 𝙥𝙧𝙞𝙘𝙚𝙨? Check out @oishiiyatai.sg 😍🥰

❇️Gyudon ($10.8)
𝚁𝚒𝚌𝚎, 𝙵𝚞𝚛𝚒𝚔𝚊𝚔𝚎, 𝙾𝚗𝚒𝚘𝚗, 𝚂𝚑𝚒𝚋𝚊𝚣𝚞𝚔𝚎, 𝚂𝚞𝚗𝚘𝚖𝚘𝚗𝚘, 𝚂𝚙𝚛𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚘𝚗𝚒𝚘𝚗, 𝙱𝚎𝚎𝚏
I rly liked the marination of the beef that had a good level of sweetness, and the beef was tender and had a nice ratio of fat:meat. Coupled with the crunchy onions, the textures were great!

❇️Oyakodon ($8.8)
𝚁𝚒𝚌𝚎, 𝙵𝚞𝚛𝚒𝚔𝚊𝚔𝚎, 𝙾𝚗𝚒𝚘𝚗, 𝙴𝚐𝚐, 𝚂𝚙𝚛𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚘𝚗𝚒𝚘𝚗, 𝙲𝚑𝚒𝚌𝚔𝚎𝚗
There were good chunks of tender chicken, coupled with the crunchy onions and chilli flakes for some spice, this was yum too!

❇️Mala Udon ($8.8)
𝚂𝚑𝚒𝚖𝚎𝚒𝚓𝚒, 𝙾𝚢𝚜𝚝𝚎𝚛 𝙼𝚞𝚜𝚑𝚛𝚘𝚘𝚖𝚜, 𝙿𝚘𝚛𝚔 𝙱𝚎𝚕𝚕𝚢, 𝚂𝚙𝚛𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝙾𝚗𝚒𝚘𝚗
MALA FANS🔥 where you at!!! This had a nice kick of mala spice/numbness and topped with nice thin tender slices of pork!

Completed the meal with some side dishes as well, their Fried Ebi ($4.2) that wasn’t overly fried, and was nicely crispy. I rly liked the Teriyaki Karaage ($5.2) too, which had big chunks of chicken, crispy outside and soft inside, & a nice balance of sweetness, savoury and spice (with the chilli flakes)! Oh and not forgetting, the Hanjuku egg ($1.6)😋😋😋

Their portions are rly good, and so generous with the meats!🥰 They’re available for delivery via @grabfoodsg @foodpandasg @deliveroo_sg. Satisfy your jap food cravings now🤤

Thank you @oishiiyatai.sg for the delish food!🍽 #relle_caferestaurant

My fav between the 2 would definitely have to be the Sammy🌟 the egg mayo was creamy with a nice savoury touch, urghhh just so perfect. Happy Lunar New Year to our customers, partners, followers, friends suppliers and everyone else whom we have cross shoulders before. 

May everyone out have a roaring year ahead, and face any obstacle with ferocity and braveness. 🐯🐯

Peace out @served.with 👦👧

As seen on @thenewpaper 

I love set meals, especially when it comes to high-stress situations like a reunion dinner. The only coordination you need is to remember to book in advance and plan how to collect on the day you eat. 

@served.with CNY Abundance Platter ($55, good for four) comes with five dishes, such as Salted Egg Cheese Mala Chicken Brioche with Purple slaw, Yuzu Men"Tako" and Omelette with Golden Floss Brioche, and Carrot Cake with Pumpkin and Truffle Chilli.

It’s $10 more for delivery, but if you’re near Bishan, you can collect from them there

As CNY 2022 draws near, once again it is time to plan and prepare for your reunion! We have got you covered for a worry-free meal bundle, so your friends, families and you can enjoy a roaring good feast. 

Look forward to dishes such as
["鸡"祥如意🐔] 1x Salted Egg Cheese Mala Chicken Brioche with Purple slaw

[如"鱼"得水🐟] 1x Smoked Salmon Aburi Garlic Cream Cheese Brioche with GLOSS sauce (Garlic Lime Orange Soybean Sesame)

CNY Abundance Platter delivers on 29 and 30 January at 11-1pm or 4-6pm. It comes with 5 dishes and 5 sauces, serves 3-4 guests at $55 (五虎 - pun intended). $10 for island-wide delivery, self-collection at Bishan now available.

I don't care to the calories counters. I just love my pineapple tarts!

Shan/Thai fusion cuisine at this white-washed, colonial-style bungalow with gorgeous, warm-hued interiors and high ceilings that makes it feel like a sanctuary outside of SG. Shan/Thai fusion cuisine served here, starting with tender beef skewers and fusion-style crab cakes.

We graduated to the Yellow Massaman Curry with pork, which was more-ish with a mildly sweet flavour, and I found it super special that there was a fruit within (forgot what it is?).

A good steal away for a warm catch up, which for our case it was such, or that private evening. No wonder a fairly polished crowd. Swipe left for a look at one of their signature cocktails. 

Psst: Be sure to take a cab/car. 

Tamarind Hill
30 Labrador Hill
S119189
Opens 12-10pm daily

Don’t Truffle with this Camembert and Truffle sourdough. Pictures here is half a slab of that tangy, pillowy bread, complete with creamy Camembert and freshly shaved black truffles.

Toast it up in the oven and it has a crispy crust with plenty of flavour. Very coveted and well worth the few months of wait by this home baker.

And of course, thanks @whatupworthy for always being my other “half”. xD

This hunky-dory piece of fried fish slice (not dory) was pretty satisfying to bite into. Went a rare other way by picking a Chinese dish in long-time, old school Western bistro @theshipsg. It was a missed opportunity though, as the flavour depth didn’t quite match the excellent texture and visual, and the soup was okay. A pity, especially at thrice the price of a usual sliced fish soup…well.

Skip the western soups, which came with our meal sets. For the grilled platter of lobster with pasta, the lobster thankfully was pretty yummy, but the sides couldn’t quite match up. A restaurant in my childhood memory, and still popular judging by the Friday crowd, which sadly is a little puzzling for the taste at a budget of mid-$20s per pax. 

The Ship Singapore
1 Scotts Road, Shaw Centre

description:
Doesn’t feel like the weekend until it’s here? Just like that sometimes. And if a cafe is on your go to this one, consider this. Pumpkin Pancake with smoked salmon, hollandaise, tobiko and silky scrambled eggs. This was very delicious, sweetness of the pumpkin (without your telling it’s there) in a pretty pillowy pancake, paired with the savouriness from the delicious Hollandaise sauce and eggs.

It’s really filling, and best to share, but oh so satisfying. Indeed, therapy in a group @grouptherapycafe . xD

Group Therapy Cafe
Cross Street Exchange
181 South Bridge Road
S058473
Opens Sun-Tues, 8am-5pm; Wed-Thurs 8am-9pm and Fri-Sat 8am-10pm

Love seafood tze char with paired with red wine in a coffeeshop? Truly, that happens here @yangmingseafood. Visited on a Sunday lunch specially for this prized (and priced) Turbot fish (swipe to the last for a look at the live fish), which isn’t commonly found, and goes at three digits for one easily. The reason? Slippery smooth, springy skin with a clean, supple white meat texture. It is yummy alright and here they steam it right on point without overcooking (which would be disastrous).

The must order for me is the Thai Style Bee Hoon. It is full of aromatic flavour, if only a tad less oily would be perfect, but hey I am not complaining. It’s worth slurping all down. Other dishes we tried include the White Pepper Crab (alright; needs a whee bit more peppery oomph) and the steamed bamboo clams (always great).

Be sure to reserve if you can, as it was a full crowd when we visited, with quite a few tables having wine to go with the meal as well. ;)

Yang Ming Seafood
150 Bishan St 11 (other branches available)
S570150
Opens daily 11.30am-2pm; 4.30𝘱𝘮-10pm

📍87 Just Thai Killiney 👍

Finally found ourselves a really nice alternative to Ah Loy Thai haha.. 🤣

The 3 dishes we tried all taste really good, very authentic Thai taste that is 🤣 We especially love the tomyum. Really packs a punch, spicy while still having a good body and balanced off by its sour, savory and sweetness. Truly a gem ❤️ The other 2 needless to say, taste awesome as well, probably it's the fish sauce and oyster sauce haha 😋 

Portion wise, it's pretty generous and surprisingly the price is quite wallet friendly too. Definitely bang for the buck ❤️

This is situated at a corner shop along Killiney Road. Basically just a short distance away from Somerset station 😁

📍Legency Jawa Mee 传奇 😋👍

Another interesting find in Toa Payoh that serves up really delicious Jawa Mee ❤️

This is a very unique noodle dish. It comes with yellow noodles in tomato based gravy, which is kinda sweet and tangy by itself. We always squeeze in the lime to make it more appetizing for our likings 😜 It's also topped some generous amount of fresh and crispy crackers, drizzled with lots of peanut bits ❤️ Definitely a very refreshing plate of noodle. Love it!

Btw, this stall sits in a coffeeshop right opposite of the Toa Payoh West Market. Haha.. perfect for a breakfast streak 🤣

Not entirely sure if this is a Penang dish but we do remember eating this a lot while we're in Penang last time. It's one of the many delicious staple food there haha.. Heck, they even have the fried version there 😂

📍Chew Kee Noodle House - Soy Sauce Chicken Noodle 釗記油雞麵 👍

This is certainly a very interesting noodle. Delicately made soy sauce chicken paired with really springy noodle 😋

We really dig their soy sauce chicken ❤️ The taste is just so on point, savory with some hints of sweetness dwelling within. Appreciate that it's not too salty. And the meat is quite tender too! Mmm~~ 😋 The noodles are also very well prepped. Very springy and tastes really good after soaking up the soy sauce ❤️ 

We're not too familiar with this dish actually. To us, it's kinda like wanton noodle + soy sauce chicken haha.. 🤣 But, gotta say this combi tastes really good 😜 And man, this is sooooo much better than the one we had at Liao Fan. Such a big diff frankly😬

Most of the folks there were going for their dumplings soup too. That's probably good. Shall check it out in our next visit 😜

description:
Homecooked Steamed Garlic Ginger White Promfret 👍

It's the first day of CNY! So, here's our fish dish for today! 😜🎉🎉

Gotta love the aroma from the stir fried garlic, ginger and chilli sauce ❤️ Thanks to that, it's doesn't have that "fishy smell"at all. And it really lifts the flavor up a lot 😋

We first steamed the fish and dished out the fishy water from it. Then prep the sauce by first, stir frying minced garlic, ginger and chilli padi with sesame oil. Add in a mixture of oyster sauce, soy sauce, hua diao wine and water into it and let it boil. Then serves the sauce onto the fish. Garnish it with some parsley. Voila! There we go 🎉🎉 Lovely dinner in the house ❤️

Fish is one of the many auspicious symbolisms in Chinese New Year. It's associated with 年年有余, which means you'll have a surplus at the end of year! 🤣

Wishing all of you a Happy Chinese New Year and a properous year ahead! Cheers! 🍊🍊🧧🧧

Ingredients:
White Promfret • Minced garlic • Minced ginger • Chili padi • Hua diao wine • Oyster sauce • Soy sauce • Sesame oil • Parsley

📍Want Food Taiwanese Delights - Taiwanese Salty Chicken Rice 盐酥鸡饭 👍

This shop serves up some seriously nice Taiwanese fares. We tried their Taiwanese Salty Chicken Rice this round 😋

Make no mistake, this is not your everyday fried chicken 😜 It's crispy on the outside, really tender on the inside, literally ❤️ The layering is just so crazy distinct, you gotta try it to understand what I mean here 🤣  Also, this is served with a little bit of braised pork in the middle. 

Yep, one whole piece of braised egg, not half. Also, some pickled cucumber slices to cut through that "jelak-ness", balancing up the meal 😋 Damn nice, all in all. Love it! ❤️

This humble little shop is sitting at one end along the Nankin Street. It has a very comfortable, retro vibe to it. The friendly boss is a Taiwanese herself too. Really reminds us of Taiwan trip some time ago 😂 Do drop by and show them some love! 😜

OMMA Korean Charcoal BBQ, a Brand New Concept Founded by Old Street Bak Kut Teh Group recently open its 2nd Outlet! It is Singapore’s 1ST Wood-Fire Korean Charcoal BBQ that cooks up Vegetables, Seafood & Meats with Smokeless Charcoal instead of conventional ones.
_
@OmmaKoreanCharcoalBBQ opts for All-Natural Wood Charcoal that burns smokelessly for less adulteration of flavours & integrity of ingredients. This comes with the option to add on 5 Types of Wood Chips ($3 per 30g), carefully selected to enhance the flavors of its food. 
⬇️
× Hickory
× Applewood
× Cherry 
× Pecan
× Jarrah
⬇️
We opt for the former, Hickory, which cuts through the fattiness of Poultry, Pork & Red Meats to thoroughly cook with punchy smokiness.
_
On the Menu are over 60 ala carte options from as low as $8.8 as well as set menus from $49. Swipe left for #OmmaKoreanCharcoalBBQ's Signature, the Japanese A4 Ribeye @ $81/180g!

Another first for me: apple crumble. Recipe is still in its early stages! Used a mix of Granny Smith and Fuji apples, stewed them with brown sugar before loading them onto the baking dish. Crumble: flour, butter, oats, digestive biscuits, demarara sugar. The apples were slightly sweeter, but that can be adjusted with lemon juice. Quite satisfied with the crumble, but I’ll probably tweak the recipe again!

Happy New Year! Never thought 2022 would come but it’s here! 2021 was great and I am thankful, but may 2022 be even better. I don’t know what God’s plan is for the new year (nobody does), but somehow He always amazes me. Stay safe everyone, and cheers to more food adventures 🥂

Sauerkraut Fish (老坛子酸菜鱼). Fish is incredibly fresh and smooth. This 酸菜鱼is slightly spicier and less sour as compared to the one I had at Chinatown. I was quite surprised to not find pickled chillies and pickled ginger in the broth as these are two commonly used ingredients in this particular dish. It’s good no doubt, but I’d prefer one that is on the sour side.

Crispy Pork (酥肉). A tiny bit disappointing as batter:meat ratio is on the higher side, plus it’s on the greasier side as well. Would have loved for the Sichuan peppercorn flavour to be more pronounced!

Egg Coated Glutinous Rice Rolls with Brown Sugar (蛋酥软糍粑). Its crispy exterior and a soft interior is reminiscent of a fried mochi, but it’s totally fine if you don’t order it.

Sichuan Peppercorn Milk Tea with Red Beans (充电花椒奶茶). A super interesting combination, but works super well. I’m not into pearls, so the red beans were very much welcomed!
Eggnog (because it’s the festive season), and Hazelnut Latte from @tomspalettesg. It’s been many years since my last visit and the ice cream’s still as creamy, still as good.

Of catch-ups and random talks about life, over @wineconnectionsg’s four-cheese (Bleu D’Auvergne, Mozzarella, Parmesan, Saint Nectaire) gnocchi, smoked chilli aglio olio, and a chocolate lava cake. This is probably the only time where I’ll order something with blue cheese, and it’s good. The aglio olio packs a nice punch and would be a favourite for spicy food lovers. Lava cake was rich and moist but I’d have loved for it to be cooked for a slightly shorter time so that there’s more lava. Ended off with a cappuccino, which probably explains why I couldn’t sleep.

Croissant-turned cinnamon brioche?🥐 

2nd attempt at viennoiserie making! 
Better dough texture this time, with a more pliable & less-sticky consistency that made the rolling much easier. Folding still remains my no.1 enemy.. with each fold causing the “book” to be fatter and fatter, and more and more difficult to flatten - as seen by the (still-too-thick dough above)🥲 1-2-3...10 I count in my mind as I roll & roll the rolling pin in an attempt to flatten the stubbornly plump dough that keeps resisting my push and returning to the original position, while balancing the force in trying not to tear the layers which causes the butter to peek out 🧈 - most discouraging part gotta be how even aft multiple rolls, the dough barely budges and flattens hardly a millimeter- indeed a true test of patience & a draining arm workout it is :’) certainly not an everyday bake, but till the next time (aft the battery’s recharged) ~

Sticky date pudding

Soft & moist with a cake-like lightness & the warm smell of spices, these mini bundlettes have a chewy sticky bite from the pieces of dates purposefully left behind & a nutty crunch from the crushed walnuts ~ made from molasses sugar, the deep roasty salted caramel melts into a puddle, allowing its flavor to soak through the warm pudding~ the perfect dessert of the season , & best paired with a cold scoop of vanilla ice cream 🍨🙃

Cacio e Pepe 🧀🍝 

The minimalist’s pasta, this literally means cheese & pepper. The traditional Roman version uses just 100% Romano cheese & pepper for the base , but mixed in some parmesan (70:30) here for a blend of flavors~ while seemingly simple, the al dente bucatini stirred in freshly grated cheese and freshly cracked black pepper complements each other in a synergistic manner, creating a salty cheesy dish with a nice spicy kick~

Indulge in @miso.salmon slurpworthy 🍜Udon originated from Inaniwa with its distinct thin and chewy, yet silky-smooth texture 😋 We also switch up their Inaniwa Udon to try a lighter alternative made from the root of a 🌱 Konjac plant called 🥢Shirataki noodles that boast very Low calories and are high in fibre 👍🏻 All these goodness paired in a broth of rich and filled with Unami flavor, ho-Jiak for sure!! 🤤

Choose from DIY but be sure to add on their signature tender poached salmon slices which are definitely the star in the dish & delicate fresh prawns that are already peeled for you 🤩💯 Besides a variety of soup & dry version of Inaniwa Udon Specialities, there’s 🍚 hearty rice bowls options too like 🍗 Yakitori Chicken with Truffled Mushroom Don, 🍣 Aburi Salmon Mentai with Edamame Don. I’m obsessed by the unlimited options 🤤 completed with a selection of sides, I’m sure #udonwanttomissit!! 😉

Back with several collections from @bakesbymabs - plenty of matcha as usual!
.
Matcha Pistachio Babka (S$7) - this babka was definitely way stronger in matcha flavour rather than pistachio. The matcha pistachio strips were bitter (rather than sweet) from the matcha (only the bread was sweet), and there was an overwhelming matcha flavour (with just a slight nuttiness from the pistachio nuts). Personally, as a matcha lover I still prefer Mab’s matchapan, but have to say that this was a pretty mean matcha (pistachio) babka and the only thing that could make this even stronger in matcha would be for there to be matcha in the babka bread batter.
.
Hojicha Fig Babka (S$7) - in my opinion, the houjicha wasn’t too prominent here, perhaps due to the use of houjicha tea leaves in the bread batter (rather than houjicha tea powder)? Couldn’t really taste the houjicha in the fig jam as well. The fig flavour was much stronger with the abundance of actual figs, and the babka was slightly sweet as a result. Topped with chopped almonds as well!
.
If you want to try her babkas, she’s having a babka box bakesale this weekend, which includes her matcha pistachio and hojicha fig babkas! (As well as her earl grey fig and black sesame babkas)
.
Also featuring some repeat bakes, such as her matchapans and matcha macarons, which were all good as usual. Mabs makes what is probably hands down my favourite matcha macaron ever - and they’re so satisfying for $2.50 a pop. For her matcha espresso macaron, the coffee flavour seemed less strong this time round, but still good nonetheless. For her matcha kinako yuzu macaron, the yuzu was really sour (idk why I keep expecting it to be less sour, probably cos of all the yuzu desserts out there) and the kinako added a slight savouriness. And then of course - the strong bittersweet matcha filling.
.
[new macaron flavour reviews continued in comments]
.
@bakesbymabs • Operating on bakesale basis, islandwide delivery fee of S$10.

[#chueonsentosa] "To eat well in England you should have breakfast three times a day" W. Somerset Maugham.
—-
It's fitting that I'm reminiscing about @capellasingapore's decadent breakfast spread a month after cos Lord knows I need me another staycation. 😂 I'm often skeptical about hotel breakfast buffets but oh boy Capella's really blew me away. The menu is pretty compact and simple, with mouthwatering dishes hailing from both local and western cuisines. The Scrambled Eggs were to die for - SO SILKY AND SMOOTH LIKE A BLANKET. And the Singapore Laksa is one of the best I've tried (rivalling even EMC's), with succulent shrimps coated in the most fragrant coconut broth I've tried. Definitely would have tried the Eggs Benedict and Prata which are often raved about if I wasn't on the verge of bursting; next time maybe? 🤔
—-
🚇: Resorts World
💵: $$$
📝: http://bit.ly/chueoncapella
—-
#whatchueeating #capellasingapore #capellacandids

[#chueonboatquay] Standing for "the golden age" in French, @labelleepoquesg is the latest addition to the vibrant riverfront F&B belt that is Boat Quay. 
—-
Here, you can enjoy Chef Firduaz's eclectic take on contemporary European cuisine, which includes keto and vegetarian-friendly options. From decadent Oyster & Iberico [$26++ for 3 pieces], to fork-tender Beef Short Ribs [$28++]. I did find some of the dishes a tad too experimental, though, but nothing a little fine-tuning can't fix.
—-
🚇: Raffles Place 
💵: $$
📝: http://bit.ly/chueonlabelleepoque
—-
#whatchueeating #labelleepoque

[#chueondempsey] Going bananas 🤪🍌
—-
Had the time of my life at @museumoficecreamsg, where there are over 10 ice-cream-themed installations including one dedicated to our homegrown Potong! Admission is on the steep side and it's definitely catered to a certain crowd, but if OOTDs and super happy pastel backdrops are your thing, don't knock it till you've tried it! The highlight of every visit is the Sprinkle Room, that's apparently so popular visitors have a 5-minute time limit to have their fill of diving into plastic sprinkles. But my favourite room is for sure the banana archway (wonder how many rubber bananas it actually took to make this arch!).
—-
🚇: Orchard
💵: $$
📷: @oo_foodielicious 
📝: https://bit.ly/chueonmoic
—-
#wherechuegoing #museumoficecream #moic

[#chueonboonlay] I never thought I would say this but I've finally checked Boon Lay off my cafe-hopping list. 🤣
—-
@surreyhillsgrocer.sg is an Australian-style, farm-to-table cafe founded by an ex-banker who earned her food business chops in Down Under before returning to Singapore to bring exclusive produce at competitive prices. The menu is straightforward, comprising usual suspects like avocado toast and eggs benedict. The Tasmanian Salmon [$26++] is one of the highlights in Surrey Hills' menu, with slow-cooked sashimi-grade salmon that's complimented by a risotto-like barley base. Portions could be a little more generous for the price, but overall, I enjoyed the salmon's freshness and the overall comforting notes!
—-
I'm all for new cafes popping up in new areas other than the usual east and central neighbourhoods, and Surrey Hills is a pretty decent entry to Singapore's cafe scene. It's a great option if you're working in the area and wanna treat yourself.
—-
🚇: Boon Lay
💵: $$
📝: http://bit.ly/chueonsurreyhillsgrocer
—-
#whatchueeating #surreyhillsgrocer

[#chueonsentosa] ✨This is your sign to book a birthday staycation at @capellasingapore! ✨
—-
Checked into paradise for my birthday last month and have no regrets. 🤩 Capella Singapore is worthy of its reputation (and not just for the 2018 Trump Kim Summit) and I was thoroughly spoilt during my stay. The service is undeniably attentive and it's almost as though each guest has an invisible butler tending to their every need! It was sooo easy to forget I was still technically in Singapore while soaking up all the creature comforts Capella had to offer. Booked the Constellation Room so I could truly, 100% be alone for the first time in 2 years. 😌
—-
Pro tip: Don't miss the complimentary workshops and classes designed for guests of all ages, from rum tasting and cocktail making to morning Yoga class. Also if you tell the concierge it's your birthday, they'll have a couple of surprises up their sleeves for you! Didn't expect to find little goodies here and there each time I returned, but that's 5-star service for you.
—-
🚇: Resorts World
💵: $$$
📝: http://bit.ly/chueoncapella
—-
#wherechuegoing #capellacandids

Barlauchcremesuppe mit creme fraiche un croutons $14
-
Soup may not immediately come to mind as the most exciting of foods, but this seasonal special from Frieda's Wild Garlic & Beer menu commanded my attention with its rich and comforting flavour. Each spoonful was practically blooming with the essence of wild garlic, essentially a more delicate and sweeter version of regular garlic. Tempered with the mellow creaminess of creme fraiche and jazzed up with crunchy croutons, this deceptively simple dish is sure to win your tastebuds over.

Churros
-
Brought to you by @diningcitysingapore and @nespresso.sg, Singapore Restaurant Week is back again from 4th - 27th March and features more than 100 top restaurants.
-
Courtesy of @burpple, I had the pleasure of trying the $68++ 4-course dinner at @alegriasgp, which has its roots as the first sangria bar in Manila and has since grown into multiple concepts and outlets across the Philippines, with Alegria Singapore being its first foray overseas. Savour Latin Asian fusion cuisine married with European technique and a heavy emphasis on Filipino flavours.
-
To end the meal on a sweet note, we got the mother of all churros. No mere sticks of churros here, instead we get an entire churros escargot. The fried dough is flagrantly fragrant on the outside with a thick coating of cinnamon sugar, and soft, fluffy - almost on the edge of gooey - within. In my mind this is the ideal texture for churros. It's paired with a sweet and luscious dulce de leche fortified with a strong hit of coffee that I loved.

Sisig Taco $8
-
No cheesy taco puns here, only honest to goodness meat in a wrap deliciousness. The Filipino inflected Sisig Taco sees moreish dinakdakan sauce coated pork belly garnished with crisp pickled onion within a soft and warm purple yam tortilla.

Chicken Inasal
-
Brought to you by @diningcitysingapore and @nespresso.sg, Singapore Restaurant Week is back again from 4th - 27th March and features more than 100 top restaurants.
-
Courtesy of @burpple, I had the pleasure of trying the $68++ 4-course dinner at @alegriasgp, which has its roots as the first sangria bar in Manila and has since grown into multiple concepts and outlets across the Philippines, with Alegria Singapore being its first foray overseas. Savour Latin Asian fusion cuisine married with European technique and a heavy emphasis on Filipino flavours.
-
A frisson of excistement passed through me as this HUGE piece of chicken landed in front of my face. Grilling over the open fire of the Parilla imparted an intoxicating charred smokiness to the succulent and juicy meat, and the addictive vinegar and citrus based Inasal sauce cut through the heft of the protein effortlessly, allowing one to power through the not insubstantial amount of meat. Served with a bowl of ebi coconut rice and a pickled kohlrabi and fennel slaw, this could safely feed two light eaters. Easily our favourite main course of the set dinner.

Coxinha
-
Brought to you by @diningcitysingapore and @nespresso.sg, Singapore Restaurant Week is back again from 4th - 27th March and features more than 100 top restaurants.
-
Courtesy of @burpple, I had the pleasure of trying the $68++ 4-course dinner at @alegriasgp, which has its roots as the first sangria bar in Manila and has since grown into multiple concepts and outlets across the Philippines, with Alegria Singapore being its first foray overseas. Savour Latin Asian fusion cuisine married with European technique and a heavy emphasis on Filipino flavours.
-
Perfect single bites, these pulled chicken croquettes had a satisfying crunch but tended toward the dry side of things, however the sweet and smoky miso onion puree came to the rescue.

How often do you guys have sandwich? Tbh I rarely make one for myself 🤪.

📍 Location: Goc Viet Vietnamese Eatery, Sunnybank
.
🛋 Ambience: (4.25 out of 5)
Located at the new building of the Sunnybank Market Square, @gocvietqld was decorated in bold-coloured wall panels, complete with bright-coloured furniture that gave off a modern and youthful vibe.
.
🍽 Food & Drink: (4.75 out of 5)
Ordered the Bun Cha Gio, or Vermicelli Noodle with Spring Rolls. The dish was packed with toppings, from fresh vegetables such as carrot and cucumber, as well as the crunchy spring rolls. The sauce joined all sections of the dish, making it perfect to have on a hot summer day.

I also had the Roast Pork Baguette or the Banh Mi. The bread was quite fluffy and filled with a generous amount of pork. I’d like it better if the pork had some crunchiness to it, but the tender texture of the meat actually worked alright.

Also tried the Northern Grilled Pork Noodle, which was served on a bamboo platter. This dish was relatively bigger in portion size compared to the previous two - but also tasted awesome with herb-packed pork.
.
👩‍🍳 Service: (4.25 out of 5)
Came here on Sunday afternoon, and the store was quite busy. Additionally, each person needed to order from the counter, hence the foods came out at different times.
.
💲 Price: (4.25 out of 5)
Most of the mains including the noodle salads and rice dishes were in the range of $14-20. Meanwhile, the banh mi costs $9 - I’d say it was affordable despite not being the cheapest option in town.
.
❓ Overall: (4.3 out of 5) 
Would like to try the soups on my next visit!
.
.
.
#brisbane #brisbanefood #brisbanefoodie #brisbanefoodies #brisbanefoodblogger #brisbaneblogger #brisbanefoodblog #brisbanedining #brisbaneeats #brisbaneanyday #brisbanerestaurants #feedfeed #eeeeats #zomatobne #putrireviews

📍 Location: Tokyo Chubo, Sunnybank
.
🛋 Ambience: (4.25 out of 5)
Located in a shopping complex, @tokyo_chubo was decorated with white walls and warm lights, complemented the modern wooden-like furniture while giving off a cozy and homey vibe.
.
🍽 Food & Drink: (4.75 out of 5)
Had their Sushi, both Sashimi Salmon and The Chef Special including the Soft Shell Crab Roll and the California Roll. The sashimi was super fresh and not fishy, while the sushi rolls were packed with a generous amount of toppings. 

Also tried their bento, specifically the Chicken Karaage and the Teriyaki Salmon. Each bento portion was huge, served with miso soup, rice, salads, and two slices of sashimi salmon. The chicken itself was crunchy and juicy, not too greasy and balanced in terms of seasoning, while the salmon was dribbled in slightly sweet-tasting sauce.
.
👩‍🍳 Service: (4.25 out of 5)
Came here around the end of the year 2021, and the place was packed. I guess they were understaffed too, noting the holiday period - hence the food took some time to be prepared although all meals ordered came at the same time.
.
💲 Price: (4.25 out of 5)
The sashimi and sushi rolls were mostly priced around $15-20, while the bento was on the $22-27 mark. It wasn’t the cheapest meal, but considering the big portion size, I’d say it’s worth it.
.
❓ Overall: (4.4 out of 5) 
I’ll come back to enjoy more dishes that they offer!
.
.
.
#brisbane #brisbanefood #brisbanefoodie #brisbanefoodies #brisbanefoodblogger #brisbaneblogger #brisbanefoodblog #brisbanedining #brisbaneeats #brisbaneanyday #brisbanerestaurants #feedfeed #eeeeats #zomatobne #putrireviews

📍 Location: Bellissimo Coffee, Coorparoo
.
🛋 Ambience: (4.75 out of 5)
Located right outside the Coorparoo Secondary College, @bellissimocoffeeau at Coorparoo was state of the art. The store had a high ceiling, decorated with modern hanging lights. To top it off, the store also had a glass window overlooking the warehouse and the roastery side of the building.
.
🍽 Food & Drink: (4.75 out of 5)
Had their almond croissant and the vegetarian toastie. The croissant was perfect for the sweet-tooth - it’s on the buttery end, not quite flaky but packed with a lot of fillings and served with the powdered sugar. Meanwhile, the toastie was full of cheese and plenty of vegetables. Complemented with the crunchy bread, the toastie was delicious and certainly fulfilling.

For the drink, I had the latte, which was brewed perfectly. It wasn’t too milky, and I couldn’t taste any acidity from over-roasting the beans. But if you are after a cold coffee, they also offer a selection of bottled cold-brew behind the counter.
.
👩‍🍳 Service: (5 out of 5)
I came here on Sunday morning, and the staff was very hospitable. Both food and drink service were also prompt.
.
💲 Price: (4.25 out of 5)
The croissant was around $7-9, while the toastie was priced around $10-12. They also offer brunch menus, which range from $14-18. I’d say it was a fair pricing.
.
❓ Overall: (4.6 out of 5) 
Would be back for more toasties, and potentially try out the brunch selection!
.
.
.

📍 Location: Thai Nakonlanna, St Lucia
.
🛋 Ambience: (3.5 out of 5)
Located at the Hawken Drive, just the complex across the IGA, @thai_nakonlanna had a small seating area indoor while also offering more tables outdoors. The interior was pretty simple, and with its wall decorated in dark brown wallpaper, the store was quite dim.
.
🍽 Food & Drink: (4.75 out of 5)
I’ve been coming for more than three times, and their Massaman Beef Curry still turned out to be my favourite. The meat was juicy and tender, easily falling apart at the touch of the spoon. The sauce was also tasty and as it was served generously, it complemented the rice very well.

I also had their Beef Fried Rice, which was packed with vegetables, red onions, and sliced meat. The meat sometimes turned tough and chewy, but overall, it was a delicious and fulfilling meal. 

Meanwhile, their Pad See Ew and Pad Thai were also packed with a generous amount of toppings. The good thing: these dishes didn’t leave too much of an oily after taste, while still flavourful.
.
👩‍🍳 Service: (3.25 out of 5)
Most of the time, there was only one waiter working in this restaurant - they were clearly understaffed, so the waiting time for the food could be very long, especially during busy hours.
.
💲 Price: (5 out of 5)
Each meal was priced around $10-15, hence very affordable when you compare it to the generous serving size.
.
❓ Overall: (4.1 out of 5) 
Would be back for the Massaman Beef Curry!
.
.
.

description:
Mark your calendar, the newly revamped swanky @ChatterboxSG reopens in 5 days (14 March!) If you think Chatterbox is just about it’s famous Chicken Rice,  you are wrong! 
.
Got a taste of some of other local favourite dishes and I left with a happy belly. Some of the dishes that left an impression (means yummy!) are the thick Mackeral & Crab Otah Otah, Lobster Laksa and the Beef Horfun!
.
Two of the new innovative dishes Lemon Butter Prawn & Sea Perch with Burnt Green Chilli were well executed too. 
.
This may not be a place for everyday fare because of its pricing but it’s lovely place for gatherings, business meals or even celebrations. Oh! Don’t forget the alcohol too, can try the tropical Chatterbox’s punch with a banana infused gin tho it’s a little sweet for me.
.
📌CHATTERBOX
333 Orchard Road, Hilton Singapore Orchard, #05-03 , S238887
⏰11.30am-2.30pm, 5.30pm-10.30pm

Sawadee Ka! Having the new 555 Tom Yum Oat Chicken from @texaschickensg for lunch: crunchy fried chicken slathered in Tom Yum spices and coated with crispy oats. Also available in Pop Corn Chicken option and also Thai Milk Tea to complete the whole Thai experience. Get $5 off when you order through the app!

When I think of @goodwoodparkhotelsg , one of the things I will always associate is their infamous durian desserts! 
.
Yes the highly anticipated yearly affair, Goodwood Park Hotel’s Durian Fiesta returns this year with a tempting line-up of elegant treats from 28 February to 24 July 2022!
.
Had the chance to try some of the new creations : D24 Crystal Apricot Dome, D24 Strawberry Mascarpone Filo Tart and D24 Lychee Blossom Cake. NEW dine-in exclusives, namely Deep-fried D24 Mochi Ball and Pan-fried D24 Blue Pea Kueh Salat, are also available only at Min Jiang at Goodwood Park Hotel. Shiokalicious! 
.
To place orders online : head to https://thedeligoodwoodparkhotel.oddle.me for delivery or self- collection from 28 February to 24 July 2022. Alternatively, guests may contact The Deli at (65) 6730 1786 or email their order form (available at https://www.goodwoodparkhotel.com/promotions/durian-fiesta-2022) to deli@goodwoodparkhotel.com to place their takeaway orders for self-collection only. Advance order of 5 days is required and the last pre-order date is 19 July 2022

Lunch time! Having Braised Meat Rice 滷肉飯 except that there is no real meat. @ShihlinsnacksSG Shihlin Taiwan Street Snacks Collaborates with @meatzerosg to Launch First Ever Guilt-Free Meat Zero Hero Ricebox! Great for those who vegetarians or even flexitarians.
.
The Meat Zero Hero Ricebox (U.P. $7.90) will be retailing at $6.90 at all Shihlin Taiwan Street Snacks outlets except for AMK Hub and NEX from now till 30 April 2022. I had their value set which comes with Sweet Plum Potato Fries and Freshmade Drink. Digging their sweet plum potato fries! 
.
Also available on all delivery platforms!

Co-founder of SBCD Korean Tofu House, Chef Nam Kyoung Soon ventures into the heartlands (first AMK now Punggol) under new express concept @soontofusg with wallet friendly prices!
.
If you are fickle minded like me, get the Assorted Tofu Soup Set which has seafood, pork and beef all in one! I love SBCD at Millenia so comparatively the portions here are smaller (but also cheaper). New on the menu is the Mandu which comes in three flavours ; Original, Kimchi and Japchae, can try! Prices start from $6 for Tofu Set and $4.50 for Mandu
.
📌Soon Tofu Soup
// 671 Edgefield Plains #01-01 S820671
// Blk 721 Ang Mo Kio Ave 8, #01-2823 S560721
