description:
[🇸🇬] #culivinarysg 
What did I expect from a $8++ bomboloni? A lot. Unfortunately, PBD’s Crème Brûlée Bombolini did not meet my expectations. 

The bombo was served in room temperature, its top part a little wet/sticky from caramelized sugar I assume. Bombo-wise, I did enjoy the richness of the flavor and it had great texture, not dry, soft, pillowy, and not greasy. I excitedly sliced the bombo open but it wasn’t flowing with any custard, in fact, the amount of custard was just what you see on the second slide (even lesser on the other half). Flavor-wise, ngl it was delicious—a hella solid vanilla custard with spot-on richness, sweetness, and texture, however, there was too little to bring any “uMpH” impact. I’m a fan of their sandwiches (tho i havent tried in a long while) but with the $8++ price tag, I don’t find this bombo worth it.
ㅇ
ㅇ
ㅇ
📍 @parkbenchdeli , Telok Ayer
#bomboloni #sgdonut #donuts

[🇸🇬] #culivinarysg 
The OG (3 Cheese) ($19++) was quite a pricey sandwich but it does have some selling points. Firstly every component was of 🤟🏻 quality and bOi was huge! I took away almost half of it home in my own container. It was really loaded with cheese (good ones) and the sourdough was toasted to perfection with good amount of butter that did not end up greasy. The sd itself was great as expected—amazingly moist and chewy on the inside with oOmph twang and crisped up exterior plus its crust wasn’t awfully thick. A simple grilled cheese done right, tho I personally feel like it needs some tomato soup or something to complete it haha!

I also bought back a loaf of Lemon Rosemary sd which I’ll review next time tgt with croissants etc! Would love to come back and try some of their tartines (but they’re quite hard to access from me so idk when)
ㅇ
ㅇ
ㅇ
📍 @starterlab.sg Tiong Bahru
#grilledcheese

[🇸🇬] #culivinarysg 
Waited >45 mins for the beef brisket ($23/200g) to come and frankly saying, I was very disappointed. The beef was VERY tough we left most of it bc they can’t be eaten,,, flavor-wise—well the bbq sauce was tasty (i adored the flavor balance!) but the beef really can’t be enjoyed. 

On the other hand, their Smoked Chicken Satay Madura ($18++) was impressive. The chicken chunks are plump, juicy, tender, and very well cooked without any chicken-y taste 😮‍💨🔥 the peanut/kecap sauce was on-point, got my Indonesian tastebuds dancing in joy. 

We had the proteins with Nasi Lemak Bakar ($1++)—pretty unusual to have rice with bbqs like the brisket but absolutely lovely with the satay 🤟🏻 notably flavorful but some parts were kinda dry

We closed of with the valrhona souffle ($12++)—not bad, a pretty well done souffle that’s molten inside and crisp outside but I wished the chocolate flavor was stronger and that they have an ice cream option since the whipped cream didn’t really bring much impact. 

Overall—the satay was rlly a saving grace but the brisket was really not it. Service was also all over the place and cold, very hard to request for things (we asked nicely :( ). Well, I came bc I heard a number of good reviews but frankly saying, we didn’t have a good time here—I hope it’s different for other people. 
ㅇ
ㅇ
ㅇ
📍 @cherryoak.sg (somewhere near farrer park)
#bbq #beefbrisket #smokehouse #sghalalfood #sghalal #satay

[🇸🇬] #culivinarysg 
Tapaoed Leckerbaer and twas raining thus the bad lighting :”). Anyways these treats weren’t disappointing at all! 

The Dark Chocolate tart $8.5 really impressed me. Firstly, the tart was crisp and secondly, the flavor left more impression than what I had expected from a chocolate-tangy stuff combo. The tart consisted of a smooooth and bold dark chocolate namelaka, tart cherry curd, and a moist brownie inside. I like how both the dark chocolate and cherry managed to stand out and complement each other so beautifully! 

Can’t resist not getting the Apple Choux ($8.5) and pretty glad I tried! I like how the vanilla creme patisserie (diplomat¿) inside were just barely sweet and that it dilutes the sweet whipped cream on top and the tangy apples. Loved the flavor play and also texture-wise the juicy small-cut apples but I just wished the choux weren’t as stale/dry~ but yea it’s fully packed with good stuff and each bite was 🤟🏻

Overall I think they’re really worth a try and as a pastry fan, I would love to try more stuffs! The bakes are a lil smaller than average but the prices are still reasonable for patisseries ✨
ㅇ
ㅇ
ㅇ
📍 @leckerbaer.sg , isetan outlet 
#leckerbaer #choux #patisserie

[🇸🇬] #culivinarysg 
A late late post but I tried Salt’s famous garlic cream cheese bun when they were regularly on sale and wasn’t disappointed! Not sure if they have it rn but they held bake-sales for these on certain occasions. 

The amount of cream cheese and garlic butter is just nice—the edges crisp up after toasting and bOi each bite was satisfying 💥. The cream cheese is well balanced in flavor—cheesy and slightly sweet with hints of sour, plus it had nice consistency. The bun itself was a nice vessel as it wasn’t soggy but not dry at all! Sufficiently soft :). Each bun costs $9 ($8 when u buy 4 cmiiw), kinda expensive but I didn’t regret trying, also it’s quite a big bun (i ate half at a time)

Along with the garlic cream cheese buns, I tried their viennoseries; a classic croissant and raisin escargot. The layers are quite distinct in view and it flaked up pretty okay but I find that the butter taste isn’t really to my liking—it felt ‘heavy’ for some reason~ but it’s just my preference. 
ㅇ
ㅇ
ㅇ
📍 @saltbistroandbar 
#garliccreamcheesebread

Sourdough karaage $20
Sharing spread platter $22
Ricotta and dried tomato pizza $20
Sourdough waffles $12
Dark chocolate mousse $14

We got the sourdough karaage thinking it’ll be a small starter to share but what came out was four ginormous pieces of chicken thighs 😂 served with kimchi mayo. Also got the sharing spread platter of avocado cream and pumpkin hummus with pita bread. Then came the Ricotta and dried tomatoes pizza - lovee the soft chewy crust! 

Dessert was chocolate mousse, followed by my favorite dish of the night - the sourdough waffles 😘🧇

Thanks for the meal, SEG!

First time making samosa from scratch. 
Took quite a while to get these crispy, flakey, mutton filled, deep-fried samosas out on a plate and we inhaled it in just minutes 😙

Love it when the husband goes out for a meeting and comes back with snacks. This time it’s pastries from @mrholmesbakehousesg !

Bacon jalapeño danish 
Fruity pebbles donut
Pumpkin cheesecake cruffin
Rocky road cruffin
California croissant
Churro croissant

The cruffins and croissants had flakey, buttery layers of pastry and were oozing with fillings! Danish was just as good if not better. And that one donut we got was fluffy, light and evenly coated with sugar.. but I’m not a big fan of the flavour.

Overall, I think the savoury pastries stood out more and I’d defo return to try their other flavours.

Mazechirashi lunch set $42
This vibrant bowl of rice is topped with a fresh selection of mixed sashimis. Love how they have my fav uni and otoro, as well as their homemade tamago which was perfect in this mix.

For dessert we had the Yumeshu jelly, milk tea icecream sandwiched between wafer biscuits and the most indulgent of the trio - milk pudding. 

Definitely one of the best Mazechirashi in town👍🏼

#latergram from April 2021
#latergram from when I made garlic butter naan and chicken tikka masala. Super please with how fluffy the naans turned out ☺️

[📍Yuan Authentic Thai Stewed Beef Noodles, Singapore ]
Found out that the owner of thjs stall is a Thai lady who moved over to Singapore over 20 years ago. Her food is legit stuff and took us all the way back to Bangkok!

[📍Yan Ji Seafood Soup, Singapore ]
Despite being located in a hawker centre, the food here at Yan Ji Seafood Soup isn’t the cheapest. But is it worth it? We think so.

We got the Crayfish Soup which cost $12 for the smallest bowl and this came loaded with prawns, fish maw, minced pork, clams and of course, the crayfish. 

The soup itself is jam packed with umami and was very rich with a slight creaminess to it. We were also very pleased with how fresh all the seafood was — no distasteful nor pungent fishy flavours to be tasted at all! What surprised us as well was the minced pork, which we didn’t expect to find since it was, afterall, a seafood soup. This added a nice texture to the overall dish and surprisingly gelled well with the rest of the components.

Would we shell out another $12 to eat this again? It’s a resounding yes from us! 

Will return: 👍🏻
See how:
Never coming back:

description:
‼️ Flash this post for 10% off ala carte menu items! ‼️

A good example of the quality of ingredients at @kyoyadiningsg: their 𝐓𝐫𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐧 ($𝟐𝟎). Fresh scallops, caviar, ikura and tobiko to pair with their somen noodles. Admittedly could do with a little more dimension in flavour but very applaudable for the integrity in its truffle flavour.

For sashimi lovers, their 𝐒𝐚𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐦𝐢 𝐌𝐨𝐫𝐢𝐚𝐰𝐚𝐬𝐞 ($𝟑𝟔 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝟐𝐩𝐚𝐱) is a must get. Seriously thick chunky slices of various fish with the quality and freshness you can taste.

Some might liken their 𝐅𝐮𝐠𝐮 𝐊𝐢𝐫𝐢𝐧 ($𝟏𝟖) (air dried puffer fish) to a fishy bakkwa, and it’s a pretty accurate comparison. Coated with a sweet smoky sauce balanced out by the mayo dip.

Had high expectations for the 𝐆𝐲𝐮 𝐒𝐚𝐧𝐭𝐨 ($𝟑𝟖), was was rather disappointed with the soggy bread. Texture-wise, the beef wasn’t doing much for me either.

A rather unique side dish worth trying, their 𝐏𝐢𝐝𝐚𝐧 𝐓𝐨𝐟𝐮 ($𝟔) is loaded with umami from the copious amount of century egg topped onto the creamy tofu. Or try their adorable 𝐂𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐩𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐚𝐫 𝐌𝐚𝐤𝐢 ($𝟐𝟖), fresh tasting maki loaded with avocado.

Btw… happy hour: 1 for 1 Suntory Premium Malts (Black or White) 😋😋😋

[invited tasting] Thanks Rex from @kyoyadiningsg & Donovan for the invite!

🏷 #EEBpromenade #EEBjapanese

It’s hard to disagree with @kanadaya.sg’s 𝐓𝐨𝐧𝐤𝐨𝐭𝐬𝐮 𝐌𝐢𝐱 𝐑𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐧 ($𝟏𝟕.𝟗𝟎). It’s a creamy tonkotsu + chicken paitan broth with rich porky umami flavour packed into its relatively light body. Comes with tender & fatty belly chashu, wood ear fungus and a whole egg.

Was rather curious (and dubious) of their 𝐒𝐩𝐢𝐜𝐲 𝐘𝐮𝐳𝐮 𝐑𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐧 ($𝟏𝟗.𝟗𝟎), but it’s a unique combi that works imo. It features a suuuuper thick spicy miso broth, accented by a citrus-y tang of yuzu. Altho the chashu collar here was pretty tough…

Compared to their ramen, the side dishes are far more average. Tried the Takoyaki during my prev visit, and the Wasabi Mayo Gyoza on this one… can’t say I’d strongly recommend either.

[invited tasting] Thanks @kanadaya.sg for the invite!

🏷 #EEBpromenade #EEBjapanese

All the rave right now is @46mittsu’s 𝐁.𝐄.𝐂. ($𝟏𝟐), understandably so straight from a visual standpoint. Look at that gorgeous ultra creamy scrambled egg~ <3. The cHUnks of thick cut bacon were honestly quite a mouthful, but added a nice savoury, salty contrast to the profuse creamy elements of this sando (e.g. the habanero gribiche sauce). Only thing I’d complain about… the bread here really wasn’t doing much for me 🤷🏻‍♀️

Or perhaps you’ll prefer the stronger flavours of the 𝐁𝐞𝐞𝐟 𝐒𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐨 ($𝟏𝟒), as did I. Well smoked beef brisket with a much needed incorporation of jumbo pickles and ratatouille to cut through the heaviness.

Side note: you’ll probably needa be up for a slight hike getting here from the MRT… also they share a space with @kura.singapore & @goodbeersg!

🏷 #EEBfortcanning
location: The Herencia at 46/58 Kim Yam Road

description:
The cream puff hype has definitely died down, but if there’s still one you must try, it’s @pantler’s. 

Their 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐮𝐱 𝐀 𝐋𝐚 𝐂𝐫è𝐦𝐞 ($𝟓.𝟓𝟎) features thiccc af custard cream that’s truly the embodiment of the word “luscious”, encased in a lightly crisp craquelin choux. Also some bits of nougatine somewhere in the mix! My only regret was not bringing a box of these back home…

🏷 #EEBtiongbahru #EEBdessert #EEBcafe

Was finally able to catch @betweenbunssg at their collab with @maxi.coffeebar last weekend~

Based off what seemed to be in everyone else’s hands at the Maxi festival, we ordered the 𝐏𝐡𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐲 𝐂𝐡𝐞𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐚𝐤 ($𝟏𝟖) from their lineup of 3. A truly hunky number with an abundance of beef slices that were a struggle to keep neatly between buns — far from a complaint. Loved the touches of spice as well, a very solid cheesesteak. 

Sure I only have one item to judge Between Buns on, but it’s enough for me to say I’m definitely looking to catch them again at a future pop-up~

ANDDD since we’re here… I’ll also mention the coffees at @maxi.coffeebar that were SO GOOD. I hate spending cafe coffee prices on coffee but I had no regrets for the The Dirty ($7.50), a delicious concoction with seven spice chai, oat milk and cold brew. Their popular Iced Cereal Milk Latte ($7.50) is also worth a shot.

🏷 #EEBtelokayer

When yogurt a balanced combo of refreshing tea blend and fresh fruit yogurt to fuel your day!🥤😉
Look forward to handcrafted yogurt 
smoothies made with milk, whole grains (ex. purple rice), and fresh fruits for a nourishing treat. Our go-to are the fresh fruit yogurt series. Enjoy this smooth and creamy combination with the perfect amount of tartness, paired with a range of fruits from strawberry, dragonfruit, to blueberries/pineapple, and our top pick - mangoes. 🥭
ℹ️ Enjoy a 1-for-1 from March 5-6 at their City Square Mall location in celebration of the grand opening of their third outlet in Singapore.

description:
A soup-er day begins with a hearty bowl of goodness! 😌🍜
We’ve always loved the focus on balance in Vietnamese cuisine. From the sour, sweet, and salty notes to the textural components, this noodle soup has it all - bún riêu! Our version started with a pork bone base infused with tomatoes and shrimp. The addition of tofu puffs and the “riêu” (tender pork and seafood meatballs) soak up the flavourful broth. Ladle all over a bed of rice noodles and enjoy with fresh herbs/vegetables! 🍅🍃

#tastebytes #vietnamesefood #vietnamesecuisine #bunrieu #noodlesoup

A claw-some feast with a host of delights! 🦀
From the classic chilli crab to creamy butter crab, pairing them with fried mantou is a must to mop up the savoury sauces. But the table favourite was definitely the claypot crab bee hoon soup! It’s a must try to enjoy a harmonious combination of sweet crab flavours and thick rice noodles in a complex, milky broth.

Living the sweet life! 😌☕️
Savour the richness of this signature dessert that is layered with Bailey’s/St-Rémy French brandy/espresso soaked ladyfingers, and a thick mascarpone cream filling. Dusted with Valrhona cocoa to finish, containing no raw eggs, and weighing in at a solid 650g, this is perfect for 4-6 pax to enjoy (if you can resist not polishing it off fully yourself 😜)!
💭 Would you opt for the classic tiramisu or with a booze boost (+39.5% more Baileys + 65% more Brandy)?

We’re forever on a noodle diet! 🍜😋
Although known for their soup noodles and bursting meatballs, our top pick would be the Hakka sauce handmade noodles. The springy and pork lard-laden noodles are generously topped with an array of components. From minced pork, ikan bilis (fried anchovies), crispy lard, shredded wood ear mushrooms, and shallots, to cilantro, spring onions, and century eggs for a touch of creaminess, this savoury and textural combination  definitely makes for a moreish dish.

After all the festive feasting in the past few months, I think it’s time for me to lose some calories.🤫
•
Recently, I’ve started to consume @dokijuice’s LEAN UP Calorie-Burning Juice, which is supposed to help to promote the release of free fatty acids in our cells using Lipid Metabolism Technology™. 
•
I’m usually pretty apprehensive about consuming this type of product, but after learning that they’ve done clinical tests in medical institutions in France, Korea, and Spain, it convinced me to try. 
•
LEAN UP uses a clinically proven formula that relies on bioactive polyphenols from Mediterranean Citrus and Brazilian Guarana to enhance the body’s metabolic rate. So far, four studies with more than 250 subjects conducted prove the efficacy of this formula, with results from subjects showing up to -5.4kg in body weight loss after 12 weeks.
•
The way to prepare it is easy: squeeze the fruit puree into a glass, add cold or temperature water, that’s it! It’s advised to drink this once per day, 30 min before a meal.👌Each box contains 4 servings.
•
There are 4 flavours available; Calamansi, Yuzu, Cranberry, and Raspberry. They actually taste pretty ok, just like drinking fruits puree. There’s nothing artificial in the taste.😋
•
•

description:
@Chatterboxsg, the iconic restaurant that has been around for 51 years, will be reopening in @hiltonsingaporeorchard on 14 March! Popular among locals and tourists alike, now they sport a chic interior and a bar.🥳 Swipe to see a sneak peek of it!
•
Chatterbox is mostly well known for their signature chicken rice, which I’ll talk about in another post. However, I want to feature one of my favorites of that night, the Lobster Laksa. The broth was thicker and robust, simmered in prawn stock. Each bowl comes with a whole Boston lobster claw. If you like your laksa very lemak, like me, you’ll love this!🥰
•
Another dish I liked was the Mackerel & Crab Otah-Otah. This otah was made with fresh mackerel fish paste and snow crab meat. I also enjoyed the Chatterbox Punch, which was a mix of 21-days vanilla, cinnamon, lemon, banana-infused gin served with house tonic. Very easy to drink!🍸
•
You can start to make a reservation via the link in @chatterboxsg’s profile.

For the starters, choose between a Fullerton Cobb Salad, Singapore Satay, or Cream of Mushroom. 
•
As for the mains, there are Pan-roasted Sea Bass, Bordelaise Beef Cheeks, Fullerton’s Hainanese Chicken Rice, and Wok-fried OmniMeat (vegetarian). I had the tender beef cheeks, and the seabass, which was drizzled with truffle celeriac mousseline.

Ended my meal on a sweet note! Featured here was the Chocolate Hazelnut Royaltine with red berries compote, which was infused with Nespresso.
•
This restaurant has an alfresco area overlooking the Singapore river, so it makes for a nice date night!

Like seriously the bestest Nasi Padang I have ever eaten. Pricier than usual but so totally worth it. The spices were cleverly tweaked to add dimensions to each dish. Even the sambal egg tasted different from the usual.

The chinchalok was already amazing by itself and the pairing with the roast pork just totally knocked it out da roof.

Warning: Lots of chilli padi here and spiciness is high. Not for those inclined to heartburn. It made my tummy go on fire but was totally worth it imo 😋

Wanted to post something else originally,  but thought this would make a happier post. 

The world is filled with depressing news and I often feel an immense sense of helplessness at not being able to do anything.

The least we can do however is to appreciate life and the simple gifts we take for granted. Having a roof over our heads, not worrying about our next meal, being secure in the predictability of the next day. Don't get me wrong. I'm not saying it's not ok to feel down. What I wrote is a reminder for myself too.

Praying for peace in our homes, in our countries and in our hearts. 

May this series on Mirri bring some cheer to you  as much as it does to me. Please don't get a bird to cheer yourself up though. It's a lot of work and her screaming drives me nuts.

Yam paste (orh nee) freshly made from scratch and fragrant walnut milk that's heartwarming yet not too sweet. 

In all honesty,  I think I'll replace my lecafe beancurd tarts with the latter. This has more fragrance and taste, though still being extremely light and refreshing. 

Pity I didn't have an oven to heat up my orh nee tart, which transforms to lava form or so I heard. 

The prices are REALLY great value taking into account that both the crust and the fillings are homemade. 

Walnut milk tarts, 4 for $9.60
Mini Orh Nee tarts, 6 for $8.40

Whether you're into tarts,  an orh nee fan, or simply looking for new desserts to try, I'd recommend you try @tartzy_tarts offerings!

Almost forgot to post this but the recent flood of yusheng posts reminded me of this deal. 

At only $12, the salmon don is a really yummy, enjoyable treat. Featuring a mix of salmon sashimi, aburi salmon belly, cubed spicy salmon, mentaiko seared salmon sashimi and ikura over Tanuki Raw's signature  mixed rice, I can't think of anywhere else that can give you this kind of value. 

The availability of outdoor seating gives me extra motivation to patronise this outlet because ya know, young kids and #staysafe.

A few things to note though. 
- This is a lunch deal avail on Mon - Thurs 1130am - 3pm. Call to cnfm and also do make reservations to avoid disappointment. 
- the Chirashi featured here is NOT under the lunch special so it's not in the same price range
- the serving is small so have a heavy breakfast  if you're planning on keeping to a tight budget

📍burnt cones @ sunset way

finally visited this super highly raved ice cream shop n their ice cream def didn’t disappoint🤩

black sesame ($5)
🐷🐷🐷🐷.2/5🐷
loved the strong nuttiness from the black sesame that was so fragrant and pronounced😍 it wasn’t too sweet and was rich and soso creamy😋

scamorza ($5)
🐷🐷🐷🐷.5/5🐷
wasn’t expecting this flavor to scream SAVORY CHEESE but it rlly did!!🤩 i was pleasantly surprised by this flavor, as the savory smoked italian cheese was actually so pronounced but went very well in ice cream form😍 it was a perfect balance of sweet and salty and was also so creamy yet light at the same time, pairing v well w the waffles😋

plain buttermilk waffles ($6)
🐷🐷🐷.3:5🐷
the waffles, unfortunately, was a little of a letdown🥺 while it was crispy on the outside, i found it a little too cakey for my liking, and would’ve preferred a fluffier, lighter texture to it😰

on the whole, am really q impressed by the ice cream quality and unique flavors🤩 redeemed by burpple deal for the one for one premium flavor ice cream which was 10/10 WORTH💯 would def b bk to try their other ice cream flavors!! which would you recommend?🤩

📍Luke’s Lobster @ Great world city 

been hearing mixed reviews of luke’s lobster but decided to give it a try anyways to decide for myself whether it was worth the hype👀

lobster roll ($25)
🐷🐷.9/5🐷
this lobster roll came with a nicely toasted brioche bun that was crusty and buttery, but what fell short of expectations was the lobster for me😢 while the lobster chunks look fat and juicy, i didn’t think it was the freshest as my throat started to itch a little after (which normally happens to me if the seafood isn’t fresh🥺) the lemon butter seasoning used here did not exactly enhance the flavors but was rather subtle… 

Luke’s Trio ($33.50)
🐷🐷🐷.1/5🐷
this came with half a lobster roll, half a crab roll and half a shrimp roll, the perfect sampler to try out all their rolls🤩 one thing good is that the rolls are generously stuffed w seafood, ensuring seafood in every mouth👍🏻

curly fries 
🐷🐷🐷.5/5🐷
the curly fries were an add on to the complete the meal, and i did enjoy the crispy fries that was paired w a side of curry aioli😋

on the whole, there are def better lobster rolls out there imo so let me know where are your go to places for good lobster rolls!!🤩
.

📍tanuki raw @ national design centre 

checked out the tanuki raw at their bugis outlet, and was pleasantly surprised by the diff variety of food in their menu here🤩

NDC truffle yakiniku 
🐷🐷🐷.9/5🐷
rlly cant go wrong w their well known rice bowls ig!! this was served w a p generous portion of us black angus short rib that was nice and tender, an onsen egg and drizzled w truffle soy sauce atop a bed of their signature rice😋especially enjoyed their signature rice which was a blend of mixed sushi rice with chopped pickles, furikake and seasoned vinegar🤤

yuzu miso salmon 
served w three slabs of grilled salmon filet marinated in their house blend yuzu miso, together w an onsen egg over a bed of steamed rice topped w furikake and tare👍🏻 salmon was nicely grilled with its meat still soft and tender😋

impossible chili fries 
🐷🐷.9/5🐷
didn’t exactly enjoy this that much unfortunately🥺 a generous portion of crispy shoestring fries topped w house made impossible meat, toban chili, creamy sesame dressing w chives n kombu. the chili and sesame dressing was a lil too overpowering for my liking, making it a lil too jelat😢

flat earth burger 
this was essentially a cheese burger, between two slices of toasty signature bread👍🏻 was surprised that they sell sandwiches at this outlet as i’ve nvr seen them in any of their other outlets🤩

surf and turf 
this sandwich came with half of it with a truffle roast beef melt, and the other half with fresh snow crab and avocados, having the best of both worlds😍

on the whole, a p decent visit to tanuki w a nice ambience here and v good service!!👍🏻 just some hits and misses w the food quality but still not too bad nonetheless😋
.

📍rise @ marina bay sands 

made a visit here to celebrate xmas and it def was a 💯meal here indeed!! we got the 6 course menu at $138++ per pax (comes w a complimentary glass of champagne) but it def was worth every dollar!!😋😋

seafood on ice 
🐷🐷🐷🐷.4/5🐷
just look at all that fresh seafood😍 each platter serves 2 which came w a whole crab, freshly shucked live oysters, tiger prawns, scallops, clams and mussels🤩 seafood was v fresh n loved the generous portions😋

roasted pumpkin soup 
🐷🐷🐷.8/5🐷
creamy and naturally sweetened with a slight nutty fragrance from the pumpkin!!😋 topped with pumpkin seeds for the added crunch🤤

baked maine lobster thermidor
🐷🐷🐷🐷.4/5🐷
this was soso satisfying too😋 only complain was that i’d wished for more🤤 the lobster was baked to perfection, topped with a layer of golden cheese😍

kurobuta pork filet rossini 
🐷🐷🐷🐷/5🐷
thin slices of kurobuta pork, topped w a thicc cut of fatty foie gras that was pan seared to give a nice outer crust😋

cod fish
🐷🐷🐷🐷.2/5🐷
this was an alternative to the lobster thermidor and rlly loved how well cooked this fish was, with a crisp exterior yet retaining its soft and tender flesh🤩 

US grain-fed beef wellington
🐷🐷🐷🐷.5/5🐷
this has got to be one of my favs of the nite🤩 i rlly loved how tender the beef was, cooked to a perfect medium, wrapped with a layer of mushroom duxelles and parma ham strips, followed by an outer layer of puff pastry😋 while the bottom of the puff pastry got slightly soggy, it was compensated for by the amazing flavors of the beef and mushrooms, and the crispy puff pastry stick on the side😍

roast turkey roulade 
🐷🐷🐷.7/5🐷
what’s xmas without turkey?🤩 turkey was tender, and it sat on a bed of smooth and creamy truffle mash potatoes😍

christmas desserts 
🐷🐷🐷🐷.5/5🐷
another shoutout to their desserts😍 i LOVED their raspberry almond log cake which came w a crispy biscuit base, mousse cake and a raspberry insert🤤 the flavors complemented each other so well and this was so light and easy to eat i finished it although i was alr so full😅 the chocolate peanut pie was rlly good too!!😋 rlly cant go wrong w a peanut and choc combi🤩 tbc in comments

📍vatos urban tacos @ south beach 

been hearing sm abt this place that i had to visit them during my staycay at jw marriott😋

bacon and blue cheese guacamole ($15)
🐷🐷🐷.9/5🐷
this came with nachos and a side of crispy bacon bits mixed into a fresh avocado guac, topped with blue cheese and candied walnuts😍 rlly love the refreshing tomatoes that cut thru the heavier cheese and bacon elements, with a nice crunch and sweetness from the candied walnuts!😋 the blue cheese might b a lil strong for some so beware if you’re not a fan of blue cheese😳

kimchi carnitas fries ($19)
🐷🐷🐷🐷.3/5🐷
while on the pricier side, this bowl of fries was LOADED with tender braised pork carnitas, sautéed kimchi, cheese, vatos hot sauce and a cilantro lime dressing for the extra acidity to cut the heaviness of this dish🤤 fries remained crispy and the toppings rlly complemented each other v well😋

grilled chicken quesadillas ($18)
🐷🐷🐷.9/5🐷
the quesadillas here came with a grilled monetary jack and cheddar cheese crust over their flour tortilla stuffed with grilled chicken and mozzarella cheese🤤 the cheese crust gave it an extra cronch but cuz of the cheese, it was slightly on the oily side. nonetheless, still a p decent quesadillas!!🤩

galbi short rib tacos (3 for $23)
🐷🐷🐷.6/5🐷
the short rib was tender and well marinated, with a korean twist, and topped with an asian slaw😋 however, i found the corn tortillas a lil too floury and had a p strong taste that overpowered the fillings🥺

chinichurri prawn tacos (2 for $14)

korean po’ boy burrito bowl ($22)
🐷🐷🐷🐷/5🐷
this came with galbi short rib and pork belly sitting atop a base of mexican rice, black beans, cheese, sautéed kimchi, sour cream, ssamjang aioli, asian slaw, pico de gallo and sriracha mayo🤩 every element was v well executed and complemented each other v well!! the meats were flavorful and tender, loving this burrito bowl with a korean twist🤩

OG Margarita ($16)
🐷🐷🐷🐷/5🐷

on the whole, a p nice place for korean influenced mexican food, with p nice ambience and good service!!👍🏻 while on the pricier side, they are onl burpple with 15% off total bill!! so go make use of ur burpple deals💯

Oggi voglio parlarvi di un piatto a cui sono molto legata perché racconta molto delle mia famiglia: la Lasagna ai carciofi !

Mia mamma è molto brava in cucina ed è un perfetto connubio di cucina napoletana (che viene dalla sua famiglia di origine) e di cucina abruzzese (che le è stata trasmessa dai miei nonni paterni).

Se considerate che è insieme a mio padre da quando aveva 14 anni potete immaginare che in lei vivono entrambe le tradizioni.

 
La cosa però piu bella non è il fatto che in cucina sia bravissima ma il fatto che lei attraverso la cucina riesca a trasferire tutto l’amore che ha…ed è tanto…vi assicuro!

Lei è una delle persone più accoglienti che io conosca e, insieme a mio padre, riescono ad essere i perfetti padroni di casa anche se passi per caso senza esserti annunciato!

Immaginatevi quindi durante le feste!!!! Le tradizioni per noi sono sempre state qualcosa di molto importante e, anche oggi, che ci apprestiamo a trascorrere la Pasqua separati; ognuno di noi ripeterà quelle tradizioni a casa propria!

Sapete che io amo il Natale…sono riuscita a sentirne il calore anche quest’anno …nonostante tutto!

Eppure se penso alla Pasqua mi vengono in mente tantissimi ricordi!

Da piccoli trascorrevamo la Pasqua in Abruzzo nella casa dei nonni!! è una casa grande con un’enorme cantina adibita a taverna!! ci incontravamo con tutti i cugini ed era una festa! Mia mamma e le miei zie si organizzavano e non mancava mail il casatiello, i salumi e la ricotta salata! Mio nonno faceva le pastiere e comprava le fave e, per il giorno di Pasqua, gli uomini andavano dal macellaio del paese a comprare l’agnello da fare alla brace!!! Erano tre giorni meravigliosi in cui si respirava allegria e affetto. Sarà per questo che il cibo che si preparava in quest’occasione per me, ancora oggi, è associato a dei meravigliosi ricordi!

Il primo piatto era quasi sempre la lasagna ai carciofi!!! da allora non è mai mancata sulla tavola di Pasqua e ho iniziato a prepararla anche io a casa mia!!!!
🔗LINK IN BIO🔗

Durante gli studi ho lavorato per anni come animatrice per bambini..specializzata nella fascia di età dai 3 ai 7 anni…facevo la burattinaia, avete presente quella che dà voce alla marionette!?!? 
la prima volta che la mia amica Letizia mi ha buttato dentro un teatrino mettendomi in mano una marionetta a forma di delfino e una di pecora, non sono riuscita neanche a parlare…le marionette tremavano e io non sapevo cosa dire…per fortuna tra le labbra del delfino c’era un sonaglino e per i primi dieci minuti sono riuscita solo ad agitare le due marionette come se fossero impossessate dal diavolo e schiacciare le labbra del delfino per fargli emettere quel suono..
.
poi, ad un certo punto, si è alzato un bambino dal pubblico e ha detto “signora pecora, tu posso raccontare una cosa!?! oggi a pranzo mamma ha fatto pasta e piselli e io non la volevo..allora lei mi ha detto che dovevo mangiarla per venire alla festa e io l’ho mangiata ma…HO GOMITATO TUTTO”…
…😅😅😅😅…come facevo a non rispondergli!?!! da lì ho iniziato la mia carriera di voci paperiniche..in falsetto…e ho iniziato a divertirmi un mondo!!!!
.
i teatrini sono stati tanti..le meravigliose conversazioni tra i bambini e le mie marionette si sono susseguite per anni e le palline di danubio mangiate non riesco neanche a contarle!!!
.
sarà per questo che preparare il Danubio mi strappa sempre un sorriso…LINK IN BIO❤️

Lo sapete che non amo i dolci ma c’è qualcosa di dolce per la quale impazzisco letteralmente: la Crostata crema e marmellata!!!

C’è qualcosa nella pasta frolla che mi ipnotizza; sin dalla preparazione, per la sua consistenza, per il suo profumo e per la consistenza. Se ci aggiungete anche la crema pasticciera che è la MIA crema, quella per la quale interrompo pure la dieta…è allora avrete scoperto il mio dolce preferito in assoluto.
 
La Crostata crema e marmellata mi ricorda una persona molto speciale, la cui dolcezza e delicatezza la rendevano una delle persone alle quali quando penso mi viene sempre da sorridere. Ho scoperto questa crostata molti anni fa e, nonostante a detta di tutti la mia sia molto buona, ho un ricordo del sapore della sua crostata che non riesco a dimenticare.

Negli anni, ogni volta che devo preparare un dolce per coccolarmi preparo questa crostata; seconda solo alla Torta con le tre erre della Nonna Elena che pure vi consiglio se amate la ricotta e il marsala (la trovate sul blog❤️)

La Crostata crema e marmellata è un dolce semplice, nessuna crema particolare, nessuna marmellata ricercata…si prepara con la marmellata che avete in casa, quella del vostro gusto preferito. Unico suggerimento che vi do è quello di farla alta perchè quando date il morso è un’altra cosa. Io utilizzo una tortiera di diametro minore per ottenere una crostata più alta.

Vi lascio alla ricetta!!!! Fatemi sapere!!! 🍰link in bio🍰

Marzo❤️❤️❤️
.
I 400 giorni di gennaio e febbraio sono finalmente passati e oggi inauguriamo il periodo che amo di più… ❤️❤️❤️
.
Anche se le temperature non lo sono ancora, io sento nell’aria già la primavera…la stagione che adoro, proprio come questo piatto: Casarecce carciofi, caciocavallo e guanciale!
.
Per me i carciofi fanno primavera. Li associo da sempre alla Pasqua, a quando trascorrevamo le feste in Abruzzo con i nonni e non mancava mai la mammarella. Mio nonno le portava da Napoli e così, sulla nostra tavola di Pasqua, c’erano sia le specialità campane che quelle abruzzesi; oltre ad esserci tutta la famiglia riunita…cosa che ormai succede sempre più raramente😞😞
 .
Come sapete adoro cucinare la pasta. Mi metto in cucina e creo…sminuzzo, manteco, emulsiono e mi rilasso. Di recente ho avuto la fortuna di collaborare con il Caseificio Lasparra, artigiani del gusto da tre generazioni, e ho provato alcuni dei loro prodotti.
.
Oggi vi propongo le Casarecce carciofi, caciocavallo e guanciale.
.
In questo piatto ci sono i miei ingredienti, quelli che non mi stancherei mai di mangiare: i Carciofi, il guanciale e il Caciocavallo. Il Caciocavallo, mamma che bontà. Ho sempre avuto una passione per i latticini, siano essi freschi o stagionati. Quando ho assaggiato questo Caciocavallo ho avuto un colpo di fulmine…ahaahahah…ed è successo anche ai miei genitori e a mio marito che lo hanno provato. Tant’è che sono riuscita a preparare solo questa ricetta sul blog perchè il caro Caciocavallo ha avuto vita molto breve nel mio frigo. 🙂
.
vi lascio il link alla ricetta in bio❤️❤️❤️

Buon lunedì a tutti!!!!! come è andato il weekend dì Carnevale??? quanti chili avete messo questo weekend??? io stimo di averne preso uno e mezzo circa🤪😅🤪….eh si perché, oltre agli gnocchi alla sorrentina, mi sono particolarmente dedicata alle chiacchiere e sanguinaccio…però ieri sera poi non ho cenato 😅😅😅😅
.
Oggi quindi mi preparo un contorno light ottimo per depurarmi, ricco di vitamine e anche saporito: i finocchi gratinati in forno!
.
Con il finocchio ho un rapporto di odio e amore. Non riesco proprio a mangiarlo crudo come consigliano tutte le nutrizioniste quando tu vorresti la merendina dolce e loro invece continuano a dire “Taglia le fettine di finocchio e tienile nell’acqua in una ciotola così quando ti viene fame lo mangi e non ti lasci tentare”…no quello proprio non riesco a farlo ma lo adoro cotto. Mi piace moltissimo gratinato con la besciamella sempre in forno e ultimamente ho assaggiato un’insalata con i Finocchi in un ristorante che rifarò a breve perchè me ne sono innamorata!!!
.

[Invited] @amiaddicted.sg is a newly-opened korean vegetarian cafe cum pottery studio 🌱 located at @capitolsingapore , just a short walk from City Hall MRT. I tried their Grilled Cheese Kimchi Sandwich 🧀 ($16) and Sweet Potato Latte 🍠 ($7). The latter was a bit powdery towards the end but the former was quite a delightful eat! 😋 A substantial amount of flavourful kimchi (on the mild spice side 🌶), vegan cheese tucked between two slices of sourdough bread which was perfectly toasted 🤩 It also came with a garden salad 🥗, hiding behind 😜 Was pleasantly surprised by the crunch of the toast, followed by the softer interior side of the bread 🍞. It had quite a good texture to it 👌👌 
—
👩‍🎨 If you’re feeling artsy-fartsy, you can also go for one of their pottery classes. Standard class starts at $80/pax, a quick wheel trial class is at $50/pax while a beginner class for 5 lessons goes for $360/pax!

Matcha cream mochi and matcha - the sweet mochi is topped with light taste of tea. Still prefer to drink freshly whisked matcha full of matcha flavour 💚🍵💚 finally finished all the matcha powder from @morihan_official

Foie gras mousse in homemade cookie topped with seasonal setoka orange. The taste of all the ingredients blended very well together and it was very tasty although it is such a small bite. On the right is deep fried smelt fish with wasabi mayonnaise topped with shredded seaweed powder. The taste is unique is good and I love it. The last one is slow cooked Sakoshi Bay Oyster coated with oyster juice gelatin topped with champagne vinegar foam. Sounds complex but so fresh and delicious 😋👍🏻👍🏻

Pistachio financier from @cafedemusesg with oolong tea - thought it was mini matcha pound cake at the first look but turned out to be pistachio flavour.. a nice little snack to pair with oolong tea 😋💚😋💕🌺💕

Kegani - seasonal hairy crab meat with cauliflower puree, ratatouille accompanied with tomato consommé jelly topped with bafun uni. A delicious fusion using premium ingredients sourced from Japan and France. This amazing dish is created by a Japanese chef trained in France and had worked in Michelin star restaurant and he is only 29 years old! This is part of the winter season Japanese-French kaiseki menu and the most suitable word to describe this dish is Heavenly!

Matcha Azuki tart by @tartebycherylkoh and genmaicha by @nakamura_tokichi_official - a tart with a decent taste of matcha but I will prefer higher quality matcha powder to be used.. my genmaicha from reputable @nakamura_tokichi_official taste much better than it..

在蘿蔓上放洋蔥炒蘑菇、
然後加上起士、番茄醬、
最後鋪上半熟蛋、灑一點碎堅果

這個做法來自以前去北歐自助旅行
大家到超市採買食材自己做早餐
那時候的我、完全不會料理
朋友炒了洋蔥、蘑菇、蛋放到生菜上
還擺盤了花椰菜跟蕃茄、配上咖啡
那時候覺得好厲害、原來可以這樣做早餐

@winestone.sg in @mercurestevens is a culinary concept that combines a selection of wines and a Modern European menu. Executive Chef S. Punniammurti, has specially curated an innovative OH-MY-SHROOMS 4-Course Dinner menu surrounding 7 types of humble and nutrient-packed mushrooms sourced locally and overseas. This menu is available from now to 31 March
.
The dining experience begins with two appetisers, Warm and Cold. One can choose between the Tagliatelle with Spicy Chorizo Sausages and Mushrooms (Tagliatelle Pasta, Swiss Brown Mushrooms, sliced Chorizo Sausages) or Pesto Prawns with Maitake Mushrooms and Tomatoes (Prawns, Fresh Basil Herbs, Maitake Mushrooms, semi-dried Tomatoes, Rocket Leaves) for the former
.
For the latter, one can opt for the Terrific Green Synonyms (Mixed Salad, Prosciutto Ham, Pink Oyster Mushrooms, roasted Pine Nuts, White Balsamic Vinaigrette) or the Smoked Duck with Hon-Shimeji Mushrooms (Smoked Duck Breast, White and Brown Hon-Shimeji Mushrooms, Herbs Dressing)
.
The main selection features Scottish Salmon with Golden Mushrooms; tender salmon fillet marinated with lemon and thyme, served with Spinach Cream and sautéed Golden Mushrooms, Grilled Ribeye with Morel Mushrooms; a generous slab of ribeye with rosemary grilled to perfection and topped with creamy Morel Mushroom Sauce, as well as Seafood with White Hon-shimeiji Mushrooms; a seafood trove consisting of prawns, scallops, slipper lobsters and black mussels cooked with tomato basil and pesto, topped with sautéed White Hon-shimeji Mushrooms
.
Lastly, the meal is complete with their decadent desserts which you can select either the Truffle Mushroom Burnt Cheesecake or the Apple and Wild Mushrooms Tart
.
📣 Make your reservation at https://www.winestone.sg
.
🏢 30 Stevens Road 01-09 @mercurestevens Singapore 257840
.
🕚 Opening Hours: 
Monday Closed
Tuesday to Thursday, Sunday: 12.00pm to 10.00pm
Friday, Saturday: 12.00pm to 10.30pm
.
💲Cost: $78.00++
.
💌 Tks @winestone.sg @mercurestevens for having us!
.

description:
Take time to make your skin happy again ~~

WOOD-FIRE DINING EXPERIENCE
 
Visited a fancier restaurant for our anniversary, here’s what we had. 

•🍞Assorted breads with homemade seaweed butter; the breads were so soft! 🧈The butter so good it deserves a photo of its own.

•🦞Lobster Bao; like a mini lobster roll. Lobster chunks served on deep fried charcoal mantou. Yums!

•🦪Grilled Normandy Oyster with caviar & nage; not bad but not our favourite. And both of us had bits of shell in the broth as we slurped the oysters down.

•🐷Western Plains Pork; pork belly, pork neck, pork leg and pork fat. This was our favourite dish of the night! All the different cuts of meat were tender and flavourful while the deep fried pork fat adds a different texture to the dish.

•🐟Grilled Seabass; seemingly ordinary grilled fish but they’ve removed the bones of the fish and it’s then dry aged. You can taste the nice flavour of the fish without any fishiness.

•🥩Australian Wagyu Striploin; recommended medium rare. Look at the beauty, the marbling. It’s cooked by taking the beef on and off the heat several times so it’s cooked to perfection instead of the outsides being more cooked and insides extremely rare.

•🍡Matcha Mochi; Complimentary as we were celebrating our anniversary. Thank you Butchers Block!

Lovely food with friendly wait staff.

🌟🌟🌟🌟
💰💰💰💰💰

📍Butchers Block
328 North Bridge Road, Raffles Arcade 02-02 to 02-07
Singapore 188719

TAIWANESE FOOD
How can we not order the 3 bowls set when the eatery is named Eat 3 bowls?

What the 3 bowls consisted of:
•Braised Pork Rice
With a good mix of fatty bits, it gives the melt in your mouth feel. The rice had generous amounts of gravy too. Tasty.

•Shredded Chicken Rice
Shredded chicken topped with fried shallots atop a bowl of rice. I was pleasantly surprised that the rice was drenched in sauce. Not at all dry and so appetising. Comfort food.

•Oyster Pork Intestine Mee Suah
The Mee Suah broth was a bit on the watery side, not too starchy (I actually like it this way). The Mee Suah was firm and not too mushy. Served with braised pork intestines, a piece of plump oyster and a dollop of minced garlic. Delish.

Also added on sides of egg and braised cabbage 🤩

Our choice of drinks:
~Fresh Milk with Grass Jelly - check out the glass full of grass jelly! But would request for less sweet next round. Like that they serve with metal straw too.

~Iced Coffee - the coffee is in the form of a piece of ice shaped like a polar bear on ice. The coffee will melt into the milk to give you ice coffee. Cute!

Overall, enjoyed the food and will be back again. However, we over-ordered for 2 pax this round. Will order lesser next time!

📍Eat 3 Bowls
462 Crawford Lane
Singapore 190462

LUNA
Been on my to-try list for a while and was so thrilled when a friend gifted me these! The insides of the box was so pretty with blue Japanese waves pattern.

What I had:
•Wild Strawberry Earl Grey Tart 🤍
Earl grey infused cream; you can definitely taste the freshness of the cream, though I wished that the Earl Grey taste could be slightly stronger. There’s a strawberry filled sphere which bursts upon cutting into. 

•Matcha Opera 💚
Matcha everything put together; matcha chiffon sponge, ganache, mousse and topped with matcha powder. So creamy, so rich with slight bitterness from the matcha powder. 

•Luna 2.0 🤎
Chocolate mousse, hazelnut sponge, salted caramel dacquoise and coated with dark chocolate glaze. So decadent. 

Each one was so good, not too sweet, not overly rich. Definitely one of the best desserts I’ve had in a while.

🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟
💰💰💰

📍LUNA @luna.singapore 
53 Amoy Street

It’s important to start any meal with a massive charcuterie board. This way, your guests will be so full during the main course, they may or may, not notice the quality of the food. If I’m having an off day, or didn’t season something well, your truffle and aperol cheese filled bellies will know no better.

If you live in Toronto, run, don’t walk to the cheese boutique. Buy yourself the pecorino truffle cheese, and the aperol cheese. Pair with all the things and escape to mouth bliss. A vacation for one’s mouth, body, spirit and mind. You’re welcome. 

Anyway, come over. I’ll try to be quiet and let this masterpiece speak for itself (the cheese speaks to me. It will speak to you too. I promise). 

See you soon. 

Ps. I cannot express to you how much I love cheese boutique

They say - if you love something set it free. If it comes back, it’s yours. If doesn’t, it never was. 

Obviously this post isn’t writing itself and my food blog Instagram account didn’t call me in the night and ask me to get back together. This account didn’t send flowers or beg for forgiveness. This account did not take me on a date or lavish me with gifts. In fact, it just sat here, all knowing. Knowing that eventually I’d find my way back. Maybe I’m needy, maybe it’s the attention, maybe it’s love.

Nonetheless, here we are. Bestie, I know it’s been a while, but I’d love it if you’d come over for dinner! 

While dinner is not just this delicious bowl of rice (it sat on the table with sautéed kale, roasted cauliflower, roasted broc and flank steak), this rice is insane and I’m in love. Plus, I love side dishes. For me, side dishes are always the star of the show. Side dishes are life!

Did I get the inspiration from tik tock you wonder? Well, I’ll never tell. But if you can’t come over, try it yourself. 

Sautéed onions and garlic in butter. Add cup of rice and toast. Add two cups of stock, tumeric and pepper. I topped it with parsley (because I love parsley) and almonds for crunch. 

Anyway, come over, we can enjoy some tequila, I’ll talk your ear off, you’ll talk mine off. Maybe play a board game? Im just so happy we made up. 

See you soon!

Bestie! I haven’t been ignoring you, I promise! It’s just, I have quite literally been buried under 5 feet of snow (I use the word literally, literally. Not in a young, fun hip, elder millennial vernacular kind-of way. Literally as in we, me and the city of Toronto, have literally been buried under a snow storm that lasted about a month (2 days. But felt like a month). 

It seemed the snow made people go mad in the city. My beloved city of Toronto and its inhabitants appear to have many feelings about all the things.  What objectively could be seen as a sweet, cozy, Canadian winter event, turned people into maniacs. People fighting, falling on ice, reaching breaking points (and the odd keener cross-country skiing down the streets, props to them, love those hardcore humans). 

So, when the world gets chaotic and frantic, I want you to come over for dinner. The snow will continue to fall but I promise to provide you with a serene and peaceful experience. 

When you come over for dinner during an epic snow storm I’m going to make you @alisoneroman anchovy tomato paste pasta. Topped with a ton of parsley and sea salt. I’ll even make some garlic bread and if I’m feeling healthy, a salad (but only if I have some sorta green in the fridge, I’m certainly not going to the store in this weather). 

The pasta will make you feel warm and fuzzy inside and we can forget how crazy everything is outside. You, me, pasta and a glass of red natural wine. 

Anyway, come over. Let’s get cozy and full. Pass the wine…

I like to think of myself as someone who is into the classics. A refined palette with loyal taste and sophistication. Some examples of classics I enjoy range from classical gap sweat pants to classical Nike shoes with a classical hoodie. I’m not one for trends, usually. I like basics…I mean classics. 

Preamble aside, when you come over for Friday night dinner I may be feeling trendy. Today is that day. It’s trendy Friday. Some trends come and go (wide leg jeans for example. Can we just take a minute to thank the fashion overlords for bringing these back into style!). Bell bottoms? Juicy couture? Classics, trends, classics, trends, who cares. 

I will say that I hopped right on to this basque cheesecake trend. Mostly because I love cheesecake. While I hate baking and following rules in general, I appreciate the ritual associated with making a cheesecake (water bath, massage, high praise, buy it jewelry, call it by its nick name, tell it you love it, etc). The ritual sucks me right in. I like how fussy the cheesecake is. 

This basque cheesecake however is much more aligned to who I really am, deep down in my soul. It’s a bit burnt, rough around the edges, a little high maintenance, but overall generally easy and nice, but if you don’t pay enough attention, it will fall apart or get angry.  But it will likely make you happy or at least laugh. 

Anyway, come over and eat this non high maintenance, no fussy, kinda burnt cheesecake with me. 

#basque #basquecheesecake #cheesecake #cheesecakelove #baking #toronto #torontobaking #shabbat #shabbatshalom #fridaynightdinner #dessert #foodwriter #foodwriting #theloserfam #foodwriters #foodstylist #homebaker #creamcheese #saudade #bonappetit #torontolife #gap #classics #nikesoccer

Do you ever feel…spicy? Like it’s a Saturday night, you put on your hottest outfit and get ready for a night out with pals, spicy? The night is young spicy (and so are we in this fictional story). We pregame at someone’s house. You wear those shoes you saved up for months to buy. We go out into the world. We are all looking hot! Looking fierce! 

Tonight is all about the spice! Spice for life, spice for friendship and maybe some spicy chicken wings (those will likely make an appearance later in the evening, after some grown-up beverages and dancing). 

Well, when you come over for dinner on a cold January evening, don’t expect the spice. January is not about being spicy (at least not for me). January for me is about comfort food, good books, Epsom salts and hot baths. I swear, despite this, I promise I’m still cool. Cool is a state of mind…at least that’s what my friend tells me (you know who you are). No skinny jeans for me. Well, no jeans at all, not since March 2020. 

What I have made for you here is a reflection of the January low-key journey into ourselves. Let’s take a big sip of air, maybe a sip of natural wine and enjoy this thing I’ve made for you. It’s simple and tasty, just right for a non spicy January. 

Chicken is made in cast iron pan. Onions, green olives and crushed tomato. A little crushed red pepper, garlic and paprika. Green peas. Roasted broccoli and plain rice. The rice pairs nicely with the sauce from the chicken. 

Anyway, come over. Let’s talk about what books we are enjoying (I’m reading Circe) and discuss which sweat pants brand is our favourite!

Whatever you do, get the Tom Yum Omelette at @mreastkitchen in SF SoMa! 🍳 

Mr East Kitchen is southeast Asian-American fusion brunch, and they actually just revamped their entire menu this past week when I visited! They currently even have a Buy 3 Get 1 Free, which my friend used for some hash browns 😂

I came by for a late brunch (lunch?) with my friend on Saturday after visiting the SF Flower Mart nearby, and this was just SO AMAZING - the bacon on top of the Tom Yum Omelette was so so flavorful (even better than Millionaire’s Bacon!), and you open the omelette up to the Tom Yum shrimp and onions hiding underneath - I normally always have to add ketchup to my eggs, but this definitely didn’t need it! 

We started with the Fresh Rolls which were not bad! We then got the Omelette Fried Rice which also came with a Tom Yum omelette, and the fried rice was delicious! But honestly the Tom Yum Omelette dish, which came with a side of sweet + sour dressed salad and potatoes, was my favorite! Highly recommend visiting to see their new menu! They also came by with a complimentary taro dessert, which was super nice 🥰

📍 Mr East Kitchen @mreastkitchen
🏙 San Francisco, California

Music and dancing 💃🏻🎶 with delicious Pan-Latin tapas and entrées - I’m in 😮‍💨

We ordered a few drinks as well as the small Paella Marinera ($47), small Paella Cascal ($35.50), Eggplant Tian ($14), Potato Gratin ($11.50), and Wild Mushroom Empanadas ($16), along with chips with guac and salsa as appetizers. 

The seafood paella (Paella Marinera) was loaded to the max with clams, mussels, lobster, fresh shrimp, calamari, and octopus - it was one of my favorite dishes of the night! Viewer be warned that Cascal is known for their paellas, but they can be a bit pricy - each dish has a small and large version, and the small is large enough to share between two people! I also really loved their salsas and guac, and their eggplant tian was so pretty and yummy. Several vegetarian options here too!

📍 Cascal @cascal.restaurant 
🏙 Mountain View, California

While roast chicken is always a crowd pleaser, suppose to be simple and easy to cook - you will for sure agree that sometimes it’s intimidating to make one. You get either undercooked or overcooked meat that has completely dried out but it doesn’t have to be that way. ⁣Right?! 
⁣
How do you keep the meat moist and protect it from drying out? Sharing some secrets below ⁣
⁣
✔️ Season generously with freshly ground salt, pepper and other herbs and spices⁣
✔️ Brush with butter before roasting⁣
✔️ Stuff your chicken with veggies or roast them on the side like lemon, garlic, rosemary etc⁣
✔️ Roast between 350F to 450F. Cooking time depends on the size of your chicken. ⁣
⁣
It’s not hard after all, roast chicken is always the best go-to winner chicken dish! ⁣

East Coast Seafood Centre, JUMBO Seafood (Bedok) 🐟🦀

HAPPY LAO HU YEAR EVERYBODY!!! Jumbo has always been one of my family's favorite places to dine in, for special occasions like birthdays and also our yearly Chinese New Year Reunion Dinner. We got the 6 pax CNY Reunion set at $468++ even though we had only 4 people because my broskis and I are 2 pax each.

These were the things that were included in this CNY Reunion Set

1. Prosperity Salmon "Yu Sheng" 
2. Braised Seafood Soup with Cod Fish (PICTURE NOT FOUND!!)
3. Deshelled Prawns with Sesame Dressing and Almond Flakes
4. Live "Soon Hock" (Marble Goby) Steamed with Soy Sauce
5. 10-Head Abalone Braised with Shiitake Mushroom and "Fatt Choy"
6. Rice Steamed with Preserved Meat and Sakura Shrimp Wrapped in Lotus Leaf
7. Chilled Lime Jelly with Peach Resin and Aloe Vera (PICTURE NOT FOUND because they split the portions before I could bring out my camera!)

I think Jumbo still holds up to its name for being a really good seafood Chinese restaurant. The prawns and fish which I had that day were really fresh and the cooking method used to prepare them amplifies how fresh they really are. The only downside of this place is that their portions are not "JUMBO" ha ha and it is pretty pricey. eek (I love watching the ships just chilling in the sea from the restaurant though!!)

So Good Char Chan Teng (Upper Thomson) eesh/10 🥟☕️

“Char Chan Teng” and “Tea Restaurant” would be the first thing you think of when I say the word “DIM SUM”. These cantonese restaurants are actually pretty common all over Hong Kong. My dad wanted some Dim Sum on his birthday, so I suggested my family this place for brunch!!!!

I think most of the stuff that I got here was eehhhhhhs which was pretty dissapointing because we travelled across Singapore FOR DIS AND IVE HEARD SO MUCH ON DIS PLACE!! My personal few that I enjoyed admist the ocean of dishes would be their Rice Roll ($4.80), Crispy Condensed Milk Bun ($2.00) and their Crispy Prawn Dumpling ($3.30).

Pasta Bar (Outram Park) 7/10 🍝🤌🏼

AFTER A MONTH OF WAITING I HAVE MANAGED TO FINALLY EAT HERE!!! I was also super glad that they had allowed us to seat at the counter to get these naise shots!!

Crab Papperdelle 🦀🍝 $36++ 

The sauce was STUPEFACENTE!! (Which means amazing in Italian according to google) The sauce’s texture was able to hold onto the sauces of the pasta and so you you that reall guuud bite of both the pasta and the sauce at the same time. I really liked that the pasta had a couple slices of crab meat which was a really nice touch. I just felt that the pasta was wayyy toooo al dante for me🥲🥲

Fettucini Truffle 🧀🍝 $36++ 

I am super huge fan of super plain pastas, so I was a huge fan of this. The cheese and truffle were really just BAM BAM BAM like look at HAOW MUCH TRUFFLES WERE THERE!! Just that once again, the noodles were a little too al dante for me💀🙃 (Now I know what truffle ACTUALLY is like, it is actually quite bland and underwhelming HAHAHAH)

This place might not have your MOST WORTH IT PASTA but it is for sure the ONE OF THE BEST PLACE TO DINE IN!!!! (The aesthetics and all is a 🤌🏼mazing)

VivoCity, Gram Café & Pancakes (Harbourfront) 9.5/10 🥞🐝

On my quest to find the best pancakes in Singapore, ive finally decided to drop by the super famous GRAM CAFE AND PANCAKES.

This pancake the perfcect fine balance of an american pancake and a souffle pancake!!! Its firm yet fluffy texture makes it alot easier to whip the syrup, the butter and whip cream on it before throwing it into your mouth. Other than the fact that it has a pretty steep price of $21.42 and a waiting time of 30 minutes, I’ll say this was an 0mg (zero milli-GRAM ha ha ha) experience 🤯🤯

matcha raspberry chocolate cake for world book “dae”!
hope you get the reference ;)

stayed up till 3am to make and decorate this - i was happy with what i made, but i didn’t win the competition this was for. why should i let that affect me?

so… i know how some feel about frosting, but i myself and everyone around me thoroughly enjoyed this one! let me introduce you to ermine buttercream frosting - a old fashioned frosting traditionally used on red velvet cake!
it incorporates a roux which makes the frosting stable, thick and fluffy, without being too sweet as the sugar levels can easily be adjusted without jeopardising the texture! another bonus is it doesn’t use powdered sugar!

ingredients: 
45g plain flour
110g sugar (i used granulated sugar, as well as dark brown for flavour. don’t use too much if you’re using natural colouring)
250ml milk, warmed
225g unsalted butter 1 1/2 tsp vanilla extract Pinch of salt 
colouring - 1 tsp of matcha powder or 2 tbsp dried raspberry powder 

method:
stir the flour, sugar and colouring (if powdered) constantly over medium heat. 
Whisking constantly, slowly pour the milk in and ensure it's lump free. It will start to thicken as it gets hotter - stir constantly!

Cook until it becomes a thick paste. Thicker texture = thicker frosting texture (still fluffy and spreadable, but "sturdier" with sharper edges when piped) 
Transfer to a bowl and cover with cling wrap, pressing down onto the surface to prevent a skin from forming.
Cool completely (but not chilled - best at room temp)
Use an electric whisk or stand mixer to beat the butter (~3 mins) until smooth and becomes pale.  Add the thick roux gradually and mix briefly. Then add vanilla and salt (and liquid/gel colouring if using) and whip for 2 to 3 minutes until it holds peaks.

decorating the cake
Ensure your cake is completely cool. crumb coat by spreading a thin layer of frosting all over and chill. then, add more frosting around the whole cake and pipe details!

i really hope you give this a try and let me know how you like it! this is such an underrated frosting :)

Checked out the rather exotic Peruvian cuisine at Canchita, and was rather impressed with the starters and mains! Ft here is their dessert to finish :)

🌮🌮𝙏𝙧𝙚𝙨 𝙇𝙚𝙘𝙝𝙚𝙨 [$14]
A classic dessert, this Tres Leches features a really moist coconut cake, topped with shaved coconut flakes, light pastry cream and fresh strawberries. Surprisingly very light on the palate and refreshing to finish, not at all surfeiting or dense ☺️

📍CANCHITA Peruvian Cuisine [Part 2/2]
[#TxTxDempsey]
.
.
.
#TxTxDessert

Make plans for an incredible brunch fix this weekend at Canchita! My first time having Peruvian cuisine and I must say they really go big on strong flavours and sauces. Space is vibrant and fun, while service staff is attentive - definitely a place worth checking out ☺️

🌮🌮𝘼𝙧𝙧𝙤𝙯 𝙘𝙤𝙣 𝙈𝙖𝙧𝙞𝙨𝙘𝙤𝙨 [$34]
Langoustine, prawns, calamari and fish rice, Peruvian pancake chilli, tomatoes, crab butter, white wine // This was like a tomato base risotto with fresh seafood. Looks a little unassuming but the rice itself was actually packed with tons of flavour. I do wish for more seafood and rice though!!

🌮🌮𝙇𝙤𝙢𝙤 𝙎𝙖𝙡𝙩𝙖𝙙𝙤 [$42]
Peruvian Cantonese stir-fried wagyu beef tenderloin, tomatoes, onions, green peas, potato fries // I love how the beef was cut into thick chunks so you get that extra juiciness and satisfaction in each bite. The fries were also p bomb - thick cut, crispy and nicely seasoned. Portion was just a tad small!

🌮🌮🌮𝘾𝙚𝙫𝙞𝙘𝙝𝙚 𝙋𝙚𝙧𝙪 [$26]
The classic recipe market fish, white tiger’s milk, red onions, sweet potato, canchita // A signature in Peruvian cuisine, ceviches are appetizing starters to have and this one featured really fresh raw fish with a wonderful tangy zest from the onions. Must get!!

🌮🌮🌮𝘾𝙤𝙢𝙥𝙡𝙞𝙢𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙖𝙧𝙮 𝘽𝙧𝙚𝙖𝙙
Love how they served this nicely toasted bread drizzled with rich olive oil (I think?)! Could’ve get enough of it as I asked for seconds and thirds to dip into my ceviche too!

槟城竟然有那么好吃的台湾美食？😍

前几个星期在槟城点外卖的时候，无意间刷到这家餐厅。看了一下菜单，着实让我心动了呢！

这家餐厅的名字很可爱，就叫做叽叽鸡排。他们主打各种道地的台湾美食，例如，甘甜地瓜、卤肉饭、盐酥鸡、超大鸡排、芒果冰等等。据说，原料都是从台湾进口，非常厉害。

那么，我点了卤肉饭 (没拍到)、卤肉面、甜不辣、盐酥鸡和阿里山蜂蜜爱玉冰。这里面真的有好多想吃的，可惜吃不了那么多，所以决定下次再点好了。

卤肉饭很不错，鸡肉吃起来很香，而且很入味。但我个人觉得它和台湾的卤肉饭有些不一样。不同之处在于，它用了鸡肉，还有就是酱汁多了五香的味道，可以说是拥有自己的特色，值得一试。

炸酱面是用了卤肉饭的佐料，多了萝卜丝和黄瓜丝。面条煮得刚刚好，不会太软烂，搭配它的酱汁和鸡肉一起吃，口感变得特别棒。

另外，甜不辣和盐酥鸡都非常好吃。甜不辣炸得很酥脆，撒上辣椒粉，咸中带点辣，辣中带甜的感觉，吃了完全停下来。更别说盐酥鸡了，简直是绝绝子！有机会一定要试试，非常推荐！

最让我印象深刻的食物大概就是他们家的阿里山蜂蜜爱玉冰了！他们家的爱玉冰很好喝，不会太甜，很解暑，有了阿里山爱玉冻的加持，我原地直接给它满分，太爱了 ❤️

description:
我心中第一名的香蕉蛋糕 🍰

前几天和同事们一起去吃年前的团圆饭，感觉特别开心。过程中，大家也有互送礼物。可爱的同事们纷纷带了柑、年饼、纪念品等等。而我自己也提前订购了 @jytaste 的香蕉蛋糕送给他们。

为什么会选择 JY Taste 的香蕉蛋糕呢？我想，是因为他们家的香蕉蛋糕很适合同事们带回去和家人、朋友们一起分享。最大的重点是，它广受好评，是个非常不错的香蕉蛋糕！

那么，我看了大家的评论也跟着心动了，直接在 IG 找卖家下单！😄

JY Taste 把他们的招牌香蕉蛋糕烤得非常香，有着一股很浓郁的牛油香气，塑料袋似乎都遮挡不住它的香。这款香蕉蛋糕光用闻的都已经垂涎三尺了呢！

我迫不及待地把它切开来，还是觉得蛋糕很漂亮。一口吃下去，你可以明显地感觉到它和其他的香蕉蛋糕不一样，确实是真材实料。蛋糕很扎实，口感湿润、细腻，又带点香蕉的颗粒。甜度对我来说也是刚刚好，特别棒！

整体来说，蛋糕上的完整香蕉为它添加了不少分，吃了也不容易腻，再来搭配一杯热乎乎的咖啡，简直就是一种幸福！这绝对是早餐和下午茶必备的蛋糕！

据说，他们还有其他种类的蛋糕，例如萝卜蛋糕、红枣蛋糕等等。有机会我还会再回购哟！❤️

#bananacake #jytaste #penangfood #penangcake #teatime #bestcake #yummyyummy #taipingfoodie #homemadecake #igeats #igdaily #foodblogger #思仁手工坊

1.1 新年快乐！🎉

新的一年，祝大家健康、快乐、平安、幸福 ❤️

2022 年的第一天，我和家人们一起吃顿久违的韩国餐，幸福就是如此。

这家的韩式料理特别好吃，就开在太平的 Aeon 广场里。以前没有疫情的时候，总是和姐妹们在那里聚餐。环境舒适，食物也美味。

今天我点了三样食物，分别有炸鸡块便当、蜂蜜鸡块便当以及炸酱面。便当盒里除了米饭和鸡块之外，还附有粉条、泡菜和炸饺子。
不得不说，他们把鸡块处理得很好，口感酥脆，肉质也细嫩，不会太硬，搭配米饭吃，非常棒！

另外，炸饺子也很不错，甜甜咸咸很开胃，我很喜欢它的味道。粉条和泡菜就是中规中矩，还可以更好。

最后，就是我的最爱，炸酱面啦！如果你也爱吃炸酱面，推荐你点它。面条Q弹，有点像拉面的感觉。酱汁很浓郁，味道是甜的，带点微微的焦苦味。他们加了黄瓜丝、萝卜丁、洋葱和肉末做点缀，整体的味道变得更加丰富，越吃越上瘾。

2022 继续努力，努力变更好 🥰

description:
简单又丰盛的圣诞晚餐 🎄

祝大家圣诞节快乐，幸福快乐。

今天的你们吃大餐了吗？或者，你也和我一样，简单地在家吃一顿美味的家常料理呢？

我的晚餐呢，有辣椒板面、干咖喱炒猪肉，还有一些过年都会吃的菜肴，比如说，卤猪肉、炸肉卷、还有猪肚汤。对我来说，这些都是记忆中最深刻，最美好的味道。

好吧，偷偷告诉你们，这些菜肴都不是我自己做的喔，我只是负责加热而已啦！它们是来自 @ladybossfoodie 的速食料理包！你只需要开火煮水，把料理包放入大约10 至15分钟，就能变出一桌的过年大菜了！这简直是超级方便！🤩

至于味道呢，我个人觉得很满意，都处于水准之上，几乎不踩雷。辣椒板面是我心中的第一名，特别的地方就在于里面的辣椒虾米。Q弹的板面搭配猪油和独特的辣椒虾米，口感变得更好，不会太辣，也没有腥味，好吃！

另外，干咖喱炒猪肉和卤猪肉很下饭。酱汁很浓郁，香味十足。猪肉吃起来不会太硬，也不会有冷冻猪肉的感觉。简单来说，很入味！我自己在卤猪肉里加颗水煮蛋，瞬间让我想起了台湾卤肉饭，超棒！只不过，我个人觉得卤猪肉可以减少些油，效果会更好。

再来，炸肉卷是一道很惊艳的料理。薄薄的外皮裹着满满的五香味肉馅，同样的，肉质鲜嫩多汁，而且它的肉是一丝丝的，非常加分。通常在外面吃到的都是皮厚肉少的呢！

最后，猪肚汤的味道很不错，香浓可口。猪肚也很软嫩，配着干文阁辣椒酱一起吃，非常棒！

整体来说，他们家的速食料理包方便又美味，非常适合懒人、不爱煮饭、又或者是生活很忙碌的朋友！爱吃美食的朋友也可以试试看哟！❤️

简单又快乐的周末日常 👧

最近太平一直在下雨，天气也因此变得很凉快。这舒服的天气就一定要有美食啦！

上次吃了 DoubleTap 的鸡蛋三明治之后，觉得很好吃。所以呢，今天我打算再点他们家不同的三明治。

他们除了有鸡蛋三明治之外，还有肉松三明治、薯饼鸡蛋三明治、金枪鱼三明治、培根起司三明治等等。每一种的卖相感觉都很不错，实在是太难选了。

最后，我决定先选择里面其中一种三明治，也就是薯饼鸡蛋三明治。薯饼是这次的主角，一整块酥脆的薯饼加进松软的吐司里，搭配鸡蛋、番茄和生菜，一大口吃下去，特别满足。

我个人觉得这款三明治很不错，因为我很喜欢薯饼的味道，外酥里嫩。薯饼的焦香让整个三明治的口感更加分，吃起来不会很腻，也不会觉得太油，我反倒是觉得越来越好吃！

如果你和我一样也喜欢薯饼和鸡蛋的组合，一定要点它！😍

It’s GIVEAWAY TIME!!! 🤩🤩🤩

Now I know where to go if I’m looking for some Nyonya and local delights.. @yummy_times_unikomo!! 🥳

They have a takeaway store at 125 Toa Payoh Lor 1  # 01-533, but they also do delivery too! 👍🏻 And they feature “traditional delicacies that remind us of our ancestor who once created historical food”! ✨

Swipe left for my tasting experience! 💕

I tried their Nyonya Curry Ayam Bento with Butterfly Pea Rice, selection of Nyonya Kuehs, Rice Kueh, Soon Kueh Set, Yam Cake and Signature Chee Cheong Fun with Special Sauce! 😋

And guess what?! There was legit nothing I tried that I didn’t love! 😱 The curry in the Nyonya Curry Ayam Bento was full of flavour and spices and was super, super tasty! And the two green flowers (Cara Pandan Kueh) in the Bento had a chewy, mochi-like consistency in the centre which was pure heaven! I loved the balance of the Bento too, it was my idea of a perfect lunch indeed! 💯✅

I also loved their Nyonya Kuehs (I could peel those rainbow layers and demolish them all day, everyday 😛) and how their Signature Home Made Chilli went so well with their Teochew Kuehs! Their Signature Chee Cheong Fun with Special Sauce was also delightful! The sauce had a perfect balance of sweet, salty and sourness to it and went so well with the Cheong Fun! 😊

Seriously everything was so authentic and tasty! You’ll love their nostalgic treats! 😉

Visit them or order up via https://yummytimes.oddle.me/en_SG/ for a “yummy time” indeed! 😜

They offer island-wide delivery and are available on Grabfood, foodpanda, Deliveroo and Oddle (under Yummy Times)! Get $5 off using the code “YUMMYTIMES” (only for first time customers with min. spend of $50) and 15% off self pick up orders with no min. spend! Contact them at 8790 4044 for customized platters. 🙌🏻

AND THREE of YOU will WIN an assortment of Teochew and Nyonya Kuehs (10 handpicked in a box)!! 😱

Happy International Women’s Day! 🥳

Sorry for being so MIA lately, I’ve actually started a new job so I’ve been super busy with that! So it was actually perfect that I was able to relax at @coastessg on the weekend for a well deserved break! 😌

@coastessg is literally a restaurant situated along a golden stretch of Sentosa’s Siloso Beach, and boy is it a piece of paradise in Singapore! 🏖 It’s the perfect place to relax on the weekend with some delicious cocktails and hearty beach food! 🍹🍸 🥘 

Tuck into generous servings of Coastes mouthwatering burgers, pizzas, pastas and delicious fresh seafood, while you soak up some sun, sand and sea! ☀️ 🌊 Coastes is totally all you need for that idyllic island getaway! 🏝 

Swipe left to watch my experience there! 💕

My favourite dishes were definitely their Fish and Chips (they were so perfectly crispy and it’s legit soo nice to have fish and chips by the beach right?! 🥰) and Lemon Curd with Summer Berries (a sweet & sour treat of lightly torched smooth lemon curd on fresh mixed berries) which was the perfect sweet finish to a wonderful meal! 😋

But we also enjoyed their Smoked Salmon & Avocado on English Muffin (brunch item), Chilli Herb Butter & Garlic Prawns, and Garden Salad! 🦐🥗

And if you’re there, YOU HAVE TO GRAB A SINGAPORE SLING! It’s so nice and sweet and refreshing and trust me, you’ll be wanting another one once you taste it! 🍹 

So what are you waiting for? Check out www.coastes.com and @coastessg, and visit them soon to get that relaxing experience you know you deserve! 😊 They’re open Monday to Thursday 9am-9.30pm and Friday to Sunday 9am-10.30pm, and their brunch is available until 3pm! ✨

Check out these cute and pretty ‘pops’ I got from @yurinka.sg! 🤩

They make these popsicles fresh with Halal friendly ingredients! 💕 They’ve been featured on @halalfoodhunt already! 🙌🏻 And the pops are perfect for kids (because they’re so colourful and cute 😛) and will bring out the kid in anyone too! 🤣 

The popsicles comes in 8 exciting flavours: CocoRie (coconut milk, mango), AuroraMint (coconut milk, chocolate, mint), NuttyButter (coconut milk, peanut butter), YogiOrange (yoghurt, milk, orange), BerryVae (yoghurt, milk, mixed berries), PoppiNee (coconut milk, strawberry), Mudbank (coconut milk, cocoa, chocolate), and BaNella (banana, milk, Nutella)!! ✨

Seriously, all the flavours are slurpilicious!! 🤤 I tried and loved the AuroraMint (I’m a sucker for anything Mint Choc and this was pure bliss, milky and refreshing at the same time) and NuttyButter (omg the peanut butter jammed in the centre is decadent and indulgent and I loved the perfect savoury sweet combo it created), but the other flavours were soo good too! The yoghurt went so well with the fruity flavours!! You just have to try them all! 🥰✅💯

I also loved how if you’re a bit lactose intolerant like me, you also have the coconut milk options! 👍🏻 They’re a perfect pick-me-up after a long day in Singapore’s typical weather conditions too! 🤪☀️

Check out @yurinka.sg for more info and order some of these pops for yourself!! Trust me, you’ll regret it if you don’t!! My whole family loved them 😌 You can order up via https://yurinkasg.stashally.com/ or https://form.jotform.com/203170760128448 🥳

So I have to tell you about the AMAZING Panna Cotta I had from @rafrohmini!!! 😱😱

I was seriously blown away by how good it was! Not only is their packaging super cute, but I thought it’s so special that their Panna Cotta comes in the most awesome flavours and they even have a range of delectable sauces to pair with them! 🤩

Swipe left to watch my whole tasting experience! ✨

I absolutely loved all of the flavours I tried but my favourites would definitely have to be the Milk Tea and the Pandan paired with their Gula Melaka syrup on top!! The tea flavour in the Milk Tea was strong and fragrant and this made it super refreshing! And boy oh boy is Pandan and Gula Melaka a match made in heaven! 🤗 

You also have to try their Original flavour with their Blueberry Compote, the Milk Tea flavour with their Vanilla Latte sauce, and their Dark Chocolate flavour with their Raspberry Coulis! These combos are also to die for! 🤤🤤🔥

I would totally demolish their Panna Cottas again and again any day! I can’t get enough of that milky goodness and they were a total hit in my household! 🤭 

You have to try them for yourself! 😋 I love how they can also do a customised, smaller version for events and weddings! 🤓 So you can definitely order from them for your next event! 🙌🏻 They have self collection and delivery available. Simply DM them to preorder! 💕

@tigafolksnco is currently running a post CNY campaign this February with their all meat Ready to Eat Feast, and thanks to them, we had the best post CNY feast ever! 🥳 

@tigafolksnco is a food event company which allows you to order Ready to Eat Meat Feasts and Ready to Cook Feasts too! And they put a lot of love into their cooking! 🥰❤️

We tried some of their Signatures which you can get as part of their Ready to Eat Meat Feasts! Just watch my video to see everything we ate! 😋✨

My personal favourite would have to be their ANGUS BEEF SHORT RIBS which were rubbed and glazed, and cooked to perfection! They were super tender and super pleasing indeed! 🤤

We also enjoyed their BURNT BUTTER CARAMEL LAMB RIBS (I loved the sauce, it was finger licking good!), PENNE CREAM PASTA WITH WILD MUSHROOM, LINGUINE WITH CLAMS, GARLIC & CILATRO WHOLE ROASTED CHICKEN, PAN-SEARED HOKKAIDO SCALLOPS AND CONFIT PRAWN WITH TOMATO SALAD (my second favourite of the night, the prawns were perfection), and BAKED SALMON (so nicely seasoned!) ✅💯

You’ve got to try everything too! You can order a feast for yourself via https://tigafolks.bio.link/ 💕 They seriously make feasting so damn easy, all you have to do is order up and it comes delivered to your doorstep so that all you have to do is sit back, relax and enjoy the food! 😌 So what are you waiting for? Check out @tigafolksnco now! 🤓
