📍 𝘏𝘦𝘭𝘭𝘰 𝘈𝘳𝘪𝘨𝘢𝘵𝘰 ⁣
⁣
Have been seeing food from this cafe all over my ig so I was really excited to try their food 🤤⁣
⁣
I had their 𝐆𝐲𝐮 𝐒𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐨 ($𝟐𝟔) which was served with a thick slab of angus beef striploin sandwiched between two japanese milk bread. This was done medium rare and I wasn’t expecting much out of this because I prefer my beef done medium but damnnn this was really flavourful and juicy 🤯 The sweetened caramelised onions that came along with it added a nice touch to the overall flavour profile of the sando! Sandwiched between two butter toasted bread was warm, soft and pillowy…… LOVE THIS!! Though it did come with a hefty price tag, I do think this is worth a try at least once ☺️ ⁣
⁣
I also tried their 𝐓𝐨𝐦𝐲𝐮𝐦 𝐒𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐧 ($𝟏𝟖) which came with their chilled tomyum broth served in a bottle!! Somen was silky and smooth which went well with the generous amount of crab meat served (swipe for close ups) 😮‍💨 This was my first time trying cold somen which was really interesting though the flavour profile of the tomyum broth could definitely be better as I couldn’t really taste the tomyum flavour. ⁣
⁣
I went with their 𝐈𝐜𝐞𝐝 𝐃𝐢𝐫𝐭𝐲 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 (𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐜𝐨𝐟𝐟𝐞𝐞) ($𝟖) and my friend had their 𝐋𝐲𝐜𝐡𝐞𝐞 𝐑𝐨𝐬𝐞 ($𝟔). The colour gradient is soooo pretty and pleasing to the eyes 😍 I gotta say that their Dirty Matcha is definitely one of the better ones out there!! It had a perfect balance of matcha and coffee which I thoroughly enjoyed throughout my meal ❤️ ⁣
⁣
Overall, I really liked the whole vibes of the cafe, and the staff were really friendly as well! Will be back soon to try their other mains and get my dirty matcha 🥰✨

📍 𝘕𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘰𝘴 ⁣
⁣
@nandossg has always been famous for their PERi-PERi Chicken, but did you know that they have recently launched their PERi-PERi bowls that incorporates local flavours? 🤯🥳⁣
⁣
Starting off with their new item, I loved how they have the options to 𝐁𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐎𝐰𝐧 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥 or opt for their 𝐒𝐢𝐠𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥𝐬 if you are unsure what to get! I opted for the earlier and went with the following: 𝐏𝐄𝐑𝐢-𝐏𝐄𝐑𝐢 𝐧𝐨𝐨𝐝𝐥𝐞𝐬, 𝐛𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐠𝐡, 𝐠𝐫𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐜𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐢 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐨𝐛𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐨 𝐦𝐮𝐬𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐦𝐬. Their PERi-PERi noodles is commonly known as mee tai mak, which is my childhood favourite noodles!! The peri-laksa sauce was generously coated all over the mee tai mak, which had a mildly spicy yet slightly sweet tang to it - really flavourful 🤤 I opted for their boneless thigh which was tender and juicy, and definitely had a spicy kick with the hot sauce that I called for 🥵 For the sides, I went with grilled broccoli which was crispy and crunchy, and portobello mushroom which Nandos provided a generous portion to fill me up🤰 ⁣
⁣
I also got my all time favourite - 𝐁𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐠𝐡 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝟐 𝐑𝐞𝐠 𝐒𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐬!! The boneless thighs were freshly grilled-to-order and is super juicy and tender! I especially enjoyed the pairing with their PERi-PERi hot sauce - it’s AMAZING 😮‍💨 The PERi-PERi chips and coleslaw never fails to amaze me, especially their coleslaw!! It’s so underrated…… please try it if you haven’t! ⁣
⁣
Thank you @getkobe for arranging and @nandossg for hosting! Have always been a fan of Nandos and their new PERi-PERi bowls is certainly a great addition to their menu ✨❤️

📍 𝘉𝘪𝘵𝘵𝘦𝘯 & 𝘊𝘰 ⁣
⁣
Received a box of 𝐃𝐚𝐫𝐤 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐋𝐚𝐯𝐚 𝐂𝐨𝐨𝐤𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐌𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐧𝐬 from @bittenandco which helped made my weekend wayyyyy better 🥰🧁🍪⁣
⁣
🍪 𝐃𝐚𝐫𝐤 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐋𝐚𝐯𝐚 𝐂𝐨𝐨𝐤𝐢𝐞𝐬: Just look at that chocolate flow even though I didn’t heat it up 😮‍💨 99.99% sure it would look better after heating it up!! The cookies were filled with oozy dark chocolate fillings enclosed with a crunchy and crispy crust. I loved how it wasn’t super sweet or cloying at all! ⁣
⁣
🍫 𝐃𝐚𝐫𝐤 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐋𝐚𝐯𝐚 𝐌𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐧𝐬: I liked how the muffins were moist and soft and at the same time being a little dense. The generous amount of dark chocolate provided was perfect to give a lava ooze that everyone needs! Would recommend for you to heat it up to get the top crispy and the insides flowy with chocolaty goodness to experience the best of both worlds 🤤⁣
⁣
If you are interested in trying their bakes, do head over to their page @bittenandco to order ✨⁣
⁣
Thank you @bittenandco for sending your bakes over ❤️🥰

📍 𝘉𝘶𝘳𝘨𝘦𝘳 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘓𝘰𝘣𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘳 ⁣
⁣
Have been wanting to try this for the longest time and it definitely exceeded my expectations 🤯😮‍💨 ⁣
⁣
I had their 𝐂𝐨𝐦𝐛𝐨 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐓𝐰𝐨 ($𝟏𝟐𝟖) which came with a 𝟏.𝟓𝐥𝐛 𝐨𝐟 𝐥𝐨𝐛𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫, 𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝟐 𝐦𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝟐 𝐝𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐤𝐬. ⁣
⁣
For the 𝟏.𝟓𝐥𝐛 𝐥𝐨𝐛𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫, I got both their steamed and grilled version as there was a half and half option. I preferred the latter as it had more smoky flavour/taste to it and a firmer meat which I enjoyed a lot!! Didn’t really enjoy the steamed lobster as it retained most of the sweetness which was too much for me and was slightly less firm. ⁣
⁣
Moving on to the star of the meal, their mains!! I opted for their 𝐎𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐋𝐨𝐛𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐥 𝐰 𝐇𝐨𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐝 and their 𝐒𝐮𝐫𝐟 & 𝐓𝐮𝐫𝐟 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐥 𝐰/ 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐄𝐠𝐠 𝐘𝐨𝐥𝐤 𝐅𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐬. Both were served with VERY FRESH and GENEROUS portion of chilled lobster meat🦞 dressed with different sauces. I would highly recommend trying their 𝐎𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐋𝐨𝐛𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐥 as I thoroughly enjoyed the lobster meat that was dressed with lemon mayo!! It was so sweet and succulent & when paired with their garlic butter sauce, OOF it just elevated the flavours to a whole new level 😮‍💨 Not forgetting their brioche bread which was perfectly toasted and evenly buttered whilst being really fluffy! The 𝐒𝐮𝐫𝐟 & 𝐓𝐮𝐫𝐟 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐥 provided the best of both worlds - chunks of lobster meat tossed in japanese mayo and a mini nebraskan beef patty which was juicy and well cooked. Together with the soft buttery brioche bread & garlic butter sauce, every mouth was amazing! ⁣
⁣
Lastly, the sides! The 𝐇𝐨𝐮𝐬𝐞 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐚𝐝 was really fresh and goes well with the salad dressing. It was refreshing to have it along with the lobster roll ☺️ Their 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐄𝐠𝐠 𝐘𝐨𝐥𝐤 𝐅𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐬 were crunchy and the flavour profile of salted egg was strong as well!⁣
⁣
Overall, I enjoyed my whole experience at Burger and Lobster - from the ambience to the friendly service staff and to the food ❤️ Prices are definitely on the steeper side but I do see myself coming back again 🥰☺️

📍 𝘗𝘦𝘻𝘻𝘰⁣
⁣
Happy National Pizza Day!! 🥳🍕

Pezzo has launched their Chinese New Year special for a limited time only!! Featuring their 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐮𝐧𝐞 𝐏𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚 and 𝐅𝐫𝐮𝐢𝐭𝐲-𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨 𝐏𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚 that is available from now till 28 Feb ✨⁣
⁣
The seasonal 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐮𝐧𝐞 𝐏𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚 was generously filled with chicken deng deng strips and capsicum, drizzled with a thousand island sauce. I liked how there was a slight spice to the pizza from the capsicum and a crunchy bite to it which provided more texture to the pizza! However, I did find the thousand island sauce a little too much as it masked the taste of the other ingredients and got heavy after a while. ⁣
⁣
Their 𝐅𝐫𝐮𝐢𝐭𝐲-𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨 𝐏𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚 would be a dream for all sweet tooth out there!! I enjoyed the sweet and sour combination from the pizza - citrus and tangy flavours from the orange and pineapple ; sweetness from the strawberries and kit kat spread. This was definitely a perfect dessert to end of the meal!⁣
⁣
Along with these pizzas, I also got to try their popular sides - 𝐏𝐨𝐩𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐧 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 and 𝐃𝐫𝐮𝐦𝐥𝐞𝐭𝐬. These sides were great for sharing and a nice pairing with the pizzas 🍕 ⁣
⁣
Thank you @pezzoopizzasg for sending these over ❤️☺️

Kakuni Don

Much had been said about Itchy Bun before it’s official launch — whilst they were supposed to have opened their doors on 22 February 2022 initially, they had finally officially done so a day after due to “unforeseen circumstances” as stated in their social media account. For those whom are not in the know, Itchy Bun is an establishment located at Prinsep Street (several doors away from Mama Diam) brought by the folks behind Fook Kin (also by the same people behind Roast Paradise) and also The Muttons from Class 95FM. Being more of an Izakaya-style establishment, the menu offers fry buckets (i.e. beer bites), Zensai, Rice Bowls, Itchy Buns (i.e Mantou Sliders) and sides. Beverages available include beer, sake and non-alcoholic options such as canned drinks — pretty much in line with the other establishments around the area. 

While we were pretty intrigued by the Itchy Buns that they have to offer initially as they seem to be the signature offerings here, but we found ourselves going for the Kakuni Don for something more substantial since we were here for lunch on a workday in office (which is pretty much a stone’s throw away from us). Ain’t a fan of Foie Gras, hence steered away from the Subarashi Don which is pretty much the full works, and instead opted for the Kakuni Don. While the portions may be a bit on the smaller side for some, the Kakuni Don is actually pretty affordably priced at $8.80+. Coming with elements such as a sous-vide egg, Ebiko, Furikake, Japanese pickles, braised pork belly and seaweed, the Kakuni Don was pretty comforting and well-executed for its price — the braised pork belly was especially delicious having absorbed all the flavours from the braising liquid; all savoury without being too heavy-handed in flavour, while not carrying undesirable porky stench. Texturally, it was a great balance between the gelatinous fatty parts and the leaner parts; soft, tender and juicy, yet carrying a good bite for the best of both worlds.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Passionfruit Meringue Tart

Heard all about the new K. Patisserie at Onze; the same building which also houses DESEM Bakery and Sugar & Tease, as well as the ever-popular Beef Sukiyaki Don Keisuke which always sees a queue during the hours that they are open. K. Patisserie is situated within the mall, tucked in a corner not too far from where DESEM Bakery and Sugar & Tease are located. The cafe is pretty moderately-sized, with a small counter facing the patrons on the left displaying the cakes and bakes available for the day upon entry; the space being decked in a pastel pink and white colour scheme with splashes of gold for the furniture and fittings. Being a patisserie, expect a variety of cakes and bakes available here; drinks available includes specialty coffee, tea, as well as a small list of non-caffeinated options such as Chocolate and Mineral Water. 

Between the two items that we had, the one that actually set a better impression would be the Passionfruit Meringue Tart. It is the more well-executed one — priced at $8, it is decently sized; what we really enjoyed here is the biscuit-like tart base which crumbles quite neatly as one slices through it. The tart base also holds the passionfruit curd within pretty well; all that while the passionfruit curd remains zingy and tangy. The meringue was actually done pretty well here; fluffy and light whilst being slightly torched without being overly sweet — cuts through the zippy notes for a good balance of flavours. Overall, a pretty satisfying dessert for those looking for something a little sour to refresh the taste buds.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Ayam Berempah Nasi Lemak (Leg)

Was pretty exciting when I had first chanced upon Wild Coco’s social media accounts —  while I am pretty much a Nasi Lemak junkie of my own, Wild Coco’s Nasi Lemak did catch my attention for how aesthetically similar their rendition is to the one served at The Coconut Club; difficult for one to not draw comparisons with especially given the slightly lower price point at $8.80 for the Ayam Berempah Nasi Lemak (Leg) here. The differences in operations at Wild Coco is quite stark however; for one, Wild Coco is just one of three brand offerings which are made available at this new coffeeshop-esque establishment at 7 Days Coffee (formerly the premises of Skinny Chef Plus) at Blk 122 McNair Road — shares the same premises and the counter as Hei Kee Wanton Mee and Bugis Xin Yuan Ji Fish Soup. Apart from serving up Nasi Lemak sets with different varieties of meat options (think also Ayam Rendang, Sambal Fried Fish etc.), Wild Coco also serves up wok-fried dishes such as Nyonya Assam Eggplant and more, as well as side dishes such as Fried Sotong. The coffeeshop largely comprises of seating good for two pax, though does offer some tables of five as well.

We were pretty much decided on ordering the Ayam Berempah Nasi Lemak when we first skimmed through the menu and came across the photos on social media — each plate of Nasi Lemak will come with the preferred choice of meat, coupled with coconut rice, egg, Ikan Bilis, peanut, sambal and cucumber.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Black Sesame Teacake 

Potong Pasir seems to be pretty buzzy these days — the sleepy, quaint neighbourhood has pretty much been given a breath of new life with the opening of The Poiz Centre, as well as some sort of gentrification ever since the Shangri-La Confectionery & Delicatessen was revamped as Kizuna. RISE is yet another new addition to the neighbourhood; run by the same folks behind Cafe Coco at Gardens by the Bay, this is their very first venture in the heartlands. Located within the same block as Kizuna, RISE is located at the opposite end just right behind a bus stop. Serving up mostly bakes that they have made in-house, they also do serve up a small selection of viennoiserie; there are also savoury selections such as a Trio Cheese Kimchi Teacake as well as a Garlic Butter + Cheese Danish. Other items available on the menu at RISE includes a variety of Brown Butter Waffles and a good range of gelatos which includes interesting flavours such as the Cheddar Cheese & Ritz Crackers. Choice of beverages include specialty coffee and tea from TWG Tea — non-caffeinated options include a 40% Dark Chocolate and Orange Chocolate.

Opting for the Black Sesame Teacake which made its appearance as we were gazing at the display chiller, it is interesting to note how the teacakes here are styled aesthetically similar to a small Chiffon cake especially with the round hole in the middle. That being said, make no mistake as the cake is pretty much a teacake at heart; the texture of the cake sits between that of a pound cake and a chiffon — still pretty light but not quite as soft and fluffy as a chiffon would be since this would be denser. This cake pretty much hit our tastebuds pretty instantly with its distinct black sesame aroma; nothing short of roasty and fragrant from the glaze to the cake — the glaze adds a distinct richness to the entire cake and antes up the overall flavour without being overly sweet.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Truffle Veal Cheek Toast

Have seen quite a number of social media posts on Three Nuts Baker, which had recently opened its doors at Space@Kovan; the mixed-use development is also home to an outlet of Soi 19 Thai Wanton Mee, The Bread Rack and Little Ceylon. Being pretty much a hole-in-the-wall bakery, the store is pretty much positioned for takeaway business; that being said, there is actually seats for three pax at the bar table that faces the window for those who are looking to dine-in at the space. Being more of a bakery, expect a whole range of cakes and pastries which includes tarts, cakes and even a cinnamon bun available here; interestingly, Three Nuts Baker also serves up open-faced sandwiches though only during limited hours (between 8am to 1pm), whilst also serving up a whole list of beverages which includes specialty coffee (including a Honey Oat Latte that is listed as a “Cold Brew”, tea from the Gryphon Tea Company, Kombucha and Felchin Swiss Chocolate, amongst others.

Wasn’t quite aware of their “breakfast” section of their menu when we headed there in the early afternoon; the folks here were actually kind enough to whip up a portion of the Truffle Veal Cheek Toast which we were pretty interested in despite us making our order slightly past the last order for breakfast item — they had also offered to re-plate the dish on a wooden platter since we were taking photos of the bakes (was told this is usually served in takeaway cardboard boxes). 

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

.
Are you ready to Roar and usher into a Roar-some year ahead? 🐯 

Check out these seasonal New Year collections from @wupaochunsg specially curated for the upcoming Lunar New Year: 
🏮Red Wine Longan - award-winning champion bread decked in a 春 festive spirit! 🌸 Filled with wine-soaked dried longans and crunchy walnuts, this massively huge and hefty bread is ideal for sharing with your family and loved ones for this festive season! ✨
🏮Lychee Happiness 💕- red bean filling, wine-soaked dried lychee, egg yolk and mochi encased within a white chocolate coated pastry skin. My personal favourite among all, with a multi dimension of flavours and textures of sweet, juicy wine-soaked lychee bits, chewy mochi, crumbly and slightly savoury egg yolk and a mildly sweetened red bean paste. Adorned with a buttery, flaky pastry skin, this somehow reminds me of a pastry mooncake with its core of lightly salted egg yolk just missing those spiral swirls. Indeed a toothsome delight that brings happiness to the palate! 🥰
🏮Prosperity fish - spicy, umami and moreishly flavorful sambal ikan bilis in a fish shaped brioche. My 2nd fav among all here!~ 
🏮Orange Maritozzo🍊- orange cream filled breadroll topped with fresh orange slices and crushed pistachio bits. 
🏮Yuzu Blossom - A pretty pink bagel filled with Yuzu infused cream cheese and crunchy walnut chunks. While I enjoyed the fragrant citrusy notes of Yuzu cream cheese, I personally found the bagel to be a tad dry with minimal fillings. 
🏮Mala Fortune- bring on the spice with a Mala Bak Kwa filled bagel topped with a crisp, crusty baked cheese layer! 🔥 A savoury bagel that packs a punch with its tangy, aromatic tinge of spice🌶.
🏮Yammy Ingot - Yam and sweet potato custard Danish pastry.  Tbh I don’t see any resemblance to an ingot here in terms of visuals. Nevertheless, I still enjoyed the pleasantly crisp, flaky texture of the pastry and the lusciously creamy purple sweet potato custard filling💜.

description:
.
Desserts (esp Matcha & most tea flavours) have always been my daily essentials, without the exception of these Tea flavoured bundlettes and blondies from @gailybakes which I am loving so Mochi! 💕 

Featured here are the soon to be launched ALL TEA flavoured Mochi bakes comprising of:
🌀Matcha Mochi Bundlettes 
🌀Houjicha Mochi Bundlettes 
🌀 Genmaicha Mochi Bundlettes 
🌀Earl Grey Mochi Bundlettes 
🌀Genmaicha Biscoff Mochi Blondie 

As the saying goes “The only men you need in life is Ramen” but for me, the only GENtlemen I need in life is GENMAICHA🍵. While Matcha & Houjicha makes the best of both worlds💚🤎, with Genmaicha it’s a Tea-riffic Trio or a Quartet with Earl grey!

The gaily looking bakes here all are mochi infused instead of centre filled, which had a fluffy, chewy and bouncy interior that’s also sufficiently moist, light and not too dense. In fact, I could easily have 2 Bundlettes at one go without any surfeiting aftermath👍🏻. Recommended to consume at room temp (on the day of delivery) or heated up in oven which I personally prefer the latter as the exterior became more crisp while the interior was softer and more moist 😋. 

As a hardcore fan of tea flavours, I truly enjoyed how the respective  flavours of each are intensely robust, esp the Houjicha Bundlette which came with a deep roasted earthiness coupled with a fragrant nutty undertone. Following closely behind is the Matcha Bundlette which had a bittersweet earthy note and lush umami-ness - my personal fav flavour among all here! 🥰 The Genmaicha was more subtle and mellow in flavour, with a lighter body as compared to Matcha. The Earl Grey mochi bundlette had a fragrant, perfumy bergamot flavour and pleasant floral-like aroma, which was delightful but a tad sweet after awhile, hence would personally  recommend this more for sharing instead. 

Continued in comments 👇🏻

.
Spicing up my day with this hearty bowl of Vegetarian Mapo Mien [$12.30++] that is generously loaded with soft, silky smooth silken tofu cubes atop a bed of noodles and coated with spicy, tangy and moreishly flavourful Sichuan Mapo sauce🔥. 

Been awhile since my last visit to @chensmapotofu and am glad to see that the spice level is customisable now!👍🏻 As an avid fan of spice, I opted for the highest level 3 which packs a punch, spicy albeit not overwhelming, with a piquantly aromatic mala-like fragrance😋. Paired with springy noodles (rice option available as well) and delicately soft, silk-like tofu cubes, it was a slurpable and relishing meal! 💕As this is the vegetarian option which I had opted for, the Signature Mapo tofu don / Mien comes with minced meat by default. Perhaps @chensmapotofu may consider introducing some plant based meat alternatives ie. @impossible_foods for the vegetarians/ flexitarians someday? 😌🤔

With the current promo of Free regular side and a drink with purchase of any mains, I also enjoyed a sumptuous side of chilled Szechuan century egg & tofu and a bottle of thirst-quenching and refreshing Calamansi to beat the heat (and spice)! ✨

PS: Promo of free side and drink with any main purchase ends on 31st Jan 2020, exclusive to the @nex.singapore outlet!

A dessert burger?! 🍔Yes that was what came to my mind (and also mentioned by the staff when I was placing my order 😹) on the first sight of this: 

Sweet Potato Tarte Tropézienne🍠 [$13] 
A new seasonal item that’s only available till 25th January (just 2 more days to check it now!), this aren’t some Tart here but a fluffy brioche sandwiched with Chiba sweet potato cream. Using Beni Haruka Satsumaimo, one of the most popular sweet potato varieties in Japan, the baked sweet potato cream is lusciously creamy and velvety smooth with a pleasant tinge of honey-like sweetness💕. As a fan of sweet potato, I certainly enjoyed the sweet potato cream filling but on the downside, the brioche was a tad dry for my liking;probably as the dessert is served chilled and buns tend to dry out faster when kept refrigated🥲. 

Of course, the main highlight here is the sweet potato cream which I really fancied, but imo the pairing with the brioche burger bun was kind of a gimmicky, run-of-the-mill thing. Would personally  prefer if it’s filled in a tart or choux pastry puff (which @tartebycherylkoh has it as a Saint Honoré that looks really good but only available as a full sized portion) for some textural contrast 😬. 
.

Ok folks! Last chance to try the @quinnsirishpub.mw collaboration of the “Phat Quinn” Burger with @phatburgerbro!
🔻
Quinn’s, a new chain of Irish taverns owned by a group of Singaporean entrepreneurs, has taken over 2 established English pubs and converted them into Irish bars. And in conjunction with their takeover, they are proud to present its first menu collaboration with All-American burger joint, Phat Burger Bro, thus giving the launch of the “Phat Quinn” Burger.
🔻
The Phat Quinn Burger is layered with crispy bacon and Irish whisky aioli spiced with garlic it’s beefy smooth consistency that adds an Irish twist to the all-American burger spectrum.
🔻
Other items which we enjoyed were the addictive fried onion rings, fried chicken wings, Laksa Spring rolls and the Grilled Chicken Skewers! Each came with their respective sauce and are easily paired with Quinn’s wide selection of beer, stout, larger and more!
🔻
The “Phat Quinn” Burger will be available only till today! However not to despair, the other items will still be available at their 2 outlets! So Seeya guys there!

Presenting this very delicious Martabak from @martabak.sg ! Most of you will be familiar with our local version of Murtabak but this is the Indo version which is Martabak spelled with an ‘A’ instead of “U”
and it’s a popular street food in indo too!
🔻
I was very lucky to try some of their new flavors which formally were towards the sweet/dessert criteria but now they have savory options too!
🔻
The Chicken Telur Martabak was as loaded as it comes! As per what I see, It’s tall eggy,  full of ingredients such as chicken, green onions , shallots and more! The impressive thing is that this is crispy even when it went through delivery! It does have the familiar local Indian taste but this is on another level! It’s almost like a platter of Mini martabak sandwiches! It also comes with 3 sauces where you can mix and match or even eat it on its own! I was really impressed! Well, a good way to describe this, is that this resembles the love child of the Telur dada and Murtabak!
🔻
Of course the best way to end your meal is some traditional street food desserts like their version of our Min Jiang Kueh. @martabak.sg comes with a host of flavors like Pandan cheese milk, Ondeh x2 special, Red Velvet and more! A good summary of what I feel is that @martabak.sg dosent short change you! They are generous with the sauces and ingredients so you are guaranteed satisfaction with a Smile on your face!

💻To order head over to

#throwback to one of the best meals I had right at the start of 2022. Over here, it’s like paradise to me! Everything they serve was gold! From the mains, to the sides and even the desserts too!
🔻
Besides their mouthwatering, succulent ox tail rendang which I posted earlier (count back 38 post. ) , other mains stood out too like the Roasted Suckling Pig which has some of the crispiest cracking skin!
🔻
The sides like the Iberico Pork Sate is another fav of mine! I guess it’s their way of calling Satay but the taste is nonetheless the same! This is a very tender and flavorful piece of meat being bbqued!!
🔻
Lastly, the dessert was simply euphoric ! Everything I wanted in a dessert, it’s there!The Kaya with Caramelize Banana Crumble and Sticky Date pudding were IMHO,  the perfect dessert! Perfect texture, taste and well plated, it’s easy to see why it’s on everyone else table! A homeage to nonya style kuehs but with an elevated touch! This is indeed the perfect ending for my meal!
🔻
Once again @tableat7 proves that a restaurant can serve 2 cuisines successfully , in this case the European along with a more South East Asian Indo cuisine! Although personally I feel they excel in the SEA cuisine as I rarely get to eat indo dishes served in an elevated format but for folks who wants something less homely or spicy, can always have the option to order from the other side of the spectrum which was pretty good too!

From L to R
🔸Kaya Banana Crumble
🔸Sticky Date pudding
🔸Iberico Pork Sate
🔸Roasted Suckling
🔸Oxtail Rendang

Check out @tableat7 at their new location -
📍41 Namly Avenue 
Level 3 (Basement) SIM Management House Singapore 267616

A bloom for @fukui.sg to welcome the start of Spring with new omakase menus. Highlighting the new spring specialities through an array of inventive sushi creations, alongside with all-time favourites by Head Chef Nick Pa’an, their new spring menu was nothing short of excellent with endless enjoyment.
•
My 10-course Kazumi Menu ($388++) that evening started with a cold appetiser (1st Photo) of Noresore, Mozuku & Hotaru Ika (Baby Conger Eel, Vinegared Seaweed & Firefly Squid), served in egg yolk mousse, and enlivened in the high notes of thrumming acidity of ponzu sauce that manages to awaken every taste bud. Followed will be their 1st seasonal dish (2nd Photo) with Medai Warayaki (Straw Smoked Japanese Butterfish) took a gentle swoosh of smokiness sealed in the meaty slices, served with Myoga (Red Ginger), thinly sliced marinated garlic and Kaiware (White Radish Sprouts). Next will be a beautiful sashimi platter (3rd Photo) with Ishidai (Striped Beakfish), Mejina with Shio Kombu (Blackfish with Salted Seaweed), Otoro (Bluefin Tuna Belly), arranged on their gorgeous ceramic plate.
•
From 21 Feb, Fukui is one of the participating restaurants to collaborate with JFOODO, an organisation within the Japan External Trade Organisation (JETRO), to launch a sake pairing campaign, SEAFOOD LOVES SAKE. You will be able to enjoy limited time-only pairings with an abundance of seafood creations in Fukui, to showcase the versatility of sake. The aforementioned dishes are served with Denshin Yuki ~Snow~ Junmai Ginjo ($186/bottle), a clean tasting sake with nuanced smoothness, addding layers of enjoyment and draws out its flavours in gentle swirls and flourishes. Will be sharing more on other dishes soon!

description:
To score a dinner slot at Chef Vincent’s popular private dining - Pun Im, is extremely difficult, but all thanks to @xiaohanjue for giving me a slot for yesterday dinner. From his menu of Thai-French fusion creations, it showcase his French cooking techniques where @vincent.pun.im trained with Le Cordon Bleu Dusit in Bangkok, combining with his love for Thai flavours.
•
It drew unanimous praises from all my foodie friends as somewhere to experience local, authentic Thai food. Starting the meal with a medley of snacks:
Miang Kham (1st Photo) - A moreish bite combines a little of 7 condiments in a fresh wild betel leaf wrap, with a dollop of sweet and savoury sauce over the leaf-wrapped bite for an explosion of flavour with every mouthful.
~
Dumpling Som O (2nd Photo) - His rendition of Thai pomelo salad in ancient style with coconut cream used in here unlike the modern one that we usually had, and wrapped in dumpling skin. A wave of herby fragrance hit the tongue first, brightened by its soft acidity, and a bolt of heat that crescendos when you least expect it.
~
Yum Taling Pling (3rd Photo) - Belimbing salad with green mango, coconut rice and a sweet and spicy sauce. It was packed with a stunning balance of saltiness, sweetness, acidity, and heat.
~
Tamarind Tart (4th Photo) - Quail egg, wing bean and nam prik makaam fillings, served in a crispy golden cup aka krathong thong. A bite into this was enough to jolt us wide awake, packed with an unlikely amount of flavour.
•
The food here generally leans towards the bolder end of the Thai flavour spectrum. Most of the dishes we had were punchy and unapologetic in their acidity and heat, but immaculate in their underlying balance. Will be sharing more details on other dishes soon.
•

Buah Keluak Fried Rice ($28) - One of Chef Damian’s signature dish since his days at Folkore. Sporting a glorious shade of black, the rice is fried with the flesh of the buah keluak, imparting its beautiful colour on every grain. Intensely fragrant and the wok hei was spot on with a perfect combination of earthy and umami, making this dish so irresistible that we ordered a 2nd serving.
•
Seafood Bee Hoon ($48/$68) - Cooked with Heng Hwa fine bee hoon with the medley of seafood in and seafood stock, made with 3 different stocks of fish, prawn, and clam, and the seafood includes fish belly, cuttlefish, prawns, clams, and scallops. The combination of textures, comforting flavours, and sumptuous ingredients will not only be memorable, but relished with delight.
•

description:
JFOODO, an organisation within the Japan External Trade Organisation (JETRO), will be launching a sake pairing campaign titled, SEAFOOD LOVES SAKE. And they will be partnering with 30 mid to high-end restaurants to showcase the versatility of sake, pairing with their signature seafood dishes of different cuisines.
•
One of the participating restaurants is Morsels, with two menus ($78++ per person/lunch menu & $188++ per person/dinner menu) for this campaign, starting from 21st Feb. First we started off with Sakari Junmai Ginjo - a fruit forward, tropical and refreshing sake, making a good complement to the two crudo dishes - Oyster with sea buckthorn shrub, tosazu vinaigrette, lemon oil, pickled samphire; and Aka Ebi with chettinad mayo atop lentil sago cracker, when their sweetness unfurls and enticingly in your mouth.
•
Moving on to the Steamed Venus Clams with a rich umami, buttery dried figs chicken broth, and is paired with a richer Genmaishu with a character that beckons you to take another sip, highlighting the umami element without being overly cloying. This pairing had us slurping down every last drop of the broth.
•

After a collection of snacks serves at Thevar to both stimulate the palate and set the tone for the meal, we were presented with the following appetiters:
Irish Oyster (1st Photo): Paying homage to his grandmother’s rasam soup, Chef Mano came up with his unique version using Irish oysters and topped with icy rasam granita, complete with finger lime.
•
Argentinian Prawn Kachori (2nd Photo): A delightful treat for the prawn lovers, where a traditional fist-sized crispy pastry shell stuffed to the brim with sweet Argentinian prawn cubes, and topped with Marigold flowers.
•
Chettinad Chicken Roti (3rd Photo): An Indian version of a nice juicy chicken taco, with incredibly tender and moist shredded chicken marinated with heady spices, well complimented with a dollop of garlic aioli and pickle in soft buttery homemade naan that will ensure a cult following.
•

Finally visited Get Together Coffee Shop and tried the newly launched Kurobuta Mee Hoon Kway ($5.50) with limited portions daily from @jiak_song 🍜

It was interesting how they combined the delectable kurobuta pork with the traditional Mee Hoon Kway which added a slight sweetness and butteriness from the ribbons of fat marbling through the meat. 🥩 I also noticed their flavourful and umami broth that the soup version came in had a distinct smokey taste that is different from the traditional broths we usually have. However, I feel that this may be an acquired taste. 

Besides their Kurobuta Mee Hoon Kway, I also enjoyed their dry version! Paired with their signature MHK chilli, every bite really hit the comfort spots for me. For those who prefer the soup version, you can also try their Signature All-in Combo Mee Hoon Kway with Minced Pork, Pork Slices, Pork Ball, and Shrimp Ball ($5.50) which includes their smooth yet QQ handmade shrimp balls! 🍤

I also tried other hawker dishes at the newly opened Get Together Coffee Shop which I will review in a separate post! 🥰

 📍Blk 177 Bukit Batok West Ave 8 Get Together Coffee Shop Singapore 650177

description:
I am a huge fan of garlic cream cheese buns and I got to say these soft and buttery buns from @morimoriyogashi really hit all the spots. 🥺

Loaded with japanese garlic, butter and japanese mayonnaise, you get a good balance of sweet and savoury with a crispy exterior to a soft, chewy and moist center! 🥯 Swipe to see more visuals of all that melty cheese, garlic and buttery goodness inside — I guarantee you won't be able to stop at one piece. I also liked how the taste of the mayo was not overwhelming and the aroma of the garlic butter was everything I need. Most importantly, you have to heat these babies up using your air fryer or oven at 160'C for about 5 minutes for that perfect crisp and CHEEESE PULL when the cheese melts. 🧀 Priced affordably at $18 for 8 pieces, y'all definitely got to try some! ✨

I also got to try their 𝙐𝙟𝙞 𝙈𝙖𝙩𝙘𝙝𝙖 𝘾𝙧𝙚𝙥𝙚 𝙍𝙤𝙡𝙡 ($𝟷𝟾.𝟿𝟶) which is made up of rolls of crepes with cream inside! Love how the cream and the soft crepe instantly melts in your mouth but I actually prefer to have it straight out of the freezer so it feels like I am having matcha ice cream! 

Thank you @morimoriyogashi for sending these yummy bakes over! Genuinely so impressed with the quality and I am excited to try more of their bakes soon! ✨
taggedFullName1: Morimori Yogashi モリモリ洋菓子

description:
🎉 @coexistcoffee.co is opening their 3rd outlet near Paya Lebar MRT on 2nd March, Wednesday! ✨ Shared a reel of their beautiful space with a "walk in the park at old London" concept and I am excited to share about their food today! 🥰

Starting off with their mains:
𝙀𝙗𝙞𝙠𝙤 𝙇𝙞𝙣𝙜𝙪𝙞𝙣𝙚 ($𝟸𝟺)
Linguine, Ebiko, Tobiko, Prawn Stock, Grilled Prawns
𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙡𝙡𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙋𝙖𝙨𝙩𝙖 ($𝟷𝟼)
Tagliolini, Scallion Oil, Aged Vinegar Cream, Fried Shallots
𝙎𝙦𝙪𝙞𝙙 𝙄𝙣𝙠 𝙍𝙞𝙨𝙤𝙩𝙩𝙤 ($𝟸𝟾)
Squid Ink Sauce, Hae Bee Hiam, Crab Meat, Firefly Squid, Chives 

My personal favourite was their ebiko linguine! I am a fan of stronger flavours so I really loved how the sauce was thick enough to coat each strand of pasta, yet not surfeiting or heavy on the palette. Nicely completed with succulent grilled prawns on the side and garnished with heaps of savoury ebiko, this was impressive! 🍤 Not forgetting their fragrant scallion pasta and flavourful squid ink risotto which were my friends' favourites, I believe the quality of ingredients used does justify the relatively steep prices to me. 🍝

The sides did not disappoint with their 𝘾𝙖𝙧𝙧𝙤𝙩 𝙘𝙖𝙠𝙚 𝙛𝙧𝙞𝙚𝙨 ($𝟷𝟺), 𝘽𝙧𝙪𝙨𝙨𝙚𝙡 𝙎𝙥𝙧𝙤𝙪𝙩𝙨 ($𝟷𝟼) and 𝙂𝙧𝙞𝙡𝙡𝙚𝙙 𝙋𝙚𝙖𝙧 𝙎𝙖𝙡𝙖𝙙 ($𝟸𝟼). Being someone who isn't a fan of vegetables, I couldn't stop reaching out for more of their brussel sprouts that contained so much flavour along with the siracha mayo and candied bacon. 🥓Carrot cake fries were drizzled with sambal mayo and I loved the texture of them — crisp on the outside and fluffy on the inside! I expected this to be greasy but I didn't have any oily mouthfeel even after having a few pieces! 🍟

For desserts, I had their 𝙈𝙚𝙡𝙤𝙣𝙖 ($𝟷𝟸) and 𝘽𝙚𝙡𝙡𝙞𝙣𝙞 ($𝟷𝟶).Both had a beautiful presentation but I preferred their melona that contains melon ice cream, yogurt mousse, prosciutto and pickled melon! It had a nice balance of sweetness and tanginess with a savoury touch from the prosciutto ham that enhanced the sweetness from the melon! 🍈

They also have an extensive drink menu featuring coffees, teas, cocktails, beers, kombucha, and more. 🍹🍻☕️🍵

description:
Always have a soft spot for yogurt based drinks 😛 Hey! I am Yogost is a pretty new spot that sits in Suntec City. Other than the classic options like Purple Rice Yogurt, they have a Fresh Fruit Series and a Yogurt Tea Blend Series - went for 1 each in these two series, for their Blueberry Pineapple Yogurt and Strawberry Lemon-yo Tea.

Enjoyed the strawberry cup that wasn’t too sweet and came with a good amount of strawberry bits. If you like sour and refreshing drinks, this is a nice one to go for! 🍓 Thought the Blueberry Pineapple combi didn’t gel as well as we hoped for, would say to skip and try the other flavours.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

description:
Definitely didn’t expect this bistro bar to be hidden right behind an unassuming stretch of bookshelves - which btw, I thought was the mall’s decor (swipe to the back to see) 😂 @chapterscosg is a new concept by @oystercosg, with a menu serving up drinks, bar bites and seafood done in a range of ways. What we had:

• Canadian Fresh Oysters (Ikura & caviar are separate add-ons)
• Chili Crab Mantou 
• Black Pepper Crab Chawanmushi 
• Righteous Mac & Cheese 

Food was decent, highlight for us was their fresh Canadian oysters, which were just right in its sweetness and brininess 🦪 You can find fresh oysters avail from $1.99 each here and they do islandwide deliveries for them too from 11.30am to 11pm. Thank you @chapterscosg & @oystercosg for the kind invite! ✨

Haven’t had much Lebanese food before, but happy we got to last weekend with @lebanist! They are a cloud kitchen that just opened doors in Orchard. 

• Singapore Sling // Raisin Saffron Quinoa | Chicken Shawarma | Garlic Spinach | Moutabel | Pomegranate Seeds | Cashew Nuts | Fried Onions | Harissa | Garlic Sauce (Toum) - this is one of their most popular bowls, and I thought it serves as a v good intro to Lebanese food w its likable medley of flavours. I’m not a fan of fried onions but they do theirs well & gave a generous heap of them 😛 Chicken shawarma was flavourful & we esp appreciated the pops of sweetness from the raisins and pomegranate seeds. If you’re building your own bowl, def recommend to consider these, or just go for their preset bowls! 

• Build Your Own Bowl // Mujadara | Falafel | Hummus | Babaganoush | Croutons | Feta Cheese | Lebanese Green Olives | Tahini | Pomegranate Dressing - we picked a variety of ingredients to try out here. Plus point - only realised after eating that everything in this bowl is vegetarian 🌱, and in fact, the whole menu is, except for the lamb/beef/chicken shawarma. We preferred their preset bowl a lot more than our own picks as it turned out a little more flat than we’d like - but that’s on us 😂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Only other thing for me was that the dips were a little too strong/salty - considering all the flavours that were alr going on, it could get a tad bit overwhelming. Otherwise, we enjoyed it a lot. Till end Feb, take 15% off orders above $49 with <WEIZHI15> - & get complimentary baklava + 2 fav person notepads as part of their V Day special. Thank you @lebanist for sharing this meal! ✨

Penang hawker signatures?!! Gurney Drive @gurneydrivesg has made a comeback after 7 years, and is now opened at Northshore Plaza ll (unit 02-03). We ordered a couple of perennial favourites, and especially enjoyed the spicy sambal fried rice and crisp, juicy prawn paste chicken wings. Noodles are served with a generous topping of fresh crisp-fried pork lard. Affordable fare to check out if you're in the neighbourhood 😉 

What we had:-

1st meal of 2022. 

#1010

📍monument lifestyle x schmear 

bagel tasting at @monumentlifestyle 🍴lowkey overwhelmed bcos there were 5 bagels, 4 mini sammies and 3 cream cheese schmears (spreads) to choose from so we were really spoilt for choice🤩 will be reviewing the more memorable flavours hehe 

[10% off details below] 

🥯 bagels: cinnamon raisin, cheddar, sesame, everything, plain
🥪 sammies: turkey ham, pastrami melt, lox smoked salmon, new yorker
🧈 schmears: strawberry, jalapeno cheddar, garlic & herb, spring onion, plain 

🍓🍓𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙬𝙗𝙚𝙧𝙧𝙮 𝙨𝙘𝙝𝙢𝙚𝙖𝙧
strawberry cream cheese sounds contradictory but this packed a punch✊ strawberry flavour gave it a slight sweetness and fruitiness that was paired with sourness of classic cream cheese, taking the sweet-n-sour combi to the next level!! withdrawal issues would be real if i didnt bring this spread home omg
5/5⭐ 

🍇🍇 𝙘𝙞𝙣𝙣𝙖𝙢𝙤𝙣 𝙧𝙖𝙞𝙨𝙞𝙣 𝙗𝙖𝙜𝙚𝙡
prominent cinnamon flavours & raisins added a touch of sweetness to the bagel but i wish there were more raisins HAHA nevertheless, this was p memorable bring the first cinnamon flavoured bagel i've tried
4/5⭐ 

🧀🧀 𝙘𝙝𝙚𝙙𝙙𝙖𝙧 𝙗𝙖𝙜𝙚𝙡
simple and savoury! bagel was generously topped with molten cheddar cheese to give a light saltiness, suitable to pair with sweeter spreads
4.5/5⭐ 

🍣🍣 𝙡𝙤𝙭 𝙨𝙢𝙤𝙠𝙚𝙙 𝙨𝙖𝙡𝙢𝙤𝙣 𝙨𝙖𝙢𝙢𝙮
the classic sammy combi that never fails to hit the spot! stacked generously with smoked salmon and cream cheese, this was undeniably a savoury delicacy in itself
4/5⭐ 

🥩🥩 𝙥𝙖𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙢𝙞 𝙢𝙚𝙡𝙩 𝙨𝙖𝙢𝙢𝙮
giving the lox a run for its money bcos this might just be my new fav! pastrami was easy to bite into and carried slight spicy kick to it that was surprisingly addictive. low spice tolerance personally but i can see myself choosing this flavour again hehe
4.5/5⭐ 

🗓 From now till end Feb, enjoy 𝟭𝟬% 𝙤𝙛𝙛 𝙛𝙤𝙤𝙙 𝙞𝙩𝙚𝙢𝙨 at all Monument outlets!! Food items include bagels, granola/acai bowls & sourdough bread toasts! This applies to anyone following me @hungryshuen and @monumentlifestyle 🎊 

Thank you @monumentlifestyle for the invite!! 🥐🥪🧈 

#hstiongbahru #hungryshuencollab

🏠 𝙃𝘽𝘽 @mamafang.sg 

these fluffy mantou-looking mochi buns are some of the best in the mochi bread genre💯 was p sad their black sesame flavour wasn't available when i ordered but no regrets choosing choc and red bean😘 

🍫🍫 𝙘𝙝𝙤𝙘𝙤𝙡𝙖𝙩𝙚
lets jump straight in to the filling first shall we because it was AMAZING - rich and decadent melted choc, was silky smooth as well and doesn't burn the throat no matter how much u eat👌👌est 50-60% dark choc, it had a slight bitterness it. bread was a lil sweet, plain mochi was soft, stretchy and squishy🥰 really liked how all the fillings are spread out evenly and generously made up most of the bread's volume💖 i could rave on and on about this!!
5/5⭐ 

🔴🔴 𝙧𝙚𝙙 𝙗𝙚𝙖𝙣
tbh red bean was a replacement for black sesame but this flavour came through!! mashed red bean filling tasted very natural, there was no artificial flavouring or sweeteners added so it felt very healthy✅ plain mochi didn't much taste so this combi carried a milder flavour profile. still not bad!!
4/5⭐ 

📝Overall: really love love LOVE these mochi buns, would definitely buy again if the delivery fee was cheaper💸😪 definitely comparable to wupaochun's and muyoo's etc, highly recommended!!👍👍 

💸 $𝟮𝟯 (buns) + $𝟵 (delivery)
👩‍🍳 Service 4/5
🤑 Affordability 4/5 
🏃‍♀️ Be back factor 4.5/5 

#hsbakes_ #hsxhbb

📍eggslut 

was adamant about not queueing for this but guess who stood 40min under the sun🥵 no regrets tho, fairfax is officially my favourite scrambled eggs burger <3 

🥚🥚 𝙛𝙖𝙞𝙧𝙛𝙖𝙭 $𝟏𝟐
these pan-fried scrambled eggs were absolutely heavenly👼👼 looks simple but was super flavourful - egg was tastefully mixed with mayo, a tinge of salt and topped with a slice of cheddar cheese - the best savoury combo any burger lover could ever ask for😭💖 brioche buns were so fragrant and soft i felt like i was like biting into a pillow!! would go back just for this👌👌
5/5⭐ 

🥩🥩 𝙜𝙖𝙪𝙘𝙝𝙤 $𝟐𝟑
the highlight was definitely the seared wagyu strips which were thicc, tender and well seasoned🧂paired with the same brioche bun, every bite was oozing with meaty juiciness! recommended for meat lovers😉
4.75/5⭐ 

🍳🍳 𝙨𝙖𝙪𝙨𝙖𝙜𝙚, 𝙚𝙜𝙜 & 𝙘𝙝𝙚𝙚𝙨𝙚 𝙨𝙖𝙣𝙙𝙬𝙞𝙘𝙝 $𝟏𝟐
reminiscent of a higher quality mcmuffin, the savoury house-made chicken sausage surprisingly packed a punch👊 a good quality patty indeed makes the difference, but i'm not sure if the price is justified🤔
4/5⭐ 

🍟🍟 𝙩𝙧𝙪𝙛𝙛𝙡𝙚 𝙝𝙖𝙨𝙝𝙗𝙧𝙤𝙬𝙣𝙨 $𝟒.𝟓𝟎
definitely definitely deserving of the praises it has received🥰 carrying both a strong truffle smell and taste is rare but they pulled it off! calling all truffle lovers📣
4/5⭐ 

🍺🍺 𝙜𝙧𝙖𝙥𝙚𝙛𝙧𝙪𝙞𝙩 & 𝙜𝙞𝙣𝙜𝙚𝙧 𝙘𝙧𝙖𝙛𝙩 𝙨𝙤𝙙𝙖 $𝟒.𝟓𝟎
this was the first thing they served after standing under the hot sun and BOY was it refreshing❄ both grapefruit and ginger elements were pronounced, would have preferred the soda to be a lil less gassy🤭
3.75/5⭐ 

📝 Overall: Mostly overpriced but its the novelty of trying it that drew us there😂 (and same goes for everybody right!!) Really glad I liked the fairfax sandwich though, because it made the wait worth it and its the only item I will go back for🏃‍♀️💨 

💸 $4.50-$23
👩‍🍳 Service 4/5
🤑 Affordability 2.5/5
📝 Overall 3.5/5 

#hssomerset #hscafehopping

📍proofer boulangerie 

midweek bread haul from @prooferboulangerie 🍞🥖 budget breads this time since they're less than $1.80 each🤑 also didn’t know they have a pizza section now :0

🍠🍠𝙨𝙬𝙚𝙚𝙩 𝙥𝙤𝙩𝙖𝙩𝙤
first time trying sweet potato bread even tho it's been around for a long time😂smooth n creamy filling texture, retained sweet potato flavour authentically. t'was a good first taste!!
4/5⭐ 

☕☕𝙘𝙤𝙛𝙛𝙚𝙚
fragrant coffee aroma, though i would have preferred a stronger coffee taste and a harder shell🤔
⭐3/5 

🔴🔴𝙧𝙚𝙙 𝙗𝙚𝙖𝙣:
filling was smooth and mixed with some ungrounded red beans. generally slightly sweet, was simple and comforting👍
3.5/5⭐ 

🌱🌱𝙜𝙧𝙚𝙚𝙣 𝙗𝙚𝙖𝙣
filling carried a light saltiness, sesame seeds add to crunch and fragrance, makes for a great light snack!!
4/5⭐ 

📝 Overall: Bread was soft and fluffy and most flavours i tried are satisfactory👌👌I know they had some *issues* last oct but noth happened when we tried the bread soo yeah hehe 

Thank you @laoniangagency and @prooferboulangerie for the invite🥐😌 

#hungryshuencollab #hsbakes_

📍so good bakery 

gifted by my parents' friend🎁 wasn't expecting much but we really liked these pastries after trying, especially the cheese tart😉 

🧀🧀 𝙘𝙝𝙚𝙚𝙨𝙚 𝙩𝙖𝙧𝙩
reviewing this first because its SO GOOD?!👍👍filling was light and cheesy and had some milkiness to it🍼 texture was smooth and silky, didn't get gelak one bit! def my new fav cheese tart💖
5/5⭐ 

🥚🥚𝙚𝙜𝙜 𝙩𝙖𝙧𝙩
they nailed this too! pastry crust was thinner than most which allowed the filling to shine through👏 eggy and custard flavours were equally balanced, every bite was just so soft and flavourful that i'm considering switching allegiance from cookie crust to pastry crust🤯
4.5/5⭐ 

🥧🥧𝙘𝙝𝙖𝙧 𝙨𝙞𝙚𝙬 𝙨𝙤𝙝
this one sat quietly in the corner but boy was it memorable in its own way✨ the highlight is definitely the filling packed to the brim with flavourful char siew that was easy to bite into🍖 buttery fragrance from the layered pastry crust was the icing on the cake, plus this didnt't get soggy even after we left it out for a few hours💨
4/5⭐ 

📝 Overall: If you're looking for pastries, skip other bakeries and go for this 💯 Can't speak for over-the-counter service since this was gifted but the food was nothing short of impressive😻 Will definitely patronise again, especially for their egg white tarts which I've yet to try! 

#hsbakes_ #hssomerset
Would be back for the tomato tarte and fluffeh soufflé 👌🏻 #voyagesingapore

description:
A 𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝘀𝗮𝘁𝗶𝘀𝗳𝘆𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗣𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗼 𝗧𝗮𝗿𝘁 from @keongsaikbakery that pistachio lovers definitely should try!🥰 The 𝗰𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗽 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝗺 𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝗶𝘀 𝗳𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗽𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗼 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝗱, 𝗰𝗮𝗸𝗲 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲; love the strong flavour which is 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝘁𝗼𝗼 𝘀𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁, 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗮 𝗵𝗶𝗻𝘁 𝗼𝗳 𝘀𝗮𝗹𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗲𝗹𝗲𝘃𝗮𝘁𝗲𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗻𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗲𝘀𝘀✨

If you're a fan of pecan, their 𝗻𝗲𝘄𝗹𝘆 𝗹𝗮𝘂𝗻𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝗣𝗲𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗧𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝗶𝘀 𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘁𝘁𝘆 𝗻𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝘁𝗼𝗼 (though i'm bias towards the pistachio hehe) with the 𝗻𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗲𝗰𝗮𝗻𝘀 𝗯𝗮𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝘀𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁𝗻𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗽𝗹𝗲 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝗱 𝘀𝗼 𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝘀𝗮𝗰𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗲. Tart shell is very solid as well💯

description:
Popped by @sunwithmoonsg awhile back when they were having their 𝐇𝐨𝐤𝐤𝐚𝐢𝐝𝐨 𝐅𝐚𝐢𝐫 (might be over now oops #latergram 😅) , as the 𝐓𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐲𝐚𝐤𝐢 𝐂𝐡𝐞𝐞𝐬𝐞 𝐈𝐦𝐨 𝐌𝐨𝐜𝐡𝐢 looked and sounded too good to resist for us #cheeselovers 🧀😛

Felt that the cheese mochi was kinda lacking though! 𝐍𝐨𝐭 𝐚𝐬 𝐜𝐡𝐞𝐞𝐬𝐲 𝐚𝐬 𝐢 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐞𝐝 🥺and the mouthfeel was kinda grainy/flour-y. I think the 𝐇𝐨𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐀𝐬𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐚𝐠𝐮𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐰𝐚𝐬 𝐰𝐫𝐚𝐩𝐩𝐞𝐝 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐞𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫 𝐬𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐛𝐞𝐞𝐟 𝐟𝐚𝐫𝐞𝐝 𝐛𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫(also from the Hokkaido Fair menu) especially the scallops which were very tender and naturally sweet, though it was tad too salty as the dish was drenched in (teriyaki?) sauce.

The Makis were pretty tempting and so we got the Spicy Aburi Salmon and Nixon Roll. 𝐈 𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐲 𝐥𝐢𝐤𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐍𝐢𝐱𝐨𝐧 𝐫𝐨𝐥𝐥 😋😋- thick, generous slices of delicious unagi with cream cheese and omelette wrapped within.✨The 𝐒𝐩𝐢𝐜𝐲 𝐀𝐛𝐮𝐫𝐢 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐥,on the other hand, was 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐚𝐛𝐮𝐫𝐢-𝐞𝐝 𝐞𝐧𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐮𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐟𝐥𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐮𝐫-𝐰𝐢𝐬𝐞 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲 𝐦𝐞𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞😅

.
.
.
.
.
.

description:
Found this cute little ice cream cafe in the North ✨its pretty spacious and they’ve got 𝐮𝐧𝐢𝐪𝐮𝐞 𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐦𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐒𝐞𝐬𝐚𝐦𝐞/𝐂𝐢𝐧𝐧𝐚𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐞𝐫 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥𝐬 to go with their 𝐰𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐨𝐟 𝐠𝐞𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐨, not to forget 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞𝐬/𝐂𝐫𝐨𝐢𝐬𝐬𝐚𝐧𝐭/𝐁𝐫𝐢𝐨𝐜𝐡𝐞 too if you’re feeling it 😛

👇🏻Here’s what we tried!👇🏻
🧇𝐂𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐜 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 
𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐫𝐢𝐧 𝐂𝐥𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞 +𝐃𝐚𝐫𝐤 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜 𝐆𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐟𝐢𝐝𝐝𝐢𝐜𝐡

🥐𝐁𝐮𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐂𝐫𝐨𝐢𝐬𝐬𝐚𝐧𝐭
𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐥 𝐏𝐨𝐩𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐧+ 𝐏𝐮𝐥𝐮𝐭 𝐇𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐦

🥣𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐒𝐞𝐬𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐞𝐫 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥
𝐌𝐒𝐖 𝐃𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐚𝐧 

🥣𝐂𝐢𝐧𝐧𝐚𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐞𝐫 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥
𝐑𝐨𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐏𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐨

𝐎𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐠𝐞𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐬 𝐡𝐚𝐝 𝐚 𝐧𝐢𝐜𝐞,𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦𝐲-𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐲 𝐭𝐞𝐱𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐢 𝐞𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐲 𝐥𝐢𝐤𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐥 𝐏𝐨𝐩𝐜𝐨𝐫𝐧 (tastes more butterscotch-y) ,𝐌𝐒𝐖 (very rich and smooth, not too sweet for me) 𝐃𝐚𝐫𝐤 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜 𝐆𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐟𝐢𝐝𝐝𝐢𝐜𝐡 (rich with a hint of alcohol) amongst the flavours i tried. 𝐑𝐨𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐏𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐨 was also nice! 

𝐈’𝐝 𝐬𝐚𝐲 𝐠𝐨 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞𝐬/𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐞𝐫 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥𝐬/𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐂𝐫𝐨𝐢𝐬𝐬𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 𝐬𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐬𝐟𝐲𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐲 𝐜𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐩𝐲 (𝐬𝐰𝐢𝐩𝐞 ⬅️ 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐀𝐒𝐌𝐑😝) 𝐰𝐚𝐬 𝐭𝐚𝐝 𝐝𝐫𝐲😅 You can really taste the flavours for the waffle bowls (bssm’s more subtle but present) and i enjoyed the lightly crisp and fluffy waffles which has a slight sweetness to it - tastewise reminded me of a palmier/kouign amann pastry kind of flavour✨

.

description: Coffee, matcha or me😝
Life is especially good on a Friday

📍the marmalade pantry @ oasis hotel downtown 🍝

carbonara ($25) - this was the better pasta of the two, but nothing spectacular about it! i like my carbonaras thick and creamy but this was a tat watery.. def can find better and cheaper carbonaras elsewhere 😅

spicy crabmeat pasta ($26) - this felt ok on the first few bites, but it’s quite dry and the crabmeat started tasting a lil weird after a while 😐 there’s also lots of pine nuts in it, which we couldn’t rly appreciate 😬 

truffle fries ($14) - the truffle taste was quite strong, portion is not bad, but the fries are on the thicker and soggier side 😞

maybe should have ordered other mains instead but we were feeling pasta-y that day unfortunately 🥲

#sgfood #sgfoodies #sgeats #carbonara #trufflefries #fries #pastaparty #themarmaladepantry
Racines @ Sofitel 🤩🐻🥩
location: Racines At Sofitel Singapore City Centre

description:
📍twenty grammes @ north bridge road

hojicha soft serve on waffle - the waffles itself was crispy and decent, but the brownie cubes were way too hard 😖 not a big fan of hojicha but this wasn’t too bad i guess! also note that this is a half waffle so it’s good for 1 pax 🙆‍♀️

molten chocolate lava cake - this was okok only, sadly the lava cake wasn’t molten at all 🙁 comes with an ice cream scoop of your choice and we chose the tokyo banana flavour! it goes q nicely with the chocolate cake but j think of it as banana ice cream 🍌 the whipped cream was kinda unnecessary and my fav part was prolly the ice cream and caramelised cookie crumbles 😋

#sgfoodies #sgeats #sgcafe #wafflesandicecream #hojichasoftserve #chocolatelavacake #dessertsg #twentygrammes

📍hopscotch @ the capitol- stumbled upon this sweet little spot on entertainer and decided to give it a try!

truffle furikake angel hair pasta ($23) - they didn’t have angel hair pasta so it was replaced w linguine! the truffle taste is pretty strong, but we found the furikake j a tat bit excessive 🤭 but overall still a v yummy dish 😋

guinness beef bourguinon aka stew ($26) - wow the beef was SO good it was the melt in the mouth kinda tender 🤤 and the mashed potato tasted much better than it looked (well, not that it looks bad)- it’s v flavourful you can even j eat it on its own!

calamari rings ($12) - we rly loved this! the batter was so crispy and the portion was decent as well 👍 

the place is a little pricey, but they do have a very worth set lunch menu between 11.30am and 2.30pm for a starter, main and drink at $20++! 🤑

#sgfoodies #sgeats #trufflepasta #beefstew #calamarirings #hopscotchsg #yummy

📍nakhon kitchen- one of my fav places to get my thai fix and it’s also super affordable! used to alw patron the hv outlet (maybe I’m biased but still feel like the food there tastes better in general though 😅) 

featuring some of my to-go dishes:
pineapple fried rice & phad thai ($6 each) - i mean.. you can’t not order these mains right? but didn’t disappoint! although we did find the phad thai a little too watery for our liking 😬 

honey chicken ($6) - i rly like this 😋 if you like sweet chicken i think you’ll like it too hehe but some may find it a little too sweet! (the portion isn’t this small don’t worry we j couldn’t wait before taking the pic 🤭)

stir-fried kang kong thai style ($6) - nakhon rly nails their kang kong dishes! the vege is j so flavourful (you gotta try the gravy) but it’s slightly spicy so take notee 

tom yum chicken soup clear ($6) - okay tom yum soup lovers yall need to try this! the chicken isn’t spectacular & quoting my friend “j give me a bowl of clear tom yum soup with nothing else inside” HAHAHAH

and no we didn’t purposely order all the $6 dishes it j happened that way 🤣🤣

#sgfood #sgfoodies #sgeats #thaifood #thaifoodlover #pineapplefriedrice #phadthai #chicken #kangkongthaistyle #tomyumsoup #nakhonkitchen

If you’re familiar with the soft tofu served at SBCD Korean Tofu House, I have good news for you. Now you can get your fix of tofu soup at pocket-friendly prices at the newly opened @soontofusg express outlet in a coffeeshop. Diners get to choose from 6 types of soft tofu sets: Beef, Pork, Seafood, Assorted, Dumpling and Vegetable. Every set comes with kimchi, rice and a pack of seaweed. Thanks @_boyz86 for the invitation and @soontofusg for your warm hospitality 😊
.

Located at Capitol Singapore, @amiaddicted.sg is a ceramic studio cum vegan Korean cafe. If you’re interested in working with clay, you should give it a try. The Korean cafe is 100% vegan so you need not worry about meat in your food. Their Birds of Paradise which tastes as good as it looks can be enjoyed as a satisfying dessert. The Grilled Cheese Kimchi Sandwich with crispy toasted bread is definitely worth sinking your teeth into

Pasta lovers, the slurpworthy Torta Di Riso Pasta with tteokbokki sauce is for you. Fresh, hearty and full of flavour, their vegan-friendly Jardin Bibimbap is a delicious Korean rice bowl. Their Doenjang Truffle Risotto is a must try for all truffle lovers. Wash it all down with their instaworthy drinks. Thanks @liveloveatwithjie for the invitation and @amiaddicted.sg for your warm hospitality 😊
.
📍Am I Addicted 
13 Stamford Road 
B2-51/52/53 Capitol Singapore 
Singapore 178905
.

Let’s dive into a sea of flavours @miso.salmon. The Inaniwa Udon which is slender and chewy is imported directly from Japan. Diners are able to select from 6 different flavours of miso soup - Original, Garlic, Spicy, Sesame, Truffle or Fish Collagen. They also offer you the choice of building your own bowl with your choice of noodles along with a delectable assortment of seafood options and add-ons
.
Get lean AF with an option of Shirataki noodles that fill your tummy so you feel satisfied longer and end up eating less. Go for the Fish Collagen Miso Soup to boost your inner glow. Fall in love with the salmon slices which are amazingly tender and succulent. Accompany your meal with tasty sides like Truffle Edamame, Mentai Mayo Tamagoyaki and Chicken Karaage with Parmesan Cheese. Thanks @james.ek for the invitation and @miso.salmon for your warm hospitality 😊
.

Welcome to the third month of the year, March. It is the start of Spring, and here are our March seasonal menus available until the 15 of March.

1. Icefish Sashimi
2. Grilled Greenling with Japanese Peppe
3. Hairy Crab and Mozuku Seaweed with Salmon Roe
4. Sea Bream with Wasabi Flower

📍breakfast club

all-day breakfast, count me in!! fun fact: i don’t usually eat breakfast but i love breakfast food 🤡

𝐟𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐝 𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 & 𝐰𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 ($11.90)
i’ve had my fair share of chicken and waffles and while many places sell them, they each have their own creation of the dish. the waffle here was thin yet fluffy. the chicken was tender and had a slight tinge of spiciness which added more flavours to the chicken. 

𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 ($12.90)
this was a classic combination that wouldn’t go wrong - sausage, eggs, baked beans, french toast and many more. i could choose between 4 different kinds of carbs and i went with the french toast cause why not HEH nothing much to shout about but every component was well-executed and flavourful. 

overall, pretty value for money!! it allows you to satisfy your breakfast cravings without breaking the bank 💸

📍luna

i wanted to try their yuzu meringue cheese tart but their tarts are on a rotational basis so it wasn’t available on the day I visited 🥺

𝐠𝐨𝐦𝐚 𝐱 𝐩𝐛 ($8.50)
i’ve been having a mini peanut butter obsession so i just had to get this. i never knew goma and pb could go so well together, especially since they’re both pretty distinct by themselves. the pb flavour was stronger while the goma was more subtle and came as a aftertaste. i would have preferred a stronger goma intensity for a earthier and nuttier taste. i liked that the tart was firm and buttery instead of crumbly. 

𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚 ($8)
just judging from the colour, you know that this probably has an intense matcha flavour. matcha chiffon sponge filled with matcha mousse and matcha ganache, topped with matcha powder and chantilly cream - this was literally a matcha lover’s dream 💭 the matcha mousse was very rich and smooth, with a tinge of bittersweetness. despite how dense the cake looked, it was still pretty moist and not too heavy. if you’re a diehard fan of matcha, definitely give this a try!! 

they have so many interesting cakes and tarts so i cant wait to drop them another visit soon 🤤🤩

📍eggslut

late to the hype but i finally had the chance to visit eggslut 😚 

𝐟𝐚𝐢𝐫𝐟𝐚𝐱 𝐬𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐰𝐢𝐜𝐡 ($12++, additional $3 for bacon)
scrambled eggs, cheddar cheese and sriracha mayo sandwiched between soft brioche buns - some say this is overhyped but i definitely see why people love it. idk how they made the eggs so creamy and fluffy 🥺 adding bacon to the sandwich was the best decision ever!! it added another level of crispiness to the sandwich and helped to cut the jelakness of the eggs. everything just worked so well together, from the caramelised onions to the eggs. it did get a little messy to eat towards the end but we all love a good yummy mess 🤍

𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 𝐡𝐚𝐬𝐡𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐰𝐧𝐬 ($4.50++)
these were great hashbrowns, nicely fried with a crispy exterior but to call them 𝘵𝘳𝘶𝘧𝘧𝘭𝘦 hashbrowns… it could probably work with a stronger flavour. the truffle flavour was pretty faint and underwhelming. i would say these were still quite affordable for 6 pieces so do give them a try too.

📍mylo’s

located near gbtb, @mylosgelato serves quality gelato along with other fresh bakes and pastries. not only that, it is also a pet-friendly cafe so you’ll get to see many cute pups while enjoying the gelato.

i tried their 𝒘𝒉𝒊𝒕𝒆 𝒄𝒉𝒐𝒄𝒐𝒍𝒂𝒕𝒆 & 𝒎𝒂𝒄𝒂𝒅𝒂𝒎𝒊𝒂 and 𝒃𝒍𝒂𝒄𝒌 𝒔𝒆𝒔𝒂𝒎𝒆. the former was on the sweeter side but i could vividly taste the white chocolate in it. i loved that there were macadamia nuts incorporated so it added more textures to the gelato. the latter, which was my personal favourite, had a very prominent black sesame flavour - nutty with a tinge of earthiness. 

they have many other interesting flavours such chestnut and milk chocolate with miso. they also regularly launch their seasonal flavours so do keep a lookout for those!! definitely a good break from the sweltering heat after exercising in the area ☀️🍃

📍imakatsu

does anyone crave for jap food all the time? i could have jap food everyday and never get sick of it 🤤 headed to @imakatsusg_tonkatsu some time back to try their dishes and left feeling very satisfied hehe

𝐦𝐢𝐬𝐨 𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐤 𝐤𝐚𝐭𝐬𝐮 𝐬𝐞𝐭 ($29++)
the best miso pork katsu i had was in japan a few years ago and i rmb how much i loved it (despite not being a fan of pork katsu and queueing for over an hour for it 🙃) i’m so glad this didn’t disappoint!! the katsu was fried to perfection, leaving a crispy exterior while maintaining the succulent and tender texture of the pork. the miso sauce was very flavourful and tasted almost like the one i had in japan.

𝐮𝐧𝐚𝐠𝐢 𝐭𝐚𝐦𝐚𝐠𝐨𝐭𝐨𝐣𝐢 𝐬𝐞𝐭 ($21++)
THIS THOUGH, definitely get this if you’re a fan of eggs and unagi like me 🤩 the amount of eggs is insane, you have your runny egg at the top and silky smooth scrambled-like eggs sitting at the bottom. each unagi slice was very plump and almost melts in your mouth with each bite. the savoury sauce was also a good match with the warm rice, although it did get a little salty towards the end.

Deviating from my usual post format to do a little throwback to the dinner menu I tried at Alma last year! 

The snacks served before the meal was indeed an experience. They were all so creatively and exquisitely made, and was indeed a journey through sight, flavours, and textures! 

The butter served alongside the bread was so so goooood. The bread was nicely toasted, giving it a slight crisp on the outside and super fluffy inside! I might just go back again for their bread 😍

Finally made it to this super pretty floral theme cafe !! 

🧇 Croissant Waffle ($23.90) 

I kinda like the croissant waffle and the kurobuta pork toulouse sausage was so juicy and flavourful! Tho the rest of the items such as roasted potato and confit tomato were average, the scrambled eggs, similar to those served at Cafe de Nicole, were really bad 🙃 

🍞 Fig & Salted Caramel French Toast ($21.90) 

Looks pretty but not worth the price. You can probably skip this! 

🍰 Pistachio Raspberry Tart ($11) 

Subtle pistachio flavoured mousse with raspberry coulis and freeze dried raspberry. The tart base is buttery and is perfectly made. 

🥤 Sea Salt Caramel Latte ($10.90) 

A little pricey for a caramel latte but it was good coffee! Not too sweet as compared to the caramel latte I've tried at other places. 

Overall, a really pretty cafe for a nice brunch with the girls or just a floral themed date! Tho the food was average, this cafe is definitely worth a visit for its super pretty floral deco. For those with furkids, you can also bring them out for date and dine at the cafe's outdoor seating area. Lastly, I gotta commend the staff for their impeccable service as one of them followed us to the pick up point with umbrellas in the heavy downpour !! 

Rating: 6 / 10

New week new food !! 🥰 I finally got a chance to try this Isreali bistro, opened by celebrity chef Eyal Shani, and they indeed did not disappoint!! 

🥙 Pita Candy Brisket ($24) 

A good option for those who prefer a mix of sweet and sour flavours. The brisket, having been seared and caramelised over the grill, was on the sweeter side and hence the "candy" brisket. It was well balanced out by the slightly sour, tangy, and nutty flavours from the tahini, tomatoes, onions, and pickles.  

🥔 Run over potato ($11)

A very simple yet yummy side! The thinly sliced potato was roasted with butter, sour cream, garlic, and herb. It was served on a flat rectangular board & was quite an interesting sight! Definitely a sharing side I would recommend to pair with your pita 😋 

🍲 Intimate plate ($24) 

A wholesome plate of beef short ribs, roots stew, tahini, and chilli. Quite a heavy side to compliment the overflowing stuffed pitas but still worth a try with the super tender beef short ribs! 

Overall, a rather fuss free restaurant with a nice selection of pita and sides. I'm in no position to judge if this is indeed authentic but imo definitely one of the better restaurants serving isreali food in Singapore! 

Rating: 8 / 10

So I kinda like the mains more than the starters! Continuing from my previous post, here are some mains I've tried ☺ 

Acquerello Risotto ($48) 

If you're sitting indoors, you're in for a treat as you could opt for the risotto to be made live! The freshly cooked risotto was mixed in the parmigiano reggiano wheel live next to our table and was definitely an added experience to that evening. The amount of truffle on it was also simply generous yumm! 

Grilled Fermin Iberico Pork Pluma ($48) 

This was recommended by the restaurant staff and the Iberico pork slices were tender soft but beyond that, I can't remember much 🙃 

Overall, I would definitely recommend this place for a business dinner or date night just b'cos of the gorgeous view. However, in terns of the food, I they were simply just underwhelming. 

Rating: 6 / 10

Second time back at Monti and having visited this restaurant both in the day and evening, I prefer the evening ambience a lil more! The highlight for Monti was the gorgeous view overlooking the Fullerton Bay but the food was a lil tiny bit of underwhelming 🙃 First up, the starters we ordered: 

Pan Seared Hokkaido Scallops ($42) 

So apparently these plump juicy scallops were served in cauliflower puree, mortadella ham, truffle, and pistachio. The flavours were very muted and I could only remember the slightly sweet & plump scallops (tho I thought they could've been fresher and sweeter). 

Burratina Cheese ($38) 

Nothing wow-mazing about this starter but the burratina was fresh and creamy, complimented well by the savoury and herbiness from the 18 months aged San Daniele Ham, basil and coratina extra virgin oil. Definitely a mix of freshness, saltiness, and creaminess from various ingredients in this starter.  

Look out for the next post for the mains! 

Rating: 6 / 10

Paid a visit to @dailyground.co which has recently opened a few months back in Bukit Timah. The Daily Plate was pretty standard and fulfilling for a big breakfast, however the ribeye steak for the Ultimate Rosti felt abit overdone on the medium-medium well side when we had opted for medium rare. Besides the mains, they also offer daily fresh bakes of croissants and danish, as well as ice cream waffles from @sugartreegelato who shares the same space. Overall, we weren't blown away by the food, but ambience and service was great.

Located within Icon Village, new patisserie @aliceboulangeriesg offers a selection of finely crafted pastries and fresh bakes. Had the opportunity to try their pastry box which comprises the Champagne Ispahan, Yuzu Tart, Sea Salt Chocolate Tart, Pistachio Dacquiose, Hazelnut Paris Brest, and the Mango Cheesecake, as well as their signature bi-colour croissants - Lychee Raspberry, Pisatchio Chocolate and Peanut Butter. The Mango Cheesecake was pretty good, with small chunks of sweet mangoes atop a creamy yet light cheesecake. But the Pisatchio Chocolate was what got me sold, for its incredibly rich chocolatey goodness and flaky buttery croissant albeit the pistachio taste wasn't as pronounced. So sinfully indulgent yet so worthy of every calorie. 🥐

A beautiful hidden gem tucked away on the 8th level of the Hillview industrial building is @coexistcoffee.co decked in a bold half red and white interior. The hype has probably died down a little since its opening mid last year, but the place was still filling up fast and was full house by an hour into operation. 

The interior isn’t just the only thing that left an impression. The waffles was perfectly crispy and fluffy within, with a thick juicy slab of chicken, their Chilli Crab Shakshuka has got crispy mantou bites and mildly spiced chilli crab-tomato based sauce to dip the carbs in. Also went with a safe big breakfast option which didn’t disappoint at all. They have since opened two more outlets at Keong Saik and Paya Lebar with different concepts and menu which I think are worth exploring as well!

Discovered another great place for authentic and delicious taiwanese food @fengfoodsg !

🌟Hakka braised meat rice 客家卤肉饭 $9
They are very generous with the amount of braised meat as you can tell from the photo!  The braised meat was flavourful, tender, juicy and meat in the mouth! The ratio of the fats and lean meat was on point and it’s not too oily. The pickle veggies aside was slightly sour but it’s so refreshing for my liking! It’s definitely a great bowl of braised meat rice 👍🏻

🌟Pork chop with noodles in beef soup 猪排红牛汤面@$12.6
The pork chop was well marinated and it’s crispy on the edge and yet so tender in the middle. It taste similar to DTF’s pork chop to me. Beside, the beef soup tasted great as well! The soup was clear yet able to taste the sweetness of the beef! It’s such a great combo 🤩

The items they serve are extensive and I would like to be back for another visit to try out the other items! Besides, there is no service charge applies ✌️

TGIF! Had a scrumptious lunch @theflyingsquirrelsg 🥰

🌟 ASSORTED SUSHI BENTO 🍣 
There were Salmon, Tuna, White Fish, Ika, Surf Clam, Ebi, Inari & Tamago sushi! I had requested the sushi to be served as aburi sushi as I have been trying to cut down the consumption of raw food 😆
The sushi were just average but not particularly amazing as it’s lacking of some flavours from the seafood. I did not manage to taste the natural fragrance of fish oil from these aburi sushi.

🌟UNAGI DONBURI BENTO 🍚 
Braised Unagi in poached egg sauce with onions, scallions & seaweed. It’s a decent bowl as the unagi were soft and flavourful! ❤️

The tuna and avacado were so creamy! However, the seaweed shells were slightly harder to my liking. I would prefer if the shells to be crispier 🤭

Delicious and affordable muffins from bake_of (#02-111) located at Amoy Street Food Centre. There are a wide range of flavours available!

My favourites are tiramisu and matcha cream cheese! As for tiramisu, it’s really replicate the tiramisu desserts which we used to have. I am quite surprised with it 🤩Love the crumble crust on top as well!

As for the matcha, the matcha taste was subtle yet it’s so creamy as there was a good amount of cream cheese in it 😋 Yummmmm ❤️

📍San Francisco, CA
happy new year everyone!! 🍾🥂✨ i hope everyone is safe and healthy after the holidays~ my first new years post will be this cute little japanese restaurant in the mission 🇯🇵 there are a lot of unique and yummy dishes that you have the try!! the restaurant is small so make sure to make reservations before you go!! the lady who runs the place is literally the nicest person you will ever meet 🥺 she’s super sweet and will take the time to help you if you have some trouble ordering even tho she is managing the whole restaurant by herself. you guys have to try this hidden gem where the food, service, and atmosphere is amazing!! 👏🏻✨

It’s a snoozy mid-week and I decided to get a cuppa from @bimbocoffeesg! Ended up ordering a couple of them as I could not make up my mind and the plethora of coffee offerings at @bimbocoffeesg were just too tempting!!

Bimbo Coffee offers the conventional coffee like black and white coffee and also really unique flavours like yuzu and cinnamon. The coffee is brewed to order and the flavours are infused by the Bimbos themselves! The beans that they used are chosen carefully to match the different profiles and they use a variety of beans for different flavours to bring out the best in each of their coffee!

I tried the rose, mint, melon and red dates flavoured coffees and also their white coffee! You can choose whether you would like to have your coffee sweetened or unsweetened when you order them. My favourite would have to be the red dates coffee because the coffee is slightly on the stronger side and leaves my caffeine cravings satisfied!

Do check out the handcrafted coffees @bimbocoffeesg if you are longing for some caffeine shots or a cuppa creamy coffee!

Claypot Rice
•
Chunks of chicken, Chinese preserved sausages, liver sausages & salted fish covering a claypot of steaming hot rice. 
•
Mixing the rice w oil & dark sauce, the rice is simply marvellous. 
If only the burnt rice stick to the side & bottom of the claypot can be completely scraped off. 
•
Something about claypot rice, the smokiness, the saltiness, the sweetness all mixed into a bowl of rice. 
Wild party in the mouth. Umami. 
•
The bowl of chicken feet & peanuts soup round up the simple yet comforting meal.

Have been eyeing these yummy looking sandwiches from @sssan.doh for a while and finally got the chance to order them! The fried chicken sandwich was tasty with juicy chicken and pickles to help to balance the richness. It would be better if the chicken was still crispy but it might have lost the crisp during the delivery process. The egg sandwich was light and fluffy, packed with a lot of egg mayo and some ramen egg. Got both and shared half each and that was a great combi hehe

@mimibbq_sg has kbbq buffets at competitive prices for the quality offered with a variety of meat. The food was pretty good and we enjoyed our meal too! I hope to be back to try their other more unique items soon 🤤

More croissants from @aliceboulangeriesg~ Got the ham and cheese and pistachio chocolate this time. The ham and cheese was tasty with a generous portion of ingredients and the pistachio chocolate was rich, had nuts to add to that crunch and it wasn't too sweet too! Had them with my @karelcapek_official new year's tea 😌

description: Had the Smao Beef Burger at @clunyfoodcourt, one of @lesamisgroupsg's relatively new food establishments.  I liked how the buns were crisp outside and fluffy inside, the patty was juicy and tasty plus the cheese and pickles added flavour to the burger. Priced affordably at $12 with fries and coleslaw, it's good for its price point and it was a very filling meal too!
So happy that Woori has army stew back on the menu again. Truly my type of comfort food with many ingredients in it and tasty soup. I love their crispy kimchi pancake too 😋

Sunday Brunch Idea ✨

Finally swing myself to @bakersbenchbakery for the first time for lunch. 

I had the Sha(Soup)Ka which was an interesting soup version of Shakshuka though it was super watered down. Add extra $3 for Sausages.

Travel with to “Hong Kong” @lhk_singapore today.

No need to go all the way to Boon Lay to satisfy your Yuan Yang or Bolo Bun Cravings. Located at the more convenient @funansg! (Though space and menu are also more limited).

@bopgelato is now at Craig Road! 

Their 3rd and newest outlet is NOW OPEN along Craig Road - just beside the basketball court of Duxton Pinnacle! 

Popular flavour like White Chrysanthemum, Strawberry Basil and pistachio are highly recommended! 

I’ve gotten the chocolaty Midnight Gianduya (read Jan-doo-ya) - super rich and hazelnuty! $6 a pop and smashed cones at $2 a pack!

Still awaiting the SG TW VTL, so shall curb the craving with some #台灣早餐 from @fongshenghaosg！

They have $5 breakfast set on Monday-Friday (7.30am to 9am) 😇 I missed it by a few, so gotten the Spicy Pork Sandwich instead. Simple and good paired with a cup of Cold Milk Red Tea to start my day well!

description:
📍@queic.singapore 🧀

Visited @oliviarestaurant_sg awhile back to try their famous burnt cheesecake (#dtxolivia) and so happens that it’s also my first post here at @dtfoodaffair 😉

The restaurant doesnt allow dining in for desserts only and I’m glad to know that they have opened up a shop nearby to serve their desserts now 

Our orders 🧾
🧀 Olivia’s Homemade Cheesecake, $15+
🧀 Olivia’s Chocolate Cheesecake, $17+
🧀 Parmesan Cheesecake, $10+

Olivia’s Homemade Cheesecake 🧀⭐️
Still the star of the show and one of the best burnt cheesecakes around! Instead of the usual slice that is served at the restaurant, you get a whole 4” tart now. Oozy blue cheese centre with a crispy tart base..mm..yummy! 😋👌🏻

Olivia’s Chocolate Cheesecake 🍫🧀
If you are not a big fan of cheese, you could try their chocolate cheesecake which is richer in chocolate and comes with hazelnut praline. The dark chocolate cream is thick, creamy and not that sweet. I prefer cheese and oozy filling so I’ll pick the original any time 😁

Parmesan Cheesecake 🧀
Another option for cheese lover. The parmesan cheese is rich, creamy and pretty strong. May get a tad cloying since it’s rich and creamy. Better for sharing!

.

.
.

description:
Sourdough Croissants from
📍@sourbombebakery 🥐

Having tried their bombolinis previously (#dtxsourbombe), I was curious about their sourdough croissants and got myself a box to try end of last year 😁

Signature Box 🎁
🥐 Ispahan
🥐 Kaya W Soy Caramel
🥐 Pistachio Mango
🥐 Black Sesame Mochi
🥐 Passionfruit Meringue
🥐 OG Croissant

They come up with new flavours pretty regularly tho so some of these flavours are no longer available 🙈 I think only the kaya and pistachio still remain in their current lineup 🙊 and ofc, the plain one as well

Anyway, before I move on to the fillings, gotta say the texture of the croissants didnt quite hit the mark for me as they are not buttery or flaky even after reheating. Not sure if that’s the case for sourdough croissants 🤔

Ispahan 🥐🌹
Light floral and lychee fragrance. The lychee custard is a bit sweet with a hint of tanginess from the raspberry rose jam

Kaya W Soy Caramel 🥐
The kaya custard is quite fragrant with a hint of coconut fragrance. A bit on the sweet side

Pistachio Mango 🥐🥭
Slightly crispier and more flakey since it’s flatter than the rest. Pistachio frangipane filling with actual mango bits. The pistachio is pretty light in flavour

Black Sesame Mochi 🥐
Oozy black sesame custard filling that is milky and mild. Not much roasted fragrance and black sesame taste. This is topped with hojicha creme that is also milky but at least has a slight roasted flavour

Passionfruit Meringue 🥐
The passionfruit curd is sourish and doesnt have that citrusy fragrance. The meringue is dense and a bit cloying

OG Croissant 🥐
Slightly flakier than the rest but still not buttery. There is a slight tang from the sourdough

Tbh, I prefer their bombolinis over the croissants 😬

💸: $39 (excluding delivery fee)

.
.
.
.
