description:
📍@onalu_sg 🥯(with PROMO code)

First tried @onalu_sg sometime last year (#dtxonalu) and this round I ordered their bagels through @pickupp.sg . Good option if you are wfh since you can get these delivered to you for free 😉 Do read on for the promo code 

My order 🧾
🥯 Deviled Spam, $8
🥯 Somethin’ Fishy, $11

Got their 2 popular flavours to try and I have made another order for other flavours for their next groupbuy. Look out for that if you are interested 😁

Deviled Spam 🥯🍳
(Spam, Cheddar & Monterey Jack Cheese, Mashed Deviled Eggs)

The bagel is soft and perfectly chewy..texture is perfect coz it’s not the tough kind 😁 As for the filling, the deviled egg (creamy egg mayo) is slightly peppery and I found the overall flavour to be on the saltish side because of the spam and cheese. Nonetheless, I still enjoyed the texture of the bagel tho!

Somethin’ Fishy 🥯🐟
The charcoal bagel is slightly chewier than the plain one but not overly tough..but between the 2, I still prefer softer bagel ofc 😝 Generously stuffed with thick cuts of smoked salmon slices that are not salty..coupled with scallion cream cheese, onions, tomatoes, capers & dill which help to balance the smoked salmon flavour and provide a nice slight tang to the overall flavour

Will be trying the ‘Otak Otak’ and ‘Bogogi Beef’ next so you can look out for that review 😉 

📢 PROMO‼️ They are currently available on @pickupp.sg and if you quote ‘dtfoodaffair’, you can get a $5 off with min. $14 purchase. Valid for both new and existing customers with unlimited usage!! 😉

Had never try nyonya food before in sg. The previous times I’ve tried were in melacca & I’ve fell in love ever since 😍

Visited @the.blueginger at their first outlet in Tanjong Pagar. It’s a 3-storey high building and they’re also a Michelin Bib Gourmand recipient 😍

Ordered most of the signature dishes including 𝐀𝐲𝐚𝐦 𝐛𝐮𝐚𝐡 𝐤𝐞𝐥𝐮𝐚𝐤, 𝐍𝐠𝐨 𝐡𝐞𝐨𝐧𝐠, 𝐂𝐡𝐚𝐩 𝐜𝐡𝐲𝐞, 𝐀𝐬𝐚𝐦 𝐟𝐢𝐬𝐡, 𝐔𝐝𝐚𝐧𝐠 𝐧𝐲𝐨𝐧𝐲𝐚 & 𝐝𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐚𝐧 𝐜𝐞𝐧𝐝𝐨𝐥. I’ve got to say the food were all hella good 😩🤤🤤 We couldn’t stop ourselves as the food were sooo flavorful & delicious. 

My favorite dish of the day would be the asam fish cus oh boy they sure know how to make that fish & that gravy, damn too good. 

The desserts were heavenly as well. But yes, pulut hitam was my top pick with that thick ass paste and right amount of coconut milk 🥥 

Overall a really nice experience here and would definitely come back for their food 😍

Entering their 9th year here in Singapore and nestled in the hustling streets of Telok Ayer, is @sarnies.sg , known for their good coffee, people & food. 

Visited them on a sunny saturday morning and was greeted with a bunch of bikers having their break time. Enjoyed the atmosphere there and immediately ordered their 𝐀𝐯𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐝𝐨 𝐭𝐨𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐞𝐠𝐠𝐬. Can never deny my love for avos. There's feta cheese, 2 poached eggs, roasted tomatoes, dill, cashew nut dukkah all on a rye sourdough toast. Gotta say they were suuuuper generous with that avo. Looks like a whole week's worth of avo to me 😂

Also got their 𝐁𝐚𝐜𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐞𝐠𝐠 𝐨𝐧 𝐜𝐢𝐚𝐛𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐚 with their home-cured bacon, two fried eggs and tomato relish. Like how crispy the bacon were and those who crave for something savory for their breakkie, this shall be it.

description:
Happy Lunar New Year, everyone 🏮

Is anyone else having dim sum this CNY? 'Twas the first time I came across a Bak Kut Teh infused Xiao Long Bao at Jia He Chinese Restaurant. Though the Bak Kut Teh flavours weren't very prominent, it still has a pretty tasty broth, and the red hue of the Xiao Long Bao is rather fitting for Chinese New Year 🧧

☕ @tobysestatesg is @tobeysestatecoffee's Asian flagship store, specializing in roasted coffee, using raw globally-sourced green beans since 1997. Popular among locals & expats for their brunch, healthy bowls and burger selection, I would like to draw your attention to their exceptional pasta dishes.

🍝 While flipping through their tagged posts, it's evident that not many customers order the pasta compared to brunch, but rest assured that they are just as good. The Prawn & Clam Pasta consists of al Dante spaghetti tossed in a tangy, spicy marinara sauce reminiscent of the chilli crab sauce, which went very well with the seafood. The clams were excellent—juicy, not rubbery and had no fishy taste. The prawns were good but might've been a little overcooked, resulting in some resistance when separating the meat from its tail. Overall, a very decent pasta dish 👍

You would have known that I go to Chatterbox at least once a month for their chicken rice and lobster laksa, and had to stop while they were undergoing renovation. They'll finally be reopened soon (currently planned for 14 March), and I'm most excited that I can resume my monthly visits again.
🔸
To me, they serve the best chicken rice in Singapore. At $25++, it might be 10x the price of a chicken rice at a hawker centre, and might not be 10x the quality (how do you measure that anyway?), but it's only at Chatterbox do I get rice that's very fragrant without being oily, and chicken that's naturally sweet in flavours without being too fat. To achieve that, they use old rice that is able to soak up flavours better, and free range chicken of a fixed age with a good balance of fat and lean meat. They also have more time and space, so they can go though a time consuming and space intensive process to cook them, not normally possible at a hawker stall. Not to mention their chilli, soya sauce, ginger, and even the soup were all really good too. So yes, I'll go there monthly for a plate of chicken rice, instead of 10 plates elsewhere.
🔸
There are other excellent dishes too. Their signatures remained as good after the renovation, with Chef Liew still at the helm. I still love their hokkien mee ($25), rojak ($15), satay ($14 for four skewers), and coconut ice cream ($15). But during my last visit, I found that I also love the mackerel and crab otah ($18), wok fried sambal wing beans ($12), coffee pork ribs ($26), lemon butter tiger prawns ($28), and sea perch with burnt green chilli ($35).
🔸
It's really one place that does hawker food really well. It's not just about serving hawker food in an aircon environment, but it's really their craft that makes me visit them over and over again.
.

This stall at AMK is famous for their Power Mee Rebus, but I found myself drawn to the Drumstick Mee Soto.
🔸
Besides the tender 'fall-off-the-bones' large chicken drumstick that almost filled the entire bowl, I also liked the soup which was savoury and robust. It has enough tumeric and chicken flavour in it, with a tinge of spice. And that thin layer of chicken oil floating on the soup kept the mee soto warm and made it especially comforting for our rainy Feb weather.
📍

If I were to rank all 12 omakase places I visited last year, Hamamoto is my number 1. You would have seen photos of fancy courses with lobster, bone marrow, and caviar, but Chef Kazu Hamamoto does each sushi really well too. The shari was flavourful, and so was the neta. I especially love how well their shimofuri goes with the rice.

description:
OH-MY-SHROOMS 🍄4-Course Dinner at Winestone, at just $78++ per person. 

This Spring, embark on a culinary journey with an all-mushroom delectable 4-Course Dinner that heralds earthy flavours at Winestone, Novotel Stevens.

Executive Chef S. Punniammurti, also known as Chef Murti, has specially curated an innovative menu surrounding 7 types of humble and nutrient-packed mushrooms, each dish bound to tantalise your tastebuds with bursting flavours.

🥗Cold Appetizer; 
Terrific Green Synonyms; Mixed Salad, Prosciutto Ham, Pink Oyster Mushrooms, roasted Pine Nuts, White Balsamic Vinaigrette. 

OR

Smoked Duck with Hon-Shimeji Mushrooms; Smoked Duck Breast, White and Brown Hon-Shimeji Mushrooms, Herbs Dressing. 

🍝 Warm Appetizer; 
Tagliatelle with Spicy Chorizo Sausages and Mushrooms; Tagliatelle Pasta, Swiss Brown Mushrooms, sliced Chorizo Sausages. 

OR

Pesto Prawns with Maitake Mushrooms and Tomatoes Prawns; Fresh Basil Herbs, Maitake Mushrooms, semi-dried Tomatoes, Rocket Leaves.

🍴Mains
Scottish Salmon with Golden Mushrooms; Salmon Fillet, Lemon and Thyme, Spinach Cream, Local Golden Mushrooms.

OR

Grilled Ribeye with Morel Mushrooms; Grilled Ribeye, Rosemary, Creamy Morel Mushroom Sauce.

OR

Seafood with White Hon-Shimeji Mushrooms; Prawns, Scallops, Slipper Lobsters, Black Mussels, Tomatoes Basil and Pesto, White Hon-Shimeji Mushrooms.

🥧Desserts; 
Truffle Burnt Cheesecake OR Apple Wild Mushroom Tarts.

I have so 🍄 Mushroom in my stomach for these delectable dishes! My favourite dish is the Scottish Salmon with Golden Mushrooms with tender salmon fillet that's marinated with lemon and thyme and served with Spinach Cream and sautéed Golden Mushrooms. It's so savoury and mouthwatering! 👍

I also like its clean and spacious interior, and also its extensive choices of wine and champagne. Get a bottle of wine starting from just $23nett. 

This curated experience is made available from now till 31st March. A must-try especially for Mushroom lovers.

Free 🅿️ Parking for diners! Winestone is located at 📍30 Stevens Rd, Novotel Stevens Level 1 Singapore 257840. For reservation, click on the link at @winestone.sg Bio or 📞64916100.

[Hidden Gem 💎] A gastronomic adventure awaits you at BRDL where you get to enjoy a splendid 4-course dinner at just $58++ per pax!

It was an exceptional meal at @brdlsg, where we sampled their exclusive dinner menu, specially curated for @nespresso.sg Singapore Restaurant Week. 

BRDL Restaurant Week Dinner Set $58++/4 course. 

🍞 Welcome Snack; Daily Rotation of surprises from the Kitchen. 

🍴 Starters; 
Foie Gras & Duck Leg Terrine (Strawberry/Brioche/Balsamic) 
OR Mussel Chowder (Blue Lip Mussel/XO Sauce) 

🍽️ First Mains; 
Roasted Cod (Ginger & Soy Veloute/Fish Maw/Preserved Cabbage Salad 
OR Green Curry Barramundi (Green Curry Tea Puree/Tom Kah/Compressed Green Mango) 

🍖 Second Mains; 
Herb Crusted Lamb Rack OR Wagyu Cheek Rendang. We had the Mongolia Pork Belly (Part of Set Lunch Menu) and BBQ Chicken as we don't really take Beef and Mutton. 
*Changing of Mains is subject to availability of the restaurant, but according to my fellow diners, their Lamb Rack and Wagyu Rendang are awesome as well! 

🥧 Desserts; Mango Sticky Rice OR Durian Cheesecake 

This meal was a gastronomical experience that left us full but still wanting for more. All dishes were prepared with great care and attention to detail; Even the desserts items, especially the Durian Cheesecake were perfectly executed. 👍 Consider ordering a bottle of dessert wine 🍷 to end off a perfect evening! 

BRDL Bar & Restaurant is situated in a modern semi-industrial building along Braddell road, and is part of the Refectory collection of F&B concepts. 📍351 Braddell Rd, Singapore 579713. 3 Course Lunch Set is also available at $38++

Both set lunch and dinner are available until 27th March. For reservation, click on the link on @brdlsg Bio.

description:
Experience Indian Cuisine, right in the heart of Singapore! 

Located within one of the shop-houses at Upper Circular Road; Restaurant Manam is a modern classy restaurant that serves hearty southern indian cuisine with spices that delight the senses. 

Drawing from the rich culinary heritage, Manam uses the finest ingredients in its spices to create aromatic and fragrant dishes, and the freshest cuts of sustainably sourced fresh meat. 

Each dish in Manam is made to order, and they are able to provide customisation upon request. Here's what we had; 🍽️

🍢Paneer Tikka ($18); Cottage Cheese Marinated With Curd and Indian Spices and Cooked in the Traditional Tandoor Oven.

🌾 Chicken Dum Biryani ($21); 
Aromatic Basmati Rice Cooked with Tender Chicken and Freshly Ground Spices.

🍲Butter chicken ($20); An Elegant Dish of Tender Chicken Simmered with Tomatoes- Cashew Gravy, Butter and Spices.

🥖Garlic Naan ($6); Indian Style Leavened Flatbread, Garlic Flavor.

🦐Eral Maangai Masala ($22);
Prawns Cooked with Raw Mango and Aromatic Spices

🍖Mutton Rogan Josh ($21);
Succulent Pieces of Mutton Braised in Gravy Flavoured with Aromatic Spices. 

📣Weekdays Lunch Special! Working in CBD area and craving for a good Briyani? Their Briyani Meal is at $14.90 and it includes Briyani + Soup/Soft Drinks + Gravy + Raita. 

Restaurant Manam is located at 📍15 Upper Circular Road #01-01, Singapore 058413 📞9824 9000 Tuesday – Sunday Lunch : 11:00am to 03.00pm & Dinner : 6:00pm to 10.00pm; Closed on Monday.

Good Morning! 🌄 Any plans for today? Well, I'm sure you would agree with me that Brunch is always a good idea - especially on a  Sunday! 🕊️

[NEW] Around the World Brunch Menu ✈️ The folks at Supply & Demand Orchardgateway has recently added 12 new exclusive dishes ($16 to $19) on their weekend 🍳brunch menu - inspired by 12 different travel destinations such as Canada, Sweden, Poland, just to name a few. 

From Asian delights to European delicacies, the chefs have added a personal touch to each dish, while paying homage to the original. Here's what we had; 🍽️

🥪Mentaiko Otak-Otak Tartine; 
🍕La Mattina Dopo (The Morning After Pizza)
🍞Toast Skagenrora
🍹Yuzu Highball
🦪Freshly Shucked Oysters
🍝Hiyashi Chuka
🍟Garlic Truffle Fries

This is the restaurant for you, if you want something more than the usual Eggs Benedict or American Big Breakfast! It's refreshing to be able to try dishes from Sweden (Toast Skagenrora) and Japan (Hiyashi Chuka), just to name a few. 

Around the World Brunch Menu ✈️is available exclusively at Supply & Demand Orchardgateway from 11.30am - 4pm on Weekends. 

Brunch without alcohol is just breakfast! Don't forget to check out their range of cocktails 🍹 🍸that's priced between $13 - $14. Getting a drink would also allow you to enjoy their Freshly Shucked Pacific Oysters Flown From USA at a special price of just $2 per piece. 

Supply & Demand Orchardgateway is located at 📍277 Orchard Rd, Level 02-13/14 Orchardgateway, Singapore 238858.

🚂 All aboard Food Junction's newest train-themed outlet at Great World; The First Local Food Court With Alfresco Rooftop Seating AndImmersive LED Display Experience! 🚃

A food court like no other; The Food Junction at Great World has recently went thru a face-lift and now offers an awesome dining experience with great-tasting food at an affordable price. 

Fitted with a 🚂 🚃 train-themed decor reminiscent of thepopular Great World Amusement Park’s Ghost Train ride and the historic TanjongPagar Railway Station, elements from train stations around the world are adopted tofurther enhance the overall immersive experience, with food stalls and walkwaystastefully designed to resemble train carriages and station platforms.The centrepiece of the outlet is a 22-metre-long LED digital ceiling that is mirrored bya railway track installation on the ground. 

Offering a diverse mix of mini restaurants and food stalls under one location, dinerscan take their taste buds around the globe with the exciting yet affordable variety ofcuisines available, ranging from Thai to Vietnamese and Japanese. Each minirestaurant also reflects its own unique concept and designated seats fordifferentiation, ensuring a varied and quality selection for diners to sample.

Here's what we had; 🍽️

🐟What The Fish; Sea Bass Half Fish with Tail (Golden Tantalising Punch) $12.80

🍔 Hungry Korean; Gourmet Chicken Burger $7.90

🐷 Viet Taste; Hanoi BBQ Pork Noodles $8.80 My Favourite 👍

🥘Queen of Wok; Red Grouper Fish Head Mini Hot Pot $28 (1-2pax) Fresh and tasty 👍

🐔 Putian Heng Hwa Cuisine; Heng Hwa Red Rice Wine Claypot Chicken $12 

🍱 Der Biergarten; Chicken Schnitzel Soba Noodles Bowl $10.90 & Smoked Salmon Salad Bowl $12.90

🍖Gyudon Toroah; Signature Gyudon with Onsen Egg $8.90 (Reg)

🥤Ke; OG Lemon Punch $3.60, Mint Lemon Punch $3.90, Kopi Slush $2.80, Coco Cloud $4.50 & Sea Salt Chendol $2.20.

Food Junction (Great World City) is located at 📍1 Kim Seng Promenade, Level 3, Singapore 237994

description:
Pepper is a true blue SG dog😂🇸🇬⁣
⁣
Pepper is almost 3 years old and it’s been a fabulous journey. Till today, I’m still learning new things about her! Whenever I make Pepper sit and stay, her ears tend to point outwards while she looks left and right. With help from the Animal & Veterinary Service, I learnt that this signifies that she is on high alert and ready to run to/front anything or anyone that she is unfamiliar with, because I am no longer giving her a sense of security by being right beside her. ⁣
⁣
As a pet owner, it is important to understand the behaviour of your pets to better manage their health and well-being. If you’re keen to learn more about animal ethology and the science behind animal behaviour, check out AnimalBuzzSG on Facebook (go.gov.sg/animalbuzz)!

[TASTING]

AUTHENTIC RUSSIAN DELIGHTS IN TANJONG PAGAR!

Despite the ongoing conflict, Dumplings.Ru @dumplings.ru are certainly doing things right by acquainting more Singaporeans with the wonders of Russian-Ukrainian food.

Highlights of my meal would definitely include the Dumpling Combo Platter ($19.90+). 

12 X dumplings, 12 X different fillings such as Paneer Cheese and Minty Ram. Super IG-worthy also la, for  the dumplings like rly colourful all👍

Another star would be the Ukrainian Borscht Soup ($9.50+). 

Wah, the soup really very power, it’s like thick and creamy yet so light on the tongue, v easy to swallow. Inside got stuff like pork, beetroot and tomato, and they all come together to form a crazy-good flavour combi.

The Cheese and Pork Chebureki ($12+) remind of 1x mahssive curry puff, minus the curry. Airy, crispy + savoury af, wah shiok!

If u aren’t already fawning over how amazing their star dishes are, try the Salted Herring or Seledka ($12.90+) or their interesting drinks, Kompot and Kvass (from $5.50+) , that u won’t find in any kopitiam I swear

We recommend: Combo Platter, Chebureki, Seledka, Borscht Soup (wish they had a buffet for at least some of their menu items istg🤩)

Main gripe: Prices for some dishes can be a bit high 

Overall: 4.25/5 (this place definitely needs more clout, we’d return again again and again)

Thanks @protegieconsultancy for helping to coordinate this as well!

[HOME-BASED TASTING]

CREAMY BASQUE BURNT CHEESECAKES BY ONE LAST LICK!

There was legit a time where I saw the recognisable burnt cheesecake show up on everyone’s story and it was trending for a bit until ppl got jelak and sian of it then suddenly disappear 

One Last Lick’s version has to be one of the better ones out there frfr, bc they managed to get wonderful balance in their cakes la

Flavours wise, the cheese really can taste one ah say serious, balancing out the sweet well ah sweechai butterfly…

Then textures also can taste the contrast, even inside the cake sia… what we mean by this is that the cheesy inside has both gooey and harder layers that you can actually taste. The exterior also got a bit of caramel taste, q happy can taste a bit of the burnt taste too. 

The high quality of ingredients used definitely justifies the price tag of $38.90! It’s more better and way less pricey than your usual Burnt Cheesecake for sure!

We recommend: the whole thing la just get, it’s that good!

Main gripe: As with most cheesecakes, it can taste a bit jelak and repetitive after a while 

Thank you again @onelastlick.sg for sending over your wonderful Basque Burnt Cheesecake!

MICHELIN BIB GOURMAND SRI LANKAN DELIGHTS AT JALAN BESAR!

Kotuwa @kotuwa.sg blew my mind sia…

Pic 1: The Chicken Kottu ($22++) was really PACKED with a multitude of flavours and textures. 

Starts off with a lil bit of spiciness, savouriness and then the aromatic spices just hits u right outta nowhere. 

A mesmerising dish that you have to try for yourself to legit know what I’m talking about frfr

Pic 2: The Watalappam Tart ($16++) clearly had us like🤨🤨at first but it was rly built different ah… 

A rly rich coconutty custard balanced out the rly distinct taste of cardamom in the tart, which was  such a refreshing combi!

Pic 3: Mix of Mutton Rolls and Crab Cutlet. Just get them ah, no questions asked. If u don’t, confirm regret one. 

If we’re talking SUPER CRISPY fried panko breaded and generous mutton and actual crab fillings, look no further already ah..

We recommend: literally anything on the menu just go try ah serious

Main gripe: some of their dishes might be on the spicier side, so I suggest u lower ur ego and politely request and hope they bring down the spiciness level of your dishes (if possible)

Overall: 4.5/5 (absolute MUST-TRY, no gimmicks here, just pure awesomeness!)

DRY SCALLION OIL NOODLES WITH FRIED PORK CHOP UNDER $15 AT HOLLAND VILLAGE!

Mian Jia Noodle Bar @mianjia_sg has these hearty, savoury scallion oil noodles that I’m straight up dying for rn. 

Topped with bonito flakes to give the dish an extra OOMPH, the noodles are flavourful throughout and their portion size also quite big.

The juicy pork chop also q generously given, with a solid crunch, gelling well with the noodles!

We recommend: Five Spice Crispy Pork Chop with Special Sauce Dry Noodle ($10.90+)

Main gripe: you might get this dehydrating feeling after a whole bowl of noodles, remember to hydrate loads too!

Overall: 4/5 (one of HV’s hidden gems!)
location: Mian Jia Noodle Bar 麺家料理

description:
WAGYU BEEF RICE BOWL, TOM YUM SEAFOOD PASTA AND COCONUT KUEH POUFFLE AT TELOK BLANGAH!

The ambience of Old Habits Cafe @oldhabitssg is retro  and super nostalgia evoking, as you see all sorts of knickknacks from the past when you walk in

I’d personally just return for the vibes central, transporting me back to the era of Kids Central, Anything and Whatever (IYKYK)

The Wagyu Beef Rice Bowl ($18.90) immediately caught my eye, with flamed and torched wagyu beef resting on a bed of butter rice, together with a selection of greens. 

Wah, so healthy ah, was the first thing I thought, but the healthy part was balanced out by the sinful homemade sauce served too. 

Tho I couldn’t pinpoint exactly what the sauce was, it tasted mayo-like with the umaminess from mentaiko sauce, which I didn’t mind at all.

The beef was on the chewy side but still robust and juicy enough for me to savour it, with their generosity being a plus point

In all honesty, the Tom Yam Seafood Pasta ($18.90) will be better known for the large amount of seafood given, rather than how appetising it was.

The sauce did have a slight sting but it lacked richness in flavour, so it was p much watery with hints of sour and spicy here and there

However, the Coconut Kueh Pouffle was a big W in our opinion

The creamy vanilla ice cream gelled well with the decadent pandan coconutty taste of the pouffle. 

A+ for creativity tho because it’s literally the first time we’ve seen a fusion of bread pudding and soufflé in a dessert🔥🔥🔥

We recommend: Wagyu Beef Rice Bowl, Coconut Kueh Pouffle, coming for their AMBIENCE

Main gripe: not exactly super near an MRT, still need take bus for 10-15 mins

Overall: 3.9/5 (return for the super retro vibes and interesting menu!)

Sen-ryo (Ion orchard)

1. Tuna trio don 
- most worth it item on the menu! The chutoro is sooo fatty that it looks like otoro! And the negitoro and akami is so fresh and amazing too! 
A plate of salmon belly - 4 thick slices for 8 dollars quite a steal!

2. Aburi mentaiko salmon - best quality to price ratio - absolute top notched - beats itacho/hitoyosushi hands down and 2 dollar a piece! Amazing!

3. Grilled chicken wings - perfectly seasoned crispy skin with moist tender meat on the inside. Yums another must get!

4. Tempura Assortment 8 dollars. Has 2 huge fresh ebi and other veges as seen. Shitake Mushroom is so plump and juicy! Ebi not as flavourful as tenjin but the price to quality factor can't be beat here!

5. Item on their seasonal menu - cheese grilled oyster
- it's ok, rather fresh but nothing too spectacular

Senryo is becoming our favourite Japanese restaurant. Quality to price is mind boggling good. However the wait times can be quite long so be prepared.

Tampopo Grand (Takashimaya)

1. Salmon chirashi
- fresh fatty salmon thickly sliced on a bed of well seasoned sushi rice. Unfortunately wasabi isn't up to par

2. Aburi salmon / crab meat maki - ooo soo good almost Comparable to that at @hitoyosushi or @kohsushibar 

3. Wagyu/unagi/korubuta trio don - the pork outshines the other two. Wagyu isn't that tender though well seasoned and eel fluffy and fresh but not grilled to perfection like the likes of @manmanunagi.

Overall good standard for a Japanese meal. Nothing too outstanding but they have definitely hit the mark on the checklist except the wasabi.
Good quality green tea too!

@mcdsg Kit Kat McFlurry 
S$3.00

This is a simple one to review. Standard McDonald’s vanilla ice cream + milk chocolate + Kit Kat balls.

Milk chocolate is too little and too thin. Doesn’t alter/cover the taste of the dbade vanilla too much, making it tasting pretty standard. The Kit Kat balls are so tiny and it doesn’t have much wafer. The wafer in the Kit Kat is something that I find really unique and with the kept at a minimal, not too sure how “Kit Kat” this is.

You still get a mouthful of Kit Kat taste when you bite multiple balls together. Good thing is that with the thinner milk chocolate cream/fudge/sauce (whatever you wanna call it), the whole ice cream + Kit Kat balls doesn’t feel overwhelming sweet.

Not a game changer for me but does it’s job as a ice cream. Makes me happy still.

Rating - 💧 💧💧

@donpieclub Signature Chicken Pie
S$7.50

Back for more!

The pie uses the same light buttery flaky crust, which has the same subtle buttery fragrance. Inside, you will find potato, sliced button mushrooms, chicken chunks, peas and amazingly, half a hard boiled egg!

Everything apart from the boil is cooked in a stew. It’s slightly dry but the chicken chunks are nicely cooked and they are pretty generous with the chicken. I never knew why people add peas and I never had nice peas before. Totally hate the peas but potato was nice and sweet. Egg here is kinda extra. Totally not needed.

I think the price is horrendous. It’s too expensive for a pie with pretty standard ingredients. Not overly great tasting as well.

Rating - 💧 💧💧

@sunkistcitrus Cool Salty Lemon Jelly Soda 
S$1.60

From @7elevensg. 

Been seeing a lot of jelly drinks popping up recently. Not sure why as none of it seems to be revolutionary (at least for the ones I’ve tried).

Instructions on the can advice consumers to give it “10 strong shakes”. I gave it a lot more shakes and ended up with a liquidity form drink, with mild bumps in texture. This is good in a way that it allows you to customize your own choice in texture. If you want it more jelly like and fun, shake it less. For me, having it in this form is totally fine. It’s way easily to drink and pour out from the opening of the can.

Taste wise, it’s pretty close to salty honey lemon. It’s has a very subtle fizz to it and everything is pretty light in taste as well. You definitely taste more salt as the main flavor, followed by the light sourness of lemon and ending off with it being sweet. Pretty standard salty lemon drink stuff.

It’s extremely high in sugar although it doesn’t take like it. 9.6g / 100ml is no joke. Always be looking what you drinking.

Rating - 💧 💧💧

@mcdsg Chocolate Pie
S$1.70

Making a comeback with the McGriddles, it’s the chocolate pie!

The crust is similar to the original Apple Pie. It’s flaky and has a nice crunch but this time with a subtle dark chocolate flavor. Chocolate flavors in the crust is not prominent and in your face but slightly different from the Apple Pie. 

Dark chocolate cream fills the centre of the pie. It’s not overly sweet, has a slightly bitter taste, mimicking 60% dark chocolate flavors. The dark chocolate is done pretty well, without the “oily”, cheap chocolate taste. It’s also creamy and has a pretty consistent texture. I like the emphasis on chocolate flavors throughout the pie, while avoiding how typical cheap chocolate products can end up tasting like.

This is something that you definitely want to have it hot. Once it cools down, the flavor, texture and satisfaction dips drastically.

Wheat Baumkuchen Teriyaki Chicken Soba
S$8.30

Mainly available in the city area, this brand has been a long time favorite of mine in terms of quick fix “healthier choice” kinda meals. I’ve added the Sous Vide egg for $1 here as I’m a huge sucker for eggs.

The star really is the sauce for the soba. Loved it to bits. It’s a mix of goma sauce with the sweetness of the teriyaki sauce, forming a perfect blend of tangy, sweet and savory. Soba is well cooked and doesn’t clump up together even after transporting the food home accounting for over 30 minutes of traveling time.

Adding the egg makes a world of difference as the yolk adds a thicker consistency and flavor. Sad to say the sous vide egg was slightly overcooked. The chicken is nicely marinated but slightly tough. Full of flavor but is a little dry. 

Always loved their offerings and prices as it’s pretty affordable. A little more soba will be nice. Oh and if anyone knows them personally, please let them know the links to their socials on their main website is not working. Both FB and IG.

◾Bonbons [$3+/pc]

Missing these bonbons from none other than @lemuelchocolate!

Lemuel Chocolate has reopened its doors to a spanking new space over at Star Vista! The bean-to-bar chocolate makers place an emphasis on quality, flavour and sustainability - roasting and churning out delectable chocolate treats right in front of your eyes to boot! @lemuelchocolate even sources and imports their quality cacao beans from farmers all over the world.

I was honoured to be invited to their soft launch/food tasting sometime ago and got to try their numerous chocolate goodies! They were also generous enough to give us a box of their eye catching geometrical Bonbons! Well, I couldn't help myself and decided to buy an additional box - #ForTheGram!

These were the flavours:
◾Key Lime Pie
◾Lady Earl Grey
◾Popcorn Pecan
◾Pear [I think?]
◾Raspberry
◾Kopi+Bing
◾Ondeh All Day
◾PB & J

I'm not usually one for Bonbons as I tend to shy away after seeing the price but boy I was missing out! It was also a little heart wrenching to pop these in your mouth as they're just too gorgeous to look at!

Each petite Bonbon packed a punch of flavour that literally exploded in your mouth. My favourite flavours would have to be their Ondeh All Day and the Key Lime Pie. Damn, now I want some more.

◾Double Scoop with Thyme Cone [$10]

Well-known ice-cream brand @bopgelato has recently opened up a new outlet over at Craig Road! Influencers alike have since been flocking to get their gram fix - with the new futuristic minimal interior that seems to be the enticing draw for all dem influenzas. (I mean influencers.)

It does seem to be a bit of a waste of space though, with extremely minimal seating in the form of a long bench that forms part of the interior design. (At least they don't offer waffles so it's mostly ice-cream grab and go.)

BOP has always been in my top 5 ice-cream shoppes, specializing in unique botanical and floral flavours such as Spiced Pear and White Chrysanthemum. I actually really liked their Spiced Pear flavour, unfortunately anyone I've recommended it to - did not agree and have crucified me for it ever since. Oops.

Having tried a few flavours before from their other outlets, I decided to go with Vanilla Fig and Strawberry Basil this time around. Both flavours were delish and definitely like perfection. The interesting notes of strawberry and basil actually tantalized my palette and I was all for it. Their signature thyme cone provided a delicious vessel as well - I normally don't go for cones but I'll make an exception.

Poor ol' Apriary has some competition now but they themselves are holding their own with more seatings and offerings of waffles as well. Of course, I'm already hoping to make a second visit to BOP soon and get my ice-cream fix again! (Though I'll be spoiled for choice between the two from now on.)

◾Lemon & Sea Buckthorn [$7+]

Hailing from Copenhagen, Denmark, @leckerbaer.sg is well-known for their Danish cookies called Småkager. Well, apart from those tantalizing little sweets, they also offer a selection of bigger bakes such as tarts, cream puffs and ice-cream sandwiches!

It was difficult to pick what to try as everything looked so good but I ultimately went with their Lemon & Sea Buckthorn tart.

A deliciously curated tart filled with lemon curd and topped with an amazing swirl of meringue - this caught my eye from a mile away. The lemon and buckthorn gives it a delectable tartness which is also balanced but yet perhaps a little overpowered from the heft of meringue on top - but hey, I'm not complaining.

Their new outlet at Keong Saik is a great respite from the crowds and a nice level up from their Orchard locale. Sadly, it seems like their prices have gone up ever so slightly since my last visit and especially with the addition of taxes - it's honestly just enough to sorta put me off from any future visits.

◾Kafe Utu's African Inspired Cuisine

If you have walked along the Jiak Chuan stretch, you'll notice a cafe/resto with a unique name called @kafeutu! 

Specializing in diverse African fare, Kafe Utu has been on my list of places to try after constantly seeing their dishes on da Instagram feed. Not to mention that I've never had African cuisine before, hence I was highly intrigued.

Unfortunately, Kafe Utu does not take reservations, hence I had to plan my visit - heading there at 6pm sharp on a weekend - right when they open.

Quite a number of dishes looked tantalizing and I decided to order a few including:

◾Goat Curry [$28]
◾Sunset Cauliflower [$15]
◾Lamb Samosa [$18]
◾Buttermilk Fried Chicken [$18]

The highlight for me was definitely their signature Goat Curry - which I would say was one of the most African inspired dishes on the menu. Packed full of flavour, the spice from their house curry paste and habanero sneakily kicked in a few moments after each bite. Luckily it was served with coconut rice and that helped to mellow the spice a lil'.

Both the Sunset Cauliflower and Lamb Samosas were delicious and flavourful as well and definitely were great starters into my foray of African cuisine. The Buttermilk Fried Chicken on the other hand felt a bit ordinary compared to the rest - with the 3 side sauces for the chicken which includes Congo Bongo & a Mango Chilli Marmalade; taking more of the spotlight. Sadly my weak ass can't handle spice so I stayed clear of them. (I did try like a tinsy tiny bit of each but it still wasn't for me.)

I simply adored the vibes at Kafe Utu - the aesthetic, music and food definitely transported me to the likes of Africa! I'm still keen to try more of their dishes as well - especially their brunch menu and even their Chilli Chocolate drink! (If only I can wake up earlier...)

◾️Soft Scrambled Eggs & Ikura [$16]

A staple cafe along Tanjong Katong, @littleroguecoffee came about with the cheekiness of lil' kids and the vision of wanting to inspire people through the F&B business.

Another cafe on my list that I've been itching to try - I've passed by their premises a couple of times with intrigue.

A number of dishes they offer dominate le Instagram page and my eyes were immediately drawn to one of the brunch dishes - their Soft Scrambled Eggs & Ikura.

I do love good scrambled eggs and Little Rogue's did not disappoint. The stunning dish consisted of bright orange Ikura that contrasted with the pale yellowness of the fluffy eggs, topped off with truffle cream, chives and served with a side of sourdough. The truffle cream was divine to boot and provided a delectable umami that complemented the bursts of savouriness from the Ikura. Definitely a must try!

Both the vibes and the food over at Little Rogue were fantastic or sure, and I was glad that I got to finally check them out. Definitely gonna plan a second visit in the future - I'm still thinking bout that teacake and I'm down to try the other flavours!

【BCD Soon Tofu @soontofusg 】

Now you don’t have to look forward to VTLs or spend a hefty price to treat your loved ones to delicious and authentic Korean 🇰🇷 cuisine!

On a mission to introduce Korean 🇰🇷 delicacies to everyone in Singapore 🇸🇬 , restaurant SBCD Korean Tofu House is continuing its heartland expansion to Punggol, after a successful opening in Ang Mo Kio.

👄Tried their signature set at their Ang Mo Kio outlet:

The soup paste is the product of five months of research and development and required six hours to make while the stew is a combination of fish and prawn powders, garlic, spring onion, and other aromatics. 

BCD Soon Tofu uses silken tofu that is specially imported premium soybean from Paju, South Korea, a city near the Korean Demilitarised Zone (DMZ), which is known for its pristine produce due to its isolated location.

📍 Rosso Vino

Crowned as one of Singapore’s best Italian restaurants, I finally paid this place a visit and it definitely didn’t disappoint.

🍝 𝐓𝐚𝐠𝐥𝐢𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐞 𝐏𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐨
This was my favourite dish of the night! Fresh handmade pasta, prawns and cherry tomatoes all tossed in their vibrant, herby pesto sauce. If your mouth isn’t watering by now, mine definitely is. The freshness of the basil is counterbalanced by the rich, punchy garlicky flavours. Everything here melds perfectly well together.

🌋 𝐏𝐢𝐳𝐳𝐚 𝐕𝐮𝐥𝐜𝐚𝐧𝐨
This is a seasonal menu item where it is only available till 31st March, I knew I had to give this a try! As the name suggests, this pizza had a flaming sambuca when it was served which resembles a volcano.

Encased in the pizza dough is a bed of melted mozzarella cheese, ham, mushrooms and tomato — simply incredible. If you’re a fan of alcohol, this pizza is a must-get! You must ensure that the alcohol is spread evenly throughout the dough and ingredients as it can get really overwhelming for the parts with more alcohol.

🫕 𝐓𝐫𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 𝐌𝐚𝐬𝐡𝐞𝐝 𝐏𝐨𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐨
I can never say no to truffle-infused mashed potatoes. Velvety and buttery mashed potatoes that are finished with a generous amount of earthy black truffle shavings and truffle oil — this was stunning ✨ 

Thank you @rossovinosg for your amazing food and warm hospitality. I will definitely be back!!

📍 Seafood Paradise

‼️ 𝐏𝐑𝐎𝐌𝐎 - 𝟓𝟎% 𝐨𝐟𝐟 𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐦𝐬 ‼️

To celebrate the 1st Anniversary of Seafood Paradise’s re-opening at VivoCity, @paradisegrpsg is offering 50% off selected items from 7th Mar till 17th April!

🦀🧈 𝘾𝙧𝙚𝙖𝙢𝙮 𝘽𝙪𝙩𝙩𝙚𝙧 𝘾𝙧𝙖𝙗 𝙬𝙞𝙩𝙝 𝘾𝙤𝙘𝙤𝙣𝙪𝙩 𝘾𝙧𝙪𝙢𝙗𝙨
This dish was originally created by @paradisegrpsg so I knew I had to choose this over their signature chilli crab. This was undoubtedly spectacular ✨ I loved how fresh the crab was, and the creamy, buttery gravy was luscious yet not overly surfeiting. I got some fried mantou on the side to mop up the remaining gravy too! We took away the rest of gravy to have it with more plain noodles at home but someone lost my gravy while we were shopping after the meal!!! 😩

This is available till 13th March so don’t miss it!! Who knows? I might drop by again for their chilli crab before the deal ends.

📍 seng kee mee sua

This dish needs no introduction. It’s none other than their 𝙎𝙡𝙞𝙘𝙚𝙙 𝙋𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙃𝙚𝙧𝙗𝙖𝙡 𝙈𝙚𝙚 𝙎𝙪𝙖 𝙎𝙤𝙪𝙥 😋 I had this on a rainy day and it defo hit the spot! The soft, silky noodles and tender pork slices were cooked to perfection. I’ll never stop dreaming of this bowl of goodness 🍜
location: Seng Kee Black Chicken Herbal Soup Pte Ltd

description:
📍 RK Eating House
 
Located at Serangoon Gardens, this is my go-to prata place if I’m craving for a wholesome plate of prata.

🫓 𝚂𝚙𝚎𝚌𝚒𝚊𝚕 𝚁𝙺 𝙿𝚛𝚊𝚝𝚊
2 crispy plain prata drenched in a pool of mutton curry, topped with 2 wobbly soft-boiled eggs and 2 kinds of sambal chilli — there is just so much going on here. Also known as 𝗣𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗧𝘀𝘂𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗶, this really overwhelmed my palate with the tsunami of flavours. The eggs helps to mellow down the spiciness of the curry with its creaminess, and the sweet-spicy sambal lifts the overall flavour profile with an extra kick from the spice.

Side note: I washed everything down with a cup of Iced Teh C Kosong and it was delightful! The tea aroma was stronger than expected in a good way, and it helped to tone down the heat in my tummy too.

📍 Thai-licious

My first visit saw me dropping by again in less than 2 weeks as their food blew me away!

🍛 𝗕𝗲𝗲𝗳 𝗚𝗿𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗖𝘂𝗿𝗿𝘆
This is one of the best renditions I’ve had so far. This green curry was rich, creamy, and had a hint of Thai basil. This variation has a thicker consistency, without being too watered down. I love how they aren’t too heavy handed with the coconut milk. Between pork and beef, we decided to go with the beef version where the bowl was loaded with tender beef slices, with the perfect bite. I’d return for this any day! If I have to fault the dish, it’ll be that the veggies are slightly undercooked.

🍳 𝗖𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗽𝘆 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝗶 𝗢𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗲𝘁𝘁𝗲
This omelette was incredibly fluffy, with a crispy exterior; where it can only be achieved by frying the eggs at high heat. Despite being deep fried, the eggs weren’t as greasy as I expected, and it went really well with the Rich curry and plain rice.

🍜 𝗣𝗮𝗱 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝗶
This is not bad but not mind blowing. Even though the noodles were on the drier side, they managed to soak up all the flavours. There was a right hint of sweetness but I feel that it can be elevated with more condiments that are served on the side.

🧋 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝗶 𝗠𝗶𝗹𝗸 𝗧𝗲𝗮
Freshly brewed in-house daily, this is the perfect drink to help cool you down from all the spicy dishes on the table. It isn’t overly sweet, and the roasted tea aroma wasn’t overpowering and balanced really well with the condensed milk. PURRRFECT!!!

I can foresee myself making repeated visits in the future to try out the other menu items and for the dishes in this post again. Bonus points for their great customer service too 💯

#GohEatSpain #8of10🍯 #ShouldGoh to @casamoralessevilla a local Seville institution since 1850.

A really interesting space with huge earthenware wine jugs lining the walls. The food was pretty good too!

We started out with a Pringa sandwich, mix of braised meat and sausages in crusty bread, delicious.

Next was their Pork Meatballs, I’m not really sure what was in the sauce but it was really tasty, and I mopped it all up with the accompanying bread.

We also had Pulpo - Octopus which was simply done, on top of boiled potatoes and a dusting of paprika. It was really tender.

Lastly, we had a house classic, Chicken and Mushrooms in Sherry, you could taste the sweetness the sherry imparted in the dish.

#GohEatSpain #5of10🍯 #CanGoh to @freiduriapuertadelacarne for some Pescaito Frito.

Was in town during the Sevilla FC v West Ham United Europa League Round of 16 1st Leg Match, so decided to soak in the atmosphere and watch the match on tv in our apartment (the cheers echoed in the streets when Sevilla scored the 1 and only goal of the match), took a stroll during half time to get some mixed fried fish and got back in time to watch the 2nd half and the goal.

The was a mix of hake, sardines, cod bites, prawns and cuttlefish. The fish wasn’t that crisp as it may have sat out for awhile before I ordered and seasoning was abit varied with some pieces being overly salty. Think it would be much better if you get there as it comes straight out of the fryer.

#GohEatSpain #6of10🍯 #CanGoh to long standing Restaurant @rinconcillo_sev that’s been operating since 1670, over 350 years.

We definitely went there for the history, as did many other patrons. The place was packed, and service suffered from it.

It was hard to get the wait staff’s attention and lots of miscommunications happened with our order, even when both speaking and pointing it out on the menu. We weren’t the only table that got wrong orders either.

There was also a strange instance when the waiter put a couple of dirty dishes from another table down in front of us, mumbled to himself while fumbling with his notepad, then picked up the dishes again, stormed into the kitchen shouting out orders, without saying a single word to us.

When the food did come, we got a Salmorejo soup which was quite tasty.

A plate of big clams came instead of the small clams we ordered, which wasn’t a big deal as the clams were pretty good.

The Braised Iberian Pig Cheek was supposed to be a tapas portion, but a full portion arrived, the meat was really tender, but not spectacular.

The Rice with Squid Ink and Prawns was initially forgotten, on hindsight, maybe we should have cancelled it, as it was overly salty and a tad disappointing. We didn’t finish it.

#GohEatSpain #6of10🍯 #CanGoh to @victormontesbilbao for Pintxos.

Popped into another iconic Pintxos bar on our last night in Bilbao.

Had the Bacon Teriyaki Toast, Txistorra Toast and Spider Crab Dip. They were pretty decent but didn’t really wow.

#GohEatSpain #8of10🍯 #ShouldGoh to @cafeirunabilbao for their Lamb Kebabs.

Popped into this long standing place in Bilbao to try their iconic Lamb Kebabs and they didn’t disappoint. The kebabs are grilled to order in front of you and the meat was tender and nicely spiced.

Also had a piece of Crab Toast which was pretty tasty.

🤤 Curry ($1.20): Nice curried potato cubes with onion bits. Another must-buy. 

😐 Hamburger ($1.10): Luncheon meat bun. One of their popular items but I find it okok.

Cheap and good bread from an old-school bakery at Serangoon Garden Market & Food Centre! 

Freshly baked at the hawker centre during operating days, the soft buns are very soft and best eaten warm. There’s a perpetual queue but the efficient staffs quickly clear it. I must say I’m amazed by their mental sum ability; calculating the total cost and changes w/o the need for a calculator. 

What I tried: 
🤤 Yam ($1.10): My fav. I got the fresh batch and it’s incredibly soft and warm. The yam filling is slightly sweet, creamy and thick. A must-buy!

🤤 Peanut ($1.10): Crunchy, fragrant, gao peanut filling. Yum!

🤤 Red bean ($1.10): The amt of filling is not as generous as the others but I don’t mind as it’s very gao and sweet. Good stuff. 

Thankful for hawkers like them who continue to churn out good and very affordable bakes for us. There are other items I have yet to try. Do come early to buy from them!

My naïve self once thot it’s hard to go wrong with kway chap. Until I had one so bad I couldn’t bring myself to finish everything. 

Thankfully, this stall serves decent kway chap. The kway chap platter ($5) comes with braised pork belly, pork skin, egg, intestines, fish cake and tau pok drizzled in the thick sauce. The kway is thin with a slight bite and it’s quite a big portion for one. The soup is quite mild and compliments well with the thick sauce from the platter. Hearsay they sold out early so do come early if you wanna try!

I finally tried this famous laksa eatery on a Monday afternoon when most of the eateries were having their off-days in this area.

This bowl of laksa ($6.30, small) is rich, full-bodied, coconutty with the right amt of spice. Trying to replicate the version I had years ago from a Kyoto based Tatsuhito Satoi who was trained under Yuji Ajiki. @bishoku.sg specialise in Truffle Aioli and Mentaiko Mayo. Freshly made weekly with finest ingredients. If you are a fan of mentaiko or truffle, their classic sauce is a must-have at home🏠

There’s a long list of food items you can pair with:

The Mentaiko mayo has a good balance of Mentai and mayo, creamy and full of umami. Goes well with Sushi, Chicken Cutlet Pasta and more

The Truffle Aioli has strong truffle fragrance and garlicky flavour which I think is perfect dip/dressing for fries! 

Over here I have created Egg Sando using the two classic sauce, here’s the recipe:
▫️1.5 hard boiled egg
▫️ 2 slices of bread
▫️Dice the egg and add 1/2 tbsp of butter, 1/2 tbsp of black pepper, a pinch of salt
▫️add 1 tbsp of @bishoku.sg Mentaiko Mayo or Truffle Aioli
▫️ Mix well and spread on your preferred bread
▫️Wrap the sandwich with baking sheet, fold in all four sides tightly 
▫️Cut it in half except the bottom baking sheet so you will be able to fold the sando

Enjoy!✨

🔍 Check out @bishoku.sg for more info

Helmed by Chef Yasuo Watanabe, this little hole in a wall @ao_ringo_sg specialises in contemporary Japanese food with heavy Spanish influence. Your only option available here is their $99.99 Omakase menu. Honestly it’s pretty decently priced for 7 outstanding courses. 

Their Omakase was fun, adventurous and definitely steered clear of your traditional nigiris and kaiseki dishes. Some highlights for the night was Chef Watanabe’s take on a seafood Paella, monkfish with a Romesco inspired sauce, and their Iberico pork pluma. 

Hands down the paella was my favourite course. Each bite was filled with seafood such as red shrimp, squid from Aomori and even fish! The Chef also used Carnaroli rice from Italy instead of the usual bomba rice for a more textural bite. As for the monkfish, this came from Aomori prefecture and was served with crushed potatoes, shunjinku (green veg), white turnip and finished with Romesco inspired sauce. This dish was outstanding. The Monk fish still retained a firm texture even after being covered in a golden crisp batter. And lucky for us, they gave us extra bread to scoop up all that delicious sauce. 

At first glance, I thought the Iberico Pork Pluma was beef cos it's Med-rare but chef said it was common for this kinda pork to be cooked to this doneness and well he was right abt that. The natural flavours of the pork shone through and was complemented by the vinegar reduction and beetroot purée.

If you’d like to see my full review of the dishes, check out my story highlights above! Their unorthodox  interpretation of Japanese and Spanish cuisine definitely piqued my interest and I’ll be back sometime soon.

Aren’t these pastries from @bakemono_bakers just gorgeous 🥰 Despite the incessant lines you’ll find here, we thought it was worth checking out! Got ourselves a few diff ones to share and a box of caneles too. 

First and foremost, they caneles were spot on. Especially after reheating, these babies are crisp and caramelised on all its edges  and boast a dense but moist baked custard. Altho they only offer one flavour currently, I can’t wait to see what else they will be coming out with.

As for the pastries, we tried some of the best sellers, namely Strawberries & Pistachio, Almond & Yuzu, Sesame & Honey and for a savoury option, their Ham & Cheese.

Top picks for me was the Strawberries & Pistachio and the Sesame and Honey pastries! The strawberry one was filled with a luscious and velvety cream and topped with fresh strawberries whilst the sesame honey pastry was an unexpected delight. The honey was a nice little twist to the already fragrant pastry. 

As for the the other two, I’d probs give it a miss if I were back again 😣

i totally forgot how massive the brunches in melb were! got ourselves a big brekkie to share down at @bricklane_melbourne the other day with my brother ✨ 

the big fry up consisted of sourdough toasts, two poached eggs, sautéed mushrooms, half a chorizo, grilled bacon and thankfully seasoned tomatoes. the meal was wholesome and ofc hearty to say the least. would probs recommend sharing this bcos of how generous the portions were and if you’re having this for brekkie/brunch, it wouldn’t be too heavy between 2 ppl! 

also coffee is legit good everywhere in melb :’)

If there’s one thing you need to try here, it’s their crack oil. We literally spammed this insanely delicious oil on everything we had at  @wildchildpizzette. 

To start off, we had some antipizettes, which were the Kurobuta Pork in our case. The crackly roasted pork was made with secret spice and house giardiniera. It’s then served with a side of crack oil and pickled vegetables to cut through the heavy flavours. 

As for the pizzas, we got the Spianata Calabrese and their special pizza of the day! The Spianata Calabrese is basically a fiery twist on your usual pepperoni. Both the spicy salami and Sichuan chili honey added the touch of heat we needed. The special on the other hand was topped with shaved parmesan, prosciutto and rocket leaves. It also came with a white sauce base rather than a traditional tomato sauce.

Check out this first ever unique cross collaboration with @nissinfoodssingapore X @ramen_keisuke !! They’ve teamed up to create two all new ramen flavours inspired by Ramen Keisuke Tonkotsu King‘s best sellers. ⠀

🌱Healthy Snacking while making a sustainable impact? @wearerefoods snacks have the goodness of all-natural, sustainably farmed ingredients that are deliciously kind to the planet. 

The sustainable impact on each snack:
✅Mixed Nuts with Salt & Pepper
- Snacking that fights water wastage.
Grown in Australian orchards. Save water by employing smart technology! With the help of moisture sensors, each tree receives just the right amount of water needed to grow almonds that are both healthy and delicious. 

✅Mixed Nuts with Seaweed
✅Almonds with Honey
- Snacking that heals the planet.
Grown in Australian orchards. Run on 75% renewable energy! Instead of using fossil fuels, these orchards harness energy from wind and solar sources. 

✅Cashews with Honey Sesame
- Snacking that improves the health of soils.
Grown in Ia Grai, Vietnam, by farmers who were trained in organic farming techniques. With the training, famous were able to improve the health of their soils and grow higher quality cashews. 

✅Cashews with Rock Salt
- Snacking that improves the lives of farmers and communities.
Grown in Ia Grai, a rural district in Vietnam. We installed 50 streetlights for our cashew farming community in Ia Grai, so everyone in the village could feel safe going outside after dark. 

✅Almonds with Rock Salt
- Snacking that saves bees.
Grown in Australian orchards that put the health of bees first. Provide fresh water sources and grow nectar-rich flowering plants to give the bees a varied and nutritious diet. Happy bees, healthy plants, delicious almonds. 

✅Natural Cashews with Rock Salt
- Snacking that brings clean water to farmers and communities. 
Grown in Ia Grai, Vietnam where access to clean water was not always available. In order to provide safe drinking water for the cashew farmers and their families, motorised water wells in four Ia Grai villages were installed. 

✅Cashew Minis with Rock Salt
- Snacking that gives children a brighter future.
Grown by farmers whose children go to Le Loi High School in Vietnam. With help and support, to provide the students of this high school with 10,000 units of school books, story books, and stationery supplies.

The Truffle Mushroom dumplings ($9.90/8pcs) are made of Impossible Meat, juicy shitake mushrooms & cabbage! There is some mild gingerly taste present in the dumplings. 🌱Smelly Tofu from Old Tu Kee is Vegan friendly and *allium-free!

If you mention you are vegetarian, they assumed you are Buddhist and will give you a set of allium-free smelly tofu with chilli and spice powder instead of chilli sauce. Their default set is vegan friendly. To play safe, indicate your dietary preference. 

I had a super hard time communicating with the staff. I told them I am vegetarian and I take onions and garlic. She refused to give me the sauce and veggie said vegetarian set they cannot give garlic. In the end.. I have to tell them that I am NOT vegetarian just to get what I want😂

The most important question now:  SMELLY OR NOT? 

🔸️NOOOOO.....If you are looking for smelly tofu that smells like clogged toilet pipes, sorry to disappoint you! The smelly tofu here is nice, but not smelly. We love it because they are well-fried and nicely seasoned. Smelly level =1, as compared to normal fried tofu at level 0.

Other then rolls and sushi, Takeshi-San serve a couple of interesting main dishes.

New on the menu will be the King Prawn and Truffle Cheese Steak ($38). Simple yet delicious, the king prawn was covered in savoury cheese though the truffle taste was faint.

Another dish to try will be their cream rich Fantastic Inaniwa Udon ($40). Thick chewy udon noodles coated in a creamy sauce, it is topped with caviar, uni and pan-seared foie gras.

Both dishes goes well with the sweet milk-based Shiroi Chardonnay too. We love it so much that we even bought a bottle home.

Grab a drink over at ELLA!

Experience the first robot barista lifestyle at Bytes Station, where you can have your gourmet coffee and healthy bites through contactless mode. Simply order and pay via the ELLA mobile app, before picking up your order at the digital locker after scanning the QR Code.

For the gym junkies or calories cautious, the ciabatta sandwiches, sourdough sandwiches and smoothies come with protein-loaded options (from SportyFood and Myprotein) and have the nutritional info on the app too!

📍Diamond Coffee · San Francisco, CA

@diamondcoffeesf is a new coffee shop (opened about two weeks ago) located on Clement Street serving an array of coffee drinks, pastries, and croffles! The space is super cute and aesthetic with indoor and outdoor seating. There were some unique coffee and tea drinks that I got to try. My favorite drink of the ones I ordered was called Pink, which was Strawberry Milk. It was perfectly sweet and the strawberries tasted quite fresh. I definitely have to try their Purple (Ube) next time. The Mojito (not pictured) was super refreshing but there were too many fresh mint leaves in it for me to fully enjoy the drink 😅.

📍Grace Street Cafe · NYC

I have been wanting to go to @gracestreetcafe for a long time and finally got the opportunity a few days ago! @gracestreetcafe is a dessert cafe serving shaved ice, boba, burnt Basque cheesecakes, and other desserts. Although it’s still a little chilly in New York, I couldn’t turn down having my favorite dessert: shaved ice. We got The Elixir, and I loved how creamy the shaved ice was, but not to the point where it just tasted like ice cream. There was also a strong matcha flavor, and the fresh taro chunks are a huge plus! Next time I want to try some of their milk teas (particularly the Rose Petal Milk Tea). The XOXO shaved ice with rose also sounded so good. 

🍵The Elixir (Matcha Shaved Ice, Condensed Milk, Red Beans, Taro, Lychee Jelly)

El Willy Spanish Kitchen 👩🏻‍🍳💗 [Part 1/2]

❣️9/10 (Overall experience)📍 El Willy, Bangkok (Thailand) #foeifyinth

✏️ If you love Spanish food, this is a must try 👌🏻. “el Willy” is a contemporary Spanish restaurant. The idea is based around “Sexy tapas restaurant” as they aimed to create a fun, creative, innovative and delicious food!

Must order:🌟🌟🌟 (for the starter)

🍅 Burrata Con Truffle [9/10]: I think they ran out of vine tomato on that day. If it was with vine tomato, then this would be perfect!!

🦐 Gambas Al Ajillo [10/10]: flavorful and super tender tiger prawns in Spanish classic olive oil with garlic and chili. Eat with well toasted sourdough and it’s a bomb 💣.

🥪 Bikini Iberico [9/10]: Super crispy, cheesy and packed with truffle aroma. Really hit a spot for a grilled cheese sandwich like me.

🍞 Foie Gras toast [8/10]: Served with apple, vanilla and popcorn powder. 

The only downside is that the restaurant is very smokey (might due to their ventilation) and your eyes can be a bit sensitive. If not because of this, it would be 10/10.

She was invited to attend a 30 minutes one-on-one Mandarin trial class on Wukong EDU platform.

Through interactive games and scenario-based teaching, Wukong Classroom guides and stimulates children's interest and curiosity in learning; it helps to enhance math and language skills through encouraging multi-perspective thinking which fosters critical thinking skills.

The Chinese class is suitable for kids aged from 4 to 18 years old while the math class is suitable to kids aged from 7 to 13 years old.

Wukong courses are fully online, and all live classes can be rewatched later. Mac, iPad, Windows and Android are all supported, so you can fit study around your family's schedule.

The only (avo)CADO I wanna do is go (coco)NUTS over these Coconut + Avocado drinks from Coco.Cado 🥥🥑

Coconut shakes are all the rage now and one place where you can get the best of both worlds is @cococadosg, a homegrown brand 🇸🇬 that serves a wide variety of coconut and avocado drinks which are naturally sweetened with fresh coconut water 🥥 and enriched with freshly cut avocados! 🥑

Besides your usual coconut shake, you can look forward to drinks with a local twist such as the Coco Cempedak Shake, Coco Rose Fresh Milk, Cado Durian Milk Shake, Cado Gula Melaka Fresh Milk and more! 🤩

Featuring these 4 drinks:
🥥🥑 Coco Cado Shake ($5.50)
Coco.Cado's speciality drink, the Coco Cado Shake combines raw coconut and fresh avocado in the perfect ratio to give a creamy, refreshing blend. There's also bits of chewy coconut flesh which lend a nice mouthfeel.

🥥🥛 Coco Shake ($4.30)
Coconut purists will enjoy the Coco Shake with its prominent coconut flavour. Just like the Coco Cado Shake, this drink isn't too gao or thick so you won't be overly full after drinking it. It isn't too sweet as well.

🥥🍫 Coco Nutella Shake ($6)
If you're a Nutella fan, go for the Coco Nutella Shake which comes with a generous dose of Nutella! The coconut flavour takes a back seat in this blend which is predominantly nutty and chocolatey

🥑🥛 Cado Durian Fresh Milk ($6)
This one is for the King of Fruits stans! You're hit with the distinctive smell of durian even before you sip on this. The avocado flavour in this drink is rather mild and you mostly taste the bold durian flavour.

More than the flavours, I really liked the pretty packaging of these drinks! They come with a cute sleeve that features their two adorable mascots, Coco 🥥 and Cado 🥑 Grabbing a cuppa is sure to add some cheer to your day! 😄

Who doesn't LAVA good pizza, especially one that looks as Instaworthy as this Vulcano Pizza from Rosso Vino! 🌋🍕

Popped by famed Italian restaurant @rossovinosg recently to try their Chef's Special Vulcano Pizza [$38, good for 2 pax] after coming across photos of it with its middle set on fire 🔥 (y'all know I can never resist visual spectacles like this!)

A homage to the founders' birthplaces which are near majestic volcanos 🇮🇹🌋, the Vulcano Pizza comes in the shape of a volcano and is stuffed with tomato 🍅 , mozzarella 🧀 , ham 🍖 and mushrooms 🍄 Where the vent of the volcano should be sits three huge pepperoni discs that are doused generously with sambuca, an Italian liqueur that boasts a distinctive liquorice flavour 🍾

Knowing that the flaming sambuca is the highlight of this pizza, I was expecting to see a strong blue flame when the waitress set the sambuca alight. Thus, it was a little disappointing to see the small flame on my pizza die out within 2 seconds of the dish being set on the table 🥺 The waitress' attempts to relight the flame and shake the plate to get the fire started also failed. Why does this volcano have to be a dormant one?! #sighpie 😭

Aesthetics aside, I did enjoy the taste of this pizza. The dough was pleasantly chewy and went well with the savoury ingredients 💯 Will recommend letting the sambuca mix with the rest of the ingredients as the alcohol taste can be a bit too heady if you eat the middle portion in silo.

The Vulcano Pizza is available till 7th March so go check it out if you're keen! 🤗

[ @outputespresso ] So… more UK food incoming! This one’s from Output Espresso, a quaint cafe tucked in the outskirts of the city Belfast. I had their Avocado Toast (Jalapeño Avocado Smash, Herb Tomato, Pickled Shallot, Crispy Egg) and their Berry Lost Bread (French toast topped with vanilla mascarpone and berry compote). Believe me when I say all these words sound foreign to me too 🤣 so to simplify it it’s basically Avocado on Toast & French Toast with Berries & Vanilla Ice Cream. I was particularly wowed by the Avocado Toast mainly for the freshness of the ingredients and the ingenuity to include the jalapeño that gives the Toast a nice extra kick 👀 The lava egg was also to die for with its crispy deep fried outer layer and the oozy runny egg in the center 😊 For the French toast  I have to say I had better ones in Singapore… or maybe my palate was just not refined enough to appreciate the masterpiece of a French toast. Verdict: Do pop by if your in the area and craving for some good vibes on a rainy, cold day 😉

I had the Creme Brûlée French Toast, the Sticky Pork Cheek Bahn as well as the Cheese Burger taco and I can tell you all 3 was just sublime 🤞. 2021, a year of self reflection. I spent most of the time this year in my room which gave me further oppurtunity to reflect on my life's choices, preferences and point of view. 一直對#冉冉生活 的#肉桂捲 充滿好奇，社團裡面吃過的人都說好吃。特地約了同鄉妹妹到城中門市一起吃#下午茶 。 我們都好喜歡這裡用餐空間，蠻寬敞，之前好像是土地銀行。肉桂捲表現中規中矩，淡淡肉桂味，麵包體也不會太乾，應該算是入門款。
➖

我好像只會為了吃#滷肉飯 才跑去三重😋 雖然離萬華也不是很遠。之前都是去吃今大，這次換另一家口袋名單#店小二魯肉飯 。一吃驚人，怎麼可以這麼清爽不油膩！同鄉妹妹一直誇說太美味，還加點多一碗我們一起分享。除了飯，一定一定一定要點無敵好吃的#蝦仁羹 ，吃起來沒有腥味，q彈又鮮甜！可愛的老闆娘還拿來他們家特製辣椒，搭配滷豆腐真是絕啊！

#friednoodles 

#炒粿條 一般在小販中心都吃得到的#新加坡美食 ，都會加血蚶，但我不敢吃蚶，所以每次點都會說不要加。在家#自己煮 想加什麼都可以，蝦仁、豬肉、油菜、雞蛋、豆芽、粿條和油麵，用黑甜醬油拌炒，真是香噴噴啊~
➖
今天是老媽逝世六週年忌日，如果還在也87了。
晚年有失智症，想想她還在的話，疫情下應該蠻辛苦，因為她都愛到處走，無法坐太久。

最近朋友都問我會回新加坡嗎？我都會說父母不在了，沒牽掛，暫時不回去也還好。異鄉人最心念的就是家裡的長輩，都會擔心他們過得好不好。父母健在的人真的要好好孝順他們，多陪伴。

My tastebuds have been blessed by @miznonsg! Israeli street food right in the heart of the city, Y E S!

🍔Folded Cheeseburger ($22)
🌯ABU Kebab ($24)

With so many ingredients practically spilling from the pita and a runny egg yolk, this was a considerable feat to consume. I loved how well the flavours meshed together, and how each bite was balanced with a crunch, as well as the tanginess of the pickle!

The ABU Kebab was amazing as well, packed with lamb and beef and all that good stuff. Seriously, can you ever go wrong with a kebab?

If you haven’t tried @miznonsg, be prepared for your tastebuds to be transported to a whole other world. Who knew a pita bread could carry so many possibilities? 🤩 also did I mention they provide FREE PITA on the side?? 🫓
.
Miznon
📍6 Stanley Street, Singapore 068725

Drooled over @carbs.monster’s review of @tigress_82soho and I had to go down to try it myself!

🍔Bulgogi Burger with Mac & Cheese ($26)
🍗Korean Honey Soy Wings (5 pieces, $12)

This Japanese Wagyu fat-infused beef🥩 Bulgogi burger was pretty decent! We didn't go for the classic Tigress as we're not too fond of blue cheese🧀, but this one tasted of nostalgic good bulgogi sauce. The patty was soft, flavourful but none too mindblowing; I loved also how the jalepenos added another dimension. Each burger comes with french fries🍟 and one more side (choose from homemade kimchi, mac & cheese, tomato pesto salad, truffle enoki, onion rings)! For $26, I'd find it a little on the pricier side!

We really enjoyed the crispy wings that packed a crunch! These were served hot, sweet, and so so yummy. After inhaling 2 pieces in record time I was left wanting more. Really liked how the sweetness of the honey balanced out the soy sauce.
.
82Soho | Kommune & Tigress
📍Orchard Gateway #03-18, Singapore 238858

If I’m craving springy, chewy fishball meepok, @mingfafishball is the place to go. While their bowls may be on the slightly pricier side, you get generous servings of yummy ingredients - fishball, fishcake, that little dumpling thing, you name it. What’s more, just get a large bowl for sharing if you can’t finish one serving alone!

We also love their Bar Chor Mee, which is sooo flavourful. They definitely know what they’re doing with the meepok, I haven’t had one bowl that’s been overcooked!
.

Couldn't resist snagging these 2-for-2 @windowsillpies off @burpple Beyond, and they were soo good!!

🍫S'mores ($7.80)
🍋Strawberry Lemon Meringue ($7.30)
🍒Morello Sour Cherry ($7.80)
🍌Banana Almond Brittle ($6.80)

My favourite was definitely the strawberry🍓 lemon meringue, which packed the tanginess I absolutely love. I'm not a huge meringue girl so I liked how there was just enough of it at the end. And did I mention that the tart crust isn't the biscuity kind but more like flakey pie crust🥧?

Don't be fooled by the Banana🍌 Almond & Cognac Pie, because the fluffy cognac cream took us by surprise! It's light and not too overwhelmingly sweet, pairing well with the sweet banana parfait and almond brittle. For those who enjoy dark chocolate🍫, the S'mores🍡 is definitely not one to be missed!
.
Windowsill Pies

Went to @gaovietkitchen bc of its hype but I was so impressed with their foods and a huge menu. 
- Big Rib Bun Bo Hue: bun bo Hue (Hue spicy beef noodle) served with a huge piece of ribs. The flavor was authentic and I wish they’d serve it with some lime or herbs on the side. The rib was tender but not to my expectation, probably bc of the fat part. But hey, my friends all loved the rib and broth. 
- Banh Beo (savory steamed rice cake with shrimp flake, fried shallots and green onion): the size is bigger than I thought, which I wouldn’t complain at all🤣 Introduced it to my friend who doesn’t eat seafood and he said he didn’t even taste the strong taste of shrimp at all. Always love Banh Beo!
- Lychee Coconut Freeze and Passion Fruit Freeze: my favorite is passion fruit❤️ a big fan of lychee but not coconut
It was a delightful experience from both the food and service. They’re low on staff so please be patient. I’ll definitely come back to have more from their menu. Wish they’d open one in the east bay😂

One of the best, or maybe the best Bánh Cuốn (Vietnamese steamed rice rolls) in the Bay area. These are my favorite:
- Bánh Cuốn Đặc Biệt: (special set) the original Banh Cuon (stuffed with ground pork and mushroom) with a lot of toppings, including shrimp cakes, different types of ham, egg roll and fermented pork ham
- Bánh Cuốn Tôm: shrimps flavor Banh Cuon with less toppings but more dry ground shrimp stuffing. So simple but so good!

Was a bit skeptical before trying this place as I saw some bad reviews about the food. We went there with not too high expectation, ordered Omakase Sashimi, Kaiden Don and Fish Tacos. 
- Omakase Sashimi: it was ok for the price you’re paying for, fresh but definitely not as excellent as some other high end sushi places, you get what you pay for and this is a place with a really reasonable price for omakase sashimi
- Kaiden Don: we loved this dish, from the presentation to the taste. This is my bf’s favorite dish
- Fish Tacos: super crispy deep fried seaweed with amazing cuts. Can’t complain anything about this one

Kept in mind that the place will be really crowded in the weekend, we arrived there pretty early, maybe around 4pm, and after 10 mins you started to see people coming. We were first in line and got seated right after they opened. A tip is to know what you’ll order beforehand since it might take a while for order to be prepared. They’re definitely understaffed. Our foods were served after 10-20 mins, which surprised me a lot after reading so many bad reviews about timing. 

Overall, a good place to try out and don’t forget to order hot sake for your meal!

We got the $168 platter for sharing which consisted of three kinds of meat (2 beef & 1 pork), a seafood pancake, a kimchi stew and a steamed egg + $88 kurobuta pork set and we couldn’t finish the food in the end hahaha.

Who is ready for brunch? Mee! It's been a while since I visited Bondi and @upsouthbondi is a great place to catch up with friends! There is also heaps of street parking so you'll definitely get a spot.
 
Acai Bowl
Acai bowl was a little sweet but I still enjoyed it. 

Shakshuka
It was a bit rainy when I visited and shakshuka was warm and comforting. It was served with spiced tomato sauce baked with two eggs topped with feta and chargrilled bread.

Dukkah Eggs
It was served with tomato, basil, rocket, and Persian feta salad topped with two dukkah eggs, labne and chargrilled bread.

Piggy in the Farm
A combination of both the corn fritters, bacon and avocado is always so good! It was served with corn fritters, house made bacon onion chutney, feta, crispy bacon, rocket and smashed avocado.
 
✨ Piggy in the Farm ($20)
✨ Acai Bowl ($14)
✨ Dukkah Eggs ($19)
✨ Classic OJ ($8)
✨ Carrot Apple Ginger ($8)

Heard about this ramen place awhile back after seeing posts on their truffle ramen when it first opened!!

I dropped by recently and tried both their 𝐆𝐞𝐤𝐢𝐤𝐚𝐫𝐚 𝐑𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐧 (𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐮𝐥𝐚𝐫 - $𝟏𝟗.𝟗𝟎) & 𝐊𝐨𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐢 𝐓𝐨𝐧𝐤𝐨𝐭𝐬𝐮 𝐑𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐧 (𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐮𝐥𝐚𝐫 - $𝟏𝟔.𝟗𝟎). What I like about their ramen is that it’s firm yet chewy, even though we left it in the soup for awhile. Their hanjuku egg was perfectly cooked/ marinated and definitely one of the best I’ve had at ramen places 💯👌

For someone who can’t really take spice, the 𝐆𝐞𝐤𝐢𝐤𝐚𝐫𝐚 (Spicy miso & minced pork) one was a bit too spicy 🌶  for me but my friend really liked it! I mainly had the 𝐓𝐨𝐧𝐤𝐨𝐭𝐬𝐮 one and the broth was thick and very creamy, not overly salty or jelat. The chashu slices were tender with a good fat to meat ratio, not too fatty for my liking 🐷 

Got 𝐆𝐲𝐨𝐳𝐚 ($𝟔.𝟗𝟎) as a side to share as well and it came with thin glossy skin, slightly crisp but I think the pork filling can be more flavourful.

Thank you @kanadaya.sg for the invite! Was a satisfying meal on a rainy day and the Paragon outlet was pretty chill 💛 They serve dons as well if you’re not into ramen!

Joined a groupbuy and got these freshly baked old school buns at less than $1 each! 🍞

𝐏𝐞𝐚𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 🥜
Peanut is crunchy with bits of sugar in it but it wasn’t too sweet! Personally find it a bit dry so it's best to eat it with a drink! 

𝐂𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 🥥
Coconut filling is moist but I think it tasted a bit bland and I wished the shredded coconut bits were more fragrant.

𝐁𝐮𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐂𝐚𝐤𝐞 ($10/box)
Soft, buttery and not oily at all. It tasted quite light and fluffy so you won’t feel jelat or heavy after eating a slice!

Heard tht there’s always a long queue at their store, and I highly recc getting the peanut bread if you love crunchy peanuts!! Best to eat it on the day itself if not it’ll get stale the next day.

💚 IG FAMOUS GREEN PASTA 💚

Been here thrice and I think I still like their 𝐩𝐫𝐚𝐰𝐧 𝐛𝐚𝐬𝐢𝐥 𝐩𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐨 𝐩𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐚 the best! Comes with plenty of peeled prawns and every strand is coated nicely with the pesto sauce. Can get a bit oily at the end though.

I think their 𝐯𝐨𝐧𝐠𝐨𝐥𝐞 deserves some limelight too! Can’t rly see in the pic but it came with lots of clams and the soup was so addictive with the white wine, my friend and I finished every drop of it.

Best to make a reservation online bef going esp on weekends!

Had my first Sando experience some time last year in Dec after seeing so many posts on it! 

𝐁.𝐄.𝐂 ($𝟏𝟐)
This is what I came specially for!! Bacon, eggs and cheese, a hearty combi that can’t go wrong right? The scrambled eggs were silky and creamy and I like the slight spice from the habenero sauce they added in it. I’m the kind of the person tht doesn’t like fatty meat at all so the bacon was way too fatty for my liking 🤐🥓

𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐊𝐚𝐭𝐬𝐮 𝐒𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐨 ($𝟏𝟒)
This was massive and I had to take small bites of it!! Like I can’t hold it with 1 hand kind of massive. The bread was very well toasted and buttery but I feel like they should have added some sauce in it because it was a quite dry? The chicken katsu was tender but I think it was seasoned unevenly because one part of it tasted super salty idk why… 🥴 Love the addition of the pickled purple cabbage though, it really helps to cut through the greasiness and gives a refreshing taste.

Overall I prefer B.E.C (minus the bacon) over the chicken katsu sando and I think their sandwiches are pretty substantial and very filling. You can order 2 flavours and share half of it with your friend! Location wise it isn’t the most convenient and easiest to find, you’ll have to walk in quite a bit after alighting from the nearest bus stop.
location: The Herencia at 46/58 Kim Yam Road

description:
Visited @theassemblyground on a Sat afternoon and got seats pretty fast! 

𝐂𝐫𝐚𝐛 𝐏𝐨𝐦𝐨𝐝𝐨𝐫𝐨 𝐏𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐚 ($𝟐𝟒)
Was contemplating between this and the truffle carbonara but decided to order this in the end! The portion was bigger than I thought and it came with generous chunks of crab meat and the sauce was good! Was afraid that it’s going to be very spicy at first but tbh I couldn't really taste any spice at all 😅 I think it can get a bit jelat so it’s better to share!

𝐁𝐨𝐦 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐤𝐚 𝐖𝐨𝐰 𝐖𝐨𝐰 ($𝟐𝟎)
Love the marinade for the fried chicken, it was crispy and a bit sweet? 😋 I think the individual components paired well together although the egg yolk was a little overcooked for my liking. Still pretty satisfying overall!

Super worth with @burpple 1f1! 🤤 Btw I think Cineleisure/ Scape is pretty dead now?? A lot of the retail shops are gone etc. So sad, it used to be quite popular back when I was in pri/sec school.
