📍777 𝑯𝑲 𝑻𝒓𝒂𝒅𝒊𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒂𝒍 𝑹𝒐𝒂𝒔𝒕𝒆𝒅 𝑫𝒆𝒍𝒊𝒈𝒉𝒕𝒔 /
#饿零饿饿

Wanted to give this stall a try for many times already but wasn’t sure why I did not go ahead with the purchase previously. For 烧肉饭, you really want the operator to give you more bigger pieces of meat and for that skin to crackle when you bite into it! And then of cos the meat has to be tender, fatty, oily and not tough. As with this stall, I think its not bad. Skin doesn’t crackle as much as I would like it to be but definitely not tough as you can evidently see the glistening pork fat sandwiched between the meat! Also it has a smoky flavour if I remembered it correctly. It didn’t WOW me in any particular way but I would say as an overall dish, its pretty alright!

The classic roast pork and char siew combo! Can never go wrong when you are unsure about which meat to order! As you can see from the picture, portion was quite decent. I would say the char siew is better than the roast pork in this stall. Previously I tried their roast pork and char siew noodles, now I try their rice. Nothing over the top, just really substantial and reasonable priced cssr fan located along the same stretch with the old legend heap seng leong coffeeshop! 🙂

📍𝑹𝒐𝒏𝒈 𝑲𝒆𝒆 𝑹𝒐𝒂𝒔𝒕𝒆𝒅 𝑫𝒆𝒍𝒊𝒈𝒉𝒕𝒔 / #饿零饿饿

Second time at Rong Kee to try their 烧肉饭, previously I had their 烧肉面 and was amazed by the super crispy roast pork skin and super satisfying roast meat! Look at that pinkish colour near the bottom of the meat, you sure know this is not going to be some tough meat. Every component were pretty acceptable; Skin were crispy, pork fat was melty and provides a oily jelat-ness thats filled with pork fat fragrance and meat that was smoky, soft but not too soft and feels quite substantial. (You know some places just give you very little roast pork? Definitely not here 😌) 

I am a simple guy and this is perhaps among one of the best roasted meat that I’ve ever tasted and its okay, come roast me however you want!! I don’t care! 😎 Roast meat aside, the brown sauce, chilli was okay tasting, average. GO FOR THEIR ROAST PORK! 🔥🔥🔥🥓🥓🥓

Muyoo’s Pork Floss Bun! Can I say I am really impressed by how fast the counter person packs the bread? Like clockwork, super swift! 🙂 Lots of floss because again, I choose the bigger ones! Swee Heng’s one its alot more sweeter than Muyoo’s, this is much more savoury and possesses a distinguishable porky, salty aroma! Floss as usual tasted harder and more good quality! Weight was surprisingly lighter than swee heng’s even though they looked almost or equal in size! Bread texture is alot more firm and has a good stretch to the buns when u tear open the bread! Overall it was semi-fulfilling and definitely pretty generous with the pork floss!!

𝑺𝒘𝒆𝒆 𝑯𝒆𝒏𝒈 1989’𝒔 𝑪𝒉𝒊𝒄𝒌𝒆𝒏 𝑭𝒍𝒐𝒔𝒔 𝑩𝒖𝒏 / 
#饿零饿饿

Time to review another floss bun! This is cheaper than breadtalk’s floss buns, priced at $1.90. But taste wise? See my review below!

Comparing only to Breadtalk’s salted egg floss bun, not their regular ones.

[Size]: slightly bigger than breadtalk’s salted egg floss bun
[Shape]: more chonky, rounder and wider than bt
[Weight]: its def denser, and heavier than bt by a little bit. I was carrying with two fingers and i felt its quite heavy for a bread/buns
[Floss texture]: soft, more nua, lighter, less rough than bt
[Buns]: soft, semi-firm, chewy, hearty
[Floss amt]: quite alot as i picked the ones with more floss 🤣. Quality wise can see very clearly that it is not as good compared to the quality at bt. Very basic kind. Not say its not good. Just normal. You go buy and see and you will know. It looks pale, more dull colored as compared to bread talks brighter, deeper and more striking colours.
[Mayo]: is def cheaper mayo. Nothing special.
[Floss aroma]: erm nothing to rave about, normal floss taste. More one dimensional compared to bt. Less atas than bt.

$1.90. Would i buy again? Maybe because its cheaper n more bigger! Tasted more normal made.

☀️Hotate Uni Roll 🧜🏻‍♀️ Happy Saturday guys!!

🍣 Limited off the menu rolls from @rappu.sg ✨

Oke sooo.. overall this is a great dish and i had quite a good time dining here. I dined here around last week, and when I posted this on my ig story some of you guys replied asking a few things on how the service was and how good the dishes are… soo here’s my honest experience 🍣😊

When I first came in, the staff did mentioned that the time limit for dining is 1hr 15min ( p.s. i don’t clearly remember whether its 1hr 10mins or 1hr 15mins) and i was told that i could stay longer here if there are no customers in line 🚶🏻‍♀️🚶🏻🚶🏻‍♂️ Given that my friend and i were there on Thursday, lunch time so the crowd is okay and we did stayed longer than 1hr 15mins as she came just from Indo after 2 years and we’re catching up on lots of things.

After seated for 5-10mins we were asked 2x for our order, which actually is quite alright as they are polite and not pushy ✍🏻

There were 2 of us and we ordered:
🐟Set of Six x 1
🦐Amaebi x 1
🥳Uni Hotate x 2

We were told that it would be great to have the sake pairing with Set of Six. I would really love to, but as we’re catching up a lot (cafe-hopping included) and have a long day ahead of us, we chose not to 👋🏻🍶

We split the Set of 6 for 2 of us and tbh its quite filling guys! Especially coz I don’t really eat rice that often. The hotate & salmon taste fresh and the nori is crisp, it would be best to eat it right away to really enjoy that crisp nori 🌊

In the middle of the way, my friend asked the staff whether the combination on Set of Six is fixed. We asked whether we could substitute one of the rolls with example, crab roll, but we’re mistaken with ordering more of the crab roll and given more portion of it.

Amaebi is fried beautifully and i really like the sauce 🦐🎊

The winner for me is definitely the hotate uni roll.  The hotate is sweet & buttery and they really give a generous amount of uni and dabs of tasty sauce (SWIPE LEFT FOR VIDEO) i like that it’s really straight to the point, just high quality absolutely delightful seafood 🎊

🍪Matcha Cheese Cookies Tart
i'm not a hardcore matcha purist, yet the matcha ganache in here was just right for me!! Love this!! Matcha is just as rich as the previous times I had it and goes really well with the cheese base.
 
Overall, these chunky cookies are a nice way to fulfill your cookie cravings. Freshly prepared! ❤️‍🔥Cookies that hit the mark, chunky and gooey, are incredibly satisfying. Also they've a vegan option too!🍃
 
—————————

@lamianpalace 📍 Lamian Palace is one of my favorite place to have lunch/ dinner with my Family. This restaurant serves varieties of Chinese food like fried rice, noodles, dim sum, etc.🥰😋

At @lamianpalace we had :
• Kungpao style chicken (Fried Chicken with Dried Chili)
• Two Variations of Sauteed Kai-Lan
• Prawns Goeng Mayonnaise (Fried Prawn with Mayonnaise)
• Deep Fried Enoki Mushroom with Salt and Pepper
• Fong Zau (Steamed Chicken Feet with Black Bean Sauce)
• Fried Wan Ton (Deep Fried Wan Ton)

Food : 5/5✨
Their dim sum is delicious and good value for money for its portion. Another menu is good, as main course and condiments. Using good quality ingredients. Recommend Menu: Kungpao Chicken and Wan Ton Fried. I have always loved their chili oil. It enhances the taste of the foods.

Ambience : 4/5✨
Good ambience. Cozy and comfort feeling. Few seats for groups and family.

Service : 5/5✨
Excellent service. Waitress can explain their menu completely. Food come at the same time. Their servers are very polite and friendly. Overall great service.

🍴 @lamianpalace 
📍Central Park Mall, Jakarta

📍 𝐣𝐢𝐧𝐣𝐣𝐚 𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧, 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐜𝐥𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢 𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐥

𝗳𝗼𝗼𝗱: 🐷🐷🐷🐷
𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚏 𝚋𝚞𝚕𝚐𝚘𝚐𝚒 𝚔𝚒𝚖𝚋𝚊𝚙 ($𝟽.𝟿𝟶) is my go-to here! though it looks small it’s surprisingly filling and each piece is packed full of sweet beef bulgogi 🥩, sliced cheese 🧀, crunchy carrots 🥕 and tangy pickles 🥒! the flavours work super well together and the whole roll is brushed with savoury sesame oil which helps tie everything together! however they’re not super consistent with the rolling: sometimes (like today) the roll doesn’t hold its shape very well. & not every piece had the same amount of ingredients 😬

𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲: 💸💸💸💸💸
solid 5/5 with their student price — $7.90 for a substantial roll of kimbap plus seaweed fries AND a drink! however without the discount i’d probably give it a 3 bc $9.30 a la carte is pretty ex for just the roll. 

𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗹𝗹: 𝟵/𝟭𝟬
love the simple yet delicious korean food from @jinjjachicken! not only is the kimbap great, i also really love their bibimbap 🍚 and of course korean fried chicken 🍗 

🟢 𝐜𝐥𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐢

sorry i’ve been mia 😭😭 will be back to posting regularly soon!!!

📍 𝐛𝐮𝐫𝐧𝐭 𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐬, 𝐬𝐮𝐧𝐬𝐞𝐭 𝐰𝐚𝐲

🥛 𝚖𝚒𝚕𝚔 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝚌𝚘𝚘𝚔𝚒𝚎𝚜 🍪 on a cone
cone had a slight chao da taste (hence the name?) n was super nice n crispy 😋 loved the smooth, creamy texture + rlly milky flavour of the ice cream! & the cute famous amos cookies they added atop the scoop 😍 however was disappointed that the ice cream was plain as i was expecting cookie bits inside ☹️

𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗹𝗹: 𝟱/𝟭𝟬
not a bad ice cream at all but was quite underwhelming!!! would give their other flavours a try tho 👌🏼

📍 𝐭𝐞𝐚 𝐭𝐫𝐞𝐞 𝐜𝐚𝐟𝐞, 𝐤𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐠 𝐰𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐥

𝗳𝗼𝗼𝗱: 🐷🐷🐷🐷
decided on the 𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚠𝚢 𝚋𝚘𝚠𝚕 (𝚜𝚖𝚊𝚕𝚕, $𝟹.𝟷𝟶), which consisted of a choice of base, pearls, QQ taro balls, QQ sweet potato balls & creamer. i opted for grass jelly as the base, which was super light & refreshing ❄️ the QQ balls were soft yet bouncy, giving a great chew without being too hard! 🤤 

𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲: 💸💸💸💸💸
my fav topping in these taiwanese desserts is the QQ balls, and most other stores only gone like 3 of them 😭 however, this bowl was packed with 𝘵𝘸𝘦𝘭𝘷𝘦 (yes, i counted 😂) of them 🤩

𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗹𝗹: 𝟴/𝟭𝟬
easily my fav taiwanese dessert place plus their bbt is rlly good too!! gotta minus points tho bc their outlets are all so far away 😭

🟠 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐝𝐢𝐮𝐦

have seen @irvins.sg’𝐬 𝐬𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐞𝐠𝐠 𝐟𝐥𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐜𝐮𝐩 𝐧𝐨𝐨𝐝𝐥𝐞𝐬 ($𝟐.𝟗𝟓) around for a while now but never tried it as i was (very) skeptical about salted egg flavoured noodles… but omg this rlly worked 😳 plus it surprisingly wasn’t as salty as i’d imagined! the noodles are also different from the typical cup noodle noodles — this one is more thick n flat like meepok and has a better bite to it. 😋

it’s pretty pricy for cup noodles tho, almost double the price of those from generic brands like myojo. 🥶 it’s good but i probs won’t eat it on a regular basis, more as a once-in-a-while treat when i’m feeling smth salted egg-y 😆

📍 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐠𝐚𝐧𝐟𝐢𝐞𝐥𝐝𝐬, 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫 𝐯𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐚
my fam & i used to love eating ribs at tony roma’s, but ever since they closed in sg we’ve yet to find a replacement. so we gave @morganfieldssingapore a try! here’s how it went…

𝗳𝗼𝗼𝗱: 🐷🐷
🥖 𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚎𝚜𝚢 𝚐𝚊𝚛𝚕𝚒𝚌 𝚝𝚘𝚊𝚜𝚝 ($𝟾.𝟿𝟶)
quite enjoyed this. the baguette had a crunchy exterior while remaining soft on the inside! however it was essentially $2+ for one piece which is 😳 

🧅 𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚛 𝚋𝚊𝚝𝚝𝚎𝚛𝚎𝚍 𝚘𝚗𝚒𝚘𝚗 𝚛𝚒𝚗𝚐𝚜 ($𝟷𝟶.𝟿𝟶)
found the batter too thick and also very oily 👎🏼

𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚌𝚊𝚛𝚗𝚒𝚟𝚘𝚛𝚎 ($𝟷𝟶𝟻.𝟿𝟶) included
🍖 𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗸𝘆 𝗯𝗼𝗻𝗲𝘀 (𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗸𝗼𝗿𝘆 𝗯𝗯𝗾): meat was fall-off-the-bone tender, the sauce was sticky and very flavourful 😋
🍗 𝟭/𝟮 𝗿𝗼𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗻 (𝘁𝗲𝗾𝘂𝗶𝗹𝗮 𝘀𝗽𝗶𝗸𝗲𝗱): didn’t like the seasoning on this, plus the chicken meat was abit dry ☹️
🍞 𝗰𝗼𝗿𝗻𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱: moist + strong corn taste! 👍🏼
🌽 𝗴𝗿𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗰𝗼𝗿𝗻 𝗼𝗻 𝗰𝗼𝗯: sadly the corn wasn’t sweet at all & lacked a good char 😪
🍟 𝗳𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗵 𝗳𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀: surprisingly well-seasoned & creamy! loved it 😍 
🥗 𝗴𝗮𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗻 𝘀𝗮𝗹𝗮𝗱 & 🌭 𝗴𝗿𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝘀𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗮𝗴𝗲: not bad but not spectacular; just ur standard salad & sausage

𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘂𝗲: 💸💸 ~$𝟯𝟳/𝗽𝗮𝘅
quite ex for mediocre food… though we had a $10 voucher, it still wasn’t very worth. 

𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗹𝗹: 𝟰/𝟭𝟬
sadly we’ve yet to find a good replacement for our old favourite restaurant 😢 if u have any recommendations pls comment below!!! 😆

🟠🟢 𝐛𝐮𝐨𝐧𝐚 𝐯𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐚

New food spot in the CBD area! 🥘 Singapore Crawfish Ramen (@sgcrawfishramen) is opened by the multi-talented @debra_loi from Ah Girls Go Army who's also a nurse, model and avid foodie. 👏

Tried their signature Crawfish Ramen (SGD12.90) and it was packed full of umami flavour. 🍜 The broth was a standout here, featuring more than 30 ingredients including crawfish.

Speaking of which, their crawfishes come from a local farm and hence tasted really fresh! The ramen noodles, airflown from Japan, were springy and equally delectable as well. 😍 Definitely recommend adding on an Onsen Egg (SGD1.50), as well as some Clams (SGD3) if you're a seafood lover, to elevate your ramen.

Thank you @debra_loi and @sgcrawfishramen for having me!

📍Singapore Crawfish Ramen 🇸🇬

A really mediocre plate of nasi lemak but branded and available at late night with multiple outlets islandwide - how much would you pay? 

Definitely not $7. 🙈

📍#iykyk 🇸🇬

Glorious, glorious meat at Incredible Roasted Meat. 🔥 This mixed platter costed a whopping SGD15, but came with so much meat - a total of 7 types!

The standout was hands down the roasted chicken wing which was meaty, juicy and decadent. 🍗 Their lup cheong was amazing too, bursting with sweetness and savouriness in every bite. A special shoutout to their pork ribs as well, for you don't really see these often at roasted meat stalls.

Overall, a really value-for-money feast! 

📍Incredible Roasted Meat 🇸🇬

A blazing hot day calls for an ice cold coffee, yes? 😎

I very much enjoyed this Iced Latte (SGD6.50) from Dutch Colony Coffee Co. (@dutchcolony) at their relatively new Tampines outlet. ☕ Can't wait to try their food and bakes someday as they look good too!

📍Dutch Colony Coffee Co. 🇸🇬

Was so excited to chance upon Holy Cow Creamery (@holycowcreamery) when I was at Lavender a while back so we went in for some ice cream! 🍦

I opted for the Chocolate OD (that's made with 4 different chocolates!) as chocolate is my litmus test for every new ice cream shop that I try. Pleased to say that it passed the test. 🍫 Out of curiosity, we also got the Bailey's flavour, which was coffee tiramisu infused with Bailey's Irish Cream. 🍾 The kick of the booze was legit so if you're one who likes alchohol in your food, get this.

To go with our ice cream, we also got a Golden Waffle with maple syrup. 🧇 Satisfyingly chewy with a decently crispy crust, their waffles were definitely above average. 

Looking forward to trying their other unique flavours! 

📍Holy Cow Creamery 🇸🇬

I love how I feel whenever I visit England and explore new towns… I feel like living in one of those  British rom coms movies that teenage Melani was obsessed with, let’s name a few just to go down memory lane: “Angus, Thongs and Perfect Snogging”, “Wild Child”, “Bridget Jones’s Diary”, “Love, Rosie”, “Bend It Like Beckham” and the list is seriously endless because there’s one thing you must know about me 🤭 No matter how all these movies are suuuper silly, I just live for movies where the triumph of romanticism, femininity are amplified and British towns/cities are shown 😂 It’s just one of my guilty pleasures! 
The only thing in my trips is that at the end of the day, there’s no English Prince Charming like in all of those rom coms 🥲

• it was Carnival season here in Italy and a few weeks ago after ages I attended the one in Verona city (I’m serious! I can’t even remember last time I went to see a carnival! The last one was at least 10 years ago or even more 😅). 
The historical “Carnevale di Verona”, according to what I read on the official page, is considered the oldest carnival held in all Europe. It involves the entire city and many other little towns around Verona and is usually held on the last Friday before Lent. The whole city center gets paralysed with its beautiful and lively parade.
Going this time in 2022 after ages  really brought back so many sweet childhood memories 🥰 Till middle school I remember my parents always taking me to the city dressed up in a costume to see the parade! I remember music, candy thrown out to all the kids, carnival floats with people dancing on it and just so much joy and craziness 🎊
Have you ever seen a carnival? Let me know in the comment below || 🥳💃🏽📸🇮🇹•

• Stopped by Euphoria High and got a bit inspired to do this little self portrait shoot ✨😶😂 I actually tra created Maddy’s makeup look from season 2 episode 1!

Hi everyone! Sorry for not being very active here, I’m having a bit of a block with my IG. It’s not that I don’t have content to post or lack of creativity…I actually have so many reels, I started again with self portrait photography and I still have plenty of pictures from past trips and walks…but for some reason I can’t find the motivation to post 😅 Maybe everything happening at the moment around the world is not helping too. I’m sure we are all feeling a bite like our heads are scrambled or foggy 😶‍🌫️ However I hope you are all doing good, looking after yourselves and are kind towards the others too! 

I’m fine. I’ll recharge and come back stronger! In the meanwhile, I hope you like these pictures || 😄✨📸 •
